INSERT INTO `Sheet1` VALUES
('GEM_2024_B_5569980', '22-01-2025 09:00:00', '22-01-2025 09:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Defence Research & Development', 'Office Of Dg (aero)', '***********', NULL, 'Custom Bid for Services - Design and Development of RTS Facility', 'Hiring of Professionals for Application Development and Maintenance', '1 Year 6 Months 1 Day', '1,25,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'Yes (Arbitration clause document) as per DOE OM No.F.1/2/2024-PPD dated 03.06.2024 Arbitration should not be routinely included in contracts', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '62,94,000', 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '08-01-2025 10:00:00', NULL, 'The technical specifications for the tender require the Design and Development of an RTS Facility. The service must be fully compliant with all regulatory and statutory requirements. Furthermore, the bidder must ensure that the service adheres to the Scope of Work (SOW), Service Level Agreement (SLA), and other specified terms and conditions.', '***********', 'Bengaluru', 'This tender (Bid Number: GEM/2024/B/5569980) is a custom bid for services related to the Design and Development of an RTS Facility, issued by the Office Of Dg (aero) under the Department Of Defence Research & Development, Ministry of Defence. The contract period is for 1 year, 6 months, and 1 day. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 125 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services, although exemptions are available for MSEs and Startups. The bid process is a Two Packet system with a Reverse Auction enabled for technically qualified bidders, excluding the highest-priced one. The EMD amount is 62,94,000. Key requirements for the bidder include having an office in the consignee''s state (Karnataka), providing a dedicated support number and an escalation matrix, and offering product support for 5 years post-warranty. The final delivery, installation, and commissioning will be at the Aeronautical Development Establishment in Bangalore. The bid also includes provisions for a Pre-contract Integrity Pact and an NDA.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the final delivery, installation, and commissioning of the designed and developed RTS Facility at the specified address, Aeronautical Development Establishment, Bangalore. The completion must be in full compliance with the detailed Scope of Work (SOW), Service Level Agreement (SLA), and all technical specifications. Additionally, the contractor must have established the mandated service and support infrastructure, including a dedicated support telephone number and an escalation matrix. The submission of the required Performance Security in the form of a Fixed Deposit Receipt or PBG after the award of the contract is a prerequisite for the formal commencement and successful execution of the project.', 'The scope of work is for the ''Design and Development of RTS Facility''. This encompasses the complete lifecycle from design to actual delivery, installation, and commissioning of the facility at the Aeronautical Development Establishment, New Thippasandra, Bangalore. The scope also includes comprehensive Service & Support obligations. The vendor must maintain a service provider office in the state of the consignee (Karnataka) and provide a dedicated/toll-free telephone number and an escalation matrix for service support. A crucial part of the scope is providing product support for a period of 5 years after the warranty expires. The entire service must be executed in compliance with the tender''s Scope of Work (SOW), STC, SLA, and all applicable regulatory and statutory norms.'),
('GEM_2024_B_5748184', '16-01-2025 18:00:00', '16-01-2025 18:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Navy', '***********', 'dgmyas.ndmb@nic.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Repair of Luff Slew Long Travel Main Hoist Motion and Auxiliary Hoist motion of ELL cranes of YAS Dept at ND MBI', 'Repair and Overhauling Service, Repair, Maintenance and Installation of Plant/ Systems/Equipments', '2 Month', '80,00,000', '7 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '9,29,250', 'Yes', 5, 14, 'Yes', NULL, 'The Buyer will have the right to award contracts to different Bidders for being lowest in particular items. The Buyer also reserves the right to do Apportionment of Quantity, if it is convinced that lowest Bidder is not in a position to supply full quantity in stipulated time.', 'Yes', 'Yes', '03-01-2025 11:00:00', 'Naval Dockyard Mumbai (Office of Senior Manager Yard Services) Shahid Bhagat Singh Road Lion Gate Mumbai 400 023 Contact No - 022 22751962/1141 Email ID - dgmyas.ndmb@nic.in Pre bid meeting is optional and not mandatory to attend Pre bid meeting', 'The technical specifications for the service detail the Repair of Luff Slew Long Travel Main Hoist Motion and Auxiliary Hoist motion of ELL cranes of YAS Dept at ND MBI. The service must maintain regulatory and statutory compliance, as well as adherence to the Scope of Work (SOW), STC, and SLA. The detailed specifications cover five different cranes: South Break Water ELL Crane No. 2, which includes a 45 KW Main Hoist Drive and a 22 KW Auxiliary Hoist Drive; South Wharf ELL Crane, with a 90 KW Main Hoist Drive, a 37 KW Auxiliary Hoist Drive, and a PM573-ETH-XC AC500 PLC; Bombay / Duncan Dock ELL Crane, featuring a 140 KVA Main Hoist Drive, 140 KVA Auxiliary Hoist Drive, 60 KVA Slew Motion Drive, 40 KVA Luff Motion Drive, and 70 KVA Long Travel Motion Drive; CG Dock North ELL Crane, with a 90 KW Main Hoist Drive and a 90 KW Auxiliary Hoist; and ACD South FOB ELL Crane, which includes a 37 KW Auxiliary Hoist Drive, 110 KW Slew Motion Drive, 55 KW Luff Motion Drive, and an Integrated System Controller PLC. The specified makes for these components include YASKAWA, GEC, ABB, CG, Siemens, and Schneider.', 'Senior Manager Yard Services', 'Mumbai', 'This GeM tender (Bid Number: GEM/2024/B/5748184) is a custom bid for the repair services of Luff, Slew, Long Travel, Main Hoist, and Auxiliary Hoist motions for five ELL cranes at the Naval Dockyard in Mumbai, issued by the Indian Navy, Ministry of Defence. The contract period is set for 2 months, with a bid offer validity of 180 days from the bid end date of 16-01-2025. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 80 Lakhs over the last three years and 7 years of past experience in similar services. The bid follows a Two Packet system with a reverse auction based on H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination. A mandatory Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of 9,29,250 is required, and a Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 5% of the contract value is to be submitted for a duration of 14 months. The scope of work involves a turnkey project including the supply, installation, testing, and commissioning of new VVVF drives and PLCs for the specified cranes. Key deliverables include AutoCAD drawings, load analysis reports, and training for yard staff. A mandatory site visit is required before bid submission. The contract specifies a 12-month warranty period from the date of work completion. Payment terms are structured in two stages: 60% of material cost upon successful inspection and the balance 40% of material cost plus 100% of labour cost upon successful completion of the entire scope of work. The tender includes comprehensive clauses on safety, labour regulations, liquidated damages, and other standard government contract conditions.', 'The work will be considered successfully completed upon fulfillment of the entire scope of work as detailed in the tender, which includes the supply, installation, testing, and commissioning of all specified components. A primary criterion is the successful completion of tests and trials for each crane system, which must be conducted as per relevant industry standards, OEM technical specifications, and to the complete satisfaction of the user, resulting in a system that is proved for satisfactory performance. The completion is formalized through a successful Joint Receipt Inspection (JRI) which includes complete functional checking of the equipment. Following this, an ''Acceptance Certificate'' or a ''Work Completion Certificate'' will be issued by the Senior Manager Yard Services, and a ''Final Inspection Note for SOW'' will be issued. Furthermore, the contractor must fulfill the 12-month warranty obligation from the date of work completion, rectifying any defects free of cost.', 'The scope of work is for the turnkey repair of Luff Motion, Slew Motion, Long Travel Motion, Main Hoist Motion, and Auxiliary Hoist Motion for five ELL Cranes at Naval Dockyard, Mumbai. For each of the five cranes (South Break Water, South Wharf, Bombay/Duncan Dock, CG Dock North, and ACD South FOB), the work includes disconnecting and removing the existing drive, followed by the Supply, Installation, Testing, and Commissioning (SITC) of a new drive. The new drive must be configured with the existing motor setup and subjected to a test/trial to ensure it meets industry standards and user satisfaction. For the South Wharf and ACD South FOB cranes, the scope specifically includes integrating all drives with a new upgraded Programmable Logic Controller (PLC) system, complete with a Crane Monitoring System and Safety Interlocks, and ensuring the supplied hardware has seven years of OEM and spare support. The scope of supply includes 14 specified Variable Voltage, Variable Frequency (VVVF) Drives and 2 Programmable Logic Controls (PLC). The contractor must provide deliverables including approved AutoCAD drawings of the new VVFD-PLC system, two hard copies of the load analysis report, and calibration certificates for all tested systems. Additionally, the bidder is required to provide training to Yard staff on programming, operation, debugging, and fault identification for the VVFD and PLC systems. The entire work, including any incidental electrical/mechanical tasks and debris removal, must be completed within a period of 02 months and comes with a 12-month warranty.'),
('GEM_2025_B_5875643', '28-02-2025 17:00:00', '28-02-2025 17:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Power', 'Contracts And Materials', 'Damodar Valley Corporation', 'Damodar Valley Corporation', 'aurobindu.maji@dvc.gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Rate Contract for OnLine Chemical Treatment of Condenser Cooling Water System at RTPS 2 X 600 MW DVC for a period of one 01 year ie 365 days', 'Facility Management Service - Manpower Based Facility Management Service- Manpower based (Version 2)', '1 Year', '24,21,00,000', '7 Years', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '7 Days', NULL, '95,22,600', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'PUNJAB NATIONAL BANK', '1,61,400', NULL, 3, 14, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '14-02-2025 12:00:00', 'https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:oJItI7Ciua_JQBSIz-88X5ZMQx26fQD_ZwKlthvN9vs1@thread.tacv2/1737987471576?context={%22Tid%22:%22cf94827a-bc3d-4b63-8feb-432960d2d81b%22,%22Oid%22:%22703f8a05-0af4-4473-ab95-38c0f043d400%22}', 'The technical specifications outline a Rate Contract for the OnLine Chemical Treatment of the Condenser Cooling Water System at RTPS 2 X 600 MW DVC for a period of one year (365 days). This service must ensure regulatory and statutory compliance, as well as adherence to the Scope of Work (SOW), STC, and SLA. The cooling water system''s technical details include 41,948 condenser tubes per unit, each 11.12 meters long with a 25 mm outer diameter and 0.7/0.9 mm thickness, made of SA249TP304 material. Key operational parameters of the system are a circulation rate of 73,200 m3/hr, a total hold-up capacity of 59,000 m3 for two units, and a rated cooling tower effectiveness of 60.56%. The feed pipe is specified as Carbon steel (ASTM 53) Gr B/ IS: 1239. The products to be supplied by the bidder include Scale Inhibitor, Corrosion Inhibitor, Polymeric Dispersant, Biodispersant, and Non-oxidizing Biocides, for which bidders must provide detailed specifications regarding their active ingredients, concentration, dosage, and physical properties.', 'Sarmila Kar', 'Purulia', 'This tender, identified by Bid Number GEM/2025/B/5875643, is issued by Damodar Valley Corporation for a one-year rate contract for the Online Chemical Treatment of the Condenser Cooling Water System at Raghunathpur Thermal Power Station (2x600MW). The project, with an estimated value of Rs. 95,22,600 and requiring an EMD of Rs. 1,61,400, aims to prevent scale, corrosion, and biological fouling in the cooling system. Bidders must demonstrate past experience in similar works at thermal power stations of at least 200 MW capacity and have an average annual financial turnover of at least Rs. 24,21,000.00, although exemptions are available for MSE and Start-up vendors. The scope of work is comprehensive, covering the supply, 24/7 dosing, regular testing, and continuous monitoring of specified non-chromate based chemicals. The contract is performance-based, with stringent success criteria tied to maintaining specific water quality parameters, corrosion rates, and biological growth limits. Failure to meet these parameters will result in penalties. The payment terms are structured as 95% against running bills and the final 5% upon successful completion of the contract. A performance bank guarantee of 3% of the contract value is mandatory for a duration of 14 months.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of all contractual obligations for the entire one-year period, demonstrated by consistently meeting the specified Performance Guarantee parameters. Key success criteria include: maintaining the differential temperature of critical heat exchangers within allowable limits; ensuring the differential pressure across the bio-fouling monitor does not exceed 20% of its initial value for more than seven consecutive days; preventing any undesirable biological growth in the cooling water system; keeping corrosion rates for Mild Steel below 3.0 MPY, Copper below 0.30 MPY, and Stainless Steel below 0.2 MPY; ensuring the scale deposition rate is less than 15 mg/dm²/year; maintaining the scaling tendency (LSI/RSI) within the specified equilibrium point; and keeping all bio-fouling parameters, such as slime-forming bacteria and TBC, within their defined limits. Successful completion also hinges on adherence to all monitoring, testing, reporting, and safety protocols outlined in the contract.', 'The scope of work entails a comprehensive one-year online chemical treatment program for the condenser cooling water system at RTPS (2x600MW) to prevent scale formation, corrosion, deposition, and biological fouling, thereby ensuring optimal heat transfer and energy efficiency. The vendor''s responsibilities are: 1. Supply and Dosing: To provide a continuous supply of eco-friendly, non-chromate based chemicals, including anti-scalant, corrosion inhibitor, polymeric dispersant, bio-dispersant, and two types of non-oxidizing biocides. The treatment must be conducted within an alkaline pH range of 8.0-8.3. 2. Manpower: To deploy sufficient and qualified manpower, including a Science Graduate as Site-in-Charge, to operate the chemical dosing system around the clock (24/7) without any interruption. 3. Monitoring and Testing: To conduct regular collection of water samples and perform a comprehensive set of daily and weekly tests for various parameters like pH, conductivity, hardness, silica, and chemical residuals. The vendor must generate daily performance reports and participate in monthly review meetings with DVC management. 4. Equipment and Infrastructure: To supply, install, and maintain all necessary monitoring equipment, such as corrosion coupon racks, scale deposit monitors, bio-fouling monitors, and microbiological test kits, for the entire treatment period. 5. Logistics and Safety: To manage the handling, safe storage, and application of all chemicals, maintain a one-month stock at the site, and provide Material Safety Data Sheets (MSDS) for all supplied products. 6. Reporting and Analysis: To provide detailed reports on system performance, chemical consumption, and conduct joint inspections during plant shutdowns to analyze any deposition and study equipment failure trends.'),
('GEM_2025_B_5937111', '01-05-2025 09:00:00', '01-05-2025 09:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Defence Research & Development', 'Office Of Dg (mss)', '***********', 'dcmm-rci@gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - MAINTENANCE CONTRACT OF CLEAN ROOM CLASS 100 AND 1000 FOR TWO YEARS', 'Cleaning, Sanitation and Disinfection Service - Outcome Based', '2 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', NULL, 'Yes', 5, 27, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '17-04-2025 11:00:00', 'CONFERENCE HALL, DCMM, RCI. CONTACT NO:040 2430 6222 MAIL ID: DCMM-RCI@GOV.IN', 'The technical specifications for the Maintenance Contract of Clean Room Class 100 and 1000 outline a comprehensive set of requirements for a two-year period. The core service involves the regular maintenance and upkeep of the clean room facility, including specified areas and a detailed list of equipment such as AHUs, a Hot Water Generator, Chilled Water Plant, Fan Filter Units, various filters, Air Showers, electrical panels, Building Automation System (BMS), Fire Alarm System, R.O Water System, and CDA Filter. The service requires a total of 8 personnel working in shifts, including a skilled Site Engineer/Supervisor with over 5 years of experience, a semi-skilled A.C. Technician with over 4 years of experience, and 6 unskilled Clean Room Technicians. The vendor must perform numerous cleaning procedures at specified frequencies: daily tasks include cleaning tacky mats, mopping floors, and cleaning service corridors and air showers; weekly tasks include cleaning external equipment areas and checking electrical items; and monthly tasks include cleaning panels and water tanks. The vendor is responsible for providing all necessary cleaning supplies, housekeeping consumables, water treatment plant consumables, and some mechanical spares like v-belts and oil. Key performance metrics include weekly particle counts logged into the BMS system and maintaining the functionality of all systems. The vendor must also adhere to strict safety protocols, provide personnel with proper safety equipment, and ensure compliance with all relevant labor laws, including the Factories Act, ESI Act, and PF Act. All personnel deployed must be Indian citizens with verified character and antecedents.', '***********', 'Hyderabad', 'This Government e-Marketplace (GeM) bid, number GEM/2025/B/5937111, is a custom bid for a two-year Maintenance Contract for Clean Room Class 100 and 1000 at the Research Centre Imarat (RCI), Hyderabad, under the Ministry of Defence. The bid is a Two Packet type with a Reverse Auction enabled, where the highest-priced bidder (H1) is eliminated. The contract period is 2 years, with a bid offer validity of 180 days. Key dates include the bid end on 01-05-2025 and a pre-bid meeting on 17-04-2025. The successful bidder must provide an e-Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 5.00% for a duration of 27 months. The scope of work is extensive, requiring the vendor to maintain the clean room facility and all associated equipment, including HVAC, electrical, and water systems, to ensure they remain functional and meet Class 100/1000 standards. The vendor is required to deploy a team of 8 personnel (skilled, semi-skilled, and unskilled) working in shifts and is responsible for all housekeeping consumables, safety equipment, and statutory compliances such as PF and ESI for their employees. Payment will be made on a quarterly basis after satisfactory completion of the job, which requires a Job Completion Certificate. The document emphasizes strict adherence to RCI''s security protocols, safety norms, and all applicable Indian labor laws.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the successful completion of the work is contingent upon several key criteria. Primarily, the vendor must consistently maintain the clean room facility to its specified standards of Class 100 and Class 1000, which is verified through particle counts checked at least once a week and logged in the BMS system. The overall functionality of the clean room and all its associated equipment must be ensured at all times. Satisfactory performance, evaluated on an ongoing basis, is a prerequisite for the release of quarterly payments. The ultimate proof of successful completion for any given period is the issuance of a ''Job Completion Certificate'' duly approved by the User and TD (Technical Directorate). Failure to provide satisfactory services can lead to the termination of the contract at any point. Furthermore, adherence to a penalty clause, where a facility downtime of one day results in a two-day contract extension, underscores the importance of uninterrupted service.', 'The scope of work is to provide comprehensive regular maintenance services for the upkeep of the Class 100 & Class 1000 clean room facility at HASD Clean Room facility, DNS, RCI for a period of two years. This includes the maintenance of all associated equipment such as Clean Room Areas (totaling 446 Sq. MT), AHUs, Hot Water Generator, Chilled Water Plant, piping, insulation, ducting, Fan Filter Units, Mini Plate Hood type Filters, Air Showers, Main Electrical Panel, Power Panels, AHU Panels, LPDB, ELDB, UPS Power Points, Building Automation System (BMS), Fire Alarm System (FAS), R.O Water System, and CDA Filter. The vendor must deploy a total of 8 personnel: one Site Engineer/supervisor, one A.C. Technician, and six Clean Room Technicians, working across three shifts and one general shift. The work involves detailed cleaning procedures with specified frequencies, including daily wet mopping, daily cleaning of service corridors and air showers, twice-weekly wipe-downs of surfaces, weekly cleaning of external equipment areas, and monthly cleaning of panels and ceilings. The vendor is responsible for providing all consumables required for housekeeping (e.g., Antistatic Floor Cleaner, mops, wipers), water treatment (e.g., Salt, caustic soda), and mechanical spares (e.g., v-belts, grease). The scope also includes performing periodic maintenance checks on systems like scrubbers and gas generators, ensuring fire and safety procedures are followed, managing stocks of consumables, and conducting weekly particle count checks. The vendor must ensure full compliance with safety norms by providing PPE and adhering to statutory labor laws, including ESI and PF provisions for all deployed employees.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6016585', '25-03-2025 10:00:00', '25-03-2025 10:30:00', '120 Days', 'Department Of Space', 'Department Of Space', 'Indian Space Research Organization', 'Satish Dhawan Space Centre Shar', 'con62.isro.ap@gembuyer.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - CAMC OF NETWORK ELEMENTS SERVERS ETC', 'Annual Maintenance Contract for Network Security Devices', '2 Year', '3', 'at least five years', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', NULL, 'Yes', 3, 26, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '13-03-2025 11:00:00', NULL, 'The technical specifications for this service detail a Comprehensive Annual Maintenance Contract (CAMC) for network elements, servers, and other related equipment procured through a custom bid. The core requirements mandate that the service must have regulatory and statutory compliance. Furthermore, the service must be in full compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Special Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA). The addon section for additional specifications is not utilized.', 'Sure Srinivasa Rao', 'Sriharikota', 'This Government e-Marketplace (GeM) bid (GEM/2025/B/6016585) is a custom bid for services issued by the Indian Space Research Organization (ISRO), specifically for the Satish Dhawan Space Centre (SDSC) SHAR. The tender is for a Comprehensive Annual Maintenance Contract (CAMC) for network elements, servers, workstations, laptops, and accessories for a contract period of two years, from April 1, 2025, to March 31, 2027, with a provision for a one-year extension. The bid process is a two-packet system with a pre-bid meeting scheduled for March 13, 2025, participation in which is mandatory for bidders to be considered for evaluation. The scope of the contract includes preventive maintenance every three months, breakdown maintenance, and free replacement of defective parts. A key requirement is the on-site deployment of six qualified technical engineers with specified experience levels (ranging from 3 to 10+ years), who will be interviewed for client suitability. The bidder must be a firm established for more than 5 years with an annual turnover of over 3 crores for the last three financial years and hold ISO27001 & ISO20000 certifications. Bidders are also required to provide authorization letters from OEMs for back-to-back service support and maintain a specified list of spare parts as site stock. Payment for the services will be made on a quarterly, pro-rata basis upon satisfactory completion of work, certified by the designated Contract Manager.', 'The work is considered successfully completed based on the satisfactory fulfillment of all contractual obligations, which is formally confirmed through a quarterly certification process. The service provider must submit quarterly maintenance status reports, logbooks, and bills, which are then certified by the Engineer-in-charge and approved by the Contract Manager of SDSC SHAR. Key performance indicators for success include: performing preventive maintenance every three months as scheduled; carrying out breakdown maintenance promptly to minimize downtime (within 3 calendar days for critical systems and 10 working days for non-critical systems); replacing all defective or damaged parts free of cost; ensuring the continuous deployment of the six mandated qualified engineers on-site; maintaining at least 70% availability of the specified spare parts (as per Annexure-A) at the SDSC SHAR campus; and submitting all required documentation for verification and payment. The final agreement that the work has been successfully completed for a given period is the issuance of the satisfactory service certificate by the General Manager, SCOF & MAFS.', 'The scope of work entails providing a Comprehensive Maintenance Contract (CAMC) for network products, servers, workstations, laptops, and other network/computer accessories located at SDSC SHAR. The contract period is for two years, from April 1, 2025, to March 31, 2027, and is extendable for one more year. The work broadly covers three main areas: 1. Preventive Maintenance: To be conducted every three months, which includes monitoring all switches and routers, housekeeping of wall mounting racks, and daily monitoring of UPS battery capacity to prevent drain down. 2. Breakdown Maintenance: To ensure high availability of all systems, including internet, surveillance, and real-time networks, by completing breakdown services with minimum downtime. 3. Replacement of Parts: Free-of-cost replacement of any defective or damaged parts covered under the contract. The scope also mandates the deployment of six full-time, qualified technical personnel (one graduate engineer with 10+ years experience, and five diploma engineers with 3 to 6+ years of experience) who must be on the bidder''s payroll. Furthermore, the service provider is required to maintain an adequate stock of specified spare parts on-site at SDSC SHAR, as listed in Annexure-A, and provide standby systems when necessary. During launch campaigns, the deployed manpower must be available on a 24x7 basis without any additional charges.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6052176', '26-03-2025 14:00:00', '26-03-2025 14:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Petroleum And Natural Gas', 'Chennai Petroleum Corporation Limited', 'Chennai Petroleum Corporation Limited', 'Chennai', 'buyer25.cpcl.tn@gembuyer.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - CPCLY25090 Refractory repair works in various Plants during Ref I LEB DHDT new HGU MI shutdown at CPCL Manali Zones 1 and 2', 'Repair and Overhauling Service, Repair, Maintenance and Installation of Plant/ Systems/Equipments', '2 Month', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '3 Days', NULL, '1,23,08,04,496', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '92,000', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 2.0, 'The entire scope of work will be split into 2 (Two) areas and the same are proposed to be awarded to 2 (Two) different Bidders, Refer Tender Document.', 'Yes', 'Yes', '19-03-2025 10:00:00', 'Chennai', 'The technical specification outlines the requirements for service CPCLY25090, which involves refractory repair works in various plants including Ref I, LEB, DHDT, new HGU, and MI shutdown at CPCL Manali Zones 1 and 2. The service must adhere to all regulatory and statutory compliance standards. Furthermore, it is mandatory for the service to be in full compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA). The specification table indicates that there are no additional add-ons or supplementary specification documents required for this service.', 'ASWIN N', 'Chennai', 'This tender, with Bid Number GEM/2025/B/6052176 and Tender Number CPCLY25090, is issued by Chennai Petroleum Corporation Limited (CPCL) for refractory repair works in various plants during a major shutdown at its Manali facility (Zones 1 & 2). The estimated value of the bid is ₹12,308,044.96 with a required Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of ₹92,000. The contract period is 2 months, with specific completion schedules of 60 days for Zone-1 and 24 days for Zone-2. The scope of work is to be split and awarded to two different bidders based on an L1, L2 evaluation methodology. Bidders must meet pre-qualification criteria, including an annual financial turnover of at least ₹55.37 lakhs and specific experience in similar refractory works. The scope involves dismantling existing refractory, cleaning surfaces, and installing new linings on a round-the-clock basis, adhering strictly to CPCL''s safety and work permit systems. The tender includes provisions for a reverse auction and purchase preferences for Micro and Small Enterprises (MSE) and Make in India (MII) compliant bidders. Payment terms are 95% on a pro-rata basis upon work completion and the final 5% after bill finalization and all clearances, with a 10% security deposit required.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed from the tender issuer''s perspective, the contractor must meet several criteria. Firstly, all repair works must be completed within the specified application time for each plant and the overall contract period, with any delays incurring penalties. Secondly, upon completion, the contractor must obtain a formal clearance from CPCL''s Inspection and/or Manufacturing departments. Thirdly, a ''Final Test Certificate'' must be issued by the Engineer-in-Charge, confirming that all works have passed final inspections and meet all technical specifications. Subsequently, the contractor must clear the entire worksite of all surplus materials, equipment, and temporary structures, and obtain a ''no-demand certificate'' from the Fire and Safety, Security, and Maintenance departments. The final step is the issuance of a ''Completion Certificate'' by the Engineer-in-Charge, which formally marks the completion and initiates the 12-month Defect Liability Period, during which the contractor remains responsible for rectifying any defects.', 'The scope of work encompasses comprehensive refractory repair services during the plant shutdown, to be executed on a round-the-clock basis. Key activities include:

1.  **Preparation and Management:** Erection and dismantling of scaffolding, arranging temporary sheds for safe material storage, and shifting materials from CPCL stores to the worksite and returning unused stock.
2.  **Dismantling and Cleaning:** Dismantling the existing refractory/ceramic lining, removing and stacking debris at designated locations up to 100m away (disposal by CPCL), and thoroughly cleaning surfaces before new application.
3.  **Installation and Repair:** Carrying out new refractory and ceramic fibre lining as per drawings, which includes welding Insultwist studs, V anchors, or other studs/mesh; supplying and applying anti-corrosive paint (Epiplus 556 or equivalent); installing backup and hot face lining; packing gaps and repairing cracks with ceramic fibre blanket, mortar, or repair castable.
4.  **Ancillary Works:** Removal and refixing of manway plugs, covering existing muffle blocks for protection, and performing any other tasks as directed by the Engineer-in-Charge to ensure work completion.
5.  **Quality and Safety Compliance:** Mobilizing an API 936 certified Quality Control Engineer, strictly adhering to CPCL safety guidelines and work permit systems, providing sufficient lighting, and ensuring all personnel use appropriate Personal Protective Equipment (PPE).
6.  **Contractor''s Supply:** The contractor is responsible for supplying all skilled manpower (minimum 90 for Zone-1 and 40 for Zone-2), all necessary machinery, tools, tackles, PPEs, lighting arrangements, welding equipment, anticorrosive paint, and portable radio receivers for site staff and CPCL personnel.
7.  **CPCL''s Supply (Free of Cost):** CPCL will provide refractory materials, ceramic fibre, ancillary materials, electrical power and water at a single point, diesel for refractory dryout, and cranes for material handling upon prior request.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6086996', '07-05-2025 14:00:00', '07-05-2025 14:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Petroleum And Natural Gas', NULL, 'Oil And Natural Gas Corporation Limited', 'Central Procurement Department', 'buyer631.ongcl.mh@gembuyer.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of Integrated Coil Tubing Services along with Nitrogen Pumping services and High-Pressure Pumping services for 3 years on call on Job to Job basis for WSS, Rajahmundry Asset', 'Oil and Gas Drilling Service', '3 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '5 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '51,90,192', 'Yes', 3, 45, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '09-04-2025 11:00:00', 'ONGC, Conference Hall, CLPG, CPD, 15th Floor, Maker Tower E, Cuffe Parade, ONGC Mumbai-400 005', 'The technical specifications detail the procurement for the ''Hiring of Integrated Coil Tubing Services along with Nitrogen Pumping services and High-Pressure Pumping services for 3 years on call on Job to Job basis for WSS, Rajahmundry Asset''. It is mandatory for the service to have Regulatory/Statutory Compliance and also be in Compliance with the Service to SOW, STC, SLA etc. There are no addon services specified in the table.', 'Deepak Rana', 'Rajahmundry', 'This bid document, number GEM/2025/B/6086996, is a two-packet custom bid issued by Oil And Natural Gas Corporation Limited (ONGC) for the hiring of integrated services. The scope involves ''Hiring of Integrated Coil Tubing Services along with Nitrogen Pumping services and High-Pressure Pumping services'' for a period of 3 years on a call-out, job-to-job basis for the WSS, Rajahmundry Asset. The bid end date is 07-05-2025, with a bid offer validity of 90 days. The tender requires an Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of 5,190,192 and an e-Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 3.00% for a duration of 45 months. A pre-bid conference is scheduled for 09-04-2025 at the ONGC office in Mumbai. Bidders are required to submit documents related to experience criteria and turnover, and must also comply with the Buyer Organization''s Integrity Pact. The evaluation method will be total value wise. The consignee for the project is Deepak Rana at the ONGC Base Complex in Rajahmundry. The document provides detailed instructions and bank account information for the submission of EMD and PBG through various modes, including online transfer (NEFT/RTGS), Electronic Bank Guarantee (e-BG), and SFMS Bank Guarantee.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is considered successfully completed upon the contractor''s fulfillment of all contractual obligations over the 3-year period. This includes the consistent and satisfactory delivery of Integrated Coil Tubing Services, Nitrogen Pumping services, and High-Pressure Pumping services as and when required on a ''call on Job to Job basis''. The key success criteria are strict adherence to the Scope of Work (SOW), Service Level Agreement (SLA), and Special Terms and Conditions (STC), as well as compliance with all applicable regulatory and statutory requirements.', 'The scope of work is for the ''Hiring of Integrated Coil Tubing Services along with Nitrogen Pumping services and High-Pressure Pumping services''. The services are to be provided for a contract period of 3 years. The operational model is on a ''call on Job to Job basis'' as per the requirements of the WSS, Rajahmundry Asset. The service provider must ensure full compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Special Terms and Conditions (STC), and the Service Level Agreement (SLA) outlined in the tender.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6090777', '13-05-2025 15:00:00', '13-05-2025 15:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Power', 'Contracts And Materials', 'Damodar Valley Corporation', 'Damodar Valley Corporation', 'ravikumar@dvc.gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; As per Scope of Work; Local', NULL, '2 Year', '2,00,000', '2 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '7 Days', NULL, '14,47,488', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'PUNJAB NATIONAL BANK', '28,950', 'Yes', 3, 26, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require an SUV for local service operations in plains areas. The acceptable vehicle models are Mahindra Scorpio, Mahindra Bolero, or Tata Sumo, with a model year of 2025, 2024, 2022, 2021, 2023, or 2020. The vehicle must be diesel-fueled and non-air-conditioned. The usage variant is as per the Scope of Work. The specification for kilometers to be travelled is NA. No add-ons are specified.', 'Bikash Kumar', 'Hazaribag', 'This is a tender (Bid Number: GEM/2025/Β/6090777, Dated: 15-04-2025) issued by the Damodar Valley Corporation under the Ministry of Power for the procurement of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV''. The contract is for a period of 2 years with a bid offer validity of 180 days. The procurement process is a Two Packet Bid with Reverse Auction enabled (H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination). The estimated bid value is 1,447,488, with a required EMD of 28,950 and an ePBG of 3% for 26 months. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 2 Lakhs for the last 3 years and 2 years of past experience in similar services. However, exemptions on experience and turnover are available for MSE and Startup entities. Technically, bidders must have experience in deploying similar commercial vehicles (MCV/MUV) for at least two years. Financially, the bidder''s average annual turnover for the last three financial years must not be less than Rs. 2,17,123.00. The scope of work involves hiring one non-AC, hard-top, diesel SUV for the Distribution Office in Hazaribag, Jharkhand, required to operate for 9 hours daily with a monthly run between 2000 km and 2500 km. The service is required for 24 months and the vehicle must be permitted to operate in both Jharkhand and West Bengal.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer (Damodar Valley Corporation), the work will be considered successfully completed based on the contractor''s consistent fulfillment of several criteria. The primary criterion is the uninterrupted provision of the specified vehicle (one Non-AC, hard-top, diesel SUV, BS-IV or above) in excellent, clean, and roadworthy condition for the entire 2-year contract period at the designated location. Success also hinges on strict adherence to the operational schedule, including 9-hour daily availability, meeting the monthly kilometer targets, and being ready for duty in both Jharkhand and West Bengal as required. The contractor must ensure full compliance with all contractual terms and statutory laws, including proper vehicle maintenance, driver qualifications (valid commercial license, good conduct), and possession of all necessary legal documents (permits, insurance, pollution certificates). Furthermore, successful completion involves seamless service delivery, which includes the immediate deployment of a suitable substitute vehicle during any breakdown, accurate maintenance and timely submission of logbooks for billing, and the avoidance of any penalties for service failures, quality deficiencies, or unauthorized absences.', 'The scope of work is for the hiring of one (1) no. Non AC hard Top covered diesel driven Commercial Vehicle(MCV/MUV) like Tata Sumo/Mahindra Marshall /Mahindra Bolero/Mahindra Scorpio or any other equivalent make or model for BS IV or Above for Distribution office Hazaribag for 02(Two) years from the actual commencement date. The normal duty hours of the vehicle on each day will be 9 (nine) hours. The vehicle is required to run a minimum of 2000 KM/Months and a maximum of 2500 KM/Month. The maximum expected hours of stay beyond the normal duty 9 hour is 40 Hrs/Month. The vehicle shall be required to perform duty in both Jharkhand & West Bengal as and when required, and the successful bidder must submit a valid road permit for both states. The vehicle must be kept in very good running and roadworthy condition at all times, equipped with a spare wheel, tools, and a FIRST AID BOX. The vehicle shall be engaged only for the purpose of Distribution section, Hazaribag, DVC. The driver must possess an active cell phone and a valid Public Service Driving License. The normal reporting point for the vehicle will be the Distribution Office DVC Hazaribag. A board marked `ON EMERGENCY DUTY, DISTRIBUTION OFFICE, DVC HAZARIBAG` must be placed rigidly at the front of the vehicle.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6098777', '10-04-2025 11:00:00', '10-04-2025 11:30:00', '75 Days', 'Ministry Of Chemicals And Fertilizers', 'Department Of Fertilizers', 'Rashtriya Chemicals And Fertilizers Limited (rcf)', 'Rcf Tr Hod Mes', 'buycon186.rcflr.mh@gembuyer.in', 'Repair, Maintenance, and Installation of Plant/ Systems/Equipments (Version 2) - Manufacturing Unit; Total price including all applicable taxes & duties for hiring on-demand Supervision services for GTG from OEM Ms Siemens Ltd Ms Siemens Energy ..', NULL, '1 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '4 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'ICICI', '1,50,000', 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications are defined for a service within a Manufacturing Unit. The requirement is for the ''Total price including all applicable taxes & duties for hiring on-demand Supervision services for GTG from OEM Ms Siemens Ltd Ms Siemens Energy India Limited AS PER SOW AND Quantum of job''. Consumables and spare parts are to be provided ''AS PER SOW AND NIT''. The estimated number of visits based on last year''s records is 0.', 'Parag Chintaman Wandile', 'Chembur', 'This GeM bid document (GEM/2025/B/6098777), issued by Rashtriya Chemicals And Fertilizers Limited (RCF), is a tender for a one-year contract for ''Repair, Maintenance, and Installation of Plant/Systems/Equipments''. Specifically, it is for hiring on-demand supervision services for Gas Turbine Generators (GTG) from the Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM), M/s Siemens Ltd / M/s Siemens Energy India Limited. The bid is issued on a proprietary basis, meaning only offers from Siemens will be considered, and all other bids will be treated as unsolicited and rejected. The scope of work involves providing a Field Service Representative (FSR) to supervise troubleshooting, repair, and maintenance of two 25 MW Siemens SGT-700 GTGs at the RCF Trombay plant. The document specifies the responsibilities of both Siemens (providing expert FSR, special tools, planning, reporting, and covering travel/lodging) and RCF (providing general tools, skilled manpower, and utilities). The contract has an Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of 150,000 INR and the offer validity is 75 days. The tender includes detailed annexures covering mandatory Health, Safety, and Environment (HSE) compliance, commercial terms and conditions, and strict adherence to all applicable Indian labour laws, including minimum wages, PF, and ESI.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer (RCF), the work will be considered successfully completed based on the following criteria: 1. Adherence to the completion timeline stipulated in the scope of work, as failure to do so will result in the levy of Liquidated Damages. 2. Full execution of all tasks outlined in the detailed Scope of Work, including expert supervision of troubleshooting and maintenance, ensuring minimal downtime, guiding the RCF team, overseeing a smooth GTG start-up post-maintenance, and submitting a comprehensive report with recommendations for efficient operation. 3. The quality of workmanship must be guaranteed for a period of six months from the date of completion, with the contractor being liable to rectify any defects arising during this period free of charge. 4. Complete compliance with all terms and conditions, including statutory and mandatory clauses related to labor laws and Health, Safety & Environment (HSE) requirements. 5. Timely and accurate submission of bills and all necessary supporting documents as per the payment terms to ensure smooth processing and final payment.', 'The scope of work involves lining up a contract for hiring on-demand supervision services from OEM M/s Siemens for two 25 MW Siemens make SGT-700 Gas Turbine cum Generators (GTG) located at RCF Trombay. The primary role of the Siemens Field Service Representative (FSR) is to correct failures, faults, operating abnormalities, or defects, and to repair, modify, or replace parts to restore the GTG to an operable condition. M/s Siemens shall depute an expert FSR (Indian or Expat) to supervise troubleshooting activities, guide the RCF maintenance team, and create a plan of action to minimize machine downtime. The FSR will study the GTG''s operating parameters, recommend efficiency improvements, coordinate with RCF''s skilled manpower, be present during the start-up after maintenance to ensure smooth operation, and submit a detailed report of all activities with recommendations. M/s Siemens is also responsible for arranging special tools like a Boroscope and covering all costs related to the FSR''s boarding, lodging, and travel. RCF''s scope is to arrange general tools and tackles, provide skilled manpower such as riggers, welders, electricians, and helpers, and supply utilities like air, water, electricity, and scaffolding if required. Regarding mobilization, RCF will intimate M/s Siemens to arrange an Indian FSR within 24 hours and an Expat FSR within 7 days.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6111418', '17-06-2025 21:00:00', '17-06-2025 21:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Army', '***********', 'anikum.25420@gov.in', 'Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium SUV; Outstation 24*7; 250Kms x 8Hrs', NULL, '10 Months 10 Day', '3,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'Yes', '50% Lowest Priced Technically Qualified Bidders', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '1,95,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', NULL, 'Yes', 3, 6, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '13-05-2025 12:00:00', 'CP-4, 439 (Independent) Engineer Squadron, Khasa cantt, Amritsar', 'The technical specifications for the required service, Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring, mandate a Premium SUV vehicle type. Acceptable car models include the Toyota Innova, Toyota Fortuner, and Toyota Innova Crysta, with a model year of 2021, 2022, or 2023. The service required is for Outstation 24*7 with a usage variant of 250Kms x 8Hrs. The vehicles must have travelled Upto 75,000 Kms and be Non-A/C, suitable for operation in a High Altitude Area. Any fuel type is acceptable. The trip type specified is one way.', '***********', 'Amritsar', 'This bid, number GEM/2025/B/6111418, is issued by the Indian Army, Ministry of Defence, for the procurement of ''Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium SUV; Outstation 24*7; 250Kms x 8Hrs''. The contract period is 10 months and 10 days, with a bid offer validity of 180 days from the bid end date of 17-06-2025. The estimated bid value is 195,000. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 3 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. Exemptions for these criteria are available for MSE and Startup entities. The requirement is for two vehicles to be deployed in Amritsar City for a duration of 15 days within the contract period. The tender follows a two-packet bid system with a 3% e-Performance Bank Guarantee required for 6 months. The document also contains detailed Additional Terms & Conditions which specify two separate requirements for a 7-seater Non-AC Light Vehicle for journeys from Amritsar to Nyoma (Leh), outlining operational procedures, vehicle and driver standards, payment terms, insurance, and various legal and compliance clauses that supersede the general GeM terms where conflicts arise.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is considered successfully completed upon fulfillment of several key criteria. Firstly, the service provider must furnish a Performance Bank Guarantee for 3% of the contract value, which acts as security for the due performance of the contract. The core of the service requires the provider to supply the specified number and type of vehicles in a road-worthy condition at the designated time and place, adhering strictly to the schedule. Throughout the service period, all documentation, particularly the Car Diary, must be accurately maintained and signed by the user, serving as proof of service delivery. Successful completion is contingent on the provider adhering to all terms, including those related to vehicle maintenance, driver conduct, and insurance. The final milestone for success is the settlement of all accounts and the submission of a ''No Demand Certificate'' by the service provider, after which the Performance Security Deposit is refunded. Any failure to provide the service as required, such as non-delivery or breakdown, will result in penalties or hiring of services at the provider''s risk and expense, indicating a failure to meet the success criteria.', 'The scope of work involves providing Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for the Indian Army for the movement of personnel and goods. The contractor must supply Premium SUV vehicles, specifically Toyota Innova, Toyota Fortuner, or Toyota Innova Crysta models from the years 2021-2023, which are Non-A/C and fit for high altitude operations. The service is required on an Outstation 24*7 basis. The primary requirement outlined is for two vehicles in Amritsar City for a 15-day period. 

A detailed requirement is specified for two lots of a 7-seater Non-AC Light Vehicle for journeys from Amritsar to Nyoma (Leh). The first lot is from 01-Jul-25 to 31-Jul-25, and the second is from 01-Sep-25 to 30-Sep-25, each covering an approximate one-way distance of 1200 km. The contractor is responsible for all operational aspects, including providing vehicles in excellent road-worthy condition with all necessary equipment such as a spare wheel, tools, first-aid box, and tarpaulins. The contractor must bear all costs related to fuel, maintenance, tolls, parking, and taxes. They must provide experienced, medically fit, and police-verified drivers with valid licenses suitable for high-altitude terrain, and is also responsible for the drivers'' rations, bedding, and professional conduct. The contractor must ensure all vehicles have valid comprehensive insurance and are registered as commercial transport with all taxes paid. The scope also includes the safe carriage of all personnel and stores, adherence to delivery timelines, and full compliance with all terms specified in the contract, including accident and insurance liabilities.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6136538', '05-05-2025 17:00:00', '05-05-2025 17:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Power', 'Contracts And Materials', 'Damodar Valley Corporation', 'Damodar Valley Corporation', 'subha.choudhury@dvc.gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of one number Diesel driven AC hard top covered vehicle Jeep or Bolero or Sumo or Scorpio or equivalent for official use of the GM,Civil, DVC, RTPS for two years', 'Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services', '2 Year', '1,89,92,499', 'last 7 years', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '3 Days', NULL, '13,29,47,491', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '25,323', NULL, 3, 26, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, 'Contracts & Materials Section, Raghunathpur Thermal Power Station, Village-Dumdumi, P.O.- Nildih, PIN Code-723133', 'Based on the Technical Specifications table, the service proposed for procurement is the ''Hiring of one number Diesel driven AC hard top covered vehicle Jeep or Bolero or Sumo or Scorpio or equivalent for official use of the GM,Civil, DVC, RTPS for two years''. The service provider must ensure YES for ''Regulatory/ Statutory Compliance of Service'' and YES for ''Compliance of Service to SOW, STC, SLA etc''. There are no Addon(s) specified for this service.', 'Dhananjay Kumar', 'Purulia', 'This GeM bid document (GEM/2025/B/6136538) is for a custom service issued by Damodar Valley Corporation (DVC), Ministry of Power, for the hiring of one diesel-driven AC hard top covered vehicle (such as a Jeep, Bolero, Sumo, or Scorpio equivalent) for a contract period of two years. The vehicle is for the official use of the GM, Civil, DVC, at Raghunathpur Thermal Power Station (RTPS). The bid end date is 05-05-2025, and the estimated bid value is 13,29,474.91. Financial requirements include an Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of 25,323 and an e-Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 3.00% for a duration of 26 months. Bidders must demonstrate past experience in similar services, meeting specific value thresholds, although exemptions are available for MSE and Startup entities. The document provides comprehensive General Instructions for bidders, including details on bid submission, a policy on debarment for non-performance or integrity breaches, and specific technical and financial credentials required. The General Conditions of Contract (GCC) outline the legal framework, covering payment terms (95% against RA bills and 5% on successful completion), penalties for service failures (e.g., Rs. 700/day for non-provision of the vehicle), liquidated damages, performance security, force majeure, and termination clauses. The scope of work specifies the vehicle type, operational hours, mileage limits, driver qualifications, and maintenance responsibilities.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is agreed to have been successfully completed upon the fulfillment of several key criteria. The primary requirement is the contractor''s consistent and uninterrupted provision of the specified vehicle with a qualified driver for the entire two-year contract period, strictly adhering to all operational terms outlined in the scope of work, including duty hours, mileage, and emergency availability. Furthermore, the contractor must ensure the vehicle and all its statutory documents remain valid and maintained throughout the contract. The ultimate measure of success is the formal certification of the executed works and services by the Engineer-in-charge of DVC. This certification, confirming satisfactory performance and the completion of all contractual obligations, is the trigger for the release of the final 5% payment and the return of the Security Deposit-cum-Performance Guarantee.', 'The scope of work is for the hiring of one number Diesel driven AC hard top covered vehicle, specified as a Sedan (up to 1400CC for ICE vehicle) that is five-seated and not older than five years, along with a driver, for the official use of the GM(Civil), DVC, RTPS for a period of two years. The vehicle is to be engaged for General Duty Hours for the Department of Civil, RTPS, with a guaranteed monthly minimum run of 1500 KM, a monthly average run of 2250 KM, and a maximum run of 3000 KM in any single month. Normal duty hours are 09 hours per day, with the vehicle required to be available on call at any odd hour for emergent needs. The contractor must provide the vehicle with all statutory documents (vehicle ownership, commercial registration, insurance, Road Tax Certificate, Fitness Certificate, Pollution Certificate) and ensure it is mechanically perfect and equipped with a spare wheel and necessary tools. The engaged driver must possess a Public Service Driving License, and a standby driver must be made available. The contractor is responsible for all running charges, including fuel, lubricants, maintenance, repairs, and driver''s remuneration. In case of a breakdown, a suitable substitute vehicle must be provided immediately. A pair of logbooks must be maintained for recording journey details and mileage, which must be endorsed by authorized DVC representatives. The vehicle must display a board marked "RTPS, DVC". The contractor is liable for a penalty of Rs. 700/- for failure to provide the vehicle for an entire shift. Fuel cost (Diesel) will be reimbursed based on a formula assuming 12 KM/ltr mileage. The contractor will also be reimbursed for parking charges and toll taxes against documentary evidence.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6159426', '07-05-2025 17:00:00', '07-05-2025 17:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Water Resources River Development And Ganga Rejuvenation', NULL, 'Central Ground Water Board (cgwb)', 'Northern Region Lucknow', 'ashwani.kumar-cgwb@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 3000 Km x 364 hours; Outstation', NULL, '7 Month', '5,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', NULL, NULL, 3, 8, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services require an SUV type vehicle, with suggested models being Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra Bolero, or Mahindra Bolero Neo. The service has a usage variant of 3000 Km x 364 hours and is for outstation duty. The vehicle model must be from the year 2023, 2024, or 2025, and should have travelled upto 50,000 Kms. The vehicle must be Non-A/C, run on Diesel, and will be operated in Hilly Areas. Additionally, outstation night charges are applicable.', 'Praveen Kumar', 'Bareilly', 'This bid, with number GEM/2025/B/6159426, is for the procurement of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 3000 Km x 364 hours; Outstation'' issued by the Central Ground Water Board (cgwb), Northern Region Lucknow. The contract period is for 7 months. The bid end date is 07-05-2025, and the bid offer validity is 120 days. Key financial requirements for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 5 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. MSEs are eligible for exemption from experience and turnover criteria. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with a Reverse Auction (RA) enabled, using the H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination rule. Evaluation will be on a total value wise basis. No EMD is required, but an ePBG of 3.00% is mandatory for a duration of 8 months. The beneficiary for the service is the Executive Engineer, CGWB, Division 16, in Bareilly, Uttar Pradesh. The scope of work specifies one SUV for outstation service in hilly areas, with the driver required to have 5 years of hilly area driving experience and a specific license. The buyer has included an option clause to vary the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the successful completion of the work is contingent upon the service provider consistently furnishing one SUV that meets all specified technical criteria for the entire contract period of 7 months. This includes providing a vehicle of the model year 2023-2025, running on diesel, suitable for hilly areas, and adhering to the usage limit of 3000 Km and 364 hours per month. A critical success criterion is the provision of a driver who possesses five years of certified driving experience in hilly areas with a valid hilly license and knowledge of minor vehicle repairs. The work will be deemed successfully completed upon the uninterrupted and satisfactory delivery of these taxi hiring services, including handling an estimated 25 outstation nights per month, to the consignee in Bareilly for the full duration of the contract.', 'The scope of work involves providing one SUV on a monthly basis for Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for a contract period of 7 months. The service is for outstation duty, primarily in Hilly Areas, with a specified usage of 3000 Km and 364 hours per month. The vehicle must be one of the following models or similar: Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra Bolero, or Mahindra Bolero Neo, with a manufacturing year of 2023, 2024, or 2025 and total mileage not exceeding 50,000 Kms. The vehicle must be a Non-A/C, diesel-fueled model. A key requirement is that the driver must possess five years of driving experience in hilly areas, hold a hilly area driving license, and have knowledge of minor vehicle repairing. The service is required for the consignee located at CGWB, DIV-16, 3rd Floor, Nirman Jyoti Building, DD Puram, Bareilly-243122. The scope also includes handling an estimated 25 outstation nights per month, for which charges are applicable.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6159599', '14-05-2025 10:00:00', '14-05-2025 10:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Defence Production', 'Yantra India Limited', '***********', 'subhajitdas.ord@ord.gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Comprehensive Annual Maintenance Contract of Server and SAN Storage at MSF DATA Center as per scope of work', 'Customized AMC/CMC for Pre-owned Products', '1 Year', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '3,18,600', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require a Comprehensive Annual Maintenance Contract of Server and SAN Storage at MSF DATA Center as per the scope of work. The service must ensure Regulatory/Statutory Compliance and also adhere to the requirements laid out in the Scope of Work (SOW), Special Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA). There are no additional addon specifications or supplementary specification documents listed in the table.', '***********', 'North 24 Paraganas', 'This bid document (GEM/2025/B/6159599), issued by Yantra India Limited under the Ministry of Defence, is for a Custom Bid for Services for a ''Comprehensive Annual Maintenance Contract of Server and SAN Storage at MSF DATA Center''. The contract period is for one year, with a bid offer validity of 180 days. The estimated bid value is 318,600. It is a Two Packet Bid with a Reverse Auction (RA) enabled, using the H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination rule for RA qualification. The document outlines specific buyer-added terms and conditions which supersede general GeM clauses. Key terms include a penalty of Rs. 2500/- per server/SAN for downtime exceeding 24 hours, and the buyer reserves the right to repair systems at the vendor''s cost if not resolved within 48 hours. Payments are to be made quarterly upon the issuance of a successful job completion certificate. The document also provides exemptions for Micro and Small Enterprises (MSEs) and Startups from turnover and experience criteria, and gives purchase preference to MSEs. The successful bidder must comply with all applicable labor laws and the detailed Scope of Work provided in a separate document.', 'The successful completion of the work is contingent upon the issuance of a ''successful job completion certificate'' at the end of each quarter. This certificate will only be issued if the vendor has met all contractual obligations for that period. This includes preventing persistent breakdowns of the server and storage systems, ensuring any downtime does not exceed the stipulated limits, and performing all unattended preventive maintenance as required. Failure to meet these conditions will result in the job completion certificate being withheld, and consequently, the quarterly payment will not be processed until the job is completed as per the contract.', 'The scope of work involves providing a Comprehensive Annual Maintenance Contract for the Server and SAN Storage at the MSF DATA Center for a period of one year. The bidder is required to comply with the detailed scope outlined in the document ''Scope of Work:1745317120.pdf'' and its associated Annexure-A, Annexure-B, and Annexure-C. The scope includes all necessary actions to maintain the uptime of the equipment, with specific penalty clauses for downtime exceeding 24 hours. It also mandates preventive maintenance of the server system. The firm''s responsibilities are inclusive of all safety equipment required for the job. The detailed technical qualifications and experience requirements for the bidder are also specified within the Scope of Work document under Sl. No. 21.'),
(NULL, '28-04-2025 18:00:00', '28-04-2025 18:30:00', '30 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Army', '***********', 'nbng4-mes@nic.in', 'Hiring of Consultancy Services - Percentage based - Functional Consultants; Building and Construction; Yes; Onsite', NULL, '1 Month 1 Day', NULL, '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '32,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require a Functional Consultant for Building and Construction. The Consulting Category/Stream is Functional Consultants and the Consultant''s Profile is Building and Construction. A Proof of Concept (POC) is required. The deployment of the consultant/resource must be Onsite.', '***********', 'Bengaluru', 'This bid document, number GEM/2025/B/6164266 dated 24-04-2025, is for the hiring of Onsite Functional Consultancy Services on a percentage basis in the Building and Construction sector. The tender is issued by the Indian Army, under the Department of Military Affairs, Ministry of Defence. The contract period is for 1 month and 1 day. The estimated bid value is 32000, and the evaluation method is total value wise. The bid is a Two Packet Bid, with the end date and time for submission being 28-04-2025 18:00:00 and the opening on the same day at 18:30:00. The bid offer validity is 30 days. Bidders are required to have 3 years of past experience in similar services, and must provide documentary evidence such as copies of relevant contracts or orders. Specifically, bidders must have completed either three similar services costing at least 40% of the estimated cost, two similar services costing at least 50%, or one similar service costing at least 80% of the estimated cost within the last three financial years plus the current financial year. No exemption for experience and turnover is available for MSEs or Startups, though MSEs are eligible for purchase preference as per the Public Procurement Policy for Micro and Small Enterprises (MSEs) Order, 2012. Bidders must also comply with MII (Make in India) requirements. No EMD or ePBG is required. The buyer reserves the right to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25% under the OPTION CLAUSE. All service providers must comply with applicable labour laws. The bid is governed by GeM General Terms and Conditions and the Service Level Agreement, with the latter overriding in case of any contradiction.', 'Successful completion and acceptance of the tendered work will be determined by the fulfillment of the following conditions: 1. Successful delivery and acceptance of the required Proof of Concept (POC). 2. Deployment of the consultant/resource Onsite as specified. 3. Completion of geological investigations at three different locations, including sub-soil extraction by drilling 100 mm diameter holes up to 10.00m from existing ground level to determine the profile of strata, water table, and sub-water pressure. 4. Collection of disturbed and undisturbed soil samples and conduction of all specified laboratory tests (Sieve analysis, Atterberg limits, moisture content, particle size, density, specific gravity, swell index, organic material, consolidation test, triaxial compression test, harmful salt) in accordance with IS-2131, IS-6403, IS-1498 & IS-2720. 5. Submission of comprehensive soil investigation reports that provide the Safe Bearing Capacity (SBC) of the soil at every 1-meter interval, with calculations governed by IS-8009, IS 2720, IS 6403, IS-1904, & IS-1080. 6. Each report must be accompanied by a detailed site plan showing bore hole locations, and all pages of the report must be serially numbered, stamped, and signed by the agency, clearly stating the job and site name. 7. Full compliance with all applicable laws and regulations, including but not limited to Labour Laws such as The Minimum Wages Act 1948 and The Payment of Wages Act 1936, as non-compliance will be treated as a breach of contract. 8. Adherence to all conditions stipulated in the GeM General Terms and Conditions and the Service Level Agreement specific to this service.', 'The scope of work involves providing onsite Functional Consultancy Services for Building and Construction, which requires a Proof of Concept (POC). The core activities include carrying out Geological investigations at three different locations spread within a 10 Km diameter. This involves sub-soil extraction by drilling 100 mm diameter holes at required locations up to 10.00m from the existing ground level to determine the profile of strata, water table, and sub-water pressure. The work must adhere to the relevant specifications of IS-2131, IS-6403, IS-1498 & IS-2720. The scope includes the collection of disturbed and undisturbed soil samples at intervals of 1.00 Mtr or at the change of strata, and conducting a series of laboratory tests on these samples as per IS specification of 2720. The required tests are: Sieve analysis, Atterberg limits, Natural moisture content, Particle size analysis test, Bulk density, Specific gravity, Free swell index and swelling properties of soil, Organix material in soil if any, Consolidation test (Compressed index value), Triaxial compression test and determination of shear parameter (C&O Test), and Harmful salt investigation. The deliverables include providing the Safe Bearing Capacity (SBC) of the soil at every 1m interval up to the bore hole''s depth, with calculations governed by IS-8009 (Pt-I)-1976, IS 2720 (PT-II)-1980, IS 6403-1981, IS-1904-1986 & IS-1080-1985. A detailed site plan showing the approximate location of each numbered bore hole must be enclosed with each site''s soil investigation report. All pages of the report must be serially numbered, stamped, signed by the agency, and must state the name of the job and the specific site. Transportation charges, including loading/unloading of heavy equipment and technician travel between the laboratory and work site, are to be included in the quoted rates.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6166425', '13-05-2025 09:00:00', '13-05-2025 09:30:00', '45 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Defence Research & Development', 'Office Of Dg (Med & Cos)', '***********', 'kamal.hqr@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; 1500 km x 260 hours; Local 24*7', NULL, '1 Year', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services'' require a Sedan type vehicle from the year 2023. The acceptable car models are Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, or Hyundai Xcent. The vehicle must have travelled up to 25,000 Kms and be equipped with Air Conditioning. The fuel type must be CNG, and the service is for operation in Plains areas. The usage variant is defined as 1500 km and 260 hours on a monthly basis, with a Local 24*7 service type. There are no Addon specified.', '***********', 'North Delhi', 'This tender, with Bid Number GEM/2025/B/6166425 dated 28-04-2025, is for ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; 1500 km x 260 hours; Local 24*7'' for a contract period of one year. It is issued by the Office Of Dg (Med & Cos) under the Department Of Defence Research & Development, Ministry Of Defence. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with an end date of 13-05-2025 and an offer validity of 45 days. The tender includes provisions for Reverse Auction (H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination) and evaluation is based on the total value. Exemptions from experience criteria are available for MSE and Startup entities. The tender also supports MSE Purchase Preference and MII Compliance. The buyer has included an option clause to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. One Sedan vehicle is required for a consignee in NORTH DELHI for a duration of 12 months. Service providers are mandated to comply with all applicable Labour Laws, and the contract will be governed by GeM''s General Terms and Conditions and Service Level Agreement.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed from the tender issuer''s perspective, the selected service provider must consistently fulfill all contractual obligations throughout the 1-year period. This includes providing a Sedan vehicle (Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, or Hyundai Xcent) of the 2023 model year with CNG fuel and air conditioning, which has run no more than 25,000 Kms. The provider must ensure the vehicle is available for Local 24*7 service, meeting the monthly usage variant of 1500 km and 260 hours. Furthermore, successful completion is contingent upon the provider''s strict compliance with all applicable Labour Laws such as The Minimum Wages Act, 1948, The Payment of Wages Act, 1936, and others as stipulated, along with adherence to the GeM General Terms and Conditions and the Service Level Agreement.', 'The Scope of Work involves the provision of one Sedan type vehicle on a monthly hiring basis for a contract period of one year (12 months). The service is required for a consignee located in NORTH DELHI. The provider must supply a vehicle from the year 2023, with acceptable models being Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, or Hyundai Xcent. The vehicle must be air-conditioned, run on CNG, and have travelled no more than 25,000 Kms. The service entails a usage variant of 1500 km and 260 hours per month, with Local 24*7 availability for operation in Plains areas. The service provider is also mandated to ensure strict compliance with all applicable Labour Laws, including The Minimum Wages Act, 1948, The Payment of Wages Act, 1936, The Payment of Bonus Act, 1965, The Equal Remuneration Act, 1976, and The Payment of Gratuity Act, 1972, as any non-compliance will be treated as a breach of contract.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6186097', '21-05-2025 15:00:00', '21-05-2025 15:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Commerce And Industry', 'Department Of Commerce', 'Government E-marketplace (gem)', 'Government E Market', 'sr.mgr-procurement@gem.gov.in', 'Hiring of Consultants - Per Person Per Months Based - Functional Consultants; Finance & Accounts; As per RFP; No', NULL, '2 Year', '40,00,000', 'last five financial years', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '3 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'State Bank of India', '2,50,000', NULL, 3, 26, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '12-05-2025 12:00:00', 'New Delhi', 'The tender outlines technical specifications for hiring two distinct consultant roles for Finance & Accounts. The first role is for a Project Lead, who must be a Functional Consultant with a specialization in Finance & Accounts. This position requires 7 to 9 years of total experience, and the deployment is hybrid. The required educational qualifications for the Project Lead are CFP/CFA (Certified Financial Planner/Chartered Financial Analyst), CA, CMA, or MBA. The second role is for a Project Associate, who is also a Functional Consultant in Finance & Accounts. This role requires 4 to 6 years of experience with an onsite deployment. The educational qualifications are the same as the Project Lead: CFP/CFA, CA, CMA, or MBA. For both positions, a Proof of Concept (POC) is not required, indicative qualifications are as per the RFP, and any additional certifications will be as indicated in the BID.', 'Anil Kumar', 'New Delhi', 'This Government e-Marketplace (GeM) tender (GEM/2025/Β/6186097) is for the "Appointment of Treasury/Investment/Transaction Advisor for GeM office" for an initial contract period of two years, extendable by one year. The primary objective is to enhance GeM''s treasury management by ensuring capital protection, mitigating risk, and optimizing tax-adjusted returns through expert investment strategies aligned with GeM''s Treasury Policy and DPE guidelines. The selection process is a Quality cum Cost Based Selection (QCBS) with a 70:30 weightage for technical and financial bids, respectively. Key responsibilities for the selected advisor include devising investment strategies, implementing the treasury policy, performance monitoring, treasury optimization, reporting to management, and assisting with all necessary documentation for banking and investments. A significant deliverable is the development and transfer of a customized digital system and automated dashboard for real-time treasury monitoring, to be completed within 150 days. Bidders must meet eligibility criteria, including an average annual turnover of at least 40 Lakhs, a positive net worth for the last three years, and relevant experience in treasury advisory for government or large corporate entities. The evaluation criteria assess the bidder''s approach, resource profile (Project Lead and Project Associate), relevant experience, Assets Under Management (AUM), SEBI registration, and financial turnover. The tender includes standard terms regarding penalties for delays, resource replacement, confidentiality, and contract termination.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer (GeM), the work will be deemed successfully completed upon the fulfillment of several key criteria. Primarily, the advisor must deliver all specified items within the stipulated timelines. This includes the submission of a comprehensive Draft Report on GeM''s treasury within 45 days, a Final Report post-feedback, and the development and transfer of a fully functional digital system and automated dashboard within 150 days of the contract award. Continuous success involves the timely and satisfactory execution of all recurring second-phase activities, such as preparing periodic performance reports, providing ad-hoc analysis, and periodically reviewing the Treasury Policy. The quality of all deliverables and services must be consistently satisfactory to GeM, as payment is directly linked to a ''satisfactory performance'' certification by the Client. Finally, success is contingent upon the advisor''s full compliance with all contractual terms and conditions and applicable laws, thereby avoiding any of the ''Events of Default'' listed in the agreement, which include failure to deliver services, misconduct, or undue delays.', 'The detailed Scope of Work for the Treasury/Investment/Transaction Advisor encompasses several key responsibilities. 1) Investment Strategy and Policy Implementation: The advisor must analyze and devise investment strategies in strict accordance with GeM''s Treasury Policy and DPE guidelines, prepare and update a comprehensive Investment Policy Statement (IPS), ensure regulatory compliance, assess working capital requirements, conduct due diligence on proposed investments, and stay updated on market trends. 2) Reporting and Communication: Prepare and present comprehensive reports on investment performance, opportunities, and risk exposure to the Management/Board/Committee. 3) Performance Monitoring and Compliance: Continuously track the performance of approved investment strategies for immediate corrective action and ensure ongoing compliance with the Treasury Policy. 4) Treasury Optimization: Provide advisory on cash flow forecasting, liquidity management, cost reduction measures, and leveraging idle funds. 5) Documentation Assistance: Manage all necessary documentation for establishing tie-ups with banks, including opening Bank Accounts, Constituent Subsidiary General Ledger (CSGL) accounts, and Demat accounts. 6) Customized Digital System/Tool: Develop, provide, and transfer to GeM a digital system with an automated dashboard for real-time performance and compliance monitoring, along with a customized database of investment opportunities. 7) Comprehensive Exit Plan: Create a detailed exit plan to ensure a smooth transfer of knowledge and information upon contract termination. 8) Confidentiality: Maintain strict confidentiality of all financial and organizational information shared during the engagement.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6186421', '18-06-2025 09:00:00', '18-06-2025 09:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Defence Production', 'Directorate General Of Quality Assurance (Dgqa)', '***********', 'phoolsingh.tare70@gov.in', 'Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs', NULL, '1 Year', NULL, NULL, 'Yes | Complete', 'Yes | Complete', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', '50% Lowest Priced Technically Qualified Bidders', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '3,90,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services require a Sedan vehicle, with suggested models being Honda Amaze or Maruti Suzuki Dzire. The service is for Local use with a usage variant of 80Kms x 10Hrs per day. The vehicle model must be from the year 2024 or 2023, having travelled up to 25,000 Kms. It must be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C), operate in Plains, and be a Diesel fuel type. The specified trip type is Return.', '***********', 'Hoshangabad', 'This is a bid document (Bid Number: GEM/2025/B/6186421) issued by the Directorate General Of Quality Assurance (Dgqa), under the Ministry Of Defence, for the procurement of Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services. The specific requirement is for one Sedan category vehicle for local use (80Kms x 10Hrs daily) for a contract period of 1 year. The service is needed in Hoshangabad for a duration of 215 days within the contract period. The bid has an estimated value of 390,000 and follows a Two Packet Bid system with a Reverse Auction for the 50% lowest priced technically qualified bidders. The bid has an offer validity of 180 days from the bid end date of 18-06-2025. The policy provides complete exemption for MSE and Startups from experience and turnover criteria and also includes provisions for MSE Purchase Preference. The buyer retains an option to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25 percent.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer, the success of the tender is contingent upon the award of the contract to a qualified bidder who subsequently provides the specified service without failure. The successful completion of the work is agreed upon when the service provider consistently supplies one Sedan vehicle, conforming to all technical specifications (including model year 2023/2024, A/C, diesel, and mileage limits), for the stipulated duration of 215 days at the designated location (Hoshangabad) as per the 80Kms/10Hrs daily usage pattern. Adherence to all contract terms, conditions, and applicable labor laws throughout the one-year contract period is mandatory for the work to be considered successfully completed.', 'The scope of work involves providing one vehicle under the ''Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services'' category for the consignee located in Hoshangabad. The service provider is required to supply a Sedan type vehicle, such as a Honda Amaze or Maruti Suzuki Dzire, of model year 2024 or 2023. The vehicle must be diesel-fueled, equipped with air conditioning, and should have been driven for up to 25,000 Kms. The service is for local, return trips within a plains area of operation. The daily usage is defined as 80 kilometers and 10 hours. This service is required for a total duration of 215 days, to be utilized within the overall contract period of one year.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6188423', '18-06-2025 11:00:00', '18-06-2025 11:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Power', 'Power Grid Corporation Of India Limited', 'Power Grid Corporation Of India Limited', 'Corporate Office Gurgaon', 'buyer3.pgcil.ghy@gembuyer.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab and Taxi Hiring Service - Without Fuel - SUV; Mahindra Bolero; 2025; ACCEPTABLE KM RUN FOR BRAND NEW VEHICLE; A/C; AS PER BIDDING DOCUMENTS', NULL, '3 Year', NULL, 'Minimum duration of 6 months in any organization', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '4 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'Yes (Arbitration clause document) as per DoE OM No.F.1/2/2024-PPD dated 03.06.2024 Arbitration should not be routinely included in contracts', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '17,000', 'Yes', 5, 39, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the hired vehicle require a 2025 model SUV, specifically a Mahindra Bolero. The vehicle must be brand new with an acceptable kilometer run, equipped with air conditioning, and run on diesel. It needs to be suitable for both plain and hilly terrains and must be provided with a driver. The engagement will be as per the bidding documents, and the cost of fuel will be reimbursed to the service provider based on actual consumption.', 'Mohammed Anas Tanveer', 'Shillong', 'This tender, with Bid Number GEM/2025/B/6188423, is issued by Power Grid Corporation Of India Limited for the hiring of one brand new 2025 Mahindra Bolero SUV on a monthly basis without fuel. The contract period is for 3 years, with a bid offer validity of 180 days from the bid end date of 18-06-2025. The tender requires an EMD of 17000 and an ePBG of 5% for a duration of 39 months. The service is required for the POWERGRID Bongaigaon - Salakati Substation in Assam, with an estimated travel of 3000 KMs per month. Key requirements for bidders include being a ''Class-I local supplier'' with a minimum of 60% local content, having a registered office in the North-Eastern Region, and possessing past experience of providing a vehicle for at least 6 months. The scope of work involves providing the vehicle in perfect condition with a driver, tools, and consumables. While the fixed hiring charges quoted by the bidder should be inclusive of GST and firm for the contract duration, costs for the driver''s salary (as per minimum wage laws), fuel, lubricants, and night halts will be reimbursed separately. The contract is for an initial period of three years and may be extended by six months based on satisfactory performance.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the successful completion of the work is contingent on several key criteria. Primarily, the contractor must consistently provide the specified brand new Mahindra Bolero vehicle in perfect, well-maintained condition, along with a qualified driver, for the entire three-year contract period as detailed in the Scope of Work. The performance of the contract must be deemed satisfactory, as this is a prerequisite for any potential contract extension and for the return of the Contract Performance Guarantee (CPG). The contractor is required to strictly adhere to all contractual terms, including compliance with statutory regulations such as the payment of minimum wages to the driver. Furthermore, the contractor must not be involved in any fraudulent activities. Failure to meet these standards, particularly unsatisfactory performance, can lead to the termination of the contract.', 'The scope of work is for the hiring of one (01) brand new closed body Mahindra Bolero vehicle with two-wheel drive for regular office work at POWERGRID Bongaigaon - Salakati Substation for an initial period of 03 (three) years. The vehicle must be provided in perfect condition along with a driver, all consumables, tools, tackles, spares, and a uniform for the driver at the contractor''s cost. The bidder shall quote a total fixed hiring charge (inclusive of GST) which will remain firm for the entire contract period. This fixed charge should include all costs except for the driver''s salary, fuel/lubricants, and night halt charges, which will be reimbursed separately. The driver''s salary will be reimbursed based on minimum wage laws for skilled manpower. Fuel (Diesel at 1 Ltr/10 km) and engine oil (1 Ltr/1000 km) costs will be reimbursed at prevailing rates, while night halt charges will be paid at Rs. 350/- per night. The vehicle is for the exclusive use of POWERGRID personnel, with normal duty hours of 8 hours per day, but must be available 24/7 for emergencies, 7 days a week. The vehicle must have a valid commercial permit, comprehensive insurance, and all necessary documentation. The headquarters for the vehicle will be at POWERGRID Office, Bongaigaon Sub-station, Assam, but it may be required to travel throughout the North Eastern Region. The contractor is responsible for all maintenance, including arranging for an alternative vehicle during breakdowns.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6199576', '27-05-2025 11:00:00', '27-05-2025 11:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Home Affairs', 'Central Armed Police Forces', 'Indo Tibetan Border Police (itbp)', '23 Bn', 'i.077012846@itbp.gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - HIRING OF PORTERS PONY FOR LRP/SRP/EXPEDITION', 'Bus Hiring Service - Regular Basis', '1 Year 10 Months 24 Day', '30,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'Yes', '50% Lowest Priced Technically Qualified Bidders', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '97,860', 'Yes', 5, 12, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the custom bid for services require the HIRING OF PORTERS PONY FOR LRP/SRP/EXPEDITION. The service must ensure YES for Regulatory/Statutory Compliance of Service and YES for Compliance of Service to SOW, STC, SLA etc.', 'Yogeshwar Prasad Joshi', 'Dehradun', 'This is a bid document (GEM/2025/Β/6199576) issued by the Indo Tibetan Border Police (itbp), Ministry Of Home Affairs, for a Custom Bid for Services - HIRING OF PORTERS PONY FOR LRP/SRP/EXPEDITION. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with a contract period of 1 Years 10 Months 24 Day. The bid end date is 27-05-2025 11:00:00, with a bid offer validity of 180 days. Key financial requirements for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 30 Lakhs over the last three years and 3 years of past experience in similar services, with exemptions available for MSE and Startups. An EMD of 97860 is required, along with an ePBG of 5.00% for a duration of 12 months. The bid is enabled for Reverse Auction (RA) for 50% of the lowest priced technically qualified bidders. MII Compliance and MSE Purchase Preference are applicable. The consignee for the service is Yogeshwar Prasad Joshi, 23rd bn itbp, seemadwar dehradun.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed, the service provider must ensure full compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Special Terms and Conditions (STC), and the Service Level Agreement (SLA). Additionally, the service must adhere to all Regulatory and Statutory requirements. As per the bid terms, any non-compliance with the applicable laws, acts, rules, or the terms of the GeM contract will be treated as a breach of contract, indicating that adherence to these stipulations is the primary measure of success.', 'The scope of work is the HIRING OF PORTERS PONY FOR LRP/SRP/EXPEDITION. This service is required by the Indo Tibetan Border Police (ITBP), 23 Bn, for a contract duration of 1 Year, 10 Months, and 24 Days. The service provider will be responsible for providing porters and ponies as needed for Long Range Patrols (LRP), Short Range Patrols (SRP), and expeditions. The work must be executed in compliance with the detailed specifications provided in the Scope of Work document (referenced as 1746431863.pdf), as well as adhering to all statutory regulations and the Service Level Agreement. The service will be delivered to the consignee located at 23rd bn itbp seemadwar dehradun.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6200576', '27-05-2025 12:00:00', '27-05-2025 12:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Defence Production', 'Hindustan Aeronautics Limited (hal)', '***********', 'buyer140.halh.ka@gembuyer.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Service Works Contract Housekeeping Works Roads and Drains at Old Central and East Extension Township in HAL Bangalore HAL FMD GR 13 25 26', 'Facility Management Service- Manpower based (Version 2)', '2 Year', '1,46,00,000', '7 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),OEM Authorization Certificate,OEM Annual Turnover,Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '4 Days', NULL, '4,83,90,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '4,83,900', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the proposed procurement detail a Service Works Contract for Housekeeping Works on Roads and Drains at the Old Central and East Extension Township in HAL Bangalore, under HAL FMD GR 13 25 26. The service is required to maintain full regulatory and statutory compliance. Furthermore, the service must be in complete adherence to the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA) as specified in the tender.', '***********', 'Bengaluru', 'This tender, with Bid Number GEM/2025/B/6200576, is issued by Hindustan Aeronautics Limited (HAL) for a ''Service Works Contract for Housekeeping Works of Roads and Drains'' at its Old Central and East Extension Township in Bangalore. The contract period is for two years with an estimated value of ₹48,390,000. The bid process is a two-packet system with a Reverse Auction feature. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum of 7 years of past experience in similar services, an average annual turnover of at least 146 Lakhs over the last three years, and legal status as a Limited or Private Limited Company. Bidders are also required to possess valid quality certifications such as ISO 9001, ISO 14001, SA 8000, or ISO 45001. The scope of work involves the daily upkeep and cleaning of roads and drains, requiring the deployment of 54 unskilled laborers. The contract specifies strict compliance with all labor laws, including timely payment of wages, ESI, and PF contributions. A security deposit of 5% of the contract value is required upon award of the contract. Payments will be made monthly after the services are rendered and all statutory compliances are verified.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the contract is considered successfully completed only after the satisfactory fulfillment of all obligations as per the contract documents. This includes the submission and payment of final bills and the subsequent release of the security deposit. A critical condition for completion is that the contractor must settle any and all claims that may arise related to the contract, including those from sub-contractors or statutory authorities. The contractor is also required to indemnify HAL and submit this indemnity along with the final bill submission to formally discharge all contractual responsibilities.', 'The scope of work involves providing housekeeping services, which includes the daily upkeep of all roads, cleaning of drains, removal of drain blockages, clearing of surrounding open areas, and disposal of debris and rubbish within the subject area. The contractor is required to supply all necessary materials, tools, and 54 unskilled labourers (1 Unskilled-II and 53 Unskilled-I). Key responsibilities include: engaging sufficient labourers and supervisors on all working days of the calendar month; immediate removal of chokages from sanitary fixtures, gully traps, manholes, and sewer lines upon complaint; daily cleaning of roads and monthly cleaning of drains; removing wall posters and writings; removing dead animals as ordered; performing necessary excavations for chokage removal at no extra cost; fixing garbage bins and placing manhole covers as directed; manually uprooting Parthenium and other unwanted plants; and cutting, cleaning, and removing grass and rank vegetation from open areas at least once every three months. The contractor must also detail a minimum of two attendants for chokage removal from various drainage systems.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6201030', '18-06-2025 11:00:00', '18-06-2025 11:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Power', 'Contracts And Materials', 'Damodar Valley Corporation', 'Damodar Valley Corporation', 'sukanti.mahanta@dvc.gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of 01 one number AC diesel engine driven MUV MPV Compact Sedan or equivalent vehicle for the Official duty under Safety Department MTPS DVC for a period of 02 two years from the date of actual commencement of work', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services', '2 Year', '2,48,91,200', '3 Years', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '5 Days', NULL, '16,59,41,683', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '33,188', 'Yes', 3, 26, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '05-06-2025 09:00:00', 'C&M Office Bidyut Bhawan,MTPS,DVC.', 'The technical specifications for the service require the hiring of one AC diesel engine driven MUV, MPV, Compact Sedan, or an equivalent vehicle for official duty under the Safety Department at MTPS DVC. The contract period is for two years from the actual commencement of work. The service must comply with all regulatory and statutory requirements. Furthermore, the service must be in full compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA).', 'Rajeev Ranjan', 'Bankura', 'This bid document, GEM/2025/B/6201030, issued by Damodar Valley Corporation (DVC) for the Ministry of Power, is for a custom service contract for the hiring of one AC diesel engine driven MUV, MPV, Compact Sedan, or equivalent vehicle. The service is required for official duty under the Safety Department at Mejia Thermal Power Station (MTPS) for a period of two years. The bid has an estimated value of 1659416.83 INR, with a required Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of 33188 INR and a Performance Security of 3% of the contract value valid for 26 months. The contract specifies a two-packet bid system with a bid validity of 180 days. Key requirements for bidders include past experience in similar services, with exemptions available for MSE and Startup entities subject to quality and technical specifications. The scope of work details the operational parameters, including 9-hour daily duty, an assured minimum run of 14400 km per year, and a maximum of 2400 km per month. The contractor is responsible for providing the vehicle with a driver and covering all associated costs such as fuel, lubricants, maintenance, and taxes. The payment terms are structured with 95% payment against running bills upon satisfactory service completion, certified by the DVC Engineer-in-charge, and the remaining 5% upon contract completion. The document outlines specific penalties for non-performance, such as a Rs. 700 penalty for failure to provide the vehicle for a full day and a Rs. 1000 penalty for refusal to deploy the vehicle to specified locations.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of several key conditions. Primarily, the contractor must provide the specified vehicle hiring service continuously for the entire two-year contract period in accordance with the Scope of Work and all other contractual obligations. This performance must be deemed satisfactory and be duly certified by the DVC Engineer-in-charge, which is a prerequisite for processing payments. To finalize the contract, the contractor must submit a ''No Claim Certificate'' to prevent any future claims. The final 5% payment and the release of the Performance Security are contingent upon the contractor having duly performed and completed all obligations under the contract. Successful completion also involves the submission of all required documentation, including final bills, and adherence to all statutory and legal requirements throughout the contract period.', 'The work involves the hiring of one AC diesel engine driven MUV/MPV/Compact Sedan or equivalent vehicle for the official duty under the Safety Department, MTPS, DVC, for a period of two years from the actual commencement of work. The normal duty hours for the vehicle are 9 hours per day. The service must meet an assured minimum run of 14400 km per year and a maximum run of 2400 km per month, with a maximum engagement of 30/31 days per month. The service includes one engaged driver. The vehicle will operate under the control of the Safety Officer at the Safety Department, MTPS, DVC. The base price for the fuel rate will be determined as of the price bid opening date. The contract period is for two years from the vehicle''s deployment date. The contractor is responsible for providing the complete service arrangement, including a vehicle with a seating capacity of 7 or 9 persons and a driver. The vehicle will be under the administrative control of the GM (Safety) or his authorized representative. All costs, including fuel, lubricants, maintenance with spares and materials, routine check-ups, servicing, overhauling, all taxes, and driver remuneration as per government rules, are to be borne by the contractor.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6205732', '27-05-2025 14:00:00', '27-05-2025 14:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Petroleum And Natural Gas', 'Oil India Limited', 'Oil India Limited', 'Oil India Limited', 'buycon18.mpng.ap@gembuyer.in', 'Hiring of Consultants - Milestone/Deliverable Based - Hiring of Consultancy services for G&G interpretation; Energy (Oil, Gas, Power, Renewables); No; Hybrid(As specified in scope of work)', NULL, '1 Month 15 Day', '200', 'successfully completed at least two (02) ‘Play Based studies or Geo scientific studies’ for structural evaluation, prospect generation and resource estimation in two (02) different sedimentary basins on area not less than 1500 SQKM in the last Seven (7) years.', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '10 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Quality & Cost Based Selection (QCBS) Evaluation Criteria', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '8,00,000', NULL, 5, 6, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for this tender outline the requirements for consultancy services focused on G&G interpretation within the energy sector, specifically covering Oil, Gas, Power, and Renewables. A Proof of Concept (POC) is not required for this project. The deployment of consultants and resources will be on a hybrid basis, with the specific details outlined in the scope of work. No addon specifications are listed.', 'Sawan Kumar Sethy', 'Bhubaneswar', 'This bid document (GEM/2025/B/6205732), issued by Oil India Limited, is for the hiring of consultancy services for a comprehensive G&G interpretation study. The project focuses on two OALP blocks, MN-ONHP-2018/1 and MN-ONHP-2018/3, located in the Mahanadi Basin, Odisha. The total contract period is 1 month and 15 days (45 days), with a stipulated mobilization period of 15 days. The objective is to delineate stratigraphic and structural configurations, generate prospects, estimate hydrocarbon resources, conduct techno-economic analysis, and ultimately recommend drilling locations. The bid is a Two Packet type, with a bid offer validity of 120 days from the bid end date of 27-05-2025. Financial requirements include an EMD of 800,000 INR and an ePBG of 5% for 6 months. The evaluation of bids will be based on a Quality & Cost Based Selection (QCBS) methodology. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include being incorporated in India with at least 20% local content, having an annual turnover of at least Rs. 2.00 Cr, a positive net worth, and specific technical experience in successfully completing at least two similar geo-scientific studies in different sedimentary basins covering an area of no less than 1500 SQKM each.', 'The successful completion of the tender is milestone-based and contingent upon the delivery and acceptance of all specified outputs by Oil India Limited (OIL) within the stipulated 45-day timeframe. The first major criterion is the successful completion of Milestone-1, which involves the G&G Interpretation and Prospect Identification. The ultimate success is achieved upon the completion of Milestone-2, which requires the submission of all final deliverables, a comprehensive presentation, and the final report. This includes providing detailed hard copies (such as Chronostratigraphic & Lithostratigraphic Correlation, Petrophysical Interpretation Reports, Time and Depth Structure Maps, and Faults Pattern Maps) and soft copies (including full interpreted data volumes in Petrel compatible format and ASCII files of all maps). The entire work, including the final interpretation report which must incorporate OIL''s views and comments, must be of a quality acceptable to the company as per international standards. The final acceptance of all reports and deliverables by OIL marks the successful completion of the contract.', 'The scope of work is to conduct a comprehensive G&G Interpretation study for two onland OALP blocks, MN-ONHP-2018/1 (Jagatsinghpur) and MN-ONHP-2018/3 (Bhadrak), in the Mahanadi Basin. The primary objective is to delineate stratigraphic and structural configurations, generate prospects, estimate in-place hydrocarbon resources, perform techno-economics analysis, rank the identified prospects and leads, and finally recommend drilling locations. The study involves the detailed interpretation of 330 SQKM of newly acquired 3D seismic data, which must be integrated with existing 2442 LKM of 2D data and 695 SQKM of 3D data, along with well information. The project is to be completed in 45 days across three phases: Phase I (5 days) for data collection, QC, and geological framework formulation; Phase II (30 days) for detailed seismic data interpretation, which includes mapping a minimum of five horizons, velocity model building, petrophysical and fault seal analysis, and prospect generation; and Phase III (10 days) for discussion, review, and submission of final reports and deliverables. The methodology covers a full spectrum of G&G analysis including Petrophysical Evaluation, Well-to-Seismic Tie, Mis-tie analysis, Fault and Horizon Mapping, Velocity Modelling, Seismic Attribute Analysis, Prospect Volume and Risking using probabilistic methods, and Techno-Economic analysis, culminating in a recommendation for a future exploration strategy.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6208411', '22-05-2025 10:00:00', '22-05-2025 10:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Air Force', '***********', 'jungle.505@gov.in', 'Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs', NULL, '1 Year', '20,00,000', '3 Year', 'No', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '99,000', 'Yes', 5, 14, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the required service detail the hiring of a Sedan type vehicle. The acceptable car models include Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, Hyundai Xcent, Tata Tigor, Ford Aspire, Volkswagen Ameo, Tata Zest, Nissan Sunny, and Toyota Etios. The service is for local use with a usage variant of 80Kms x 10Hrs. The vehicle model must be from the year 2020, 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024, or 2025 and should have travelled upto 75,000 Kms. The vehicle must be Non-A/C and will operate in Plains. The required fuel type is Diesel. For addons, the type of trip is specified as RETURN.', '***********', 'Betul', 'This bid document, GEM/2025/B/6208411, is issued by the Indian Air Force, Ministry of Defence, for the procurement of ''Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs''. The contract period is for one year with a bid offer validity of 120 days. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 20 Lakhs over the last three years and three years of past experience in similar services. Exemptions for turnover and experience criteria are available for startups. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with a Reverse Auction (RA) enabled, using the H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination rule. The evaluation method is based on the total value. Key financial requirements include an Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of 99,000 INR and an e-Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 5.00% for a duration of 14 months. The scope involves providing 05 Non-AC Sedan class cars daily on an as-required basis for 12 months at Air Force Station, Amla, Betul (MP), with a daily duty of 10 hours or 80 Kms. The vehicles must be of a 2020 model or newer, with less than 75,000 Kms covered, and must be commercially registered with all necessary permits and insurance. The contract includes specific terms related to penalties for non-performance, termination clauses, a fall clause, and a force majeure clause. Payment will be made on a monthly basis after the submission of countersigned logbooks.', 'The successful completion of the work from the tender issuer''s perspective is contingent on the service provider''s consistent adherence to all contractual obligations. The key success criteria include: 1. Punctual and full deployment of the specified number and type of vehicles (05 Non-AC Sedans) in excellent condition as per the daily or weekly supply orders issued by the buyer. 2. Accurate maintenance of a daily logbook for each vehicle, recording kilometers run and hours of deployment, which must be countersigned daily by the buyer''s representative. 3. Timely submission of the countersigned monthly logbook reports along with the invoice to facilitate monthly payments. 4. Strict compliance with all service provider obligations, including vehicle maintenance, driver conduct, and possession of valid documentation, throughout the contract period. 5. Fulfilling the entire contract without triggering termination clauses, such as failing to deploy vehicles on five separate instances. The contract is considered fully completed after all obligations are met, which extends 60 days beyond the service period for the validity of the Performance Bank Guarantee.', 'The scope of work entails the hiring of 05 Non-AC (Sedan Class) cars for a period of 12 months to be provided to the Air Force Station, Amla (MP). The service is required on a daily, as-and-when-needed basis, with a total annual quantity not to exceed 1200 cars. Each vehicle deployment is for a duration of 10 hours or 80 kilometers, whichever is greater. The service provider must supply specific models of sedan cars such as Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, etc., from the year 2020 or newer, with mileage not exceeding 75,000 Km. The vehicles must be in excellent working condition, commercially registered with yellow number plates, and equipped with a first aid kit. The scope includes providing skilled drivers with a minimum of two years of experience, a valid license, and police verification. The cost of hiring is all-inclusive of the driver''s salary, fuel, maintenance, insurance, taxes, and any toll or parking charges. The service provider is responsible for maintaining a daily logbook for each vehicle, which must be countersigned by the buyer''s representative. The provider must ensure immediate replacement in case of vehicle breakdown or seizure and is solely liable for any accidents, damages, or traffic violations. The service provider must also adhere to all service obligations, including driver conduct, vehicle cleanliness, and compliance with all applicable laws.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6222461', '11-06-2025 17:00:00', '11-06-2025 17:30:00', '30 Days', 'Ministry Of Information And Broadcasting', 'Ministry Of Information And Broadcasting', 'All India Radio', 'All India Radio Vijayawada', 'khsaikumar@prasarbharati.gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of Taxi on as and when required basis', 'Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services', '1 Year', '10,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', '50% Lowest Priced Technically Qualified Bidders', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '5,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service are defined under the Core section. The service is described as ''Hiring of Taxi on as and when required basis'' through a custom bid functionality. The service provider is required to affirm compliance with all regulatory and statutory requirements. Additionally, the provider must also ensure full compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and the Service Level Agreement (SLA). There are no addon specifications listed for this service.', 'Kaki Hemanth Sai Kumar', 'Vijayawada', 'This bid document, GEM/2025/B/6222461, is for a custom service contract for the ''Hiring of Taxi on as and when required basis'' for All India Radio, Vijayawada. The contract period is for one year, starting from July 1, 2025. The bid is a Two Packet system with an estimated value of 500,000, and it is enabled for a Reverse Auction among the 50% lowest priced technically qualified bidders. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 10 Lakhs for the last three years and three years of similar past experience, although exemptions are available for MSEs and Startups. The scope of work involves providing SEDAN, SUV, and PREMIUM SUV class vehicles for local and outstation operational activities on hourly package rates. The supplier must own at least three taxis, which should be recent models (2023/2024) in good condition with all necessary permits, insurance, and safety equipment. Drivers must have at least two years of experience. The contract requires a Performance Security of 5% of the contract value. Payments will be made monthly within 30 days of bill submission. The document details specific liquidated damages for various defaults like non-deployment of vehicles, delays, and misbehavior, and outlines conditions for contract termination, which include mutual consent, breach of contract, or cumulative penalties reaching 10% of the contract value.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer (All India Radio), the successful completion of the tender is achieved when the service provider fulfills all contractual obligations for the entire one-year contract period without any premature termination. This includes consistently providing the specified vehicles and services as per the Scope of Work, adhering to all terms, conditions, and Service Level Agreements (SLAs). Key success indicators are the contract running its full term without being terminated due to material breaches or the accumulation of penalties rising to 10% of the contract value. The final measure of success is the satisfactory completion of the contract term, which subsequently leads to the release of the contractor''s Performance Security two months after the contract completion date.', 'The scope of work is to provide vehicles of class SEDAN, SUV & PREMIUM SUV for the operational activities of All India Radio, Vijayawada, for both local and outstation travel on an hourly package rate, as and when required. The contract period is for 12 months starting from 01st July, 2025, or the date of contract execution. The vehicles supplied must be of latest models, preferably 2024 or 2023, with less than 50,000 kilometers run, and must be in good condition. They should be registered as Transport Vehicles with all necessary permits and comprehensive insurance coverage, and be equipped with an emergency medical first aid kit and a fire extinguisher. The drivers provided must have a minimum of two years of driving experience, hold a valid license, and be polite and punctual, and should not be under the influence of any intoxicating substances. The supplier must own a minimum of three taxis and is responsible for providing an immediate replacement in case of a breakdown. Mileage for billing will start and terminate at Akashvani, Vijayawada. The supplier is also required to maintain a log book/trip sheet for all journeys, which must be signed by the travelling official.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6222930', '14-06-2025 12:00:00', '14-06-2025 12:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Navy', '***********', 'nitish.c289@navy.gov.in', 'HIRING OF LMV', 'Hiring of Vessels, Hiring of Boats, Hiring of Chartered Aircrafts, Hiring of Helicopter Service, Hiring of Logistics Facility, Hiring of Creative Agency, Hiring of PR Agency, Hiring of Safety Consultant, Hiring of Sanitation Service, Hiring of Mortuary Van, Passenger Car', NULL, '11,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Past Performance, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), OEM Annual Turnover, Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '1,12,471', NULL, 5, 14, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, '***********', 'Uttara Kannada', 'This is a tender (Bid Number: GEM/2025/B/6222930) issued by the Indian Navy, Ministry of Defence, for the HIRING OF LMV. The total quantity required is 1. The bid end date is 14-06-2025, with an offer validity of 180 days. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a Minimum Average Annual Turnover of 11 Lakhs over the last 3 years, 3 years of past experience in similar services, and a past performance record of supplying 30% of the bid quantity in at least one of the last three financial years. The OEM Average Turnover required is 4 Lakhs. The procurement is reserved for ''Make In India'' products, specifically for Class 1 Local Suppliers with a minimum of 50% local content. Exemptions from turnover and experience criteria are available for MSEs and DPIIT registered Startups. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with an EMD amount of 112471 and requires an ePBG of 5.00% for a duration of 14 months. The evaluation method is total value wise, and a Reverse Auction will be conducted among technically qualified bidders. The service is required for a consignee in Uttara Kannada with a delivery period of 45 days. The buyer has included an additional scope of work document and specific terms and conditions, including an option clause to vary the order quantity by up to 25%.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be deemed successfully completed upon fulfillment of the following criteria:
1. The provision of the HIRING OF LMV service for the specified quantity of 1 unit.
2. Strict adherence to all requirements, terms, and conditions outlined in the buyer-added SCOPE OF WORK document.
3. Commencement of service within the stipulated delivery period of 45 days for the consignee at Uttara Kannada.
4. Full compliance with all Buyer Added Bid Specific Terms and Conditions and the General Terms and Conditions of the contract.
5. Successful submission and maintenance of the required 5% ePBG for the entire contract duration of 14 months, which serves as a guarantee of performance.
6. Compliance with all applicable statutory laws, including all mandated Labour Laws.', 'The scope of work involves the HIRING OF LMV(1). The total quantity required is one unit. This service is to be provided to the consignee located in Uttara Kannada. The stipulated delivery period, likely referring to the commencement of the service contract, is 45 days from the date of the order. A more detailed scope of work is specified in a separate document titled ''SCOPE OF WORK'' uploaded by the buyer, which is applicable to the HIRING OF LMV(1) item.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6225998', '17-06-2025 18:00:00', '17-06-2025 18:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Environment Forest And Climate Change', NULL, NULL, 'Delhi', 'prashantsharma.cpcb@gov.in', 'Hiring of Social Media Agency - As per RFP; As per RFP; As per RFP', NULL, '3 Year', '2,00,00,000', '5 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '1,80,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'State Bank of India', '5,00,000', 'Yes', 5, 38, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, '04-06-2025 11:00:00', 'https://meet.google.com/ipc-ovqy-sey', 'The technical specifications for the hiring of a Social Media Agency are outlined in two categories: Core and Addon(s). Under the Core specifications, the requirements for Social Media, Language Versions, and Handles Required are all to be as per the RFP. Under the Addon(s) specifications, the requirement for a fresh photoshoot for creating a photobank is listed as NA (Not Applicable), and the requirement for developing video content of 1-2 minute duration with fresh shoot is also listed as NA.', 'Meena', 'Delhi', 'This is a bid document (GEM/2025/B/6225998) issued by the Central Pollution Control Board (CPCB), under the Ministry of Environment, Forest, and Climate Change, for the ''Hiring of Social Media Agency''. The contract period is for 3 years with an estimated value of 1,80,00,000. Key requirements for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 200 Lakhs over 3 years and 5 years of past experience in similar services. The selection process is a Two Packet Bid based on Quality & Cost Based Selection (QCBS) with a weightage of 65% for the technical score and 35% for the financial score. The scope of work is extensive, covering social media account management, public complaint management, content creation and posting, multimedia content creation including videos, providing training to CPCB officers, and deploying a dedicated onsite team of five personnel (Team Coordinator, Content Writer, Graphic Designer, and two ORM/Complaint Management Executives). The tender includes detailed eligibility criteria, a technical evaluation matrix, standard terms and conditions, penalty clauses for non-performance, and a requirement for a 5% performance security deposit from the successful bidder. Payment will be made on a quarterly basis. The document also includes an Integrity Pact to ensure a fair and transparent bidding process.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of several key conditions. Primarily, the agency must execute all tasks as detailed in the Scope of Work, adhering to the specified standards of performance, quality, and timelines throughout the contract period. This includes the timely submission of all required deliverables, such as periodic social media analysis reports, sentiment analysis reports, and other reports as required by CPCB. Ongoing success is measured by the agency''s ability to meet quality standards and timelines, with provisions for replacing professionals in case of unsatisfactory performance. Final successful completion of the contract is marked by the ''Project Handover on Closure'', where the firm is required to hand over the entire documentation, designs, configurations, all related information, scripts, modules, and multimedia creatives to CPCB upon the completion or termination of the contract.', 'The scope of work for the hired agency involves comprehensive management of CPCB''s social media presence and public communications. This includes: 1. Social Media Account Management: Managing CPCB''s accounts on platforms like X (formerly Twitter), Facebook, YouTube, Instagram, and LinkedIn; responding to all queries within 24 working hours; platform moderation 6 times a day; analyzing comments and generating reports on trends, follower growth, and reach; running digital campaigns and popularizing CPCB''s content. 2. Public Complaints Management: Receiving, recording, forwarding, and tracking public complaints received through social media and other official channels, and preparing reports on actions taken. 3. Revamping Accounts: Providing a new look to CPCB''s social media accounts as directed. 4. Content Posting: Posting a minimum of three creative updates (text, infographics, photos, videos, quizzes, etc.) or as communicated by CPCB. 5. Multimedia Content Creation: Designing CGI, creatives, posters, videos, and animations, with the bidder arranging all necessary licenses and IPRs. This includes creating a repository of high-quality photos/creatives and producing around 10 short videos (60-80 seconds) over the project duration. 6. Training: Providing skill up-gradation and capacity building training for CPCB officers. 7. Communication and Media Outreach: Designing communication and promotional strategies to strengthen CPCB''s social media profile. 8. Security and Storage: Ensuring the security of social media accounts and archiving all content to be handed over to CPCB. 9. Support and Infrastructure: Taking over from the existing team, providing 24x7 support, and arranging all necessary software, hardware, and licenses. 10. Manpower Deliverables: Deploying an onsite, full-time team comprising one Team Coordinator, one Content Writer, one Graphic Designing & Animation Expert, and two ORM/Complaint Management Executives, all meeting specified minimum experience requirements.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6226198', '04-06-2025 18:00:00', '04-06-2025 18:30:00', '180 Days', 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Urban Development Department Uttar Pradesh', 'E-municipalities - Eservices To Citizens And Employees Of Urban Local Bodies Of Uttar Pradesh', 'Directorate Of Localbodies Up', 'con7.uddup.up@gembuyer.in', 'Hiring of Consultants - Per Person Per Months Based - Project Management Consultancy or Unit; Storm Water and urban flood management; Graduate / Post Graduate with Domain Knowledge Expetise; NA', NULL, '2 Year', '75,32,02,12,22,02,22,32,02,324', '7 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'Disputes not resolved amicably by conciliation will be decided by an Arbitral Tribunal appointed as per Clause 9.4.2 and Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996. The place of arbitration shall be Lucknow and the language English.', 'In case of dispute, parties will first approach Director, Urban Local Bodies for amicable resolution. If unresolved, it will be escalated to Principal Secretary, Department of Urban Development, GoUP and CEO of Consultant to meet and resolve. If still not settled within specified timeframes, it may proceed to arbitration.', 'PUNJAB NATIONAL BANK', '10,00,000', NULL, 5, 27, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, '21-05-2025 12:00:00', 'Revati hall, Directorate of Local Bodies (DLB), Urban Development Department(GoUP)', 'The technical specifications for the hiring of consultants are detailed in two sections. The ''Core'' specifications require the consulting category to be Project Management Consultancy or Unit, with a profile in Storm Water and urban flood management. The required qualification for consultants, resources, or SMEs is a Graduate / Post Graduate with Domain Knowledge Expetise. The total experience required for consultants/resources is 20 years and above, with a hybrid deployment model. Certifications should be as indicated in the BID. A Proof of Concept (POC) is not required (NA). The ''Addon(s)'' section specifies that the required expertise, educational qualification, and position of the consultant will be as per the Additional Terms and Conditions (ATC).', 'ASHISH SRIVASTAVA', 'Lucknow', 'This GeM bid (GEM/2025/B/6226198) is a Request for Proposal (RFP) issued by the Directorate of Urban Local Bodies (DoULB), under the Urban Development Department of Uttar Pradesh, for the selection of a Project Management Unit/Consultancy (PMU/PMC). The objective is to implement and manage the “Urban Storm Water Drainage Scheme" across the state to address challenges of urban flooding. The contract period is for two years, with a bid offer validity of 180 days. The selection process is a Quality and Cost Based Selection (QCBS) with a 70:30 weightage for technical and financial proposals, respectively. Bidders must be a single entity with at least 7 years of past experience in similar services and meet financial criteria, including a minimum average annual turnover of 75 Crores from consulting business over the last three years. The scope of the consultancy includes providing technical, managerial, and operational support, project management, capacity building, stakeholder management, and developing an Online Project Management Portal. The PMC will be responsible for reviewing master plans, DPRs, designs, and ensuring technical compliance, while also providing hand-holding support to Urban Local Bodies (ULBs) throughout the project lifecycle. An Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of 1,000,000 INR and a Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 5% of the contract value for 27 months are required.', 'The work will be considered successfully completed upon fulfillment of several criteria from the tender issuer''s perspective. A primary success criterion is the development and deployment of a fully functional Online Project Management Portal that meets all requirements of the Authority, has undergone thorough testing and quality assurance, is deployed in a production environment, is integrated with the PM-Gati Shakti portal, and for which end-users and administrators have received necessary training and support. Overall success of the consultancy hinges on the satisfactory performance against Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) which will be monitored monthly and will directly impact the payment of personnel. Furthermore, the timely and satisfactory submission of all required deliverables and reports, including the Inception Report, Monthly Progress Reports, and the Final Completion Report as per the Terms of Reference, is essential for the successful completion of the engagement. The performance security will be returned within 60 days after the successful completion of the entire consultancy.', 'The scope of work for the Project Management Consultant (PMC) is comprehensive, covering project management, capacity building, stakeholder engagement, and IT system development. In Project Management, the PMC will provide hand-holding support to the Directorate Urban Local Bodies (DLB) for the Storm Water drainage scheme. This includes reviewing and ensuring the sufficiency of Drainage Master Plans, designs, reports, layouts, estimates, and BOQs from executing agencies; examining feasibility reports and DPRs for technical compliance; assisting Urban Local Bodies (ULBs) in preparing procurement documents; and aiding in the creation of a ''Manual for Storm Water Drainage System and Maintenance''. The PMC will manage inter-departmental coordination, prepare and submit inception, monthly, and final reports, and monitor project progress using PERT/CPM tools. The scope also includes the Development of a Stormwater Drainage Directory and conducting regular impact assessments. For Capacity Building, the PMC will prepare IEC action plans, develop training curricula, and provide training to officials and stakeholders on relevant technologies and management practices. Under Public participation and stakeholder management, the PMC will facilitate collaboration between government agencies, technical experts, and citizens. A key deliverable is the Development of an Online Project Management Portal for project approval, management, and supervision, which includes all phases from requirement gathering and design to deployment, training, and support. The PMC must also maintain a knowledge repository and provide its own required T&P equipment and software for project assessment and evaluation.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6227414', '20-06-2025 12:00:00', '20-06-2025 12:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Navy', NULL, 'ito-wncmomb@navy.gov.in', 'Hiring of Professionals for Application Development and Maintenance - Development and related roles; Full stack developer; 3 years and Less than 6 years, Hiring of Professionals for Application Development and Maintenance - System admin/Security related roles; System Administrator; 3 years and Less than 6 years, Hiring of Professionals for Application Development and Maintenance - System admin/Security related roles; Linux Administrator; 3 years and Less than 6 years, Hiring of Professionals for Application Development and Maintenance - Development and related roles; Support engineer (Support envisaged or specifics to be detailed in SoW); 3 years and Less than 6 years, Hiring of Professionals for Application Development and Maintenance - Development and related roles; Helpdesk operator/executive; 1 year and Less than 3 years, Hiring of Professionals for Application Development and Maintenance - System admin/Security related roles; Security expert; 3 years and Less than 6 years', NULL, '2 Year', '65,00,000', '5 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', 'This bid has been created/published with floor price(minimum value) selected by the Buyer. Service Providers are advised to quote above the minimum floor value.', '1,26,30,720', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '6,31,536', 'Yes', 3, 26, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '16-06-2025 10:00:00', 'SA ILMS, ILMS Centre, Material Organisation, Ghatkopar West, Mumbai, 400086', 'The technical specifications outline the requirements for hiring professionals across six distinct roles for application development and maintenance, with all positions requiring onsite deployment. For a Full Stack Developer (3-6 years experience), the role involves development tasks requiring certifications like CSM or CISM, and proficiency in languages like C++, C, MySQL, PHP, HTML5/CSS, VB.NET, and frameworks like .NET. A System Administrator (3-6 years) will handle system and security roles, needing a CISA certification and experience with platforms like SharePoint, various databases, and tools including Office 365. Similarly, a Linux Administrator (3-6 years) also requires a CISA certification and shares a similar technical skill set to the System Administrator, focusing on Linux environments. The Support Engineer role (3-6 years) is for development-related support, requiring an MCSE certification and broad technical expertise in various platforms and tools. A Helpdesk Operator/Executive (1-3 years experience) requires an MCSE certification with skills in MySQL, HTML5/CSS and platforms like ERPNext and Office 365. Lastly, a Security Expert (3-6 years) needs CISA, CISM, or CISSP certifications and expertise in languages including jQuery, platforms like SharePoint, and functional domains like Aadhaar Authentication. For all roles, a relevant graduate degree (BCA, B.Tech, B.Sc(CS/IT)) or a Graduate degree with a Diploma in Computers is necessary, and the buyer will conduct an interview before deployment.', NULL, 'Mumbai', 'This Government e-Marketplace (GeM) bid (GEM/2025/B/6227414) issued by the Indian Navy, Ministry of Defence, is for the ''Hiring of Professionals for Application Development and Maintenance'' for a contract period of 2 years. The bid, with an estimated value of INR 126,307,20, seeks to procure services of various IT professionals including Full Stack Developers, System Administrators, Linux Administrators, Support Engineers, Helpdesk Operators, and Security Experts. The key requirements for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 65 Lakhs for the last three years and 5 years of past experience in similar services. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with an EMD of INR 631,536 and requires a Performance Bank Guarantee of 3% for 26 months upon award. The scope of work details the deployment of 08 professionals to manage, develop, and maintain various IT systems and applications, including website development, server administration, network security, and user support, operating six days a week from 0900 to 1800 hrs. The Service Level Agreement specifies conditions such as quarterly payments post-submission of a user satisfaction certificate, and a penalty of Rs. 1000/- per day for the absenteeism of an engineer. The contract will be governed by the laws of India and includes standard clauses on non-disclosure, liquidated damages for delays, and termination conditions. Bidders are required to be financially sound, have an office in the consignee''s state, and adhere to all Indian labor laws, including timely payment of salaries to deployed staff.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is considered successfully completed upon fulfillment of several key criteria. Primarily, the successful deployment and continuous availability of the specified number of qualified professionals who perform all duties detailed in the Scope of Work to the satisfaction of the buyer. Adherence to the Service Level Agreement is critical, which includes maintaining service hours, ensuring minimal downtime, attending to all defects registered on the IT support portal on the same day, and avoiding penalties for absenteeism by providing suitable relief. Furthermore, the contractor must comply with all bid terms and conditions, including the timely submission of a 3% Performance Bank Guarantee, and the strict adherence to statutory and labor laws, particularly the clause requiring the service provider to pay salaries to their staff before claiming payment from the buyer. The ultimate measure of success for each service period (quarterly) is the issuance of a ''User Acceptance/ Satisfactory Certificate'' by the buyer, which is a mandatory document for the processing of payments and formally confirms that the services rendered have met the required standards.', 'The IT Services contract requires the provision of 08 employees to cover all IT assets and resources at the customer site. The roles and their responsibilities are as follows: 

1. Full Stack Developer (1): Responsible for enhancements, development of the MO (Mbi) website and other digital initiatives, software installation, integration of the website with the ILMS application, development of HR management modules, ensuring data backup, generating automated reports for Overtime and IT Support portals, integrating the Aadhaar-based attendance system, and liquidating observations from VA checks. 

2. Server Administrator (1): Manages SharePoint server, VMs, MO Website server, SIEM, and other servers. Responsibilities include web and database server management, ensuring NUD/NCN updates, installing, configuring, and deploying servers, performing routine maintenance and upgrades, monitoring server performance, managing resources, ensuring compliance with IT/InfoSec policies, and maintaining server configuration records. 

3. Linux Administrator (1): Manages and configures NavIOS 3.0 and 4.0 PCs, migration to the latest NavIOS version, SETROD application, and printer configuration. Duties include installing and deploying Linux-based systems, routine maintenance, Antivirus installation, resolving configuration issues, handling Digital Signature usage issues, implementing security policies, and maintaining system documentation. 

4. Security Administrator (1): Ensures cyber hygiene and adherence to IT and InfoSec policies. Tasks include installing and configuring Antivirus, monitoring and upgrading security tools, assisting in investigating security incidents, conducting cyber awareness activities and lectures, performing SNAP audits, and ensuring the safe usage of sDrives. 

5. Desktop Engineer (2): Addresses user complaints regarding Naval applications. Responsibilities include Lotus ID creation and transfers, e-Pehchaan and NIC mail issues, forwarding firewall change requests, resolving local PC functionality issues, password maintenance, software management, installation of whitelisted software, attending IT support calls, and assisting in IT services for various events and locations. 

6. Coordinator cum data entry operator (1): Tracks and manages all data on the IT Support portal. Duties involve allocating tickets to staff, liaising with HQWNC/CITO/Web Team, documenting issues, maintaining records of audits and reports, coordinating with AMC staff, prioritizing user complaints, coordinating with the Data Centre for user queries, and managing escalations.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6228575', '04-06-2025 15:00:00', '04-06-2025 15:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Power', NULL, NULL, 'Bureau Of Energy Efficiency', 'avadhm.pandey@beeindia.gov.in', 'Hiring of Agency for IT Projects- Milestone basis', NULL, '2 Year', '1,50,00,000', '5 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), OEM Authorization Certificate, OEM Annual Turnover, Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '40,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Bank Of Baroda', '1,00,000', 'Yes', 3, 36, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '21-05-2025 15:00:00', 'https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_MDQ1OTliNmQtYTI5My00NDg5LTlmODAtOWVkZmU4MzIxYjcz@thread.v2/0?context={"Tid":"79304f37-e0bb-4919-ac85-bff78fa2faff","Oid":"832477bf-dd6c-48be-a87b-b8ae7aa5e163"}', 'The technical specifications are for hiring an IT agency for IT projects on a milestone basis. The core requirements include a scope of work detailed in the Request for Proposal for the Redesigning, Hosting, and Maintenance of the iDeeksha Website. The necessary resources are to be as specified within the scope of work. The deployment of the core team is required to be onsite, and all deliverables and timelines must adhere to the specifications outlined in the RFP.', 'Anil Kumar Rai', 'New delhi', 'This bid, GEM/2025/B/6228575, is for the hiring of an IT agency on a milestone basis by the Bureau Of Energy Efficiency, Ministry Of Power. The contract period is for 2 years with an estimated value of 4,000,000 INR. The project involves the redesigning, hosting, and maintenance of the iDeeksha Website (https://www.ideeksha.in/), which serves as an Industrial Decarbonisation and Energy Efficiency Knowledge Sharing Platform. The evaluation method is based on the Least Cost Method (LCS) for technically qualified bidders who score a minimum of 70 marks. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 150 Lakhs for the last three years and 5 years of past experience in similar services. The scope of the project includes complete website redesign to be bilingual (English/Hindi), responsive, and SEO-friendly; implementation of a robust Content Management System (CMS); secure hosting on servers in India with 99% uptime; ongoing maintenance and updates; and providing dedicated on-site and off-site support personnel. The agency must ensure compliance with various standards including GIGW, WCAG 2.0, and obtain STQC certification for the website.', 'The successful completion of the tender is contingent upon the timely delivery of a fully redesigned, functional, bilingual, and responsive iDeeksha website that meets all specified requirements. A critical success criterion is adherence to stringent security and compliance standards, including obtaining STQC certification and ensuring conformity with GIGW and WCAG 2.0 - Level AA guidelines. The agency must successfully migrate all existing content, implement a user-friendly Content Management System (CMS), and host the website with a guaranteed uptime of at least 99%. Ongoing success will be measured by the agency''s ability to provide prompt and proper maintenance, regular content and software updates, bug fixing, and the submission of regular, comprehensive status reports (monthly, half-yearly, yearly) as per the payment terms. Furthermore, the provision of dedicated on-site and off-site support personnel for the entire two-year contract duration is mandatory. The agency''s overall performance must consistently meet the standards required by the Bureau of Energy Efficiency, as failure to do so could result in penalties for delays or termination of the contract.', 'The scope of work is to engage an IT agency for the redesigning, hosting, and maintenance of the iDeeksha Website for a contract period of 2 years. The key tasks are categorized as follows: 
1. Website Re-design: This involves the evaluation of the existing website and a complete redesign with suitable navigation, ensuring compatibility with modern browsers (Microsoft Edge/Safari/Chrome/Firefox). The agency must migrate all content from the existing site to the new one. The website must be responsive for viewing on various devices (mobiles, tablets, laptops), implemented in a bilingual format (English and Hindi) from day one with a single-click switch, and developed using Unicode for the Hindi version. The design and structure must be SEO friendly, with clutter-free navigation, a hierarchical sitemap, and a robust search feature based on file names, tags, and content. It must include mechanisms for automatic and manual content archival, a separate blog section, links to social media and other portals, and an NLP-enabled Chatbot/Helpdesk. A test site must be created for staging updates. 
2. Content Management System (CMS): A simple, point-and-click CMS must be provided that allows management of user groups with different control levels. It should be able to display up-to-date content, handle omnichannel publishing (website, mobile app, social media), generate user visit statistics, automate content updates and rollbacks, create print-ready pages, back up previous versions, and schedule content publishing and expiration. 
3. Hosting and Maintenance: The website is to be hosted on primary and backup servers located in India, with 500 GB of hosting space each and ensuring at least 99% uptime. The agency will be responsible for migration, prompt maintenance, security updates for CMS/web server tools, designing/updating web pages and banners, removing broken links, renewing the domain name, bug fixing, and providing weekly analytics reports. The agency must also conduct stress and load testing to ensure pages load within 5 seconds and provide monthly, half-yearly, and yearly status reports to BEE. 
4. Security and Compliance: The agency must ensure all developed modules are error-free and hack-proof, passing mandatory QC and QA testing. The website must conform to W3C, GIGW, and WCAG 2.0 - Level AA guidelines, and the agency must obtain STQC certification. It must be IPv6 compliant, adhere to user interface design guidelines, and implement best practices as per CERT-In. The agency is responsible for the website''s information security, including providing an SSL Certificate and quarterly source code. 
5. On-Site and Off-Site Support: The agency must provide one dedicated Website Developer for on-site support at BEE''s Head Office (with 5+ years of experience) and one dedicated Website Developer for off-site support (with 7+ years of experience) for the entire 2-year contract. This includes 24x7 monitoring, an Escalation Matrix, and a Business Continuity Plan.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6229364', '28-05-2025 14:00:00', '28-05-2025 14:30:00', '45 Days', 'Ministry Of Power', 'Bhakra Beas Managemet Board', 'Bhakra Beas Management Board', 'Bhakra Beas Management Board, Chandigarh', 'xenomhsr@bbmb.nic.in', 'Hiring of Earth Moving Equipments, Material Handling Equipments and Cranes (per Hour basis) - As Per Buyer''s Requirement; Earth Moving Equipment; JCB, Hiring of Earth Moving Equipments, Material Handling Equipments and Cranes (per Hour basis) - As Per Buyer''s Requirement; Material Handling Equipment; Tractor with Disc Harrow, Tractor with Rotavator, Tractor, Tractor with Disc Plough, Tractor with C.., Hiring of Earth Moving Equipments, Material Handling Equipments and Cranes (per Hour basis) - As Per Buyer''s Requirement; Crane; Mobile Crane', NULL, '10 Months 4 Day', '1,00,000', '2 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The tender requires the hiring of three types of equipment. For the JCB, the equipment must be an Earth Moving Equipment, specifically a JCB, with a manufacturing or registration year up to 10 years from the contract award date. For the Tractor, it is classified as Material Handling Equipment and must come with various attachments including a Disc Harrow, Rotavator, Disc Plough, Compressor, and Trailer. The manufacturing or registration year for the tractor should also be up to 10 years. For the Crane, it is specified as a Mobile Crane under the Crane equipment type, with a manufacturing or registration year of up to 10 years. For all three categories of equipment, the general specification is as per the buyer''s requirement, and the fuel, operator/crew, and cleaner/helper are not to be provided by the buyer.', 'Tarun Dewan', 'Hissar', 'This bid document, GEM/2025/B/6229364, issued by the Bhakra Beas Management Board, Ministry of Power, is for the hiring of Earth Moving Equipment (JCB), Material Handling Equipment (Tractor with various attachments), and Cranes (Mobile Crane) on a per-hour basis. The contract period is 10 months and 4 days. The bid is a two-packet system with a validity of 45 days from the bid end date of 28-05-2025. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 1 Lakh over the last three years and 2 years of past experience in similar services. The work is to be performed at the 220 KV Sub-Station in Hisar under the supervision of the designated Reporting Officer, Tarun Dewan. Key conditions include the requirement for the successful bidder to deploy vehicles on an on-call basis within 2 hours, with the quoted price being all-inclusive of fuel, maintenance, and operator costs. The bidder must maintain a log book for usage verification, and bills will be paid quarterly. The vehicles must be up to 10 years old and possess all valid licenses. Specific requirements include providing a helper with the crane at no extra cost and being able to supply a crane with a boom up to 45 feet on special request.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed, the contractor must consistently adhere to the following criteria from the tender issuer''s perspective: The specified equipment (Tractor with attachments, Crane, JCB) must be deployed to the designated site on an on-call basis within 2 hours of the request, or round the clock in emergencies. The equipment must be in good working condition with all valid licenses and operated by a licensed driver, following all safety protocols for work at a 220 KV substation. The contractor must maintain an accurate vehicle log book detailing the hours and area of usage, which must be regularly verified and signed by the SDO incharge. All contractual obligations, such as providing a helper for the crane and deploying a crane with a boom up to 45 feet when specially requested without extra charges, must be met. Finally, successful completion involves submitting quarterly bills as per GEM procedure, supported by the verified log book, against the fixed rate agreed upon in the contract.', 'The service contract is for the hiring of Tractor, Crane, and JCB, which includes the working of the crane, JCB, and tractor at 220KV BBMB Hisar Sub-Station Satroad Hisar or nearby places as per the direction of the SDO incharge or any other representative authorized by Addl. S. E. / O & M Division Hisar. The quoted price must include all running expenditures like HSD, engine oil, repair, breakdown, cleaner, and driver charges, which shall not be paid by BBMB separately. The time for repair of breakdown during the work will not be counted. The successful bidder must follow all laws and safety measures for working at the 220 KV substation. The vehicle should be deployed on an on-call basis by BBMB within 2 hours or round the clock in case of emergency. The vehicle may be used as and when required by BBMB on an hourly basis with total usage sealed during the contract period. The provided vehicle must have all valid licenses and certificates, and the driver must have a valid driving license. One helper is to be provided with the driver of the crane with no extra charges. A vehicle log book must be maintained to record usage hours and area, to be verified by BBMB representatives. No extra payment will be made for transportation time. In general, a mobile crane with a boom up to 32 feet is required, but on special request, a telescopic crane with a boom up to 45 feet must be deployed without extra charge. The tractor will be used for cleaning turfs, wild growth, garbage transportation, and spraying weedicide, and must have attachments like shrub Master, Harrow, Cultivator, Rotavator, and Spray Tank as required.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6232332', '18-06-2025 11:00:00', '18-06-2025 11:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Power', 'Power Grid Corporation Of India Limited', 'Power Grid Corporation Of India Limited', 'Corporate Office Gurgaon', 'buycon51.pgcil.tr@gembuyer.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab and Taxi Hiring Service - Without Fuel - MUV; Mahindra Bolero Camper, Isuzu Dmax; 2024 or 2025; 0-25,000 kms; A/C; 24 X 7 365 Days', NULL, '3 Year', NULL, '7 years', 'No', 'No', 'Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '22,000', 'Yes', 5, 37, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the vehicle hiring service require a Multi-Utility Vehicle (MUV) of the type Mahindra Bolero Camper or Isuzu Dmax, from the model year 2024 or 2025, or a vehicle registered in the same or previous year. The vehicle should have a vintage of 0-25,000 kms. It must be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C) and run on Diesel, Petrol, or Hybrid fuel. The service engagement is for 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, 365 days a year. A driver is required to be provided with the vehicle. The terrain for operation includes Plain and Hilly areas, covering On Road, Off Road, Local, and Outstation travel. The fuel cost will be provided by the buyer and reimbursed to the service provider based on actual consumption.', 'M Balu', 'Dharmapuri', 'This bid document, GEM/2025/B/6232332, issued by Power Grid Corporation Of India Limited (POWERGRID), Ministry of Power, is for the procurement of a Monthly Basis Cab and Taxi Hiring Service for a contract period of 3 years. The service requires one MUV type vehicle (Mahindra Bolero Camper or Isuzu Dmax, 2024/2025 model) with a driver, operating 24x7, 365 days a year. The tender specifies a bid end date of 18-06-2025 and an offer validity of 90 days. The consignee is located at POWERGRID''s office in Dharmapuri, Tamil Nadu. The estimated monthly travel is 2323 KMs. Financial requirements include an EMD of 22,000 INR and an ePBG of 5% of the contract value for 37 months. The evaluation method is total value wise. Bidders must meet shortlisting criteria based on past experience in similar vehicle hiring services, with specific contract value thresholds. The scope of the contract outlines that the contractor will provide the vehicle and driver, bearing costs like taxes, insurance, and maintenance. POWERGRID will reimburse the driver''s wages as per minimum wage laws, fuel charges (at 1 Ltr/12 KM), toll taxes, and uniform costs. The payment will be made within 15 days of bill submission, which must include a GST invoice, verified logbook, and proof of wage payment. The document includes detailed Additional Terms & Conditions (ATC), payment terms, and various forms for bidders to complete, such as a Bid-Securing Declaration.', 'The work is considered successfully completed when the contractor consistently provides the specified MUV vehicle and a skilled driver for the entire 36-month contract period with 100% availability, 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. Success is contingent upon maintaining the vehicle in perfect, clean, and safe running condition with all required permits and documents (Registration, Insurance, Taxi Permit, Pollution Control) kept valid at all times. The contractor must ensure the driver is uniformed, courteous, sober, adheres to all traffic regulations, and follows the instructions of the Officer-in-Charge. Furthermore, successful completion requires the meticulous maintenance and timely submission of daily logbooks for all vehicle movements and the submission of accurate monthly bills with all stipulated supporting documents (GST invoice, proof of wage payment, verified logbook) to facilitate timely payment. The contractor must comply with all statutory obligations, including labor laws and the Motor Vehicle Act, and fully indemnify POWERGRID against any liabilities or damages arising from the execution of the contract.', 'The scope of work involves providing one Multi-Utility Vehicle (MUV) of the type Mahindra Bolero Camper or Isuzu Dmax (2024/2025 model) on a hire basis with a skilled driver for a contract period of 36 months. The service must be available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, 365 days a year at the POWERGRID, Dharmapuri TLM location. The contractor is responsible for all costs associated with the vehicle, including road taxes, insurance (comprehensive with occupant coverage), registration fees, maintenance, repairs, and lubricants. The vehicle must be kept in perfect running condition, be equipped with A/C, and have a valid Taxi Permit. The contractor must also provide a uniformed driver who holds a valid license and ensure the driver''s good conduct. In case of vehicle breakdown or non-availability, the contractor must provide an immediate replacement vehicle at their own cost. While the contractor bears the vehicle''s operational costs, POWERGRID will reimburse the following upon submission of documentary proof: driver''s monthly wages as per prevailing minimum wage laws, fuel charges at a rate of 01 Ltr / 12 kM based on the actual run, toll tax, border entry fees, parking charges, and a uniform reimbursement of ₹3500/- per year.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6239604', '26-05-2025 15:00:00', '26-05-2025 15:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Air Force', '***********', 'blue.pro@nic.in', 'Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs', NULL, '8 Months 20 Day', NULL, '2 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '22,680', 'Yes', 5, 8, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services require a Sedan vehicle type. The acceptable car models include Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, and Hyundai Xcent. The service is for Local usage with a variant of 80Kms x 10Hrs. The vehicle model year should be between 2021 and 2025, and the total kilometers travelled must be up to 25,000 Kms. A Non-A/C vehicle is required, and it must be operable in both Hilly and Plain areas. The fuel type can be any. For addon services, the type of trip specified is return.', '***********', 'Jodhpur', 'This bid document (GEM/2025/B/6239604), dated 16-05-2025, is issued by the Indian Air Force, Department of Military Affairs, Ministry of Defence, for the procurement of ''Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs''. The contract period is for 8 months and 20 days, requiring a bidder with 2 years of past experience. The bid follows a Two Packet system with a Reverse Auction (RA) based on H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination. The bid offer validity is 180 days from the bid end date of 26-05-2025. The evaluation method is on a total value basis. An EMD of 22680 is required, and an ePBG of 5.00% for a duration of 8 months is applicable upon contract award. The beneficiary is the AIR FORCE PUBLIC FUND at 33 SU AIR FORCE STATION JODHPUR. The tender specifies the hiring of two Sedan-type vehicles for a duration of 180 days in Jodhpur. The vehicles should be models from 2021-2025, Non-A/C, and have travelled up to 25,000 Kms. The document includes several buyer-added terms and conditions, including an option clause to vary the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. It also details specific requirements for vehicle hiring under the Ministry of Defence (MoD), covering aspects like insurance, accident liability, demand for vehicles, inspection, and rejection criteria. Bidders must comply with all applicable laws, including Labour Laws, and adhere to the General Terms and Conditions and Service Level Agreement of the GeM portal.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed, the service provider must consistently meet the following criteria from the tender issuer''s perspective: The provider must supply two Sedan vehicles that strictly adhere to all technical specifications, including vehicle model, year, kilometers travelled, and non-A/C requirement. The vehicles must be available for the specified duration of 180 days at the designated location in Jodhpur. The provider must respond to transport indents, typically given with 24-hour notice, and also be prepared for urgent demands. All supplied vehicles must be commercially registered with all taxes paid, and drivers must possess necessary permits. Vehicles must pass qualitative inspections by the consignee at any time and any rejected vehicle must be replaced promptly at the seller''s expense. The seller must ensure all vehicles are properly insured, indemnify the Government against any accident-related claims, and maintain proper documentation like the Car Diary, which must be signed by the officer using the vehicle. Full compliance with all contract terms, MoD-specific clauses, and applicable laws is mandatory for successful completion.', 'The scope of work involves providing ''Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services'' to the Indian Air Force in Jodhpur. The service provider is required to supply two Sedan-type vehicles for a total duration of 180 days within the contract period of 8 months and 20 days. The vehicles must meet specific technical requirements: they should be models such as Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, or Hyundai Xcent, manufactured between 2021 and 2025, with mileage not exceeding 25,000 Kms. The vehicles are required to be Non-A/C and suitable for operation in both Hilly and Plain areas. The usage pattern is defined as ''Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs'' for return trips. The provider must ensure vehicles are commercially registered and all taxes are paid. The service includes providing qualified drivers with valid permits. The operational requirements include reporting to the consignee to receive transport demands, which will normally be provided with a 24-hour notice. The provider must maintain a ''Car Diary'' for each vehicle, and time and distance will be calculated from the designated reporting point. The provider is also responsible for all insurance, liabilities from accidents, and must display an ''ON MILITARY DUTY'' board on the vehicles when in use by the buyer. The bidder must submit an acceptance certificate for this scope of work.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6240203', '20-06-2025 10:00:00', '20-06-2025 10:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Navy', '***********', 'krishna.kale@navy.gov.in', 'Decorative Plant and Bouquet Service- Monthly Rental Model - Wreaths; Hiring of services for decoration of war memorial with Wreath and Flowers; Not Applicable', NULL, '1 Year', '1,00,000', '1 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications outline the requirements for a ''Wreaths'' service type, specifically for the hiring of services for the decoration of a war memorial with wreaths and flowers. The key specification for the flower arrangement is that the War Memorial must be decorated with garlands of 6 meters in length. There should be 10 such garlands on each side of the memorial, arranged in a Tricolor formation using Marigold flowers, Jasmine flowers, and folded green leaves, with any additional requirements as per the scope of work. Other specifications such as Variety of Plants, Height of Plant, Width of Plant, and Material of Pot/Tray are listed as Not Applicable for this service.', '***********', 'Pune', 'This Government e-Marketplace (GeM) bid (GEM/2025/B/6240203), issued by the Indian Navy under the Ministry of Defence, is for the procurement of ''Decorative Plant and Bouquet Service'' which entails the hiring of services for the decoration of a war memorial with wreaths and flowers. The contract has a duration of 1 year. The bid is a Two Packet type with a total value wise evaluation method and includes a Reverse Auction. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 1 Lakh over the last 3 years and 1 year of past experience in similar services, with exemptions available for MSEs and Startups. The service is required at INS Shivaji, Naval Base, Lonavala, Pune, for a total of 5 times during the contract period as and when required. According to the Service Level Agreement, the vendor is responsible for all transportation, managing vehicles within the base, and paying their own labor. Work completion will be certified by a nominated representative of the Commanding Officer, INS Shivaji. Payment terms are 100% on delivery and acceptance by the buyer, processed by PCDA (Navy), Mumbai, with no advance payments.', 'The work is considered successfully completed upon the inspection and acceptance of the procured items and services by the representatives nominated by the Commanding Officer, INS Shivaji. Following this, a Work Completion Certificate will be issued by the wing, which is a prerequisite for the final user acceptance and processing of payment.', 'The scope of work involves hiring services for the decoration of the War Memorial located at INS Shivaji, Naval Base, Lonavala, Pune. This service is to be performed 5 times during the contract period on an as-and-when-required basis. The specific task is to decorate the memorial with garlands, each 6 meters long, with 10 garlands placed on each side. The garlands must be arranged in a Tricolor formation using Marigold flowers, Jasmine flowers, and folded green leaves, with additional decorations as per the specified scope. The vendor is fully responsible for all transportation of materials and personnel to and within the site, and for the payment of their workers. The work must be carried out during the specified working hours: 0900 hrs to 1730 hrs from Monday to Friday, and 0900 hrs to 1330 hrs on Saturday.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6241557', '17-06-2025 19:00:00', '17-06-2025 19:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Army', '***********', 'dhadey.583p@gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of Loader Cum Excavator JCB Per Hour Basis', 'Hiring of Earth Moving Equipments, Material Handling Equipments and Cranes (per Hour basis)', '10 Months 4 Day', '2,93,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),OEM Authorization Certificate,OEM Annual Turnover,Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '73,19,600', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '3', 'Yes', 3, 6, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require the hiring of a Loader Cum Excavator JCB on a per-hour basis. The service must ensure full regulatory and statutory compliance. Additionally, the service must be in compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA).', '***********', 'Jammu', 'This GeM bid document (GEM/2025/B/6241557), issued by the Indian Army, Ministry of Defence, is for a custom service contract for the ''Hiring of Loader Cum Excavator JCB Per Hour Basis''. The service is required for a period of 10 months and 4 days, specifically from 01 June 2025 to 31 March 2026, in the Durbuk Region. The tender, valued at an estimated 73,19,600, is a two-packet bid open to registered Co-operative Transport Societies of the Ladakh region. Prospective bidders must have a minimum average annual turnover of 293 Lakhs over the last three years and 3 years of similar service experience. The contract is governed by extensive Additional Terms and Conditions (ATC) that detail all qualitative, technical, administrative, and operational requirements. Key terms include the mandatory submission of a 3% Performance Bank Guarantee by the successful bidder, an option clause to increase the contracted quantity by up to 50%, and specific payment terms involving a 1% trade discount. The evaluation of bids will be based on the lowest overall combined value (lowest basket rate). The document provides comprehensive details on vehicle and crew standards, bidding procedures, contract execution, and penalties for non-compliance.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is considered successfully completed when the contractor has consistently provided the ''Hiring of Loader Cum Excavator JCB'' service in full compliance with all terms and conditions throughout the entire contract period. This includes supplying vehicles that meet all qualitative, technical, and administrative requirements at the specified time and place as demanded by the Contract Operating Officer. Success is further defined by the absence of significant breaches or failures that would warrant contract rescission, such as failing to supply at least 90 percent of the daily demand or exceeding the permissible number of monthly failures. The final measure of successful completion is the fulfillment of all contractual obligations, leading to the final settlement of accounts and the execution of a ''No Demand Certificate'' (IAFA-451) by the contractor, which allows for the refund of their Performance Security Deposit.', 'The scope of work is for the provision of Civil Hired Transport (CHT), specifically Loader Cum Excavator (JCB) and Hydra, on an as-required basis for the Indian Army in the Durbuk region from 01 June 2025 to 31 March 2026. The service will be billed according to the Bill of Quantity (BoQ), which includes rates for up to 8 hours, rates for extra hours, and charges for empty running. The contracted quantity is an approximation and may be increased by up to 50% under the Option Clause. The contractor must ensure the provided vehicles are not older than 18 years, are mechanically fit, and are in good working condition. Specific requirements for the JCB include having one serviceable spare wheel, tools, fire extinguishers, functional wipers, odometer, horn, lights (including beacon), and adhering to all emission norms. The vehicles must be roadworthy, have a valid pollution under check certificate, and be equipped with a First Aid Box. The contractor must also provide all necessary gear like tarpaulins and ensure vehicles display ''ON MILITARY DUTY'' signs when employed. The scope also includes adherence to all operational protocols such as procedures for vehicle demand and deployment, safety, crew conduct, documentation, and compliance with instructions from the Contract Operating Officer (COO). The contractor is responsible for all crew-related requirements, including valid permits and identity documents.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6246741', '18-06-2025 12:00:00', '18-06-2025 12:30:00', '30 Days', 'Ministry Of Consumer Affairs Food And Public Distribution', 'Department Of Food And Public Distribution', 'Food Corporation Of India (fci)', 'Fci Dhanbad', 'sushilg.fci@gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Onsite Comprehensive Annual Maintenance Contract and its accessories (AMC) along with the Live Web Streaming/Feeding of total 13 CCTV Cameras installed at FSD Dhanbad', 'AMC of Integrated Security and Surveillance System', '1 Year', NULL, '3 Year', 'Yes', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), OEM Authorization Certificate *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '70,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', NULL, NULL, 5, 12, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service, procured through a custom bid functionality, outline an Onsite Comprehensive Annual Maintenance Contract (AMC) for 13 CCTV cameras and their accessories, which includes Live Web Streaming/Feeding, at FSD Dhanbad. The service must strictly adhere to all regulatory and statutory compliance requirements. Furthermore, it is mandatory for the service to be in full compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA). There are no addon services specified.', 'Sushil Kumar Gond', 'Dhanbad', 'This tender, issued by the Food Corporation of India (FCI), Dhanbad, is for a Custom Bid for Services involving an Onsite Comprehensive Annual Maintenance Contract (AMC) and its accessories, along with Live Web Streaming/Feeding for a total of 13 CCTV cameras located at FSD Dhanbad. The contract period is for one year, with a possibility of a six-month extension based on performance evaluation. The estimated bid value is Rs. 70,000. Bidders are required to have a minimum of three years of past experience in providing similar services. The bid follows a Two Packet Bid system. The primary objective of the contract is to ensure the uninterrupted, 24x7x365 functionality of the CCTV surveillance system for effective security monitoring. This includes the continuous capture, display, storage, and retrieval of video data. The scope of work is comprehensive, covering maintenance of hardware like servers, NVRs, and cameras, as well as software aspects such as API integration, media server interface, and web page integration. The successful bidder will be responsible for all repairs, replacements, and preventive maintenance, including quarterly checks. A key performance requirement is to respond to any breakdown complaint within 24 hours and resolve it within 48 hours, failing which a penalty will be imposed. Payment will be made on a six-monthly basis upon submission of a satisfactory performance report. The successful bidder must deposit 5% of the bid value as a Security Deposit.', 'The successful completion of the work from the tender issuer''s perspective is determined by the following criteria:
1. The entire CCTV system, including all 13 cameras and associated peripherals, must be maintained in a fully functional state on a 24x7x365 basis without any interruption throughout the contract period.
2. Continuous, clear, and effective capturing of video images, along with their display, storage, and retrieval, must be ensured for security surveillance purposes.
3. The contractor must adhere to the service level agreement, which requires a response to any breakdown or complaint within 24 hours and complete resolution within 48 hours.
4. Regular preventive maintenance must be conducted, including quarterly servicing of all connected hardware.
5. Upon completion of the contract period, the entire CCTV surveillance system and all equipment must be handed over to FCI in a satisfactory and fully working condition.
6. For the purpose of formal acceptance and payment, a satisfactory performance report must be submitted by the Manager (D), and upon final completion, the Depot Manager will issue a Certificate of Final Acceptance.', 'The scope of work entails an Onsite Comprehensive Annual Maintenance Contract (AMC) and its accessories, which includes the ''Live Web Streaming/Feeding'' of a total of 13 CCTV cameras installed at FSD Dhanbad of FCI, Jharkhand Region. The primary objective is to ensure the entire CCTV system is functional 24x7x365 without interruption. The contractor must take over the work within 7 days of the Work Order. The work includes:
1.  **Hardware Management**: Installation and maintenance of an appropriate server, Network Video Recorder (NVR), firewall, and licensing for 13 cameras. This includes the repair or replacement of any defective parts with those of equivalent or higher specification, with a mandatory standby arrangement. All defective items must be replaced without extra cost.
2.  **Networking and Configuration**: Configuration of DVRs, assignment of static IPs, port forwarding for HTTP, RTPS, NAT, firmware upgrades, and enabling DDNS server, insta cloud interface, RTSP, and API.
3.  **Software Integration**: Management of Cameras API Integration, Media Server interface, RTMP streaming integration, and integration with the official Food Corporation of India webpage.
4.  **Maintenance and Support**: Conducting periodical servicing and preventive maintenance, including quarterly checks of all connected hardware. The contractor must respond to any complaint within 24 hours and resolve it within 48 hours. Service engineers must be available for emergency services during the contract period. All repairs are to be conducted on-site wherever possible.
5.  **System Handover**: Ensuring proper backup of video recordings as instructed and handing over the entire CCTV system in a satisfactory working condition to FCI upon the expiry of the contract.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6247127', '12-06-2025 14:00:00', '12-06-2025 14:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Petroleum And Natural Gas', 'Na', 'Oil And Natural Gas Corporation Limited', 'Central Procurement Department', 'buycon96.ongc.adi@gembuyer.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - hiring of services for Internal Cleaning, Inspection, Repair, Hydro Testing and R-Stamping of Pressure Vessels at Process complexes under MH, NH and B&S Assets', 'Operation And Maintenance Of Electro-Mechanical Installations', '5 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria,Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '7 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '70,20,979', 'Yes', 3, 62, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the tender outline the requirements for the hiring of services for Internal Cleaning, Inspection, Repair, Hydro Testing, and R-Stamping of Pressure Vessels at process complexes under MH, NH, and B&S Assets. The core requirements mandate YES for Regulatory/Statutory Compliance of the service and YES for Compliance of the service to SOW, STC, SLA etc. A detailed technical appendix (Appendix-1 of SoW & SCC) provides an exhaustive list of 454 vessels subject to these services. This list details specifications for each vessel including its associated Asset (MH, NH, or B&S), Process Complex, Process Platform, a specific Vessel Description (e.g., HP Separator, Fuel gas Pre-Scrubber, Cyclone Separator), its unique Tag Number, Inside Diameter (mm), Total Length (mm), Orientation (Horizontal/Vertical), and Insulation Type (Insulated/Non-insulated). This comprehensive list forms the basis for the scope and scale of the technical work required under the contract.', 'Y Premjit Singha', 'Mumbai', 'The GEM bid document (Bid Number: GEM/2025/B/6247127) issued by Oil and Natural Gas Corporation Limited (ONGC) is for a custom service contract for the ''hiring of services for Internal Cleaning, Inspection, Repair, Hydro Testing and R-Stamping of Pressure Vessels at Process complexes under MH, NH and B&S Assets''. The contract period is for 5 years with a bid offer validity of 90 days from the bid end date of 12-06-2025. The tender follows a Two Packet Bid system with a total value-wise evaluation method. Financial requirements include an EMD amount of 7020979 and an ePBG of 3.00% for a duration of 62 months. The Scope of Work (SoW) document details the execution of these services on approximately 454 pressure vessels across 14 process complexes in ONGC''s Western Offshore fields. The SoW specifies the contractor''s responsibilities, including internal cleaning, non-destructive testing, repair procedures as per API 510, hydro testing, and final documentation. The contractor is required to mobilize ten qualified teams and provide all necessary tools, equipment, and consumables. ONGC will provide logistical support such as offshore boarding, lodging, and transport. Payment terms are structured on a quarterly basis upon successful completion of work on vessels and submission of requisite documents, including a Job Completion Certificate. The tender documents also include detailed Instructions to Bidders, general contract conditions, and emphasize compliance with MSE and Make in India policies.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer (ONGC), the successful completion of the work for each vessel is formally acknowledged through the issuance of a ''Job Completion Certificate'' by the respective platform authorities. The criteria to achieve this success include: 1. Satisfactory Execution: The contractor must complete all specified tasks, including internal cleaning, inspection, repairs, R-stamping (as per ASME codes), and hydro testing, to the full satisfaction of ONGC. 2. Comprehensive Documentation: Submission of all required technical documents is mandatory. This includes detailed inspection reports (NDT, Holiday Test), health check reports, as-built drawings of repaired vessels, reports on revised maximum allowable working pressure and residual life, and a final Project Summary Report for each vessel. 3. Third-Party Verification: The work must be validated by an ONGC-appointed Third Party Inspection (TPI) agency. This includes witnessing the hydro testing and approving the final inspection. Repairs and R-Stamping must be supervised by an ASME inspector. 4. Warranty and Guarantee: The contractor must provide a 12-month warranty for all materials, workmanship, and services from the date of job completion for each vessel. If any performance is found non-satisfactory during this period, the job must be repeated at no extra cost to ONGC.', 'The detailed scope of work involves the comprehensive internal cleaning, inspection, repair, hydro testing, and R-stamping of approximately 454 pressure vessels located at 14 process complexes across ONGC''s Mumbai High (MH), Neelam & Heera (NH), and Bassein & Satellite (B&S) assets. The key activities are: 1. Internal Cleaning: This includes positive isolation and depressurization of vessels, flushing, proper ventilation, sludge removal, and cleaning of all internals, shell, and nozzle attachments. 2. Inspection: The contractor will conduct initial visual inspections and Non-Destructive Testing (NDT) such as flaw detection, wet magnetic particle inspection, DP test, and detailed wall thickness measurements. The vessel is then to be offered to ONGC''s Third Party Inspection (TPI) agency for final inspection, based on which a definitive repair scope will be prepared by the contractor. 3. Repair and R-Stamping: Following API 510 standards, this includes submitting repair procedures for approval, carrying out repairs under the supervision of an ASME inspector, replacing damaged internals (spares procured by contractor, cost reimbursed by ONGC), repairing pits, metal filling, and conducting glass flake lining after welding jobs. R-stamping is required for repaired vessels. 4. Hydro Testing and Boxing Up: After repairs, the vessel must be hydro tested at a specified pressure. The contractor is responsible for replacing all studs, nuts, and gaskets for opened flanges, re-fitting internals, removing scaffolding, restoring all instruments, and conducting a final leak check at operating pressure. 5. Documentation and Mobilization: The contractor must submit detailed milestone plans, all inspection and repair reports, as-built drawings, and project summary reports. The contractor is required to mobilize ten teams, each consisting of qualified personnel including a Supervisor, Technician, Fireman, and Riggers, along with all necessary tools and equipment.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6258279', '12-06-2025 11:00:00', '12-06-2025 11:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Chemicals And Fertilizers', 'Department Of Fertilizers', 'The Fertilisers And Chemicals Travancore Limited', 'Kerala', 'buyer53.fctl.kl@gembuyer.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring services of Backhoe loader (JCB) with operators for the Raw Material department at FACT Cochin Division, Ambalamedu, Kochi', 'Hiring of Special Purpose Mining or Earth Moving Machines (Monthly Basis), Hiring of Earth Moving Equipments, Material Handling Equipments and Cranes (per Hour basis)', '1 Year', '8,00,000', '7 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', '1747823524.xlsx', 'If any dispute arises out of or relating to or in connection with this CONTRACT, between the CONTRACTOR and the OWNER/FACT, the same shall be amicably settled through mutual discussions, failing which, the unresolved dispute(s) shall be referred to arbitration in accordance with the provisions of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996, as amended from time to time and number of Arbitrator shall be one. The venue of the Arbitration shall be at Ernakulam and the proceedings shall be in ENGLISH. Any legal proceedings relating to or in connection with this contract shall be limited to the exclusive jurisdiction of the High Court of Kerala.', NULL, 'State Bank of India', '65,000', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Purchase preference will be given to MSEs as defined in Public Procurement Policy for Micro and Small Enterprises (MSEs) Order, 2012 dated 23.03.2012 and its subsequent Orders/Notifications. Bidders will get the benefit of PP policy only if they are MSE bidders at the time of submission of their offers.', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service detail the procurement of ''Hiring services of Backhoe loader (JCB) with operators for the Raw Material department at FACT Cochin Division, Ambalamedu, Kochi''. Key requirements include mandatory regulatory and statutory compliance, as well as adherence to the Scope of Work (SOW), Special Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA). The service provider is eligible for 100% Input Tax Credit (ITC) on both GST and GST Cess. The designated consignee and reporting officer is Thirupathi Banavath at the Stores Department, Ambalamedu (PIN 682303). The procurement is for a single project or on a lumpsum basis, with no additional requirements specified for the consignee.', 'Thirupathi Banavath', 'Ambalamedu', 'This tender (Bid Number: GEM/2025/B/6258279), issued by The Fertilisers And Chemicals Travancore Limited (FACT) under the Ministry Of Chemicals And Fertilizers, is a custom bid for the hiring of a Backhoe loader (JCB) with operators for the Raw Material department at FACT Cochin Division in Kochi, Kerala. The contract period is for one year. The bid follows a Two Packet Bid system with a total value wise evaluation method. Key eligibility requirements for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 8 Lakhs over the last three years and 7 years of past experience in similar services. The Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) required is Rs. 65,000, and a Security Deposit of 10% of the work order value is mandatory upon contract award. The tender specifies that purchase preference will be given to Micro and Small Enterprises (MSEs) and to ''Make In India'' products as per government policy. The scope involves providing a Backhoe loader (manufactured in 2022 or later) with operators for continuous, round-the-clock operations, including charging materials, cleaning, and other tasks as directed. The contractor is responsible for ensuring 100% equipment availability, all statutory compliances including PF and ESI for their personnel, and adherence to strict safety regulations detailed in the tender documents. Final payment is contingent upon the satisfactory completion of work, site clearance, and settlement of all claims.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer (FACT), the work will be deemed successfully completed based on the fulfillment of several key criteria. Primarily, the contractor must ensure 100% availability of the Backhoe loader service throughout the contract period, including providing a spare loader within 24 hours during any breakdown, as non-availability incurs significant penalties and is considered a breach of contract. The work must be performed to the complete satisfaction of the company''s officers, as final payment is contingent on the completion of the work in all respects and its formal takeover by FACT. The contractor must adhere strictly to all terms outlined in the Scope of Work (SOW), Special Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA). Furthermore, successful completion requires full compliance with all applicable statutory and regulatory laws, particularly labor laws (ESI, PF) and safety regulations. Finally, before the final payment is released and the contract is considered concluded, the contractor must ensure the clearance of the site, settlement of any pending claims related to their labor, and rectification of any noted defects.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring of one Backhoe loader (JCB) of make 2022 or newer, complete with operators, for the Raw Material department at FACT Cochin Division, Ambalamedu. The service is required for continuous operations, 24 hours a day, across all three shifts, including Sundays and holidays. The key tasks include: Charging Sulphur from the godown to the charging bin at the Sulphuric Acid Plant at a rated speed of 1 bucket/minute; performing spillage cleaning and other cleaning activities at the raw material department, boat basin area, and acid plants; charging lime at the pollution control department; sweeping Rock Phosphate at the godown; and carrying out any additional backhoe operations as instructed by the Shift In-Charge. The contractor must ensure 100% availability of the loader by deploying a spare during breakdowns or maintenance. The contractor shall provide one operator per shift, ensuring they have valid licenses, police clearance, and ESI/PF registration. While FACT will provide High-Speed Diesel free of cost, all other consumables like oils, grease, and coolant, along with daily preventive maintenance, are the contractor''s responsibility. The contractor or their supervisor must be available at all times and maintain an office or residence near the premises for efficient coordination.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6258606', '20-06-2025 10:00:00', '20-06-2025 10:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Mines', 'Materials', 'National Aluminium Company Limited, Bhubaneswar', 'Alumina Refinery Nalco Damanjodi', 'buycon6.naclb.or@gembuyer.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - HIRING OF FOUR NUMBER OF BOLERO OF MAHINDRA & MAHINDRA MAKE JEEP OF MODEL: 2024 OR LATER ON MONTHLY BASIS', 'Vehicle Hiring Service - Per Vehicle-Days basis', '2 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '3 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '1,25,000', 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for this custom bid detail the procurement of a service for the HIRING OF FOUR NUMBER OF BOLERO OF MAHINDRA & MAHINDRA MAKE JEEP OF MODEL: 2024 OR LATER ON MONTHLY BASIS. It is mandatory for the service to have YES for Regulatory/Statutory Compliance and YES for Compliance of Service to the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA). There are no addon services specified in the table.', 'Debashisha Chhotaray', 'Damanjodi', 'This is a Two Packet, custom bid (GEM/2025/B/6258606) issued by National Aluminium Company Limited, Alumina Refinery, Damanjodi for the service of HIRING OF FOUR NUMBER OF BOLERO OF MAHINDRA & MAHINDRA MAKE JEEP OF MODEL: 2024 OR LATER ON MONTHLY BASIS. The contract period is for 2 years with a bid offer validity of 120 days from the bid end date of 20-06-2025. The bid requires an EMD amount of 125,000, and no ePBG is necessary. The evaluation method is total value-wise, and the bid is enabled for Reverse Auction with H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination. Bidders are required to submit documents for Experience Criteria and other certificates as requested in the ATC. The bid supports MII Compliance and MSE Purchase Preference. The service provider is mandated to comply with all applicable laws, including various Labour Laws, and the bid is governed by GeM''s General Terms and Conditions and the Service Level Agreement.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following criteria: The service provider must supply and maintain four Bolero jeeps of Mahindra & Mahindra make, model 2024 or later, on a monthly basis for the entire contract duration of 2 years. The service must strictly adhere to the defined Scope of Work (SOW), Service Level Agreement (SLA), and all terms and conditions of the contract. Continuous compliance with all regulatory, statutory, and applicable laws, including but not limited to Labour Laws such as The Minimum Wages Act 1948 and The Payment of Wages Act 1936, is mandatory. Successful completion is contingent on the uninterrupted and compliant delivery of the specified vehicle hiring service throughout the contract period.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring of four (4) Bolero vehicles of Mahindra & Mahindra make, with the model being 2024 or later. The service is to be provided on a monthly basis to the National Aluminium Company Limited, Alumina Refinery at Damanjodi. The contract duration for this service is two (2) years. The service provider must ensure that the service is in full compliance with all regulatory and statutory requirements. Furthermore, the provider is mandated to adhere to the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), Service Level Agreement (SLA), and all applicable laws and acts, including Labour Laws such as The Minimum Wages Act, 1948, The Payment of Wages Act, 1936, The Payment of Bonus Act, 1965, The Equal Remuneration Act, 1976, and The Payment of Gratuity Act, 1972.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6258854', '17-06-2025 20:00:00', '17-06-2025 20:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Power', 'Power Grid Corporation Of India Limited', 'Power Grid Corporation Of India Limited', 'Corporate Office Gurgaon', 'buyer1.pgcil.kkde@gembuyer.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of an agency for conducting Thermo scanning of CLR insulators in various transmission lines under PMJTL', 'Scanning and Digitisation Service (Version 2)', '3 Month', '10,00,000', '7 Years', 'Yes', 'No', 'Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', 'Not applicable', 'Two Packet Bid', '7 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '1,77,000', 'Yes', 5, 6, 'Yes', NULL, 'Purchase Preference as admissible under the policies of Government of India in vogue', 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications provided are for the ''Hiring of an agency for conducting Thermo scanning of CLR insulators in various transmission lines under PMJTL''. The service proposed must have YES for Regulatory/Statutory Compliance and YES for Compliance of Service to SOW, STC, SLA etc. The details for the ''Core'' and ''Addon(s)'' specifications are not mentioned in the table.', 'Sanjib Prasad', 'Nadia', 'This GeM tender (GEM/2025/B/6258854) is issued by Power Grid Corporation Of India Limited for the ''Hiring of an agency for conducting Thermo scanning of CLR insulators in various transmission lines under PMJTL''. The contract has a duration of 3 months and is a two-packet bid. Key requirements include an EMD of 177,000 INR and a 5% ePBG for 6 months. Bidders must meet specific qualifying criteria, including technical experience in scanning 400 KV or higher transmission lines and a Minimum Average Annual Turnover (MAAT) of at least INR 133.10 Lakh. The scope of work involves scanning specified 765kV and 400kV lines, providing all necessary equipment (including a 765 KV suitable camera), personnel, logistics, and submitting detailed GPS-tagged thermal and visual image reports in POWERGRID''s specified format. The work must be completed within 3 months and adhere to stringent safety provisions detailed in the document.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed from the tender issuer''s perspective, the contractor must complete the thermo-vision scanning of all specified transmission lines within a 03-month period from the GeM contract order date. A crucial pre-requisite is the submission of a valid calibration certificate for the testing kit before work execution. The primary success criterion is the submission of a comprehensive analysis report for each insulator, which must include high-resolution, GPS-tagged thermal and visual images, detailed analysis in PDF format, and a summary in Excel format, all adhering to the POWERGRID format. The final acceptance of the work and release of payment is contingent upon the submission and subsequent verification of these reports by the Engineer-In-Charge.', 'The scope of work is to conduct Thermo-vision scanning of CLR insulators on specific transmission lines as per the direction of the Engineer-In-Charge (EIC). The designated lines are: A) 765kV D/C New Ranchi-Medinipur T/L (269 Kms, 718 towers), B) 400kV D/C Chanditala-Medinipur T/L (37 Kms, 98 towers), and C) 400kV D/C Medinipur-Kharagpur T/L (37 Kms, 101 towers). The contractor is responsible for the deployment of the team and all associated costs, including food, lodging, and vehicles. The scope also includes providing a thermos-vision camera suitable for 765 KV transmission lines and submitting its valid calibration certificate before executing the work. For deliverables, the contractor must capture and submit GPS-tagged thermal and visual images along with an analysis report for each insulator to POWERGRID. The report must be in PDF format with detailed analysis and a summary in Excel format. The entire work is to be completed within 03 months from the date mentioned in the GeM contract order, with an overall quantity variation limit of +/- 25%.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6261836', '02-06-2025 18:00:00', '02-06-2025 18:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Defence', 'Dg Of Defence Estate', '***********', 'ddgcoord-dgde@gov.in', 'Hiring of Consultants - Per Person Per Months Based - Management Consultants; Legal Consultant / Advisor; LLB with Domain Knowledge Expertise; NA', NULL, '1 Year', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '14,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The tender requires the hiring of Management Consultants with the profile of Legal Consultant/Advisor. There are two categories of consultants being hired. The first category is for 5 consultants, each requiring a total experience of 4 to 6 years. The second category is for 1 consultant requiring a total experience of 10 to 14 years. For both categories, the indicative generic qualification is an LLB with Domain Knowledge Expertise, and the required expertise is as a Legal Expert/Legal Advisor. The deployment for all consultants will be Onsite. No Proof of Concept (POC) or certifications are required for this role.', '***********', 'South west delhi', 'The bid, identified by number GEM/2025/B/6261836 and dated 22-05-2025, is for the hiring of consultants by the Dg Of Defence Estate, under the Ministry of Defence. The contract period is for one year with an estimated value of 1,400,000. The tender specifies the hiring of Legal Consultants/Advisors on a per-person, per-month basis. A total of six consultants are required: five with 4-6 years of experience and one with 10-14 years of experience. The required qualification is an LLB with domain expertise in land management matters, including sale/purchase, transfer, mutation, removal of encroachment, title suits, and knowledge of various acts such as the PPE Act, Property Act, Cantonment Laws, and Land Acquisition Act. The bid is a Two Packet Bid, and the offer validity is 90 days from the bid end date of 02-06-2025. The buyer has an option clause to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. Past experience in similar services is required, with exemptions applicable for MSEs and Startups.', 'The work will be considered successfully completed when the provided legal consultant/advisor, who must be an advocate, demonstrates the required experience as per the specifications and possesses proven exposure to matters related to land management, including sale/purchase/transfer, mutation, removal of encroachment, title suits, PPE Act, transfer of Property Act, and vigilance cases. The consultant must have knowledge of relevant laws such as the Right to Fair Compensation and Transparency in Land Acquisition, Rehabilitation and Resettlement Act 2013, Administrative Laws, Cantonment Laws, and Municipal Laws. A key success criterion is the consistent fulfillment of official work requirements. Failure to meet these requirements will necessitate an urgent replacement of the consultant within 02 days of a written notice.', 'The scope of work involves providing the services of a Legal Expert/Legal Advisor to handle matters related to land and its management. The consultant''s responsibilities include dealing with sale/purchase/transfer of property, mutation processes, removal of encroachments, title suits, vigilance cases, and matters falling under the PPE Act and Transfer of Property Act. The expert must possess comprehensive knowledge of and be able to provide advice on various laws, including Administrative Laws, Municipal Laws, Cantonment Laws, and the Land & Acquisition Act. The work requires the consultant to be deployed onsite for the duration of the contract, which is 12 months.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6263796', '09-06-2025 17:00:00', '09-06-2025 17:30:00', '60 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Defence Production', 'Bharat Earth Movers Limited (beml)', '***********', 'buyer223.bemlb.kl@gembuyer.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of AC Hatchback Car, Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of AC Sedan Car, Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of AC Premium Sedan Car, Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of AC Higher End Car, Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of AC Luxury Car, Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of AC Bolero Vehicle', 'Vehicle Hiring Service - Per Vehicle-Days basis Vehicle Hiring Service - Per Vehicle-Days basis Vehicle Hiring Service - Per Vehicle-Days basis Vehicle Hiring Service - Per Vehicle-Days basis Vehicle Hiring Service - Per Vehicle-Days basis Vehicle Hiring Service - Per Vehicle-Days basis', '1 Year', NULL, 'Minimum 5 years'' Experience in the Similar Field', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '38,000', 'Yes', 5, 18, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications outline the requirements for the hiring of six distinct categories of vehicles through a custom bid functionality. The services procured are for the Hiring of an AC Hatchback Car, an AC Sedan Car, an AC Premium Sedan Car, an AC Higher End Car, an AC Luxury Car, and an AC Bolero Vehicle. For each of these vehicle hiring services, it is mandatory for the service provider to ensure Regulatory and Statutory Compliance of the service. Furthermore, the provider must guarantee that the service is in full compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Special Terms and Conditions (STC), and the Service Level Agreement (SLA).', '***********', 'Palakkad', 'This bid, number GEM/2025/Β/6263796, is issued by Bharat Earth Movers Limited (BEML), Palakkad, under the Ministry of Defence for the hiring of six types of air-conditioned vehicles on a rate contract basis for a period of one year. The required vehicles include AC Hatchback, AC Sedan, AC Premium Sedan, AC Higher End, AC Luxury, and an AC Bolero. The contract is intended for the transportation of VIPs, BEML officials, auditors, and customers. The bid is a two-packet system with a reverse auction feature. Key financial requirements include an EMD of 38,000 and a Performance Bank Guarantee (PBG) of 5% of the contract value, valid for 18 months. The contract allows the buyer to alter the quantity or duration by up to 50%. Bidders must quote a lumpsum rate for each vehicle category, covering specified minimum daily kilometers and hours for local and outstation duties. Payments will be made monthly based on actual usage and certified bills. The terms mandate that vehicles must not be more than five years old, be well-maintained, and operated by licensed, uniformed, and well-behaved drivers. The contractor is responsible for all operational costs including fuel, maintenance, driver''s salary, insurance, and taxes. A price variation clause is applicable for fuel cost fluctuations beyond 5%. Successful completion of the contract requires adherence to all terms, submission of proper documentation, and will result in the refund of the security deposit.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer (BEML), the work will be considered successfully completed upon fulfillment of the following criteria throughout the contract period: The contractor consistently provides the specified types of vehicles in good, clean, and roadworthy condition on an ''As and When Required'' basis without delays. All vehicles provided must be no more than 5 years old with functional air conditioning. Drivers must be licensed, uniformed, punctual, and professional in conduct. The contractor must ensure adherence to all statutory requirements, including valid vehicle registration, insurance, fitness certificates, and emission tests. Accurate maintenance of logbooks and the timely submission of daily trip sheets, duly endorsed by the user department, are mandatory. Monthly bills must be submitted correctly on time, certified by the Maintenance Department, and accompanied by statutory tax payment receipts. In the event of a vehicle breakdown, an alternative vehicle must be arranged promptly. Upon the conclusion of the one-year contract, the refund of the security deposit, based on the recommendation of the Maintenance department, will signify the final acceptance of the successful completion of all contractual obligations.', 'The scope of work involves providing five types of AC Cars (Hatch back, Sedan, Premium Sedan, Higher End, Luxury) and one AC Bolero vehicle to BEML Ltd, Palakkad Complex on a rate contract basis for a period of one year. The service is to be provided on an “As And When Required Basis” for the official use of VIPs, VVIPs, senior BEML officials, inspection agencies, auditors, customers, and other visitors. The specific vehicles required are: one AC Hatchback (Swift/Celario or equivalent), one AC Sedan (Swift Dzire/Etios or equivalent), one AC Premium Sedan (Ciaz/City or equivalent), one AC Higher End car (Innova Crysta or equivalent), one AC Luxury car (Innova Hycross/Carnival or equivalent), and one AC Bolero vehicle. The service includes the vehicle, fuel, and a driver. For the five types of cars, the rate must cover a minimum of 150 Km/12 Hrs per day for local duty and 250 Km/24 Hrs per day for outstation duty. For the Bolero, the rate must cover a minimum of 50 Km/12 Hrs for local duty and 250 Km/24 Hrs for outstation duty. The quoted rates per day must be all-inclusive, covering costs such as Fuel, Maintenance, Driver''s salary (including BATA for Day), Insurance, Emission test, Fitness certificate, and Road Tax. Rates for extra kilometers and extra hours beyond the base slab must be quoted separately.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6263919', '17-06-2025 17:00:00', '17-06-2025 17:30:00', '60 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'North Western Railway', 'North Western Railway', 'srdmecnw@jp.railnet.gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of 09 Ton capacity truck between Jaipur Ajmer Jaipur for transportation of Railway wheels Railway Material for 80 round trip for a period of two years', 'Goods Transport Service - Per Trip based Service', '2 Year', '6,00,000', '1 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '1,04,16,968', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '20,900', NULL, 5, 30, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service detail the hiring of a 09 Ton capacity truck for transportation between Jaipur, Ajmer, and back to Jaipur. This service is for moving Railway wheels and Railway Material for a total of 80 round trips over a period of two years. The service must maintain compliance with all regulatory and statutory requirements. Furthermore, it must adhere to the specifications laid out in the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA). There are no additional addon services specified.', 'Bhoor Singh Meena', 'Jaipur', 'This bid, number GEM/2025/B/6263919, is a custom bid for services issued by the North Western Railway, Ministry of Railways. The tender is for the hiring of a 09 Ton capacity truck for the transportation of Railway wheels and material between Jaipur and Ajmer for 80 round trips over a contract period of two years. The estimated bid value is 10,41,696.8 INR, with an Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of 20,900 INR and a required e-Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 5% for 30 months. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 6 Lakhs over the last three years and at least one year of past experience in similar services. Past performance requires the successful completion of similar services, defined as road transportation for entities like Indian Railways, government bodies, or large private companies with a turnover exceeding 500 Crores. The evaluation method is based on the total value. The bid follows a Single Packet Bid system. The successful contractor is responsible for providing the truck with a driver and attendant, ensuring all necessary documentation (driving license, registration, PUC, permits) is valid, and bearing all costs including fuel, taxes, and salaries. The contractor must also adhere to various labor laws and government schemes for their employees.', 'The work will be considered successfully completed upon the satisfactory execution of the assigned services as per the contract terms. The primary criteria for success, from the tender issuer''s perspective, is the issuance of a ''Certificate of Completion'' by the competent authority (Manager or Senior Section Engineer). This certificate is provided only after it is determined that the service has been completed in all respects satisfactorily and has passed any final tests that may be prescribed. For final payment and release of the Performance Guarantee, the contractor must also submit a ''No Claims Certificate'', confirming that all dues have been settled and no further claims will be made against the Railway.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring of a 09 Ton capacity truck to transport Railway wheels and Railway Material for 80 round trips between Jaipur and Ajmer over a two-year period. The contractor''s responsibilities include: providing a truck of sufficient capacity and in good condition with a driver and attendant at the specified location within the stipulated time upon demand by the Railways; transporting the loaded goods from Jaipur to Ajmer and vice versa; placing the truck under the crane at designated locations in Carriage and Wagon Workshop, Loco Workshop, or General Store in Ajmer, and at the Coach Care Complex in Jaipur. The contractor must also arrange for necessary items like chains, wire ropes, and gutka to secure the materials during transportation. The loading and unloading of the materials will be performed by Railway staff and resources at both locations. The contractor must provide details of two trucks, not more than five years old, with all valid documentation including registration, insurance, fitness certificate, road tax, PUC, and an All Rajasthan Permit. The contractor is also responsible for providing a replacement vehicle within five hours in case of a breakdown, failing which penalties will be imposed. All work must be carried out in consultation with the Senior Section Engineer (C&W) and must not affect railway operations.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6267823', '07-06-2025 16:00:00', '07-06-2025 16:30:00', '30 Days', 'Gujarat', 'Labour And Employment Department Gujarat', 'Directorate Of Employment & Training', 'Employment Head Office', 'buycon13.det.gj@gembuyer.in', 'Vehicle Hiring Service - Per Vehicle-Days basis - SUV/MUV; 2022, 2023, 2024; Outstation; Plain; 2500km; Round Trip', NULL, '2 Year', '5,00,000', '1 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '3,30,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '27-05-2025 15:00:00', 'District Employment Office Mahisagar, Second Floor, Collector office campus,', 'The technical specifications for the Vehicle Hiring Service require an SUV/MUV vehicle from the manufacturing years 2022, 2023, or 2024. The approved vehicle brands include Hyundai i10, Hyundai i20, Maruti Suzuki alto, Maruti Suzuki Wagon R, and Maruti Swift. The vehicle must be diesel-fueled, equipped with air conditioning, and have a vintage mileage between 0-25,000 kms. The service is intended for outstation, round trips on plain terrain, with a usage variant of 2500km. Specifications for State, District, and Zipcode are NULL. No Night Hault addon is required.', 'Pagi Vishalkumar', 'Lunavada', 'This bid, number GEM/2025/B/6267823, is issued by the Directorate Of Employment & Training, Gujarat, for a Vehicle Hiring Service. The contract period is for 2 years. The service required is on a per vehicle-day basis for an SUV/MUV for outstation round trips with a usage of 2500km. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with an estimated value of 330,000. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 5 Lakhs for the last 3 years and 1 year of past experience in similar services, with exemptions available for MSE and Startup entities. Purchase preference is available for MSEs. No EMD or ePBG is required for this tender. The bid includes an option clause allowing the buyer to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. The consignee is Pagi Vishalkumar at the District Employment Office Mahisagar. The evaluation method will be on a total value wise basis.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the service provider''s fulfillment of the entire 2-year contract by consistently providing a vehicle that meets all specified technical and operational requirements. This includes supplying the correct type of vehicle (SUV/MUV of specified brands and year), adhering to the service parameters (Outstation, 2500km usage, Round Trip), and ensuring compliance with all terms of the contract and Service Level Agreement. A key condition for success is the submission of all required vehicle-related documents to the office. Continuous adherence to all applicable laws, including but not limited to labor laws, throughout the contract period is mandatory for the work to be deemed successfully completed.', 'The scope of work is to provide a Vehicle Hiring Service on a per vehicle-day basis for a contract period of 2 years. The service provider must supply an SUV/MUV vehicle of the brand Hyundai (i10, i20) or Maruti Suzuki (alto, Wagon R, Swift), manufactured in 2022, 2023, or 2024. The vehicle must be diesel-powered, have functioning air conditioning, and a mileage between 0-25,000 kms. The service is for outstation round trips on plain terrain, with a usage requirement of 2500km. The service is to be provided to the consignee Pagi Vishalkumar at the District Employment Office in Mahisagar, Gujarat. The requirement is for 1 vehicle-day within the contract period, with a maximum of one vehicle needed per day or event. The service provider is also responsible for submitting all documents related to the vehicle to the office as per the SLA. The provider must comply with all applicable labor laws. The buyer retains the right to modify the contract quantity or duration by up to 25% under the option clause.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6267928', '17-06-2025 18:00:00', '17-06-2025 18:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Navy', '***********', 'budgetofficer-dit@nic.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of Managed Service Provider (MSP) for Hosting and Management of IN applications on Meity Empanelled Government Community cloud (GCC) cloud Service Provider (CSP)', 'Hiring of Agency for IT Projects- Milestone basis', '3 Years 3 Month', '13,00,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), OEM Authorization Certificate, OEM Annual Turnover *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '3 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '1,37,47,579', 'Yes', 5, 41, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '03-06-2025 15:00:00', 'ROOM NO. 130, 1ST FLOOR, ''C'' WING, SENA BHAWAN, NEW DELHI-110011, CONTACT - 011-21411596', 'The technical specifications for the custom bid service outline the requirement for hiring a Managed Service Provider (MSP). This MSP will be responsible for the hosting and management of IN applications on a Meity Empanelled Government Community Cloud (GCC) Cloud Service Provider (CSP). The service must ensure full adherence to all regulatory and statutory compliance requirements. Additionally, the service must be in complete compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA).', '***********', 'Central delhi', 'The bid document GEM/2025/Β/6267928, issued by the Indian Navy, Department of Military Affairs, is for a custom service contract for the ''Hiring of a Managed Service Provider (MSP) for Hosting and Management of IN applications on Meity Empanelled Government Community cloud (GCC) cloud Service Provider (CSP)''. The contract period is 3 years and 3 months. The bid is a Two Packet type, with a bid validity of 180 days from the end date of 17-06-2025. Financial eligibility requires a minimum average annual turnover of 1300 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. Exemptions for these criteria are available for Micro and Small Enterprises (MSEs). The bid process includes a Reverse Auction with an H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination rule. An EMD of 13747579 and an ePBG of 5.00% for a duration of 41 months are required. The bid supports MII and MSE purchase preference policies. A pre-bid meeting is scheduled for 03-06-2025. The bid is governed by GeM''s General Terms and Conditions, supplemented by buyer-added conditions which mandate bidders to be financially sound and to comply with all applicable labour laws.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be deemed successfully completed upon the awarded contractor''s fulfillment of all contractual obligations for the entire contract duration of 3 years and 3 months. The primary success criterion is the seamless and continuous hosting and management of the specified IN applications on the Government Community Cloud, strictly adhering to the defined Scope of Work (SOW). Success is further measured by the consistent compliance with all performance metrics and service levels detailed in the Service Level Agreement (SLA), adherence to the Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and maintaining all necessary regulatory and statutory compliances throughout the service period.', 'The scope of work entails the hiring of a Managed Service Provider (MSP) to deliver comprehensive services for the hosting and management of Indian Navy (IN) applications. The selected provider is responsible for ensuring these applications are hosted on a Meity Empanelled Government Community Cloud (GCC) Cloud Service Provider (CSP) platform. The work includes all activities necessary for the secure and efficient operation and management of the applications for the entire duration of the contract. The provider must ensure the service is delivered in full compliance with the detailed Scope of Work (SOW), the Service Level Agreement (SLA), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and all applicable regulatory and statutory requirements.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6269728', '20-06-2025 10:00:00', '20-06-2025 10:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Power', 'Contracts And Materials', 'Damodar Valley Corporation', 'Damodar Valley Corporation', 'somnath.chanda@dvc.gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of Ambulance service for KTPS DVC', 'Monthly Ambulance Service (All Inclusive)', '2 Year', NULL, '3 Years', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '3 Days', NULL, '24,08,299', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Bank of India', '48,166', NULL, 3, '26 Months', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require the hiring of an ambulance for KTPS DVC. The service must maintain regulatory and statutory compliance and adhere to the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA). The ambulance must meet specific requirements including general, essential, mechanical, regulatory, and special features. General requirements state that the vehicle must have cushioned seats, good quality interior upholstery, be roadworthy, and have all safety measures like wipers, door locks, and handles in perfect working order. Essential equipment includes a spare wheel, a set of tools, a First Aid Box, and other necessary items for smooth operation. Mechanically, the vehicle must be perfect overall with a fully functional brake, steering, and suspension system, and have tyres, horn, headlights, and indicators in good condition. For regulatory compliance, the ambulance must adhere to the State Motor Vehicle Act, State/Central Government Pollution Norms, and possess the requisite permit to operate as an ambulance. Special ambulance features include specific interior provisions such as one seat-cum-stretcher, one folding seat-cum-ladder, a seat for the doctor, two clamps for oxygen cylinders, a water container and washbasin cabinet, a tube light in the patient''s cabin, and a hook for holding a saline bottle. Safety features must include a flasher light, siren, a fire extinguisher mounted on the driver''s partition, and a Medical/First Aid Box.', 'Jairaj Toppo', 'Koderma', 'The GEM file, Bid Number GEM/2025/B/6269728, is a tender issued by Damodar Valley Corporation (DVC), under the Ministry of Power, for the hiring of one ambulance service for KTPS DVC. The contract period is for two years with an estimated bid value of Rs. 2,408,299. The service requires a non-AC hardtop ambulance (such as a Bolero Neo, Tata Sumo, or Tata Winger) on a round-the-clock basis for two years. The bid process is a Two Packet Bid with a bid offer validity of 180 days from the bid end date of 20-06-2025. Key financial requirements include an Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of Rs. 48,166 and an e-Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 3% of the contract value, valid for 26 months. The price basis for the contract is variable, linked to the price of diesel. Payment terms are structured as 95% of the contract price to be paid against monthly RA bills upon satisfactory completion certified by the Officer-in-Charge, with the remaining 5% released after the contract is completed. The tender includes several important clauses, such as a Liquidated Damages (LD) clause of 0.5% of the order value per week of delay, capped at 10%, and a penalty clause of Rs. 3,000 per day for failure to provide the vehicle. The successful bidder must furnish a Security Deposit-cum-Performance Guarantee of 3% of the order value. The tender mandates strict adherence to all statutory regulations, including EPF and ESI schemes for the deployed workers. Sub-letting of the contract is not permitted.', 'For the tender to be considered successfully completed from the issuer''s perspective, several criteria must be met. The primary criterion is the satisfactory execution of the service throughout the entire two-year contract period, with performance being acceptable in the opinion of DVC. On a monthly basis, success is determined by the satisfactory completion of the job, which must be duly certified by the designated Officer-in-Charge. The submission of monthly bills is contingent on this certification. Furthermore, a monthly performance evaluation report must be completed and jointly signed by the contractor''s representative and the Engineer-in-charge; failure to submit this report will result in the withholding of payment. The final 5% of the payment is released only after the successful completion of the entire contract, signifying that fulfilling the full term is a key success factor. Additionally, the execution of the formal agreement and the submission of the required Security Deposit-cum-Performance Guarantee are mandatory prerequisites for the contract to proceed, and their fulfillment is integral to the successful execution of the order.', 'The scope of work involves providing one non-AC hardtop covered ambulance, specified as a Bolero Neo, Tata Sumo, Tata Winger, or an equivalent model, for round-the-clock (24-hour) duty inside the Power House of KTPS, DVC for a period of two years. The primary duty of the vehicle is the transportation of patients who have sustained injuries due to plant accidents, illness, or other physical ailments from the plant to KTPS hospital, as well as to other referred hospitals in and around KTPS, and for other medical emergencies as required. The vehicle has a maximum permitted run of 3000 KM per month. The contractor is fully responsible for all operational aspects, including the procurement of fuel, lubricants, and spares. The scope also includes all routine maintenance, repairs, servicing, overhauling, and ensuring the vehicle is mechanically perfect and roadworthy with a functional odometer at all times. The contractor must engage three drivers who possess a Public Service Driving License and are trained for emergency situations. The contractor is liable for the payment of wages to the drivers and ensuring compliance with all statutory provisions, including the EPF Act. The vehicle must be registered as a Public Service/Commercial Vehicle and possess all statutory documents, including ownership, insurance, road tax token, fitness certificate, and pollution certificate. The ambulance must be equipped with specific inbuilt provisions like a seat-cum-stretcher, a folding seat-cum-ladder, a doctor''s seat, clamps for two oxygen cylinders, a water container with a washbasin cabinet, a flasher light with a siren, and a fire extinguisher. The contractor shall be responsible for the safe travel, punctuality, and comfort of all passengers. Penalties will be deducted from monthly bills for failure to provide the vehicle on any given day (Rs. 3000) or for refusing to travel to designated locations (Rs. 1000). The contractor must also maintain a pair of logbooks (for odd/even months) to record details of all journeys, which must be duly endorsed by the authorized DVC authority.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6270422', '19-06-2025 15:00:00', '19-06-2025 15:30:00', '45 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'South Western Railway', 'South Western Railway', 'anil.kumar0810@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - MUV; 1250 Kms per month; Outstation 24*7', 'Supply of Four-Wheel passenger road vehicles such as Tata Sumo/Safari, Mahindra Scorpio/Bolero, Toyota Innova/Qualis, Chevrolet Tavera etc.', '2 Year', NULL, 3, 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '11,75,976', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '23,520', 'Yes', 5, 28, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require a Multi-Utility Vehicle (MUV) of the type Mahindra Bolero Camper, Tata Xenon, Mahindra Imperio, or Isuzu Dmax. The vehicle is for a usage variant of 1250 Kms per month with outstation 24*7 service. The vehicle model should be from the years 2025, 2024, 2023, or 2022, with total travel up to 25,000 Kms. It must be a Non-A/C, diesel-fueled vehicle suitable for operation in both Hilly and Plain areas.', 'Krishna Kumar M P', 'Vasco-da-gama', 'This bid document, GEM/2025/B/6270422, is for the hiring of a single Non-AC MUV for a contract period of 2 years (730 days) for the South Western Railway. The service required is on a monthly basis for 1250 Kms per month with 24*7 outstation availability for the use of ADME/VSG. The bid end date is 19-06-2025, and the estimated bid value is 1175976. A key consignee is Krishna Kumar M P located in Vasco-Da-Gama, Goa. Financial requirements include an EMD amount of 23520 and an ePBG of 5.00% for a duration of 28 months. Additional qualifications for bidders include owning at least one vehicle, having at least one driver on payroll, and a minimum of 3 years of experience in the related field. The tender is governed by the General Conditions of Contract for services of Railways 2018 or the latest version and requires the submission of a 5% Performance Guarantee within 30 days of receiving the Letter of Acceptance. The scope includes all operational costs like fuel, driver''s salary, maintenance, taxes, and permits for travel in Karnataka, GOA, Maharastra, Tamilnadu, and Andhra Pradesh.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer, the work will be deemed successfully completed based on the contractor''s consistent adherence to the following criteria: The contractor must supply one non-AC MUV as specified, from the model years 2022-2025, in good, clean, and mechanically sound condition, available 24/7 as per the user department''s instructions. The vehicle must be provided with a qualified, healthy, and well-behaved driver who is not more than 40 years old. All journeys must be accurately recorded in a log book and countersigned daily by a railway official, which forms the basis for monthly payments. Successful completion involves providing the vehicle and driver without fail; any non-availability will attract penalties. In case of a breakdown, an alternative vehicle must be arranged within one hour. The contractor must fulfill all legal and statutory obligations, including vehicle taxes, permits, insurance, and labor laws for the driver. The vehicle''s performance and the driver''s conduct must remain satisfactory to the railway administration throughout the contract period. Adherence to all terms, including displaying ''ON RAILWAY DUTY'' boards and changing seat covers as specified, without incurring penalties, constitutes successful performance.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring of one Non-AC Multi-Utility Vehicle (MUV) such as a Tata Sumo/Safari, Mahindra Scorpio/Bolero, or similar, for the use of ADME/VSG on a daily basis for a period of two years (730 days). The vehicle shall be kept with the Railway for 24 hours a day and used as per the instructions of the User Department. The service includes a minimum of 1250 Kms per month. The contractor is responsible for providing the vehicle along with a qualified driver, sufficient fuel (diesel), and covering all expenses including maintenance, repairs, lubricating oil, driver''s salary, daily batta, toll charges, parking charges, and any other incidental costs. The vehicle must be of manufacturing year 2022, 2023, 2024, or 2025, in excellent mechanical condition, and kept clean. The contractor must ensure the vehicle has a valid permit to travel in Karnataka, Andhra Pradesh, Tamil Nadu, Goa, and Maharashtra. An alternative vehicle must be provided during major repairs or breakdowns. The contractor must maintain a log book for all vehicle usage, which will be countersigned by a Railway official for payment processing. The contractor is also responsible for all legal and statutory compliances, including Road Tax, RTO registration, insurance, and adherence to Labour Law, ESI, PF, etc., for the driver. The vehicle must display ''ON RAILWAY DUTY'' boards, and have clean seat covers changed every third day.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6274426', '07-06-2025 13:00:00', '07-06-2025 13:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Agriculture And Farmers Welfare', 'Department Of Agriculture Cooperation And Farmers Welfare', 'National Institute Of Agricultural Extension Management (manage)', 'Hyderabad', 'mvenugopal@manage.gov.in', 'Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Local; 40Kms x 5Hrs 80Kms x 10Hrs 120Kms x 12Hrs, Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; Local; 40Kms x 5Hrs 80Kms x 10Hrs 120Kms x 12Hrs, Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium SUV; Local; 40Kms x 5Hrs 80Kms x 10Hrs 120Kms x 12Hrs, Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Outstation; 250Kms x 8Hrs 300Kms x 10Hrs 400Kms x 12Hrs 500Kms x 14Hrs, Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium SUV; Outstation; 250Kms x 8Hrs 300Kms x 10Hrs 400Kms x 12Hrs 500Kms x 14Hrs', NULL, '1 Year', '89,00,000', '5 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '22,34,520', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '67,000', 'Yes', 3, 14, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the short-term cab and taxi hiring services are detailed across five categories. For Local services, Sedan, SUV, and Premium SUV types are required. All must be of model years 2025, 2024, or 2023, have travelled up to 50,000 Kms, be air-conditioned, operate in plains, and can use any fuel type. The usage variants are 40Kms x 5Hrs, 80Kms x 10Hrs, and 120Kms x 12Hrs. Specific car models include Honda Amaze and Maruti Suzuki Dzire for Sedans; Maruti Suzuki Ertiga and Mahindra Scorpio for SUVs; and Toyota Innova and Jeep Compass for Premium SUVs. For Outstation services, Sedan and Premium SUV types are specified. These vehicles must also be from model years 2025, 2024, or 2023, have travelled up to 75,000 Kms, be air-conditioned, operate in plains, and use any fuel. The usage variants for outstation travel are 250Kms x 8Hrs, 300Kms x 10Hrs, 400Kms x 12Hrs, and 500Kms x 14Hrs. The specified car models for outstation are the same as their local counterparts.', 'Pullabhotla Rama Murthy', 'Hyderabad', 'This bid document, GEM/2025/B/6274426, is for the procurement of Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for the National Institute Of Agricultural Extension Management (MANAGE) in Hyderabad, under the Ministry Of Agriculture And Farmers Welfare. The contract period is one year, with a bid offer validity of 90 days. The estimated bid value is 2,234,520. The services required cover various vehicle categories including Sedan, SUV, and Premium SUV for both Local and Outstation travel, with predefined kilometer and hour packages. Bidders must have a minimum average annual turnover of 89 Lakhs for the last three years and 5 years of past experience in similar services. Key requirements for bidders include possessing a fleet of at least 10 owned vehicles, having 10 drivers on payroll, and a geographic presence in Hyderabad, Telangana. The bid is a two-packet system, and financial documents with a price breakup are required. An EMD of 67,000 is mandatory, and a performance security (ePBG) of 3% is required for 14 months upon award. The document includes detailed buyer-added terms and conditions, a Scope of Work, and a Service Level Agreement (SLA). The SLA outlines service standards, vehicle and driver requirements, obligations for both buyer and service provider, service tracking through logbooks, and a penalty structure for non-compliance, such as non-deployment, breakdowns, and driver misbehavior.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon fulfillment of the following criteria:
1. Consistent provision of vehicles that meet all specified requirements, including vehicle type (Sedan, SUV, Premium SUV), model year (2025, 2024, 2023), and condition (air-conditioned, clean, mechanically sound, with all necessary permits and safety equipment).
2. Strict adherence to the agreed-upon schedules, with vehicles and drivers reporting to the designated location on time. Delays and non-deployments must be minimized and handled with prompt replacement vehicles as per the SLA.
3. Full compliance with service standards, ensuring drivers are professional, licensed, experienced, courteous, and maintain good conduct without any instances of misbehavior or intoxication.
4. Accurate and timely maintenance of logbooks for every trip, duly signed by the authorized user, to facilitate transparent and correct billing.
5. Seamless execution of the contract without incurring repeated penalties or breaches of the Service Level Agreement. The contract is subject to termination if cumulative penalties exceed 10% of the contract value or if there are repeated SLA breaches.
6. Adherence to all statutory and legal obligations, including labor laws and the Motor Vehicles Act, with the service provider bearing full responsibility.
7. Submission of correct invoices along with supporting documents like logbooks for processing payments as per the defined payment cycle.', 'The scope of work involves providing Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services on a daily basis for the National Institute Of Agricultural Extension Management (MANAGE) in Hyderabad. The service includes the provision of vehicles with a driver and fuel for both local and outstation travel. The services are categorized by vehicle type and usage:
1. Vehicle Types: The service provider must supply vehicles from three categories: Sedans (e.g., Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire), SUVs (e.g., Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra Scorpio), and Premium SUVs (e.g., Toyota Innova, Toyota Fortuner).
2. Travel Categories:
   - Local Travel: For travel within city limits or up to 50 km one-way. The required usage variants are 40 KM x 5 Hours, 80 KM x 10 Hours, and 120 KM x 12 Hours.
   - Outstation Travel: For travel outside city limits or more than 50 km one-way. The usage variants are 250 km x 8 hrs, 300 km x 10 hrs, 400 km x 12 hrs, and 500 km x 14 hrs.
3. Vehicle Standards: All vehicles provided must be air-conditioned, from the model years 2025, 2024, or 2023, and adhere to specified mileage limits (up to 50,000 km for local, 75,000 km for outstation). They must possess all necessary permits and clearances, including fitness certificates, PUC, comprehensive insurance, and registration. Vehicles must be in excellent working condition and equipped with a first-aid kit and fire extinguisher.
4. Driver and Service Standards: The provider must ensure drivers are licensed, have a minimum of two years of driving experience, are courteous, and maintain professional conduct. The service provider is responsible for maintaining logbooks, managing contingencies like breakdowns by providing immediate replacements, and complying with all applicable labor and transport laws. The contract duration is for one year.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6274756', '18-06-2025 10:00:00', '18-06-2025 10:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Home Affairs', 'Central Armed Police Forces', 'Indo Tibetan Border Police (itbp)', '1 Bn', 'i.107011881@itbp.gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - HIRING OF PORTER AND PONY FOR TRANSPORTATION OF FRP HUTS', 'Manpower Outsourcing Services - Man-days based, Manpower Outsourcing Services - Fixed Remuneration, Manpower Outsourcing Services - Minimum wage', '10 Month', '3,00,000', '2 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', '50% Lowest Priced Technically Qualified Bidders', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '10,13,21,100', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '30,500', 'No', '5%', 'up to 60 days after the expiry of contract period', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '06-06-2025 09:00:00', 'OFFICE OF THE COMMANDANT, 1ST BN, ITB POLICE FORCE, SUNIL, JOSHIMATH, DISTT-CHAMOLI (UTTARAKHAND) 246443', 'The technical specifications for this custom bid detail the requirement for the HIRING OF PORTER AND PONY FOR TRANSPORTATION OF FRP HUTS. The service must ensure full compliance with all regulatory and statutory regulations. Furthermore, the service provider must adhere to the specifications laid out in the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and the Service Level Agreement (SLA).', 'Rajesh Kumar Meena', 'Joshimath', 'This GeM bid (GEM/2025/B/6274756), issued by the 1st Battalion of the Indo Tibetan Border Police (ITBP), Ministry of Home Affairs, is a custom tender for the service of ''HIRING OF PORTER AND PONY FOR TRANSPORTATION OF FRP HUTS''. The contract period is for 10 months with a bid offer validity of 180 days from the bid end date of 18-06-2025. The estimated bid value is Rs. 10,13,211.00. Prospective bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 3 Lakhs for the last three years and 2 years of past experience in similar services. The bid follows a two-packet system and the evaluation method is based on the total value. An EMD amount of Rs. 30,500 is required. The primary objective is to transport government stores, rations, construction materials like cement, sand, stone, and FRP Huts to the forward posts of the 1st Battalion located in Joshimath, Chamoli, Uttarakhand. The service also includes providing support for Long Range Patrols (LRPs), Short Range Patrols (SRPs), and other military operations. The successful bidder must furnish a performance security of 5% of the contract value and ensure all porters and ponies are insured and medically fit. The contract outlines detailed terms for timely delivery, billing procedures via the GeM portal, and penalties for non-compliance or delays.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed based on the following criteria:
1. Timely Execution: The contractor must complete the transportation and stocking of all designated government rations and stores at the forward posts by the deadline of 31.10.2025. In exceptional circumstances, the deadline may be extended to 30.11.2025.
2. Safe and Complete Delivery: The contractor is fully responsible for the safe delivery of all government goods from the dispatching post to the designated receiving post without any shortage, damage, or loss. Any discrepancies will result in financial recovery from the contractor''s bills or performance security.
3. Documentation and Verification: Successful completion is verified through the submission of proper challans, signed by both the dispatching and receiving posts, for every consignment. The bills generated on the GeM portal must be supported by these verified challans.
4. Adherence to Contractual Obligations: The contractor must fulfill all terms, including providing the required number of medically fit and insured porters/ponies, ensuring their payment, and adhering to all specified loads and routes.
5. Final Clearance: The contract is formally concluded upon the successful completion of all haulage for the contract period and the submission of a ''no dues'' certificate by the contractor, which then allows for the release of the Performance Security.', 'The scope of work involves the engagement of porters and ponies for transportation and logistics support for the 1st Battalion, ITBP, at Sunil, Joshimath, Uttarakhand. The detailed scope includes the following tasks:
1. Transportation of Construction Materials: The contractor must transport materials such as Stone, Sand, Aggregate, Cement, and FRP Huts (including 360 panels and miscellaneous accessories) to various Border Outposts (BOPs). Specific routes include Lapthal to Chyudang, Upper Rimkhim to Ati Sen, and Upper Rimkhim to Takuli Sen.
2. Material Collection: The scope includes the collection of stone, sand, and aggregate required for construction work from the nearest available ''Nallah'' or other specified locations.
3. General Stores Haulage: Transportation of all types of government property, various rations, and other stores to the forward posts of the battalion.
4. Operational Support: Providing porter and pony support for military and operational activities, including Long Range Patrols (LRP), Short Range Patrols (SRP), mountaineering expeditions, and rescue operations.
5. Adherence to Load Specifications: The work must be carried out adhering to the standard load capacities, which are 60 kg for a pony/mule and 20 kg for a porter.
6. Miscellaneous Government Works: The contractor is also required to provide porters for other miscellaneous government tasks as needed, with a carrying weight of 20 kg.
The contractor is responsible for the insurance, medical fitness, character verification, lodging, and boarding of all porters and pony handlers engaged for the work.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6274972', '11-06-2025 12:00:00', '11-06-2025 12:30:00', '180 Days', 'Gujarat', 'Panchayats And Rural Housing Department Gujarat', 'N/a', 'Arvalli District Panchayat', 'dao-agri-arv@gujarat.gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Outstation 24*7', NULL, '9 Months 20 Day', '6,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'No', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '3,02,400', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'sbi modasa', NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require the provision of an SUV type vehicle, with suggested models being Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra TUV300, or Mahindra Bolero. The service is defined by a usage variant of 2000 km and 320 hours for outstation 24*7 duties. The vehicle model must be from the years 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024, or 2025, having travelled up to 50,000 Kms. It must be a non-air-conditioned vehicle that operates on diesel fuel and is intended for use in plains. No specific add-ons are mentioned.', 'Pragneshbhai Parmar', 'Modasa', 'This bid, GEM/2025/B/6274972, is for the monthly hiring of a single SUV cab service for the Arvalli District Panchayat, Gujarat. The contract duration is 9 months and 20 days, with a potential extension of up to 6 months based on satisfactory performance. The service requires the vehicle for 2000 km and 320 hours per month for 24*7 outstation duties. The estimated bid value is 302,400. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 6 Lakhs for the last three years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. The bid is a Two Packet system with evaluation based on the total value. Key buyer-added conditions mandate that the service provider must be registered in Gujarat, own at least one vehicle, and submit a 3% EMD of the bid amount. All terms and conditions for the service are governed by the Gujarat State Procurement Policy 2024.', 'The tender document specifies that the service contract may be extended for up to 6 months beyond the initial contract date, subject to ''SATISFACTORY PERFOMANCE AND MUTUAL CONSENT''. Therefore, the primary success criterion from the tender issuer''s perspective is the consistent delivery of satisfactory performance throughout the contract period, which would warrant a contract extension. The document does not provide a more detailed breakdown of specific performance metrics.', 'The scope of work is to provide one SUV vehicle on a monthly hiring basis to the Arvalli District Panchayat for a contract period of 9 months and 20 days. The service must cover a usage of 2000 km and 320 hours per month for outstation 24*7 duties. The vehicle provided must be a Non-A/C, diesel model from the years 2021-2025, such as a Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra TUV300, or Mahindra Bolero. The service provider is required to be a firm registered in Gujarat and must own at least one vehicle in their name. All other terms and conditions related to the execution of this work will be as per the Gujarat State Procurement Policy 2024 Resolution No. SPOJ 02021-188460-CH-DATED 14-03-2024.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6275506', '13-06-2025 12:00:00', '13-06-2025 12:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Navy', '***********', 'logo-pallava@navy.gov.in', 'Vehicle Hiring Service - Per Vehicle-Days basis - SUV/MUV; 2024, 2025, 2023; Local; Plain; 100Kms x 24Hrs; Round Trip', NULL, '1 Year', '11,00,000', '2 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '11,07,245', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '33,000', NULL, 5, 14, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '09-06-2025 11:00:00', 'Conference Hall, Admin Block, INS Pallava, Anupuram 603127.', 'The technical specifications for the Vehicle Hiring Service require an SUV/MUV type vehicle from brands such as Toyota Innova, Mahindra Bolero, or Mahindra Bolero Camper, with a manufacturing year of 2024, 2025, or 2023. The service is for local use on plain terrain, with a usage variant of 100Kms x 24Hrs for a round trip. The vehicle must be equipped with Air Conditioning (AC) and can have a vintage mileage of either 0-25,000 kms or 25,000-50,000 kms. Any fuel type is acceptable, and a night hault is required. The State, District, and Zipcode are not specified.', '***********', 'Kancheepuram', 'The bid, number GEM/2025/B/6275506 dated 03-06-2025, is issued by the Indian Navy, Department of Military Affairs, Ministry of Defence, for the procurement of ''Vehicle Hiring Service - Per Vehicle-Days basis - SUV/MUV; 2024, 2025, 2023; Local; Plain; 100Kms x 24Hrs; Round Trip'' for a contract period of one year. The bid concludes on 13-06-2025 at 12:00:00, with an estimated value of INR 1107245. Bidders must have a minimum average annual turnover of 11 Lakhs over the last three years and two years of past experience, though exemptions for MSE and Startups are available. The procurement will follow a Two Packet Bid system with a Total Value Wise evaluation and a subsequent Reverse Auction. An Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of INR 33000 and an electronic Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 5% for a duration of 14 months are required. A pre-bid meeting is scheduled for 09-06-2025 at INS Pallava, Anupuram. The service requires the provision of 365 vehicle-days in Kanchipuram, with a maximum of one vehicle per day and a mandatory night hault for the entire contract period. A specific condition mandates that bidders must have a local office in Tamil Nadu.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is considered successfully completed upon fulfillment of several criteria. The primary condition is the consistent and uninterrupted provision of the specified vehicle hiring service for the entire one-year contract period. This includes providing one specified SUV/MUV for 365 vehicle-days to the consignee in Kanchipuram, strictly adhering to all technical specifications such as vehicle brand, manufacturing year, AC fitment, and the 100Kms x 24Hrs usage variant. Success is also defined by the fulfillment of additional requirements, notably the provision of a night hault for all 365 days of the contract. Furthermore, successful completion is contingent on the service provider''s complete adherence to all terms, conditions, and applicable laws, particularly labour laws, as stipulated in the bid document, with any non-compliance being treated as a breach of contract.', 'The Scope of Work entails providing a ''Vehicle Hiring Service'' on a per vehicle-day basis for a contract period of one year. The service is for the consignee located in Kancheepuram. The contractor is required to supply one SUV/MUV type vehicle for a total of 365 vehicle-days. The vehicle must be a Toyota Innova, Mahindra Bolero, or Mahindra Bolero Camper with a manufacturing year of 2024, 2025, or 2023. It must be equipped with Air Conditioning (AC) and be suitable for local, round trip services on plain terrain. The standard usage is defined as 100 Kms per 24 hours. A critical component of the scope is the mandatory provision of a night hault for the vehicle for the entire 365-day contract period. To be eligible, the service provider must operate a local office within Tamil Nadu. Additional details on the scope are referenced in an external document ''Scope of Work:1748929656.pdf''.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6276089', '20-06-2025 16:00:00', '20-06-2025 16:30:00', '90 Days', 'Cabinet Secretariat', NULL, NULL, 'Admin-ii, Cabinet Secretariat, Rashtrapati Bhawan, New Delhi', 'verma.deapak89@gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of 02 Canteen Attendants (Cook/Helper)', 'Manpower Outsourcing Services - Minimum wage', '1 Year', NULL, '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '6,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '30,000', 'Yes', 3, 14, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the ''Custom Bid For Services - Hiring Of 02 Canteen Attendants (Cook/Helper)'' mandate that the service must comply with all regulatory and statutory norms. Furthermore, the service must adhere to the Scope of Work (SOW), Special Terms and Conditions (STC), and the Service Level Agreement (SLA). The core service required is the hiring of two Canteen Attendants who can function as a cook or helper. There are no add-on specifications mentioned in the table.', 'Deepak Verma', 'New delhi', 'This bid document (GEM/2025/B/6276089), issued by the Cabinet Secretariat in New Delhi, is for a ''Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of 02 Canteen Attendants (Cook/Helper)'' for a one-year contract, with a possible six-month extension based on performance. The bid is a Two Packet type with an estimated value of INR 600,000, requiring an EMD of INR 30,000 and a 3% performance guarantee (ePBG). Bidders are required to have three years of past experience in similar services. Exemptions for experience and turnover criteria are provided for MSEs and Startups, and MSEs are also eligible for purchase preference. The scope involves providing two semi-skilled personnel to prepare and serve tea, coffee, and snacks during high-level meetings and at the office canteen counter. Key bidder qualifications include having an office in the consignee''s state, ISO 9001 certification, and registration with EPF and ESI for a minimum of 30 employees for the past three years. The service provider is responsible for paying salaries to their staff as per the minimum wage rates notified by the Govt. of NCT of Delhi before claiming reimbursement from the buyer.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed from the tender issuer''s perspective, the service provider must ensure the following: 
1. Consistent and satisfactory performance of the deployed personnel as per the defined scope of work, which is the primary condition for any potential contract extension.
2. Full adherence to the Service Level Agreement (SLA), including deploying personnel with the specified educational qualifications (Secondary School) and submitting their police verification prior to engagement.
3. Strict compliance with all statutory and regulatory requirements, including the timely payment of salaries and wages (as per Govt. of NCT of Delhi''s minimum wage rates for Semi-Skilled workers), EPF, and ESIC contributions for the deployed staff.
4. Submission and maintenance of all required documentation, including ISO 9001 certification, GST returns, and EPF/ESI challans throughout the contract period.
5. Fulfilling all buyer-added terms and conditions without fail, such as maintaining a service office in the consignee''s state and providing support as required.', 'The scope of work is to provide services for the hiring of two Canteen Attendants, who will function as a Cook/Helper. These deployed personnel will be classified as Semi-Skilled and are required to have educational qualification certificates up to Secondary School, which must be submitted to the buyer. Additionally, police verification of the deployed manpower must be submitted to the consignee before their engagement. The duties of the personnel include serving as catering staff during high-level meetings, where they will be responsible for preparing and serving tea, coffee, and snacks. They will also be required to be stationed at the Canteen counter to serve snacks to the employees of the office. Overtime allowance will be admissible on a case-by-case basis as per prevailing rates.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6276462', '17-06-2025 17:00:00', '17-06-2025 17:30:00', '60 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'Central Railway', 'Central Railway Stores Deptt', 'dycec@pa.railnet.gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - MUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Outstation', NULL, '2 Years 1 Day', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '34,40,304', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '68,820', 'Yes', 5, '30 Months', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the required service detail a Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Service. The core requirement is for a MUV (Multi-Utility Vehicle) with a usage variant of 2000 km x 320 hours for outstation service. The vehicle model must be from the year 2024 or 2025 and should have travelled upto 75,000 Kms. Acceptable car types include Mahindra Bolero Camper, Mahindra Imperio, Tata Xenon Yodha, Mahindra Scorpio Getaway, Tata Xenon XT, Maruti Suzuki Eeco, and Force Trax Cruiser. The vehicle must be Non-A/C, run on Diesel, and be suitable for operation in both Hilly and Plain Areas. There are no addon specifications mentioned.', 'Mohit Singh', 'Pune', 'This bid document, GEM/2025/B/6276462, issued by the Central Railway Stores Department of the Ministry of Railways, is for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services. The service requires three MUV-type vehicles for a contract period of 2 years and 1 day, intended for outstation use with a monthly limit of 2000 km and 320 hours. The estimated bid value is 3,440,304 INR. The bid end date is 17-06-2025. Key financial requirements include an EMD of 68,820 INR and an ePBG of 5% of the contract value for a duration of 30 months. The evaluation method is based on the total value. The service provider must have a geographic presence in Maharashtra and an office in the state of the consignee. The vehicles provided must be from the 2024 model year only, be less than 3 years old, and comply with detailed specifications including being non-A/C and diesel-powered. The contract includes several buyer-added terms, such as the requirement for the contractor to submit vehicle and driver details within 7 days of the contract award and a 5% E-PBG within 15 days. The scope of work details operational requirements, driver conduct, statutory compliances, and billing procedures. The contract is for 24 months and can be terminated with a 30-day notice.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be deemed successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following criteria: 1. Submission of a 5% E-PBG (issued by a Nationalized/Scheduled Bank) within 15 days from the award of the contract. 2. Within 7 days of the contract award, the bidder must submit all required vehicle details including RC copy, PUC, Insurance, and Driver Details to the user, and these details must also be updated on the GeM Portal. 3. Provision of three vehicles that strictly adhere to the technical specifications, including being of the 2024 registration year only, mechanically sound, and well-maintained. 4. Continuous and uninterrupted availability of the vehicles and drivers on a 24/7 basis, including at short notice. 5. Strict adherence to all operational conditions, such as maintaining log-sheets, ensuring drivers are well-behaved, uniformed, and possess valid licenses, and using the vehicle exclusively for Central Railway. 6. Compliance with all statutory laws, including payment of minimum wages to the driver and maintaining valid insurance for the vehicle. 7. Timely and accurate submission of monthly bills along with signed duty slips and log sheets for payment processing. 8. Failure to comply with the documentation and E-PBG submission requirements will lead to contract termination and forfeiture of the E-PBG.', 'The scope of work involves providing monthly basis cab and taxi hiring services for the official use of Supervisors engaged under PSSA in the Dy.CE/C/PA & STR unit. The contractor is required to supply 3 four-wheeler MUV vehicles for a period of 24 months. The vehicles must not be more than 3 years old, must be registered in the year 2024, and should be mechanically sound, in good fettle, and decently maintained with neat and clean seat covers. The service must be available round the clock, even at short notice. The quoted rates shall be all-inclusive of costs such as fuel, consumables, wages, repairs, servicing, all taxes (including GST), licenses, levies, and insurance; only parking charges will be reimbursed upon production of original coupons. The contractor must maintain log-sheets for each vehicle. The supplied vehicles cannot be owned by any Railway Officer/staff or their family members and must be used exclusively for Central Railway, bearing a ''Govt of India'' sticker. The driver provided must be well-dressed, well-mannered, acquainted with the area, possess a valid original driving license and a live mobile phone connection. The contractor is fully responsible for the safe running of the vehicle, any accidents, and all legal and statutory obligations related to the vehicle and the driver, including minimum wages and insurance. The contractor must submit a list of proposed vehicles with their details with the offer. Monthly bills are to be submitted along with log-sheets for payment, which will be made through EFT. The contract cannot be assigned or sublet.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6277991', '17-06-2025 21:00:00', '17-06-2025 21:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Finance', 'Department Of Financial Services', 'National Housing Bank (nhb)', 'Ihc Lodhi Road New Delhi', 'buycon88.nhbn.dl@gembuyer.in', 'Hiring of Consultants - Milestone/Deliverable Based - Tax Consultant; As per RFP; No; Hybrid(As specified in scope of work)', NULL, '3 Year', '2,00,00,000', '7 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'State Bank of India', '2,00,000', 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, '04-06-2025 16:00:00', 'Through VC', 'The technical specifications for the ''Hiring Of Consultants - Milestone/Deliverable Based - Tax Consultant'' require the consultant to belong to the ''Tax Consultant'' category. The consultant''s profile must be as per the Request for Proposal (RFP) document. There is no requirement for a Proof of Concept (POC). The deployment of consultants or resources will be on a hybrid basis, as specified in the scope of work. There are no additional specifications or ''Addon(s)'' listed.', 'Mukul', 'New delhi', 'This GeM bid (GEM/2025/B/6277991) issued by the National Housing Bank (NHB), under the Ministry of Finance, is for the appointment of a Tax Consultancy Firm for a 3-year contract period. The purpose is to procure assistance and services for all direct and indirect tax matters. The bid process follows a two-packet system and will be evaluated based on the Quality & Cost Based Selection (QCBS) method with a 70:30 weightage for technical and financial scores respectively. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum of 7 years of experience (5 years for Startups & MSEs), an average annual turnover of 200 Lakhs (1 crore for Startups & MSEs) for the last three years, and a physical office in Delhi/NCR. Bidders are required to submit an Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of 200,000 INR. The contract is renewable annually, subject to a satisfactory performance review. The scope of work is extensive, covering all aspects of direct and indirect taxation, including but not limited to, vetting of advance tax, filing of returns, assistance in tax proceedings and appeals, TDS and GST compliance, international taxation advisory, and providing regular updates and training on tax laws. The successful bidder will be required to sign a Service Level Agreement and a Pre-Contract Integrity Pact to ensure adherence to performance and ethical standards.', 'The work is considered successfully completed upon the faithful and satisfactory execution of all assignments as per the detailed Scope of Work and the Service Level Agreement (SLA). Key success criteria from the tender issuer''s perspective include: performing all services with due diligence, efficiency, and economy in accordance with generally accepted professional standards; ensuring the time and quality of the service, which are the essence of the contract; safeguarding the bank''s legitimate interests and acting as faithful advisers in all matters. Successful completion also means avoiding any negligence, lapse, error, or breach of contract that could lead to penalties, pecuniary loss for the Bank, or the invocation of the Performance Bank Guarantee. The contract''s annual renewal is contingent upon a satisfactory performance review, which serves as a periodic measure of success. The ultimate success is the complete fulfillment of all contractual terms and obligations for the entire duration.', 'The selected tax consultancy firm will be responsible for verifying all types of taxes payable by the Bank and finalizing tax components for all financial transactions. The scope of work includes: Vetting of Advance Tax, Deferred Tax Asset (DTA)/Deferred Tax Liability (DTL) computation on a quarterly/half-yearly/annual basis. Preparation, checking, scrutinizing, and filing of income tax returns, including revised returns. Assisting in direct and indirect tax proceedings, which involves preparing details for submission and appearing before tax authorities. Handling Assessment/Re-assessment proceedings, drafting and filing of appeals, refund claims, and appearing before appellate authorities. Following up with tax authorities and preparing quarterly status reports on direct and indirect taxes. Furnishing opinions on day-to-day tax matters and queries from various departments. Updating the Bank on amendments in tax laws, rules, and regulations, and providing guidance on their applicability. Guiding the Bank on existing and future tax laws and assisting in policy making. Providing services for tax planning and assessing the impact of Indian Accounting Standard (Ind-AS). Issuing necessary certificates under the Income Tax Act 1961. Calculating and verifying Tax Deducted at Source (TDS) for contractors, consultants, rent, and other payments; computing monthly TDS; and verifying TDS for employee salaries (Form 16). Filing quarterly TDS returns and verifying Form 16A. Managing GST compliance, including calculation/verification of monthly GST liability, utilization of Input Tax Credit, preparation and filing of GST returns, and handling TDS under GST. This also involves managing the Invoice Management System, CENVAT/Input Tax credit availment, and providing guidance on GST vouchers/invoices. The firm will also advise on accounting issues, provide opinions on audit queries, advise on international taxation (including DTAA certificates like FORM-15CB), check tax computation for retiring employees, appear for show cause notices, prepare Statement of Financial Transactions (SFT), certify ECB returns, ensure state-level tax compliances, assist in professional tax matters and ICDS compliance. The firm must meet all tax compliance requirements, provide quarterly certification, offer training to Bank staff, prepare and update a tax compliance booklet for NHB, finalize Form 16 & 12B, calculate tax on arrears and new perquisites, and handle any other tax-related references from the Bank. The scope covers existing tax laws and any similar laws introduced in the future.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6278289', '17-06-2025 20:00:00', '17-06-2025 20:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Army', '***********', 'towering.tenth@nic.in', 'Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; Outstation; 250Kms/ 20Hrs, Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium SUV; Outstation; 250kms x 20 hrs', NULL, '10 Months 4 Day', '5,00,000', '2 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), OEM Authorization Certificate, Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'Yes', '50% Lowest Priced Technically Qualified Bidders', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '2,48,475', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The tender outlines technical specifications for two categories of short-term cab and taxi hiring services. The first category is for an SUV, with specified models being Mahindra Scorpio, Mahindra XUV 500, and Mahindra Bolero. This service is for outstation use, with a usage variant of 250Kms/20Hrs, requires a Non-A/C vehicle, and is intended for operation in Hilly Areas. The vehicle model year should be 2023, 2024, or 2025, with mileage up to 50,000 Kms. The second category is for a Premium SUV, with specified models including Toyota Innova, Honda CR-V, and Toyota Innova Crysta. This service is also for outstation use with a usage variant of 250kms x 20 hrs and for operation in Hilly Areas, but requires an A/C vehicle. The model year and mileage requirements are the same as the standard SUV (2023, 2024, or 2025, and up to 50,000 Kms). For both categories, any fuel type is acceptable, and the trip type is specified as One Way.', '***********', 'North Sikkim', 'This bid, number GEM/2025/B/6278289 issued by the Indian Army, Ministry of Defence, is for the procurement of Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services. The specific requirements are for two types of vehicles: SUV and Premium SUV, both for outstation use with a 250Kms/20Hrs package. The contract period is 10 months and 4 days. The bid is a Two Packet type with a total estimated value of 248475. Financial prerequisites for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 5 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 2 years of past experience in similar services, though exemptions are available for MSEs and Startups. A Reverse Auction will be enabled for the 50% lowest priced technically qualified bidders. The consignee is located in North Sikkim, requiring 31 SUVs and 5 Premium SUVs. Key buyer-added conditions include the service provider having an office in the state of the consignee, the seller bearing all costs for accidents, insurance, and taxes (including tolls), and vehicles being subject to inspection and rejection by the buyer if they do not meet qualitative standards. Vehicles must be equipped with specific fitments like star plates and a fire extinguisher. The buyer retains an option to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 50%.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed when the service provider consistently supplies the specified number and type of vehicles (SUV and Premium SUV) that fully conform to the technical specifications and qualitative standards approved by the Buyer. Success is contingent on the vehicles passing inspection by the consignee or their authorized representative at any time before or during their use. The provider must immediately comply with any instructions given during inspection. A critical success factor is the ability to replace any rejected vehicle at once, at the seller''s own risk and expense, without causing delays. The work is successfully performed if the services are rendered for the required duration without any failure that necessitates the buyer arranging for alternative transport. Essentially, success is defined by the uninterrupted provision of compliant, approved, and reliable vehicle hiring services as per the contract''s terms and the satisfaction of the end-user/officer.', 'The scope of work involves the provision of short-term cab and taxi hiring services for the Indian Army in North Sikkim. The contractor is required to supply a total of 36 vehicles: 31 units of SUV-type vehicles (Mahindra Scorpio, Mahindra XUV 500, or Mahindra Bolero) and 5 units of Premium SUV-type vehicles (Toyota Innova, Honda CR-V, or Toyota Innova Crysta). All vehicles must be from the model years 2023, 2024, or 2025 with a maximum of 50,000 Kms travelled. The service is for outstation usage with a 250Kms/20Hrs package, operating in Hilly Areas. The SUVs are required to be Non-A/C, while the Premium SUVs must be A/C equipped. The service provider''s responsibilities include ensuring all vehicles are commercially registered, fully insured, and have all taxes and permits paid, including inner line permits for drivers operating in protected areas. The provider must bear all operational costs including fuel, maintenance, lubricants, toll taxes, and entry taxes. Vehicles must be fitted with an ''ON MILITARY DUTY'' board when in use, along with a star plate on the front and rear, a flag rod, and a fire extinguisher. The service provider must also maintain a dedicated toll-free number for service support and have a physical office located in the state of the consignee. The provider is fully liable for any accidents or damages and must indemnify the Government against any claims.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6278592', '17-06-2025 20:00:00', '17-06-2025 20:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Army', NULL, 'towering.tenth@nic.in', 'Bus Hiring Service - Short Term - Outstation; 16-18; Non Deluxe (NDX); 250', NULL, '10 Months 4 Day', NULL, '2 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), OEM Authorization Certificate, OEM Annual Turnover *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'Yes', '50% Lowest Priced Technically Qualified Bidders', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '4,50,780', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service are categorized under ''Core''. The ''Type of Service'' required is Outstation. The ''Vehicle Seating Capacity'' should be 16-18. The ''Comfort Category'' is specified as Non Deluxe (NDX). The ''Per Days KM Usage'' is 250, and the ''Per Days Hr Usage'' is 16. The vehicle''s ''Fuel Type'' must be Diesel, and the ''Years of Vehicle Model'' is required to be 2023. There are no specifications listed under the Addon section.', NULL, 'North sikkim', 'This is a bid document (GEM/2025/B/6278592) issued by the Indian Army, Ministry of Defence, for a ''Bus Hiring Service - Short Term - Outstation; 16-18; Non Deluxe (NDX); 250''. The bid end date is 17-06-2025, with an offer validity of 180 days. The total contract period is 10 months and 4 days, with a requirement of 2 years of past experience, for which exemptions are provided for MSEs and Startups. The estimated bid value is 450780. The selection will be through a two-packet bid system followed by a reverse auction for the 50% lowest priced technically qualified bidders. No EMD or ePBG is required. The requirement is for 22 buses in North Sikkim. Key conditions include the bidder being financially sound, not subcontracting without prior consent, and the service provider having an office in the state of the consignee. The provider must also offer dedicated service support via a toll-free number and an escalation matrix. A crucial payment term mandates the service provider to pay salaries to their staff before claiming payment from the buyer. The successful bidder is required to submit a Performance Security.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be deemed successfully completed upon the fulfillment of several conditions. The primary criterion is the due performance of the contract, meaning the seller must provide the bus hiring service exactly as per the agreed technical specifications, quantity, and location. The seller is held liable and responsible for this performance. A critical condition for payment, and thus success, is that the Service Provider must pay salaries and wages to their contracted staff first and then claim payment from the buyer, providing statutory documents (PF, ESIC) and bank statements as proof. The successful bidder must also submit the required Performance Security after the award of the contract, which serves as a guarantee of performance. Finally, the provider must maintain the required service and support infrastructure, including a local office, a dedicated toll-free number, and an escalation matrix, for the duration of the service.', 'The scope of work is to provide a ''Bus Hiring Service - Short Term - Outstation''. The service entails supplying 22 buses to be deployed in North Sikkim. The service is specifically required for 1 day during the overall contract period. Each bus provided must adhere to the following technical specifications: Type of Service must be Outstation with a Vehicle Seating Capacity of 16-18. The Comfort Category is Non-Deluxe (NDX) with a Per Days Usage of 250 KM and 16 hours. The vehicles must be of the 2023 model and operate on Diesel fuel. Additionally, the scope includes service and support requirements, where the Service Provider must have an office located in the state of the consignee, provide a dedicated/toll-free telephone number for service support, and an Escalation Matrix of telephone numbers for service-related issues.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6278645', '17-06-2025 18:00:00', '17-06-2025 18:30:00', '45 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'East Coast Railway', 'Office Of Pcmm', 'srdme_sbp@sbp.railnet.gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of one AC Road Vehicle Inova Crysta or equivalent for official use of ADRM East Coast Railway at Sambalpur for a period of three years', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services', '3 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '2,64,12,492', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '52,830', NULL, 5, 38, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for this service require the hiring of one AC Road Vehicle, specifically an Inova Crysta or an equivalent model, intended for the official use of the ADRM East Coast Railway at Sambalpur for a contract period of three years. The service must maintain full compliance with all regulatory and statutory requirements. Furthermore, the service must adhere completely to the terms outlined in the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and the Service Level Agreement (SLA). No addons or additional specification documents are listed for this procurement.', 'Manish Kumar Sinha Roy', 'Sambalpur', 'This GeM bid (GEM/2025/B/6278645), issued by the East Coast Railway, Ministry of Railways, is for a custom service contract for the hiring of one AC road vehicle, an Inova Crysta or equivalent, for the official use of the ADRM at Sambalpur. The contract period is for three years with an estimated bid value of Rs. 26,41,249.2. Key financial requirements include an EMD of Rs. 52,830 and an e-Performance Bank Guarantee of 5% for a duration of 38 months. Bidders must meet minimum eligibility criteria, including having completed one similar single service contract for at least 35% of the advertised bid value within the last three financial years. A ''similar service'' is defined as the supply of light passenger vehicles to Government, Semi-Government, PSUs, or Corporations. Additionally, bidders must demonstrate an aggregate financial turnover of at least 1.5 times the bid value and have access to liquid assets equivalent to 5% of the bid value. The scope of work mandates the provision of a commercially registered vehicle, not more than two years old, available 24/7 with a driver. The successful contractor will be responsible for all operational costs, including fuel, maintenance, and driver''s salary. Payments will be made on a monthly basis, with reimbursements for fuel and toll charges as per the specified norms. The contract is governed by the Indian Railway General Conditions of Contract for Services, January 2018, and includes specific penalty clauses for non-performance and service deficiencies.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed, the contractor must consistently adhere to all contractual obligations throughout the three-year period. The primary criteria for success from the tender issuer''s perspective include: the continuous, uninterrupted 24/7/365 availability of the specified vehicle (Air-conditioned Toyota Innova Crysta or similar, not more than two years old) and a qualified driver. The vehicle must be available immediately upon demand at any time. In the event of a breakdown, a replacement vehicle of the same or higher specification must be arranged promptly. The vehicle must be maintained in an immaculately neat, clean, and serviceable condition, both internally and externally, with the air-conditioning system fully functional at all times. The provided driver must be courteous, always dressed in a neat and clean white uniform, and equipped with a mobile phone for constant availability. Accurate and timely submission of monthly bills and the maintenance of a signed log register for all trips are mandatory. Final success is marked by the completion of the service period without termination, the satisfactory passing of the final bill based on a ''No Claims Certificate'' from the contractor, and the subsequent issuance of a ''Completion Certificate'' by the competent authority.', 'The scope of work requires the tenderer to provide one road-worthy, multi-utility, air-conditioned four-wheeled vehicle of the ''Light motor vehicle'' category (Toyota Innova Crysta or Similar). The vehicle must not be more than two years old as on the closing date of the tender and must be registered as a commercial vehicle. The work involves deputing the vehicle for the official use of the Addl. Divisional Railway Manager, Sambalpur, on a round-the-clock (24 hours a day, 365 days a year) basis. The service area includes the jurisdiction of East Coast Railway and locations outside it, including engagement at abnormal hours for attending railway accidents and emergencies. The contractor must supply a replacement vehicle of the same or equivalent type in case of breakdown. The vehicle will run approximately 2000 Kms per month, with payment made against the actual kilometer earning. The contractor is responsible for providing courteous drivers in neat and clean white uniforms, equipped with mobile phones to ensure round-the-clock availability, and must abide by all labor laws. The contractor is solely responsible for all maintenance, servicing, safe running of the vehicle, and must indemnify the Railway against any loss, damage, or accident claims. The vehicle must be equipped with safety items like a fire extinguisher and a first-aid box. All operational costs, including Fuel & Lubricant, maintenance/repair charges, driver''s salary, Road Tax, and Toll Tax, are to be borne by the contractor. A detailed log of kilometers earned shall be maintained daily and signed by the designated authority.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6278785', '17-06-2025 18:00:00', '17-06-2025 18:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Home Affairs', 'Central Armed Police Forces', 'Border Security Force (bsf)', '12 Bn Bsf', 'sreejith112@bsf.nic.in', 'Hiring of Boats - ENGINE FITTED COUNTRY BOAT (EFCB); Less than 5 years; Without Air-Conditioning; 7-10 Persons; 50; Jet Drive / Jet Propulsion; Wood; Repair kit, Rescue Life Jackets, Lifebuoys, Fire Extinguisher, First Aid Box, Raincoat Gum Boot; Ser..', NULL, '10 Months 6 Day', '15,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),OEM Authorization Certificate,OEM Annual Turnover,Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '5 Days', NULL, '30,00,610', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '90,018', 'Yes', 3, 14, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the hiring of boats require an ENGINE FITTED COUNTRY BOAT (EFCB) that is less than 5 years old and made of wood, without an air-conditioned closed cabin. The boat should have a seating capacity for 7-10 persons and an accessory carrying capacity of 50 Kilos. It must be powered by a Jet Drive / Jet Propulsion engine of 5-10 HP, with a draft of 3, a weight of 1, and be capable of a speed of 8 knots. The dimensions are specified as 24 to 30 feet in length and 6 to 8 feet in width. The service provider is responsible for providing fuel. Each boat must be equipped with essential life-saving and fire-fighting accessories, including a Repair kit, Rescue Life Jackets, Lifebuoys, Fire Extinguisher, First Aid Box, Raincoat, and Gum Boot. The area of operation and delivery location is 12 BN BSF NARAYANPUR MALDA, with an estimated travel distance of 10 per day. Ration is required, and fuel charges are included if the service provider supplies the fuel.', 'Sreejith P R', 'Malda', 'This bid, number GEM/2025/Β/6278785, is for the ''Hiring of Boats - ENGINE FITTED COUNTRY BOAT (EFCB)'' for the Border Security Force (BSF), specifically the 12 Bn Bsf under the Ministry of Home Affairs. The contract period is for 10 months and 6 days. The estimated bid value is 3,000,610 INR, with a required EMD of 90,018 INR. The tender is a Two Packet Bid with a Reverse Auction enabled. Key requirements for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 15 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services, with exemptions available for MSEs and Startups. The scope involves providing 11 EFCBs, less than 5 years old, with specific dimensions, a 5-10 HP jet propulsion engine, and a capacity for 7-10 persons. The service provider is responsible for fuel, maintenance, repair, and salaries of the boatmen. The boats are to be deployed at 12 BN BSF NARAYANPUR, MALDA (W.B.) for a total of 304 operation days. The tender includes strict conditions regarding personnel verification, penalties for defective boats and absent boatmen, and security protocols, including a prohibition on passing sensitive information.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of several key criteria. Primarily, the contractor must provide and maintain 11 ENGINE FITTED COUNTRY BOATs (EFCBs) that consistently meet all technical specifications for the entire contract duration of 304 operational days without any unauthorized downtime. This includes ensuring the boats are fully operational, properly equipped with all specified life-saving and safety gear, and their fitness is maintained as per periodic checks by a board of officers. Successful completion also hinges on the contractor''s adherence to all operational and administrative requirements, such as deploying police-verified boatmen who meet the age and residency criteria, and ensuring boats are available for rotation between locations as directed. Furthermore, the contractor must strictly comply with all security protocols, with no instances of information leakage. Finally, the contractor must fulfill all financial obligations, including the timely submission of the Performance Security post-award and ensuring prompt payment of wages to their staff, as this is a prerequisite for claiming payment from the buyer. The absence of penalties related to defective equipment, personnel absence, or security breaches will be a key indicator of successful contract execution.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring and operation of 11 ENGINE FITTED COUNTRY BOATs (EFCB) for the Border Security Force for a contract period of 10 months and 6 days (304 operational days). The boats must be less than 5 years old, made of wood, and equipped with a 5-10 HP Jet Drive / Jet Propulsion engine. Each boat must have a seating capacity of 7-10 persons, a carrying capacity of 50 kg for accessories, and be capable of a speed of 8 knots. The dimensions should be 24-30 FT in length and 6-8 FT in width. The service provider is responsible for supplying the boats fully equipped with a Repair kit, Rescue Life Jackets, Lifebuoys, Fire Extinguisher, First Aid Box, Raincoat, Gum Boot, and a Sand box. The provider must also supply qualified boatmen who are a minimum of 18 years of age, residents from at least 10 Kms outside the deployment area, and have undergone character and police verification. The provider is fully responsible for the fuel (POL), repair, maintenance, insurance of the boats, and the daily wages of the boatmen. The area of operation is 12 BN BSF NARAYANPUR MALDA, and the provider must be prepared to rotate or shift the boats and boatmen between different BOPs as per operational requirements. The provider is also liable for any incidents or third-party claims and must submit a bond to that effect.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6280084', '17-06-2025 17:00:00', '17-06-2025 17:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Defence Production', 'Armoured Vehicles Nigam Limited', '***********', 'kvijayakumar@ord.gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of Non AC 07 Seater Utility Vehicle of Tariff 24Hrs and 100 Kms per day per vehicle on regular basis Qty 1825 Vehicle Days', 'Vehicle Hiring Service - Per Vehicle-Days basis', '1 Year', NULL, '1 Year', 'Yes', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '56,71,142', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '1,70,134', NULL, 3, 14, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require the hiring of a Non-AC 07 Seater Utility Vehicle based on a tariff for 24 hours and 100 Kms per day per vehicle, provided on a regular basis. The total quantity required is 1825 Vehicle Days. The service must ensure full Regulatory and Statutory Compliance and must also be in compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA). No add-on services are specified.', '***********', 'Tiruvallur', 'This bid, number GEM/2025/B/6280084, is for a custom service for the hiring of Non-AC 07 Seater Utility Vehicles for Armoured Vehicles Nigam Limited, under the Ministry of Defence. The contract period is for one year, with a total requirement of 1825 vehicle days. The estimated bid value is 5,671,142, with a required EMD of 170,134 and an ePBG of 3% for 14 months. The bid is a two-packet type and requires bidders to have at least one year of past experience in similar services, though MSEs are exempt from this criterion. Evaluation will be conducted on a total value basis. Key buyer-added conditions include a 25% option clause, allowing the buyer to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration, and a requirement for bidders to quote a single lumpsum rate for the total 1825 vehicle days, inclusive of all levies. The beneficiary for the service is the Heavy Vehicles Factory (HVF) in Avadi, Chennai.', 'The work will be considered successfully completed upon the consistent and uninterrupted provision of the ''Hiring of Non AC 07 Seater Utility Vehicle'' service for the entire contract period of one year, totaling 1825 Vehicle Days. Success is contingent on the service provider''s strict adherence to the specified tariff of 24 hours and 100 Kms per day per vehicle. Furthermore, the provider must ensure and maintain full compliance with all regulatory and statutory requirements for the vehicles and operations. The definitive measure of success is the complete fulfillment of all obligations outlined in the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and the Service Level Agreement (SLA).', 'The scope of work entails providing ''Hiring of Non AC 07 Seater Utility Vehicle'' services on a regular basis for a contract period of one year. The total service quantum is specified as 1825 Vehicle Days. The service is to be provided on a tariff basis covering 24 hours of availability and 100 kilometers of usage per day for each vehicle. The service provider is responsible for ensuring that all vehicles and operations are in full compliance with all regulatory and statutory norms. The scope also mandates adherence to all applicable labor laws as specified in the bid document. The bidder is required to quote a single lump-sum rate for the entire 1825 Vehicle Days, which must be inclusive of all applicable levies.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6280366', '17-06-2025 18:00:00', '17-06-2025 18:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Education', 'Department Of Higher Education', 'Delhi University', 'Indira Gandhi Institute Of Physical Education & Sports Sciences', 'buyer1.igipess.delhi@gembuyer.in', 'Hiring of Sanitation Service - Sweeper; 6; All Areas; All Areas; Daily; 2', NULL, '2 Year', '25,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '50,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Bank Of Baroda', '2,50,000', NULL, 5, 26, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the ''Hiring of Sanitation Service'' require Sweeper as the category of resource, working 6 days a week across all designated areas. The cleaning cycle is daily, with a frequency of 2 times per day. The buyer is responsible for providing consumables, equipment, and cleaning agents. The service provider is responsible for providing the necessary machineries. For addons, it is specified that consumables, equipment, cleaning agents, and machineries to be provided by the service provider are not applicable (NA). Further detailed specifications outline the areas to be swept at regular intervals. The total plot area is 23459.54 sqm. Specific cleaning frequencies are provided for various sections including the Basement (Gym - Once Per Day), Ground Floor (covering classrooms, corridors, hall, labs, offices, toilets, etc., with frequencies ranging from Once to Thrice Per Day), First Floor (covering similar areas with frequencies from Once to Thrice per Day), Second Floor (also covering corridors, classrooms, toilets, etc., with frequencies of Once to Twice Per Day), and the Third Floor Open Area (Roof) to be cleaned once per fortnight. Additionally, walls with tile work are to be cleaned, including Varandah/Corridors (Once Per Day), rooms with wall tiles (Once Per Fortnight), and Glass Walls/Window pans (Once Per Fortnight).', 'Lalit Sharma', 'New delhi', 'This is a bid invitation (Bid Number: GEM/2025/B/6280366, Dated: 27-05-2025) issued by the Indira Gandhi Institute Of Physical Education & Sports Sciences, Delhi University, under the Ministry of Education for the ''Hiring of Sanitation Service - Sweeper''. The contract period is for 2 years with a bid offer validity of 180 days from the bid end date of 17-06-2025. The estimated bid value is 50,00,000. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 25 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. The bid is a two-packet system, and evaluation will be on a total value basis. An EMD amount of 2,50,000 is required, and a Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 5.00% is mandated for a duration of 26 months. The service requires the deployment of 8 resources to cover an approximate area of 2,52,510 sq. ft. in Vikaspuri, New Delhi, with a specified minimum monthly wage of 21,006 per resource.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following criteria: The consistent provision of sanitation services by deploying the stipulated 8 sweepers for 6 days a week for the entire contract period. All areas detailed in the scope of work, including various floors, rooms, open areas, and walls, must be cleaned according to the specified frequencies (ranging from thrice per day to once per fortnight). The service provider must supply and maintain the required machinery, specifically one floor cleaning machine. The service must be executed in full compliance with the terms of the Bid document, the Service Level Agreement, and all applicable laws, particularly labor laws such as The Minimum Wages Act, 1948. Any non-compliance will be treated as a breach of contract.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring of sanitation services, specifically for 8 sweepers, to perform cleaning duties 6 days a week. The service provider is required to supply necessary machinery, including one floor cleaning machine, while the buyer will provide consumables and cleaning agents. The cleaning activities are to be carried out across a total plot area of 23459.54 sqm, with detailed frequencies for different zones. Basement: Gym (Once Per Day). Ground Floor: Areas like Classrooms, Conference Room, Multipurpose Hall, Labs, Office/Library, Parking, Passage, Record Room are to be cleaned Once Per Day; Corridor and Staircase are Twice Per Day; Reception Area and Toilets are Thrice Per Day. First Floor: Classrooms, Conference room, Labs, Porta Cabins are Once Per Day; Corridor and Staircase are Twice Per Day; Toilet is Thrice per Day. Second Floor: Shed Area and Open Area are Once Per Day; Corridor, Classrooms and Staircase are Twice Per Day; Toilets are Thrice Per Day. Third Floor: Open Area (Roof) is to be cleaned Once per fortnight. Walls with Tile work: Varandah/Corridors where wall tiles are Installed (598.78 sqm) to be cleaned Once Per Day; Room where wall tiles are Installed (1769.58) and Glass Walls / Window pans are to be cleaned Once Per Fortnight.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6280682', '17-06-2025 19:00:00', '17-06-2025 19:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Home Affairs', 'Central Armed Police Forces', 'Border Security Force (bsf)', '71 Bn Bsf Baishnabnagar West Bengal', 'arvindnarayan.9@bsf.nic.in', 'Hiring of Boats - Country Boat; Less than 500; Inboard; Wood; Repair kit, Rescue Blanket, First Aid Box, Safety Hand Lantern', NULL, '1 Year 10 Months 4 Day', '38,00,000', '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Ce Certificate, OEM Annual Turnover, Additi (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (R ATC)', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '1,21,70,560', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '3,65,116', NULL, 3, 14, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications outline the requirements for a Country Boat to be hired. The boat must be less than 5 years old, made of wood, and feature an inboard engine. It is required to have a seating capacity for 7-10 persons and a carrying capacity of 500 kilos for accessories, without any air-conditioning facility. The boat''s dimensions should be a width of 8 to 10 feet, a depth of 3 to 3.5 feet, a length of over 20 feet, and a draft of 2.2 feet. The engine power is specified as 10 to 24 hrs, with a speed of 2 kms per hour and a weight of 1 to 2. The service provider is responsible for supplying fuel and providing essential life-saving and fire-fighting accessories, including a repair kit, rescue life jackets, lifebuoys, and a fire extinguisher. Ration is required, and the service provider must cover fuel charges. The area of operation, delivery, and re-delivery is the 71 Bn BSF Border Area.', 'Arvind Narayan', 'Baishnabnagar', 'This bid document, issued by the 71 Bn BSF Baishnabnagar West Bengal under the Ministry of Home Affairs, is for the hiring of 32 Engine Fitted Country Boats (EFCBs). The contract period is 1 year, 10 months, and 4 days, with a bid offer validity of 180 days from the bid end date of 17-06-2025. The estimated bid value is 12,170,560. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 38 Lakhs over the last three years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. Key documents required include experience criteria, bidder turnover certificates, and OEM annual turnover. The scope of work involves deploying 32 boats with one boatman and POL (Petroleum, Oil, and Lubricants) per boat across 12 different Border Outposts (BOPs) primarily for the period of 01.04.2025 to 31.03.2026. The document outlines detailed technical specifications for the boats, eligibility and qualification criteria for bidders, and extensive terms and conditions, including clauses on penalties, performance security, arbitration, and termination of the contract. It also specifies strict operational protocols for the boatmen and penalties for non-compliance, such as equipment failure or security breaches.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the continuous and uninterrupted provision of 32 fully functional boats, each with a designated boatman and required POL, for the entire contract period at the specified locations. Success is contingent on the vendor''s strict adherence to all technical specifications, including boat condition, age, and onboard safety equipment. The vendor must provide timely servicing and rectification of defects within 15 days, and in case of a non-functional boat, arrange an immediate alternative to avoid operational disruption. Adherence to all operational and security protocols, including submission of verified boatmen details, is mandatory. The contract is deemed successfully fulfilled upon completion of the full term without any breaches leading to termination, with all monthly service obligations met, and after the final settlement of payments, including the deduction of any penalties incurred for downtime, defects, or other non-compliances.', 'The scope of work is to hire a total of 32 Engine Fitted Country Boats (EFCBs), with each boat being provided with POL (Petroleum, Oil, and Lubricants) and one boatman. The deployment is scheduled across twelve designated BOPs/places under the 71 Bn BSF: Khandua (2), Kathakali (2), Boyraghat (5), Bhagirathi (2), Pirojpur (1), Noorpur (2), Chandnichak (3), Chapghati (2), Bajitpur (3), Nimtita (3), Sovapur TP (5), and Daulatpur (2). The primary duration for the service is from 01.04.2025 to 31.03.2026, with a shorter period for Daulatpur (01.07.2025 to 30.09.2025). The vendor''s responsibilities include covering all costs for the boatman''s salary and POL, for which BSF will not provide boarding or lodging. The vendor is entirely responsible for the repair, maintenance, and any damage or loss to the boats, and must maintain a reserve POL quota for 30 hours on each boat. Each boat must be equipped with four life jackets and two life buoys. The BSF retains the right to rotate boats and boatmen between BOPs as per operational needs. The seller must also adhere to administrative requirements, such as uploading scanned GST invoices and payment confirmations to the GeM Portal.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6280808', '18-06-2025 18:00:00', '18-06-2025 18:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Civil Aviation', 'Airports Authority Of India (aai)', 'Airports Authority Of India', 'Airports Authority Of India- Surat', 'buycon220.aai.gj@gembuyer.in', 'Hiring of Air Conditioners and Desert Coolers - Monthly Based - Desert Cooler; Plastic Body Cooler', NULL, '3 Years 1 Day', '5,00,000', '7 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '3 Days', NULL, '35,01,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '1,05,030', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, 'MSE Purchase Preference rules', 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the required Desert Coolers are detailed across two tables. The coolers must be Desert Coolers with a plastic or ABS body, floor-mounted with a stand, and not more than one year old from the date of contract award. They need to provide cooling functions with a nominal air capacity of 5000 CuM/Hr or a suitable capacity to meet site requirements. The power supply required is 230 volts +/- 10%, 50 Hz, single-phase AC. Key features include a sump tank capacity of at least 100 liters (or as suitable for the 5000 nominal capacity), provision for castor wheels, a drain hole for each cooler, and Honey Comb filter pads. The coolers must be equipped with a Fan On/Off Switch, a Speed Regulator Switch, a Pump Set On/Off Switch, and vertical/horizontal auto swing. Installation and manpower are required, but a remote control and transformer are not applicable. The fan size must be suitable for 5000cm/h, and the blade material should be as per OEM specifications.', 'Umesh Kumar Singh', 'Surat', 'The tender, identified by Bid Number GEM/2025/B/6280808, is issued by the Airports Authority of India (AAI), Ministry of Civil Aviation, for the "Hiring of Dessert Air cooler for CISF accommodation at Surat International Airport, Surat (for Years 2025-28)". The contract period is for 3 years and 1 day, with an estimated bid value of ₹35,01,000. The scope involves the hiring of 80 plastic body desert coolers on a monthly basis. The tender follows a Two Packet Bid system with a bid offer validity of 90 days from the bid end date of 18-06-2025. Bidders are required to have a minimum of 7 years of past experience in similar services, an average annual turnover of at least ₹5 Lakhs for the last three years, and a minimum net worth of ₹1.75 Lakh. The work involves providing and maintaining the coolers, including installation, manpower, and all necessary services to ensure they are fully operational. The contract requires an Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of ₹1,05,030. The work is to be executed at various CISF accommodations and offices at Surat Airport.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of several key criteria. Primarily, the entire system must be satisfactorily commissioned and handed over officially to the Engineer-in-Charge, who will record the certified date of completion. This certification is contingent upon a final inspection confirming that there are no defects in the work. Furthermore, the contractor must have removed all surplus materials, rubbish, debris, and any temporary structures from the site, leaving the premises clean. The contractor is also required to submit all necessary documentation, including completion plans, catalogues of all equipment, and maintenance manuals. Only after all these conditions are met, and the work has been measured by the Engineer-in-Charge, will a final certificate of completion be issued, marking the successful completion of the work for each year and initiating the defect liability period. Finally, at the closing of the contract, the contractor is responsible for handing the site back to AAI in a good working condition.', 'The scope of work is for the provision of 80 Desert Coolers, with a capacity of 5000CM/Hr or suitable, on a hiring basis for various CISF unit locations including accommodation, barracks, and offices at Surat Airport for a period of three years. This is a comprehensive contract that includes the supply, installation, testing, commissioning, loading, unloading, and dismantling of the coolers. The contractor is responsible for all maintenance activities, including inspection, checking, servicing, overhauling, and attending to an unlimited number of breakdown calls to ensure the coolers remain fully serviceable. This includes the supply and replacement of any required consumables, spares, and defective components. The contractor must also provide technical manpower/operators as and when required. All associated costs for installation, such as providing suitable size stands, wire, cables, switches, sockets, transportation, and maintaining a logbook and daily serviceability reports, are included in the contract. The contractor is also required to seal windows with materials like wooden plywood to prevent hot air from entering, at no extra cost. All electrical connections from the provided switchboards to the coolers are also within the contractor''s scope. Any faults must be rectified within 24 hours of being reported. At the end of each summer season (approximately 4 months) and upon contract completion, the contractor must remove all the desert coolers from the site. The safety and security of the coolers are the contractor''s responsibility throughout the contract period.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6281077', '11-06-2025 20:00:00', '11-06-2025 20:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Coal', 'Coal India Limited', 'South Eastern Coalfields Limited', 'Secl Bilaspur Chhattisgarh', 'bijay.pd6515@coalindia.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab and Taxi Hiring Service - Without Fuel - SUV; Mahindra Bolero, Mahindra Scorpio; 2023; 0-25,000 kms; A/C; 12 , Monthly Basis Cab and Taxi Hiring Service - Without Fuel - SUV; Mahindra Scorpio, Mahindra Bolero; 2023; 0-25,000 kms; A/C; 12 , Monthly Basis Cab and Taxi Hiring Service - Without Fuel - SUV; Mahindra Bolero, Mahindra Scorpio; 2023; 0-25,000 kms; A/C; 16', NULL, '3 Years 1 Day', '24,00,000', '7 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC)', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '7 Days', NULL, '79,71,13,695', 'Item wise evaluation/', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'State Bank of India', '21,97,54,39,89,33,675', NULL, 5, 38, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the required service are detailed across three schedules for the hiring of Monthly Basis Cab and Taxi Services. The Core requirements specify the Vehicle Type as SUV, specifically identifying the Type of car as Mahindra Bolero or Mahindra Scorpio. The Years of Vehicle Model required is 2023 with a Vintage in KM of 0-25,000 kms. All vehicles must be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C). The Engagement Hours per Days vary by schedule: Schedules 1 and 2 require 12 hours per day, while Schedule 3 requires 16 hours per day. Fuel is to be provided by the Buyer in the form of reimbursement to the Service Provider as per actual consumption. A Driver is required for all vehicles. The Type of Terrain is specified as Plain, and the Fuel type of the vehicle must be Diesel. The quantity of vehicles required is 1 for Schedule 1, 2 for Schedule 2, and 1 for Schedule 3.', 'Bijay Prasad', 'Bishrampur', 'This GEM Bid Document (Bid Number: GEM/2025/B/6281077) is issued by the Ministry of Coal, specifically South Eastern Coalfields Limited (SECL), Bishrampur Area, for the hiring of 04 Light Motor Vehicles (SUVs) for daily official work. The contract period is 3 years and 1 day with an estimated bid value of Rs. 79,71,136.95. The work is divided into three schedules: Schedule 1 involves 1 vehicle for Amera OCP (12 hours/day); Schedule 2 involves 2 vehicles for Kumda Sub Area (12 hours/day); and Schedule 3 involves 1 vehicle for Amgaon OCP (16 hours/day). Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 24 Lakhs and 7 years of past experience in similar services. The vehicles must be Mahindra Bolero or Scorpio, model 2023, not older than 2 years from the tender opening date. The bid includes provisions for EMD (Earnest Money Deposit) exemption for MSEs, but EMD is required for others (approx 1.25% of estimated cost). The evaluation method is Item wise. The document outlines strict terms regarding vehicle condition, compliance with GST and labour laws (including CMPF/EPF), and prohibits Joint Ventures for this specific value (under Rs. 2.00 Crores). The price quoted must include rental, driver wages, and taxes, while fuel is reimbursed based on actual running and defined fuel efficiency (11 kmpl or 13 kmpl).', 'From the tender issue perspective, the work will be agreed as successfully completed upon the satisfactory deployment of the required 04 vehicles (SUVs) along with competent drivers for the entire contract duration of 3 years (1096 days) as per the specified schedules. Success is defined by the issuance of a Completion Certificate by the Engineer-in-charge/Designated Officer-in-charge, certifying that the work was executed in every respect in accordance with the contract, including the maintenance of logbooks, adherence to safety norms, uninterrupted service without frequent breakdowns, and full compliance with statutory obligations such as payment of minimum wages, CMPF/EPF contributions, and taxes. The final refund of the Security Deposit is contingent upon this certification.', 'The detailed Scope of Work involves the hiring of 04 numbers of Light Motor Vehicles (LMVs), specifically SUVs (Mahindra Bolero/Scorpio), for the daily official work of different departments of the Bishrampur Area, SECL, for a period of 03 years (1096 days). The work is categorized into three schedules: Schedule 1 requires 1 vehicle for Amera OCP engaged for 12 hours/day with an average running of 140 km/day and fuel efficiency of 11 kmpl. Schedule 2 requires 2 vehicles for Kumda Sub Area engaged for 12 hours/day with an average running of 100 km/day and fuel efficiency of 13 kmpl. Schedule 3 requires 1 vehicle for Amgaon OCP engaged for 16 hours/day with an average running of 140 km/day and fuel efficiency of 11 kmpl. The contractor must deploy vehicles not older than 2 years from the tender opening date. The scope includes providing skilled drivers (1 driver for 12-hour shifts, 2 drivers for 16-hour shifts), ensuring vehicle maintenance, insurance, and paying for consumables like oil and lubricants. The contractor is responsible for all statutory payments including driver wages (Minimum wages + Bonus) and CMPF/EPF. Fuel costs are reimbursed by SECL based on actual running and the specified fuel efficiency. The contractor must also maintain a logbook for mileage and time, provide substitute vehicles in case of breakdowns, and ensure vehicles are equipped with safety features like seat belts and first-aid boxes.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6281374', '17-06-2025 21:00:00', '17-06-2025 21:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Army', '***********', 'anikum.25420@gov.in', 'Bus Hiring Service - Short Term - Outstation; 40-42; Non Deluxe (NDX); 250', NULL, '9 Months 4 Day', '8,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'Yes', '50% Lowest Priced Technically Qualified Bidders', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '4,50,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', NULL, 'Yes', 3, 6, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '10-06-2025 09:00:00', '439 (I) engineer squadron, khasa, amritsar', 'The technical specifications are for an outstation Bus Hiring Service. The required vehicle is a Non-Deluxe (NDX) bus with a seating capacity of 40-42. The vehicle model must be from the year 2022 and should be diesel-fueled. The expected usage is 250 kilometers and 8 hours per day.', '***********', 'Amritsar City', 'This GeM bid document (GEM/2025/B/6281374) issued by the Indian Army, Ministry of Defence, is for a ''Bus Hiring Service - Short Term - Outstation''. The service requires Non-Deluxe (NDX) buses with a 40-42 seating capacity for a contract period of 9 months and 4 days. The estimated bid value is 450,000. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 8 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services, although exemptions are available for MSEs and Startups. The contract involves a two-packet bid system and requires a 3% e-Performance Bank Guarantee for 6 months. The scope of work specifies the hiring of three 42-seater Non-Deluxe buses for the route from Amritsar to Nyoma (Leh) in two lots during July 2025 and September 2025. The document lays down extensive buyer-added terms and conditions, including vehicle specifications (2022 model, clean, no dents, functional amenities like drinking water), driver requirements (valid license, experience in high-altitude terrain, medically fit, verified credentials), and operational protocols (vehicle provision on 72-hour notice, risk and expense clauses for failure to supply, and accident/insurance liabilities). Payment will be strictly based on the actual number of days traveled, with no advance payments, and is subject to the submission of proper documentation like signed Car Diaries and bills.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed, the following criteria must be met from the tender issuer''s perspective:
1. The service provider must furnish a Performance Guarantee of 3% of the contract value within the stipulated time.
2. The specified number of Non-Deluxe, 42-seater buses of the 2022 model must be provided in accordance with the schedule outlined in the contract (one bus for July 2025 and two buses for September 2025).
3. All vehicles must be supplied in excellent, road-worthy condition, meeting all specified requirements such as cleanliness, functional lights, valid pollution certificates, and necessary permits.
4. Vehicles must be provided punctually at the designated time and place upon receiving a demand indent, adhering to the 72-hour standard notice or 12-hour urgent notice period.
5. In the event of a vehicle breakdown, a replacement must be provided within one hour at the service provider''s cost.
6. Drivers provided must be properly licensed, medically fit, well-behaved, and possess adequate experience for driving in high-altitude terrain.
7. The service must be completed without any breach of contract terms, including safety, insurance, and confidentiality obligations.
8. All required documentation, including accurately filled Car Diaries and bills, must be submitted correctly for payment processing after the completion of services. 
9. The contract must be completed for its entire duration without being terminated due to default or failure to perform by the service provider.', 'The scope of work is to provide a Local Purchase Contract for Bus Hiring Service for the Indian Army, specifically for the movement of personnel and goods. The service entails providing Non-Deluxe (NDX) 42-seater buses. 

Key requirements are as follows:
1. Vehicle Details: The buses must be of the 2022 model year, diesel-fueled, and maintained in good condition without dents and with intact windows. They must be equipped with quality cushioned seats, two emergency exits, waterproof overhead luggage carriers, and a 40-liter stainless steel container for drinking water. The vehicles must be properly cleaned inside and out before each duty.

2. Schedule and Route: The requirement is for one bus from 01-Jul-2025 to 31-Jul-2025 and two buses from 01-Sep-2025 to 30-Sep-2025. The designated route is from Amritsar to Nyoma (Leh).

3. Operational Conduct: The service provider must supply vehicles upon receiving indents, typically with a 72-hour notice, which may be reduced to 12 hours for urgent military needs. The quoted rate must be inclusive of all associated costs such as halts, tolls, parking, taxes, and loading/unloading time. The vehicles must display an ''ON MILITARY DUTY'' board when hired.

4. Driver and Vehicle Condition: All vehicles must be registered for commercial use with all taxes paid and possess valid permits. They must be road-worthy and equipped with a serviceable spare wheel, tools, a first aid box, and have all essential components like lights, wipers, and horn in working condition, along with a valid pollution certificate. The drivers must hold a valid license, be medically fit, have their credentials verified, and possess experience in driving in hilly/high-altitude conditions. The provider is responsible for the driver''s rations and bedding.

5. Contingency and Safety: In case of a vehicle breakdown, a replacement must be provided within one hour at the seller''s risk and expense. The provider is responsible for the safe carriage of all personnel and stores and must maintain confidentiality regarding the nature of the duty. The provider must indemnify the government against any claims arising from accidents.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6281614', '18-06-2025 10:00:00', '18-06-2025 10:30:00', '45 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Defence', 'Controller General Of Defence Accounts', '***********', 'ashishagarwal.dad@hub.nic.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of Casual labour', 'Cleaning, Sanitation and Disinfection Service - Outcome Based, Manpower Outsourcing Services - Minimum wage', '1 Year', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', NULL, NULL, 3, 14, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service are detailed in the ''Core'' section. The proposed service is for the ''Hiring of Casual labour'' procured through a custom bid functionality. The service provider must ensure ''Regulatory/ Statutory Compliance of Service'' and also maintain ''Compliance of Service to SOW, STC, SLA etc''. There are no addon specifications mentioned.', '***********', 'New delhi', 'This is a Bid Document (GEM/2025/B/6281614) dated 28-05-2025 issued by the Controller General Of Defence Accounts, under the Ministry of Defence. The tender is for a ''Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of Casual labour'' with a contract period of one year. The bid closing date is 18-06-2025. It is a Two Packet Bid with a total value wise evaluation method. No Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) is required, but an e-Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 3.00% is required for a duration of 14 months. The bid allows for MSE and Startup exemptions for the years of experience criteria. The successful bidder must provide the service in compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), regulatory laws, and other terms. The document also includes an internal sanction order for the hiring of ''01 Semi Skilled Casual Labour for one year'' with a sanctioned value of Rs 3,71,170/-.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer, the work will be deemed successfully completed upon the service provider''s adherence to several key conditions. Primarily, the service must be delivered in full compliance with the defined Scope of Work (SOW), Special Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA). A critical success factor is the mandatory and verifiable compliance with all applicable labour laws, including but not limited to The Minimum Wages Act 1948, The Payment of Wages Act 1936, The Payment of Bonus Act 1965, The Equal Remuneration Act 1976, and The Payment of Gratuity Act 1972. Any deviation or non-compliance will be treated as a breach of contract, indicating a failure to meet the success criteria.', 'The detailed Scope of Work is referenced as a separate document (1748403331.pdf) and is not fully detailed within this file. However, based on the available information, the scope of work entails the ''Hiring of Casual labour''. The ''Sanction for Payment'' annexure specifies the precise requirement as the provision of ''01 Semi Skilled Casual Labour for one year''. The service is to be rendered for the consignee located in NEW DELHI. The provider will be responsible for sourcing, deploying, and managing this labour while ensuring strict adherence to all statutory and regulatory compliances, especially all applicable labour laws as stipulated in the tender.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6283067', '20-06-2025 14:00:00', '20-06-2025 14:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'East Central Railway', 'East Central Railway Hq Hajipur', 'dp.singh66@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium SUV; 2500 Km x 350 hours; Outstation 24*7, Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium SUV; 2500 Km x 350 hours; Outstation, Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium Sedan; 2500 Km x 350 hours; Outstation', NULL, '2 Year', '75,00,000', '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '1,47,11,880', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'State Bank of India', '2,23,560', NULL, 5, 30, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The tender requires two types of vehicles under its technical specifications. The first category is for a Premium SUV, with acceptable models including Toyota Fortuner, Toyota Innova Crysta, and Toyota Hycross. This vehicle is for a usage variant of 2500 Km x 350 hours on an Outstation 24*7 basis. The second category is for a Premium Sedan, with acceptable models being Maruti Suzuki Ciaz, Honda City, and Hyundai Verna, for a usage variant of 2500 Km x 350 hours on an Outstation basis. For both vehicle categories, the specifications are consistent: the vehicle model must not be more than 3 years old, should have travelled up to 25,000 Kms, must have air conditioning, can be of any fuel type, and must operate in both Hilly and Plain areas.', 'Shailendra Kumar', 'Hajipur', 'This bid, number GEM/2025/B/6283067, is issued by the East Central Railway Hq Hajipur, under the Ministry of Railways, for the procurement of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services''. The services are categorized into two types: one Premium SUV (2500 Km x 350 hours; Outstation 24*7) and nine Premium Sedans (2500 Km x 350 hours; Outstation). The contract period is for 2 years. The estimated bid value is INR 14711880, with an EMD amount of 223560 and an ePBG requirement of 5% for 30 months. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 75 Lakhs for the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. Bidders must also have a fleet of owned vehicles equivalent to at least 25% of the demand and a geographic presence in Bihar, Jharkhand & UP. Specific buyer-added conditions include the requirement for vehicles to have 6 airbags, the submission of all vehicle documents within 10 days of contract award, and the provider having an office in the state of the consignee. The evaluation method will be total value wise on a two-packet bid system. The consignee and reporting officer is Shailendra Kumar at the PCE Office, East Central Railway, HQ, Hajipur.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the successful completion of the work is contingent upon several criteria. Firstly, the successful bidder must submit all required documents for the supplied vehicles as per the SLA within 10 days after the award of the contract. Secondly, the provided vehicles must meet the specified safety feature of having 6 airbags. Thirdly, the service provider must ensure the timely arrival of the regular vehicle and provide a substitute vehicle promptly in case of any failure, failing which penalties will be imposed. Fourthly, the services must be rendered as per the requirement of the official without any timing restrictions, and the overall performance must remain satisfactory to avoid an ''UNSATISFACTORY'' rating. Fifthly, the provider must maintain a service office within the state of the consignee and provide a dedicated toll-free number for support. Finally, the successful bidder must furnish the Performance Security in the prescribed format (Account Payee Demand Draft or Fixed Deposit Receipt) within 15 days of the contract award.', 'The scope of work involves providing Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for a contract period of 2 years (24 months) to the East Central Railway HQ, Hajipur. The requirement is for a total of 10 vehicles, split into two categories: 1 Premium SUV and 9 Premium Sedans. Both categories have a usage variant of 2500 kilometers and 350 hours per month for outstation duties, with the SUV service specified as 24*7. The vehicles must not be more than 3 years old, must have travelled up to 25,000 Kms, and must be equipped with air conditioning and 6 airbags. The area of operation includes both Hilly and Plain areas. Acceptable models for the Premium SUV are Toyota Fortuner, Toyota Innova Crysta, or Toyota Hycross. For the Premium Sedan, acceptable models include Maruti Suzuki Ciaz, Honda City, or Hyundai Verna. The service provider is required to own at least 25% of the total vehicles supplied, have a service office in the consignee''s state (Bihar), and provide a dedicated telephone number for support. The service must be flexible, with no timing restrictions, and available as per the requirements of the designated official.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6283451', '17-06-2025 21:00:00', '17-06-2025 21:30:00', '30 Days', 'Ministry Of Finance', 'Department Of Revenue', 'Central Board Of Direct Taxes (cbdt)', 'Income Tax Department, Nashik', 'addlcitr1abd.itax@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 3000 Km x 364 hours; Outstation', NULL, '1 Year', '12,00,000', '2 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '6,30,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require an SUV type vehicle, with specific model options including Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Hyundai Creta, Mahindra Scorpio, or KIA Seltos. The vehicle must be a 2025 or 2024 model with up to 25,000 Kms travelled. The service is for outstation use, with a usage variant of 3000 Km x 364 hours. It must have Air Conditioning (A/C) and will operate in the plains region, with any fuel type being acceptable. Regarding tax details, the Reverse Charge Mechanism (RCM) is applicable. The GST as per RCM is 5%, and an optional RCM is also marked as ''Yes''. No Input Tax Credit (ITC) on GST or GST Cess is available.', 'Sudarshan Bugdimwar', 'Latur', 'This bid, number GEM/2025/B/6283451, is for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for an SUV to be used for 3000 Km x 364 hours for outstation duty. The contract period is for one year. The tender has been issued by the Income Tax Department, Nashik, under the Central Board Of Direct Taxes (cbdt), Ministry of Finance. The bid end date is 17-06-2025, and the estimated bid value is 630,000. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 12 Lakhs over the last three years and two years of past experience in similar services, with no exemptions for MSE or Startups. The evaluation method will be total value wise. The contract requires one vehicle to be provided to the Income Tax Officer in Latur, Maharashtra. The terms and conditions specify that the service provider must have an office in Aurangabad or Latur, the vehicle''s RC book must be in the bidder''s name, and the rate must be all-inclusive covering costs like driver''s salary, fuel, maintenance, and insurance. The provider is responsible for all vehicle-related expenses and must provide a dedicated vehicle and a driver with at least three years of experience. Payments will be made monthly based on a log book, and penalties may be applied for non-compliance. The contract can be terminated by either party with a one-month notice.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following criteria:
1. Provision of a dedicated SUV vehicle and a dedicated driver, meeting all the specified technical requirements (model, year, condition), available round the clock including holidays.
2. The driver must be experienced (minimum three years), trained, licensed, wear a uniform, and adhere to all traffic rules and instructions from the department.
3. Immediate arrangement of a suitable substitute vehicle in case of breakdown or unavailability to ensure uninterrupted service.
4. Accurate and diligent maintenance of a log book detailing daily usage, which must be signed by the designated officer and submitted with the monthly bill.
5. Strict compliance with all instructions issued by the Department and the officer assigned to the vehicle.
6. The service provider must bear all expenses related to the vehicle, including fuel, maintenance, insurance, taxes, and driver''s salary, as part of the all-inclusive monthly charges.
7. Timely payment of salaries and statutory dues to the contracted staff, with documentary evidence submitted to the buyer before claiming payment.
8. Indemnifying the Department against any loss, damage, or third-party claims arising from driver negligence, poor maintenance, or accidents.', 'The scope of work involves providing one SUV vehicle on a monthly hiring basis for a contract period of one year to the Income Tax Department in Latur, Maharashtra. The service provider is required to supply a vehicle of the 2024 or 2025 model year, from a list including Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Hyundai Creta, Mahindra Scorpio, or KIA Seltos, with air conditioning and having run no more than 25,000 kilometers. The service package is for a monthly usage of up to 3000 kilometers and 364 hours, primarily for outstation duties, with a provision to carry forward any unused kilometers. The provider must supply a dedicated, trained, and experienced (minimum 3 years) driver with a valid driving license. The vehicle and driver must be available 24/7, including holidays. The scope includes bearing all operational costs such as driver''s salary, fuel, repairs and maintenance, insurance, vehicle tax, and any other incidental expenses. The service provider is also responsible for maintaining a daily log book for the vehicle''s usage, which will form the basis for monthly payments. In case of a vehicle breakdown, a substitute vehicle must be provided immediately. The provider must indemnify the department against any liabilities arising from the operation of the vehicle.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6284133', '20-06-2025 14:00:00', '20-06-2025 14:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'East Central Railway', 'East Central Railway Hq Hajipur', 'dp.singh66@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2500 KM x 350 hours; Outstation', NULL, '2 Year', '75,00,000', '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '1,48,44,192', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'State Bank of India', '2,24,230', 'Yes', 5, 30, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the required service detail the type of vehicle and its operational parameters. The core requirement is for an SUV vehicle. The acceptable car models include Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Maruti Suzuki XL6, Hyundai Creta, Mahindra Scorpio, and KIA Seltos. The service is for outstation usage with a monthly variant of 2500 KM and 350 hours. The vehicles provided must not be older than 3 years and should have travelled a maximum of 25,000 Kms. The air conditioning requirement is specified as Non-A/C. The area of operation covers both Hilly and Plain areas, and any fuel type is acceptable. No specific add-ons are listed.', 'Shailendra Kumar', 'Hajipur', 'This is a bid for Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for 11 SUV vehicles, operating for 2500 KM x 350 hours per month for outstation duty, with a contract period of 2 years. The bid, with number GEM/2025/B/6284133, is issued by the East Central Railway Hq Hajipur, under the Ministry of Railways. The bid end date is 20-06-2025, with an estimated value of INR 14844192. Key requirements for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 75 Lakhs for the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. There is no exemption for MSE or Startups on experience and turnover criteria. The bid is a Two Packet Bid, and an EMD of INR 224230 is required. A performance security (ePBG) of 5.00% is mandatory for a duration of 30 months. The service provider must have an office in the consignee''s state (Bihar, Jharkhand & UP) and own at least 25% of the vehicle fleet. The vehicles must not be older than 3 years and should be equipped with 6 airbags. The evaluation method is based on the total value. The consignee is Shailendra Kumar at PCE Office, Rail Niketan, East Central Railway, HQ, Hajipur, for a duration of 24 months.', 'The work will be considered successfully completed based on the following criteria from the tender issuer''s perspective: 1. All vehicle documents, as per the details given in the SLA, must be submitted by the successful bidder within 10 days after the award of the contract. 2. Regular and timely arrival of the specified vehicle is mandatory. In case of non-arrival, a substitute vehicle must be provided promptly, failing which the vehicle will be marked absent, leading to payment deductions and potential penalties. 3. The service must be consistently available without any restriction on timing, adhering strictly to the requirements of the concerned official. 4. Maintaining a satisfactory performance record is crucial. Any report of bad performance from a client or user department will result in the bidder''s overall performance being deemed "UNSATISFACTORY". 5. Provision of vehicles with specified higher safety features, specifically with 6 airbags.', 'The scope of work involves providing Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services. The service requires the deployment of 11 SUV-type vehicles. The acceptable vehicle models include Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Maruti Suzuki XL6, Hyundai Creta, Mahindra Scorpio, and KIA Seltos. These vehicles must not be older than 3 years and must have travelled less than 25,000 Kms. Each vehicle is required for outstation service with a monthly usage cap of 2500 KM and 350 hours. The vehicles must be Non-A/C and equipped with 6 airbags for higher safety. The operational area includes both Hilly and Plain terrains, and the geographic presence for the service is required in Bihar, Jharkhand & UP. The service must be available as per the requirement of the officials, with no restrictions on timing. The contract duration is 2 years (24 months). The service provider must have an office in the state of the consignee and provide a dedicated/toll-free number for support. The provider must also submit commercial vehicle papers registered in their company name for at least 25% of the total vehicles to be supplied.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6284586', '20-06-2025 10:00:00', '20-06-2025 10:30:00', '60 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'North Central Railway', 'Ncr', 'pulkit.srivastava29@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - MUV; 1500 km x 320 hours; Outstation 24*7', 'Supply of road vehicles to Central/State Govt, Semi Govt. bodies of Central/State Govt. and Public Sector undertakings on hiring basis', '2 Year', '24,00,000', '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '47,82,360', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '95,700', 'Yes', 5, 26, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require a Multi-Utility Vehicle (MUV). The acceptable types of cars include Mahindra Bolero Camper, Tata Xenon, and Isuzu Dmax. The specified usage variant is 1500 km x 320 hours for an Outstation 24*7 service. The vehicle''s model year should be 2025, 2024, or 2023, with total travel up to 25,000 Kms. It must be a Non-A/C vehicle capable of operating in both Hilly and Plain Areas. Any fuel type is permissible. No specific add-ons are mentioned.', 'Lokesh Pratap Singh', 'Tundla', 'This GeM bid document, number GEM/2025/B/6284586, is for the hiring of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services, specifically a Multi-Utility Vehicle (MUV) for the North Central Railway, Ministry of Railways. The contract period is for 2 years with a bid end date of 20-06-2025. The estimated bid value is 4782360, with an EMD of 95700. The scope involves providing five MUVs for the TRD Depots at Phaphund, Etawah, Tundla, Hathras & Khurja for regular inspection and breakdown attendance. Bidders must meet eligibility criteria including a minimum average annual turnover of 24 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. The evaluation process is a Two Packet Bid system, and bidders will be technically evaluated based on a scoring matrix where a minimum of 60 marks is required to qualify for the financial bid opening. The criteria for technical evaluation include previous work experience, financial turnover, years of operation, and size of the workforce. The bid includes detailed special conditions, a scope of work, and requires bidders to submit several undertakings and certificates, including a declaration that all submitted documents are true and factual.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is considered successfully completed upon the consistent and uninterrupted provision of the specified vehicle and driver service in full compliance with all terms and conditions. This includes ensuring the 24-hour availability of the MUV for up to 1500 km per month, covering all operational costs such as driver, fuel, and maintenance, and adhering to vehicle specifications like age (not more than three years old) and equipment (GPS enabled). Success is formally acknowledged through the monthly certification of work to the satisfaction of the Engineer and the countersigning of bills by the concerned In-charge, which then authorizes payment to the contractor. The proper maintenance of logbooks, adherence to all legal and statutory requirements, and the ability to provide an alternative vehicle during breakdowns are also critical indicators of successful performance.', 'The scope of work is for the "Hiring of Multi utility vehicle (MUV) for TRD Depot Phaphund, Etawah, Tundla, Hathras & Khurja for regular inspection and attending break down under Electrical/Traction Distribution department in Prayagraj Division" for a 24-month period. This entails the supply of a Diesel driven Multi Utility Vehicle (MUV) Dual Crew Cab with a seating arrangement for 5 persons and an open dala. The vehicle is to run up to 1500 Km per month with 24-hour availability for loading Electrical TRD machines, materials, and personnel for day-to-day maintenance, regular inspections, and attending breakdowns within the depot''s jurisdiction and Prayagraj Division. The scope includes all associated costs such as the driver, fuel, lubricants, spares for repairs, and all admissible taxes (octroi, toll tax, etc.). The vehicle must be no more than three years old, capable of running on both pucca and kachcha roads, and must be parked at a nominated Railway premise. It must be equipped with mobile charging, a GPS tracker, and an Android mobile phone with data connectivity for remote instructions. The contractor must ensure the driver has a valid license and all necessary vehicle documents are available at all times. The MUV should be provided with facilities like a fabricated channel on the dala for transporting ladders and TRD equipment, and a GI steel box for emergency tools.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6286198', '19-06-2025 14:00:00', '19-06-2025 14:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Petroleum And Natural Gas', 'Gail India Limited', 'Gail India Limited', 'Noida', 'buycon7.gail.noida@gembuyer.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - TOTAL QUOTED PRICE INCLUDING GST FOR HIRING OF SERVICES FOR HORTICULTURE MAINTENANCE WORKS AT GAIL JUBILEE TOWER AND GAIL VIHAR FOR TWO YEARS AS PER ATTACHED TENDER / ATC AND SOR FORMAT', 'Horticulture Service – Manpower Based Model', '2 Year', '48,00,000', 'Seven (7) years', 'No', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '4 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '2,54,000', 'Yes', 2.5, 25, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '04-06-2025 11:00:00', 'THRU MS TEAMS AS PER LINK PROVIDED IN SECTION-I, CLAUSE NO. 2(F) PAGE NO.7 OF TENDER', 'The technical specifications for the service detail the procurement of horticulture maintenance services for GAIL Jubilee Tower and Gail Vihar for a two-year period through a custom bid. The service requires a total quoted price that includes GST and must be formatted as per the attached tender, ATC, and SOR documents. It is mandatory for the service to be compliant with all regulatory and statutory requirements. Furthermore, the service must adhere to the specifications outlined in the Scope of Work (SOW), Special Terms and Conditions (STC), and the Service Level Agreement (SLA).', 'Mayank Gupta', 'Noida', 'This GeM bid (GEM/2025/B/6286198) is a two-packet tender issued by Gail India Limited, Noida, for the hiring of horticulture maintenance services for a contract period of two years at GAIL Jubilee Tower and GAIL Vihar. The bid end date is 19-06-2025, and the offer validity is 90 days. The required Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) is Rs. 2,54,000, and a Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 2.50% is required for 25 months. While startups are eligible for exemptions from experience and turnover criteria, Micro and Small Enterprises (MSEs) are not. The Bid Evaluation Criteria (BEC) includes technical and financial requirements. Technically, bidders must have experience in similar horticulture maintenance works, with options of one single work order of Rs. 59.96 Lakhs, two work orders of Rs. 37.48 Lakhs each, or three work orders of Rs. 29.98 Lakhs each within the last seven years. Financially, bidders must have a minimum average annual turnover of Rs. 37.48 Lakhs, a positive net worth, and a working capital of Rs. 7.50 Lakhs. The scope of work involves comprehensive horticulture maintenance including upkeep of lawns, plants, soil operations, pest control, and maintenance of indoor and outdoor plants at various GAIL locations in Noida.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer (GAIL), the work is considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of several key conditions. Primarily, the contractor must perform all services as detailed in the Scope of Work to the complete satisfaction of the Engineer-in-Charge (EIC). Following the completion of work, the contractor must successfully address and rectify any deficiencies or defects that arise during the 07-day Defect Liability Period. Final acceptance is contingent on the submission of all required final documents, including a ''No-Claim Certificate'', ''No-Dues Certificate'', and an ''Indemnity Bond''. The ultimate measure of success is the issuance of the ''Completion Certificate'' and subsequently the ''Final Certificate'' by the EIC, which formally confirms that the contractor has fulfilled all obligations under the contract.', 'The scope of work involves providing comprehensive horticulture maintenance services for a period of two years at GAIL Jubilee Tower, Info-hub Building (Sector-1), GAIL Vihar (Sector-23), and the Guest House (Sector-105) in Noida. This includes the day-to-day routine maintenance and upkeep of all horticulture-related infrastructure. Key activities include the maintenance of lawns, flower beds, and planted areas through soil operations, application of manure and fertilizer, and planting of various seedlings, saplings, trees, and shrubs. The contractor will be responsible for horticulture operations such as de-weeding, watering, pruning, and controlling insects and fungi through spraying insecticides. The work also covers the maintenance of shrubs, trees, topiaries, hedges, and both indoor and outdoor ornamental plants, which includes regular watering, soil working, cleaning, and providing necessary supports. The scope extends to the supply of miscellaneous items like good earth, dump manure, cement concrete pots, and providing watering services via tanker. Additionally, the contractor must supply and maintain various potted indoor and outdoor plants on a hiring basis for the entire contract duration, ensuring seasonal rotation. All waste and rubbish generated from these activities must be removed and disposed of daily by the contractor at their own risk and cost.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6287321', '19-06-2025 13:00:00', '19-06-2025 13:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Defence', 'Dg Of Defence Estate', '***********', 'buycon16.dde.ua@gembuyer.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium SUV; NA; Local 24*7', NULL, '1 Year', '20,00,000', '2 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require a Premium SUV vehicle, specifically a Toyota Innova Crysta model from the year 2025. The vehicle is intended for Local 24*7 service type and will operate in Plains. It must be equipped with Air Conditioning and run on Petrol. The total distance to be travelled is up to 25,000 Kms. The Usage Variant is specified as NA.', '***********', 'Dehradun', 'This bid, number GEM/2025/B/6287321, is for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for a Premium SUV. The contract period is for 1 year. The bid is issued by the Dg Of Defence Estate under the Ministry Of Defence. Key dates include the bid end date on 19-06-2025 and bid opening on the same day, with a bid offer validity of 120 days. Financial requirements for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 20 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 2 years of past experience in similar services. Exemptions for turnover are available for MSE and Startup entities. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with a Total value wise evaluation method. The service requires one Premium SUV vehicle, specifically a Toyota Innova Crysta of the 2025 model, for a duration of 12 months in DEHRADUN. The contract includes an Option Clause allowing the buyer to increase or decrease the quantity or duration by up to 25%. The service provider must ensure compliance with all applicable labor laws. The bid is governed by the General Terms and Conditions and the Service Level Agreement of the GeM Marketplace.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following criteria:
1. The service provider must supply one Premium SUV conforming to all technical specifications (Toyota Innova Crysta, 2025 Model, A/C, Petrol) for the entire contract period.
2. The vehicle and service must be consistently available on a 24*7 basis for local use at the specified location (DEHRADUN).
3. The service must be rendered for the full contract duration of 1 year (12 months) without any breach of contract terms.
4. The service provider must adhere strictly to all buyer-added terms and conditions, GeM General Terms and Conditions, and the Service Level Agreement.
5. Full compliance with all applicable laws, particularly labor laws such as The Minimum Wages Act 1948, must be maintained throughout the contract period.', 'The scope of work involves providing one Premium SUV for cab and taxi hiring services on a monthly basis for a contract period of one year. The service is required for the consignee located in DEHRADUN. The vehicle provided must be a Toyota Innova Crysta of the 2025 model year, running on petrol, and equipped with air conditioning. The service must be available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week (Local 24*7) for operations in Plains. The total travel for the vehicle is estimated to be up to 25,000 Kms during the contract period. The service provider is responsible for ensuring the vehicle and driver comply with all regulatory and legal requirements, including all applicable labor laws. The work must be performed in accordance with the terms laid out in the bid document and the GeM Service Level Agreement. A separate document for the Scope of Work is referenced as ''1748502410.pdf'' but its contents are not provided within this file.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6287742', '19-06-2025 15:00:00', '19-06-2025 15:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'North East Frontier Railway', 'North East Frontier Railway', 'sulabh.bisht@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 1800 KM X 360 Hours; Outstation 24*7, Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 1800 km x 360 hrs; Outstation 24*7', NULL, '3 Year', '49,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '3,22,29,197', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '64,500', 'Yes', 5, 38, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications outline the requirements for two separate Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services. Both services require an SUV type vehicle, with specific examples being Mahindra XUV 500, Mahindra Scorpio, and Mahindra Thar. The usage variant for both is 1800 KM X 360 Hours per month for outstation 24*7 service. The required vehicle models should be from the year 2025 or 2024, with total travel not exceeding 25,000 Kms. The vehicles must be Non-A/C and suitable for operation in both Hilly and Plain areas. Any fuel type is acceptable. No specific add-ons are required.', 'Sulabh Bisht', 'Siliguri', 'This GeM bid (GEM/2025/B/6287742), issued by the North East Frontier Railway, Ministry of Railways, is for the arrangement of two Non-AC SUV vehicles for a contract period of three years. The service is for the use of Officers, Supervisors, and Shed Staff of Diesel Loco Shed/SGUJ for attending to line failures and other official work. The estimated bid value is ₹32,22,919.7, with an EMD of ₹64,500. The tender follows a two-packet bid system. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum of 3 years of similar experience, an average annual turnover of ₹49 Lakhs for the last three years, and a satisfactory work experience of completing one similar contract valued at least 35% of the tender''s advertised value. Bidders must also demonstrate financial liquidity of at least 5% of the bid value. The evaluation process includes a technical scoring system where bidders must achieve a minimum of 60 marks based on criteria such as previous work experience, turnover, years in operation, and workforce size. The scope involves providing one SUV for 36 months and a second for 29 months. The vehicles must be less than one year old, commercially registered, and available 24*7 with an experienced driver. The contract includes all costs such as fuel, maintenance, insurance, and taxes.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed, the contractor must fulfill several key criteria from the tender issuer''s perspective. The primary measure of success is the issuance of a ''Completion Certificate'' by the competent railway authority, which confirms that the contractor has completed the assigned services in all respects satisfactorily. This is a prerequisite for the release of the Performance Guarantee (PG). Other critical success criteria include: strict adherence to all terms and conditions, ensuring 24*7 availability of the specified Non-AC vehicle in excellent running condition; providing an expert and experienced driver who reports for duty within 30 minutes of intimation; replacing any broken-down vehicle within two hours to avoid operational disruption. Furthermore, the contractor must submit monthly bills correctly with all required supporting documents, such as the log book, parking slips, and driver''s payment receipt, for verification and certification by the designated railway representative. Adherence to all statutory regulations, including labour laws, and avoiding penalties for non-performance are also integral to the successful completion of the contract.', 'The scope of work is for the “Arrangement of 02 nos. Non-AC vehicle for use of Officers, Supervisors and Shed Staff for attending line failure loco and official works of Diesel Loco Shed/SGUJ for a period of 03 years". This involves providing two Non-AC SUV vehicles, such as a Mahindra XUV 500, Mahindra Scorpio, Tata Safari, Tata Harrier, or a similar model. The service includes the provision of a driver, and all associated costs like vehicle maintenance, repair charges, toll tax, road tax, insurance, fuel, consumables, and parking fees. The operational area covers the entire Katihar Division, APDJ Division, DHR section, and Hilly Area. The vehicles must be in excellent running condition and not more than one year old from the date of the e-tender opening. The contract specifies providing the first vehicle for a duration of 36 months and the second vehicle for 29 months.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6287861', '19-06-2025 14:00:00', '19-06-2025 14:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Chemicals And Fertilizers', 'Department Of Chemicals And Petrochemicals', 'Hindustan Organic Chemicals Limited', 'Ambalamugal, ernakulam', 'vinodh.wo@hoclindia.com', 'Custom Bid for Services - HIRING OF A/C AMBULANCE AND NON A/C BOLERO FOR HOCL KOCHI FOR A PERIOD OF TWO YEARS', 'Monthly Basis Cab and Taxi Hiring Service - Without Fuel', '2 Year', NULL, '1 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '68,900', 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service detail the procurement of ''HIRING OF A/C AMBULANCE AND NON A/C BOLERO FOR HOCL KOCHI FOR A PERIOD OF TWO YEARS'' using a custom bid functionality. The service must ensure full regulatory and statutory compliance. Furthermore, it is mandatory for the service to be in complete compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Special Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA). There are no addon specifications mentioned in the table.', 'K V Vinodhkumar', 'Ernakulam', 'This bid document, GEM/2025/B/6287861, issued by Hindustan Organic Chemicals Limited (HOCL) under the Ministry of Chemicals and Fertilizers, is for a custom service contract for the ''HIRING OF A/C AMBULANCE AND NON A/C BOLERO FOR HOCL KOCHI FOR A PERIOD OF TWO YEARS''. The contract period is two years, with an Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of 68900. The tender follows a Two Packet Bid system. Key pre-qualification criteria for bidders include being a registered business entity, having at least one year of experience in taxi hiring, and maintaining an office within 20 KMs of Ambalamugal. The scope of work involves providing an AC Ambulance (Force Traveller/Tata Winger) for round-the-clock service and a Non-AC Bolero for 12 hours daily (09:00 to 21:00), inclusive of driver and fuel. The vehicles provided must not be more than three years old and must be registered on or after April 1, 2022. The ambulance must be equipped with specified medical and emergency equipment. The contract stipulates a security deposit of 5% of the contract value and includes a liquidated damages clause of 0.5% per week of delay, capped at 5% of the total contract value. Payments will be made on a monthly basis after the submission of certified bills and trip sheets. The document includes several annexures detailing the scope of work, bid submission instructions, general terms, technical bid forms, compliance declarations, and adherence to labor and safety laws.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer (HOCL), the successful completion of the work is contingent upon several criteria. Firstly, the contractor must provide continuous and uninterrupted service of the specified AC Ambulance and Non-AC Bolero for the entire two-year contract period, adhering strictly to the specified timings (24/7 for the ambulance and 12 hours for the Bolero) and operational on all days, including holidays. Secondly, successful performance is measured by the monthly submission of accurate bills accompanied by trip sheets and logbooks, which must be duly certified by an authorized HOCL officer. Thirdly, the contractor must ensure that the vehicles are consistently maintained in excellent running condition, are fully compliant with all statutory norms (insurance, tax, pollution control), and that the ambulance is equipped with all the specified medical and safety equipment at all times. Finally, adherence to all contractual obligations, including providing a substitute vehicle during maintenance, ensuring drivers meet the specified standards of conduct and qualification, and complying with all safety and labor laws, is essential for the work to be considered successfully completed. The completion of the contract within the stipulated time without incurring liquidated damages is a definitive measure of success.', 'The scope of work is for the contract of providing one AC Ambulance (Force Traveller/Tata Winger) and one Non-AC Bolero on a hire basis to HOCL, Kochi, Ambalamugal for a period of two years, effective from 18.07.2025. The service includes the provision of a driver and fuel for both vehicles. The AC Ambulance is required for round-the-clock (24 hours) service daily, while the Non-AC Bolero is required for 12 hours daily, from 09:00 Hrs to 21:00 Hrs. The service must be available on all days, including Sundays and holidays. The vehicles must be registered on or after 1st April 2022 and should not be more than three years old. They must be maintained in very good running condition with proper upkeep and have all valid documentation, including tax, insurance, and pollution certificates. The rates quoted must be inclusive of all costs such as driver''s wages, fuel, and other incidental charges, and will remain firm for the contract period. A daily log book must be maintained for recording time and distance. The ambulance must be equipped with specific general, safety, and emergency care equipment, including a wheeled stretcher, oxygen supply, suction unit, resuscitation kits, splints, and dressings. The contractor is responsible for providing a substitute vehicle during maintenance or repairs and must comply with all statutory regulations and HOCL''s safety and security guidelines. The contractor must also indemnify HOCL against any accidents, fines, or penalties arising from negligence.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6288507', '19-06-2025 15:00:00', '19-06-2025 15:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Petroleum And Natural Gas', NULL, 'Oil And Natural Gas Corporation Limited', 'Cauvery Asset Karaikal', 'buycon857.ongcl.py@gembuyer.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of Catering and Housekeeping services for renovated office canteen for a period of three years', 'Canteen Service - Best Price on Fixed Menu Rate Model, Canteen Service - Employee Welfare Model, Catering service (Duration Based)', '3 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '4 Days', NULL, '78,38,553', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '78,500', NULL, 3, 39, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications outline a requirement for the Hiring of Catering and Housekeeping services for a renovated office canteen for a period of three years. The service must adhere to all Regulatory and Statutory Compliances. Furthermore, compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA) is mandatory. There are no add-on services specified.', 'R Kamaraj', 'Neravy', 'This bid document, number GEM/2025/Β/6288507 dated 29-05-2025, is a tender by Oil And Natural Gas Corporation Limited, Cauvery Asset Karaikal, under the Ministry Of Petroleum And Natural Gas. The tender is for a custom bid for ''Hiring of Catering and Housekeeping services for renovated office canteen for a period of three years'', with a contract period of 3 years. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with an estimated value of 7838553 and requires an EMD of 78500 and a Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 3.00% for 39 months. The bid submission deadline is 19-06-2025 at 15:00:00, with the opening scheduled for 15:30:00 on the same day. The bid offer validity is 90 days. Documents required from sellers include Experience Criteria and other certificates as specified in the Additional Terms and Conditions (ATC). MSE Purchase Preference is applicable. The buyer retains an option clause to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25 percent.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the contractor''s fulfillment of several key obligations for the entire contract duration. This includes the satisfactory and complete delivery of all services as defined in the Scope of Work (SOW), adherence to the performance metrics outlined in the Service Level Agreement (SLA), and compliance with all applicable Regulatory and Statutory requirements. The contractor must also abide by all Standard Terms and Conditions (STC) and any Buyer Added Bid Specific Terms and Conditions mentioned in the contract.', 'Hiring of Catering and Housekeeping services for renovated office canteen for a period of three years'),
('GEM_2025_B_6288665', '09-06-2025 17:00:00', '09-06-2025 17:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Commerce And Industry', 'Department Of Commerce', 'Rubber Board', 'Head Office', 'buycon1.rbrbrd.kl@gembuyer.in', 'Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - MUV; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs', NULL, '9 Months 4 Day', '3,00,000', '2 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '5,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Service require a Premium SUV vehicle, specifically mentioning Toyota Innova as an option. The service is for Local usage with a variant of 80Kms x 10Hrs. The vehicle model should be from the years 2025, 2024, 2023, 2021, or 2022, with total travel up to 1,00,000 Kms. The vehicle must be equipped with A/C and be suitable for operation in both Hilly and Plain Areas. The fuel type can be any. The service is for return trips.', 'Nagalakshmi Ammal R', 'Kottayam', 'This is a bid document (GEM/2025/Β/6288665) issued by the Rubber Board, Head Office, under the Ministry Of Commerce And Industry for the procurement of ''Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - MUV; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs''. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with an estimated value of 500,000. The contract period is 9 Months and 4 Days, starting from 01.07.2025 to 31.03.2026, for a required service duration of 200 days. The consignee is Nagalakshmi Ammal R at the Rubber Board Head Office in Kottayam, requiring one vehicle. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 3 Lakhs for the last three years and 2 years of past experience in similar services. No EMD or ePBG is required. The technical specifications mandate a Premium SUV like a Toyota Innova, model year 2021-2025, with A/C for local travel. The buyer has included an option clause to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. The scope of work specifies the places of supply as Rubber Board Head Office and the National Institute for Training, both in Kottayam.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon fulfillment of the following criteria: The supplier must consistently provide one vehicle of the specified type (Innova AC or equivalent Premium SUV) meeting the model year requirements (2021-2025) at the designated places of supply for the entire duration of 200 days within the contract period. The vehicle must be available with all valid documentation, including RC book, Pollution certificate, Insurance, Road Tax, and Taxi permit. The supplier must adhere to all financial terms, including bearing costs like toll and parking fees, with the quoted rate being inclusive of GST. For payment processing, the supplier must submit accurate monthly bills supported by individual trip sheets with odometer readings for all trips performed, in accordance with GeM guidelines.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring of one Air Conditioned MUV vehicle, specified as a Premium SUV (e.g., Toyota Innova) of model year 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024, or 2025. The service is required for a total of 200 days within the contract period of 01.07.2025 to 31.03.2026. The places of supply are the Rubber Board Head Office, Kottayam – 686 002 and the National Institute for Training, Kottayam – 686 009. The supplier is responsible for providing the vehicle at the place of requirement. The quoted rate must be inclusive of GST, and additional expenses such as toll fees and parking fees must be borne by the vehicle provider. The supplier must enclose copies of the vehicle''s RC book, Pollution certificate, Insurance, Road Tax, Taxi permit, and other relevant documents with the bid. Billing will be done on a monthly basis, supported by individual trip sheets with odometer readings for all trips performed, and payments will be made according to GeM guidelines.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6288898', '09-06-2025 17:00:00', '09-06-2025 17:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Commerce And Industry', 'Department Of Commerce', 'Rubber Board', 'Head Office', 'buycon1.rbrbrd.kl@gembuyer.in', 'Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - MUV; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs', NULL, '9 Months 4 Day', '3,00,000', '2 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services require a MUV (Multi-Utility Vehicle), specifically a Mahindra Bolero Camper, for local service. The usage variant is defined as 80 Kms x 10 Hrs for return trips. The vehicle model must be from the years 2025, 2024, 2022, 2023, or 2021, and it should have travelled up to 1,00,000 Kms. The vehicle must be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C) and be suitable for operation in both Hilly and Plain areas. Any fuel type is acceptable.', 'Nagalakshmi Ammal R', 'Kottayam', 'This is a bid document (GEM/2025/B/6288898) issued by the Rubber Board, under the Ministry Of Commerce And Industry, for the procurement of Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services. The service requires one MUV type vehicle for a local duty of 80 Kms x 10 Hrs. The contract period is specified as 9 months and 4 days, with the actual service required for 200 days between 01.07.2025 and 31.03.2026. The bid is a Two Packet system with evaluation based on the total value. Prospective bidders must have a minimum average annual turnover of 3 Lakhs for the last three years and 2 years of past experience in similar services; no exemptions are provided for MSE or Startups. No EMD or ePBG is required. The service location is Kottayam, specifically for the Rubber Board Head Office and the National Institute for Training. The buyer has included an option clause to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. Bidders must comply with all applicable labour laws and GeM terms and conditions.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be deemed successfully completed upon the consistent fulfillment of the following criteria throughout the contract period: 1. The supplier must provide the specified vehicle (Bolero AC or equivalent MUV) at the required places of supply (Rubber Board Head Office and National Institute for Training, Kottayam) for the entire duration of 200 days as per the schedule. 2. The provided vehicle must continuously meet all technical specifications, including model year, mileage, and functional A/C. 3. The supplier must furnish all required documentation, such as RC book, Pollution certificate, Insurance, Road Tax, and Taxi permit. 4. Accurate monthly bills, supported by individual trip sheets with correct odometer readings for all journeys, must be submitted in accordance with GeM guidelines for timely payment processing. 5. The supplier must bear all additional expenses like toll and parking fees, as the quoted rate is inclusive of all charges except GST. 6. The supplier must ensure full compliance with all applicable Labour Laws as stipulated in the bid document.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring of one MUV (Multi-Utility Vehicle), specifically a Bolero AC, for Short Term Cab & Taxi Services. The service is required for a total of 200 days within the contract period of 01.07.2025 to 31.03.2026. The places of supply are the Rubber Board Head Office, Kottayam – 686 002 and the National Institute for Training, Kottayam – 686 009. The supplier is responsible for providing the vehicle at the specified location. The rate quoted by the supplier must be inclusive of GST, and all additional expenses such as toll fees and parking fees are to be borne by the vehicle provider. The supplier must submit copies of the vehicle''s RC book, Pollution certificate, Insurance, Road Tax, and Taxi permit along with the bid. For payment, the supplier must provide monthly billing with an individual trip sheet detailing the odometer readings for all trips performed, in line with GeM guidelines.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6289002', '09-06-2025 17:00:00', '09-06-2025 17:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Commerce And Industry', 'Department Of Commerce', 'Rubber Board', 'Head Office', 'buycon1.rbrbrd.kl@gembuyer.in', 'Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium Sedan; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs', NULL, '9 Months 4 Day', '3,00,000', '2 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services require a Hatchback vehicle, specifically a Maruti Suzuki Swift. The service is for Local use with a usage variant of 80Kms x 10Hrs. The vehicle model should be from the years 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024, or 2025, with total travel up to 1,00,000 Kms. The vehicle must be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C) and be suitable for operation in both Hilly and Plain Areas. Any fuel type is acceptable. The service should accommodate return trips.', 'Nagalakshmi Ammal R', 'Kottayam', 'This is a bid invitation for the procurement of Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for a Premium Sedan, specifically for local use at 80Kms x 10Hrs. The bid, numbered GEM/2025/B/6289002, is issued by the Rubber Board, Head Office, under the Ministry of Commerce and Industry. The bid end date is 09-06-2025, and the contract period is specified as 9 months and 4 days. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 3 Lakhs over the last three years and 2 years of past experience in similar services. No exemptions for MSE or Startups on experience and turnover criteria are provided. The evaluation method is based on the total value. The service requires one Maruti Swift AC vehicle for 200 days to be supplied at the Rubber Board Head Office and National Institute for Training in Kottayam. The contract includes an option clause allowing the buyer to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. Bidders must comply with all applicable labor laws, and the bid is governed by GeM''s General Terms and Conditions and Service Level Agreement.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed, the supplier must consistently provide the specified vehicle (Maruti Swift AC) at the designated places of supply (Rubber Board Head Office, Kottayam and National Institute for Training, Kottayam) for the entire required duration of 200 days within the contract period. The supplier is responsible for all additional expenses, including toll and parking fees, and the quoted rate must be inclusive of GST. A critical success criterion is the timely submission of all required documentation, including the vehicle''s RC book, Pollution certificate, Insurance, Road Tax, and Taxi permit. For payment processing, the supplier must submit monthly bills accompanied by individual trip sheets with accurate odometer readings for all trips performed, in accordance with GeM guidelines.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring of one Maruti Swift AC vehicle. The service must be provided at two locations: 1) Rubber Board Head Office, Kottayam – 686 002 and 2) National Institute for Training, Kottayam – 686 009. The service is required for a duration of 200 days within the contract period of 01.07.2025 to 31.03.2026. The terms and conditions mandate that the supplier provides the vehicle at the place of requirement, with rates quoted inclusive of GST. All additional expenses such as toll and parking fees are to be borne by the vehicle provider. The supplier must enclose copies of the vehicle''s RC book, Pollution certificate, Insurance, Road Tax, and Taxi permit with the bid document. Monthly payments will be made as per GeM guidelines, based on monthly billing supported by individual trip sheets with odometer readings for all completed trips.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6290496', '20-06-2025 10:00:00', '20-06-2025 10:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Army', '***********', 'ashkum.19450@gov.in', 'Printing of Flex or Banner, Trophy for Winner and Runnerup , Medal, Sports Jersey Tshirt and Half Pant, Volleyball, Volleyball Net, Sports Shoe, Preparation of Ground and other Administrative arrangements, Hiring of Transport for Conveyance of Villagers, Refreshment for participants and audience, Miscellaneous expenditure', 'Volleyball Net as per IS 3345', NULL, '1,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Past Performance, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), OEM Annual Turnover, Compliance of BoQ specification and supporting document *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Group wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, 'Schedulewise', 'No', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the tender are detailed across several items required for a sports tournament. For each category—Printing of Flex Or Banner, Trophy For Winner And Runnerup, Medal, Sports Jersey Tshirt And Half Pant, Volleyball, Volleyball Net, Sports Shoe, Preparation Of Ground And Other Administrative Arrangements, Hiring Of Transport For Conveyance Of Villagers, Refreshment For Participants And Audience, and Miscellaneous Expenditure—the specific details are provided in external ''Specification Document'' and ''BOQ Detail Document'' which are available for viewing. A consolidated list of requirements for the ''CONDUCT OF SPORTS TOURNAMENT AND DISTRIBUTION OF SPORTS ITEMS IN VILLAGE WANGLEE & NAMLEE OF KAMJONG DISTRICT (MANIPUR)'' specifies the following items and quantities: Printing of Flex/ Banner (02 Nos), Trophies including a 1st Trophy for Winner and a 2nd Trophy for Runner (02 Nos), Medal for Individual Competition (20 Nos), Sports Jersey (Tshirt & Half pant) (20 Pair), Volleyball (NIVIA) (20 Nos), Volleyball Net (10 Nos), Sports Shoe (20 Pair), Preparation of Ground & other administrative arrangements/Hiring of CHT for conveyance of Villagers (01 Job), Refreshment for participants (01 Job), and Miscellaneous Expenditure (01 Job).', 'Rohit Bhagchandani', 'Bishnupur', 'This bid, with number GEM/2025/Β/6290496, is issued by the Indian Army under the Ministry of Defence for the ''CONDUCT OF SPORTS TOURNAMENT''. The tender involves the supply of various goods and services for a sports event in Manipur. The total quantity of items is 98. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with a group-wise evaluation method. The key dates are Bid End on 20-06-2025 and Bid Opening on the same day, with a bid offer validity of 120 days. Prospective bidders must meet several eligibility criteria, including a minimum average annual turnover of 1 Lakh for the last three years, three years of past experience in similar services, and an 80% past performance record. The OEM must have an average turnover of 8 Lakhs for the last three years. MSEs are eligible for exemption from turnover and experience criteria. The required deliverables include printing of banners, trophies, medals, sports jerseys, volleyballs, volleyball nets, and sports shoes. Services to be provided encompass ground preparation, transport for villagers, refreshments, and miscellaneous expenditures. All goods and services are to be delivered to the consignee at ARMY GATE, NEAR DC COMPLEX, BISHNUPUR, Manipur 795133 within 60 days. The buyer reserves the right to exercise an option clause to increase or decrease the order quantity by up to 25%.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer, the work will be deemed successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following conditions: 1. The supply and execution of all specified goods and services as per the quantities and technical specifications detailed in the BOQ and Specification Documents. 2. Timely delivery of all items and completion of all services within the stipulated 60-day delivery period to the designated consignee address: ARMY GATE, NEAR DC COMPLEX, BISHNUPUR, Manipur 795133. 3. Submission of all required documentation, including acceptance certificates like CRAC, to provide proof of supply and successful execution of the contract. 4. Full compliance with all Buyer Added Bid Specific Terms and Conditions, as well as the General Terms and Conditions (GTC) of the tender throughout the contract period.', 'The scope of work involves the complete arrangement, supply of goods, and provision of services for the ''CONDUCT OF SPORTS TOURNAMENT AND DISTRIBUTION OF SPORTS ITEMS IN VILLAGE WANGLEE & NAMLEE OF KAMJONG DISTRICT (MANIPUR)''. The contractor is responsible for delivering the following items and services to the consignee located at ARMY GATE, NEAR DC COMPLEX, BISHNUPUR, Manipur 795133 within a 60-day period. 

Goods to be Supplied:
- Printing of Flex/ Banner: 2 Nos
- Trophies: 2 Nos (one 1st Trophy for Winner and one 2nd Trophy for Runner)
- Medals for Individual Competition: 20 Nos
- Sports Jerseys (Tshirt & Half pant): 20 Pairs
- Volleyballs (NIVIA): 20 Nos
- Volleyball Nets: 10 Nos
- Sports Shoes: 20 Pairs

Services to be Provided:
- Preparation of Ground & other administrative arrangements: 1 Job
- Hiring of Transport for Conveyance of Villagers: 1 Job
