- Miscellaneous Expenditure: 1 Job'),
('GEM_2025_B_6291081', '12-06-2025 20:00:00', '12-06-2025 20:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Civil Aviation', 'Airports Authority Of India (aai)', 'Airports Authority Of India', 'Trichy International Airport', 'buycon11.aai.kolkata@gembuyer.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of Vehicles on Need and Call Basis for Tiruchirappalli International Airport', 'Monthly Basis Cab and Taxi Hiring Service - Without Fuel', '2 Year', '2,50,000', 'last seven years', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '16,66,696', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '50,000', 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require the hiring of vehicles on a need and call basis for Tiruchirappalli International Airport. The service must maintain regulatory and statutory compliance. Furthermore, the provider must ensure compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA). There are no addon specifications mentioned in the table.', 'Parthasarathy Selvaraj', 'Trichy', 'This GeM bid (GEM/2025/B/6291081), issued by the Airports Authority of India (AAI) for Trichy International Airport, is for a two-year contract for ''Hiring of Vehicles on Need and Call Basis''. The bid, a Two Packet type, has an estimated value of INR 1,666,696 and requires an EMD of INR 50,000. The bid end date is 12-06-2025, with an offer validity of 180 days. The contract involves providing various types of vehicles as specified in the Scope of Work. Key pre-qualification criteria for bidders include having a registered office within a 50 km radius of Trichy, an annualized average financial turnover of at least Rs. 2,50,000 over the last three financial years (with exemptions for MSE/Startups), and specific past experience in providing similar services. Bidders must also possess a minimum of 10 vehicles of specified categories. The evaluation of bids will be on a total value wise basis. The contract terms detail conditions for payment (monthly), security deposit (10% of contract value), vehicle and driver standards, and liabilities. The agreement also includes clauses for dispute resolution, termination, and force majeure.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is considered successfully completed through the consistent and satisfactory fulfillment of all contractual obligations throughout the two-year contract period. Success is measured by the contractor''s ability to provide the specified vehicles on a need and call basis without fail, adhering strictly to the conditions regarding vehicle quality, maintenance, and driver conduct. The regular and timely submission of accurate monthly bills accompanied by duly filled and signed Trip Sheets serves as a recurring validation of service delivery. The ultimate success of the contract is marked by its completion for the full term without the imposition of penalties for defaults (such as delays, non-provision of vehicles, or poor service quality) and without the need for early termination due to unsatisfactory performance. The final payment and release of the security deposit after the contract''s expiry would signify that all obligations have been met successfully.', 'The scope of work involves the contractor providing various types of tourist vehicles on a ''Need & Call Basis'' for Tiruchirappalli International Airport. The contractor must be able to supply vehicles at any point in time, even at short notice (2 hours for local trips and 5 hours for outstation trips). The required vehicle types include Sedan (e.g., SWIFT DZIRE), SUV (e.g., MAHINDRA BOLERO), Premium Sedan (e.g., HONDA CITY), Premium SUV (e.g., TOYOTA INNOVA CRYSTA), Mini Van/Bus (15-20 seater), Goods Carrier (e.g., TATA 407), and a 52-Seater Bus. All vehicles provided must be of the latest models, white in color, and maintained in excellent running condition. They must be kept clean, equipped with valid documentation (RC, Insurance, PUC, Fitness Certificate), and provided with amenities like a first-aid box, bottled water, tissues, and newspapers. Drivers assigned must be uniformed, licensed, punctual, well-behaved, and equipped with a mobile phone. The contractor is responsible for all operational aspects, including coordinating bookings, ensuring drivers follow the shortest routes, and obtaining necessary security passes and permits for airport operations. The contractor bears sole responsibility for their drivers'' employment, wages, and adherence to all applicable labor laws and is fully liable for any accidents or damages caused by their vehicles or personnel.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6291295', '18-06-2025 10:00:00', '18-06-2025 10:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Army', '***********', 'mansin.71802@gov.in', 'Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Local; 120Kms x 12Hrs, Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Outstation; 250Kms x 8Hrs, Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium SUV; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs, Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium SUV; Local; 120Kms x 12Hrs, Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium SUV; Outstation; 250Kms x 8Hrs', NULL, '9 Months 5 Day', NULL, '2 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), OEM Annual Turnover, Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '3,26,200', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The tender requires five categories of short-term cab and taxi hiring services. For Sedan vehicles, the services are for Local use (120Kms x 12Hrs) and Outstation use (250Kms x 8Hrs), both requiring Non-A/C vehicles from the options of Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, or Toyota Etios. For Premium SUV vehicles, three services are specified: Local use (80Kms x 10Hrs), Local use (120Kms x 12Hrs), and Outstation use (250Kms x 8Hrs), all requiring A/C vehicles from the options of Toyota Innova, Toyota Fortuner, or Toyota Innova Crysta. Common specifications across all categories include vehicle model years of 2022, 2023, 2024, or 2025; maximum travel of up to 25,000 Kms; operation in Hilly + Plain Areas; any fuel type; and one-way/return trips.', '***********', 'Agartala', 'This bid, GEM/2025/B/6291295, is a two-packet tender issued by the Indian Army, Department of Military Affairs, Ministry of Defence, for the procurement of Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services. The estimated bid value is INR 3,26,200. The services are required for a contract period of 9 months and 5 days, specifically for the 57 Mountain Artillery Brigade at Agartala Military Station, Tripura West. The tender details five distinct categories of vehicle hire: Non-A/C Sedans for local and outstation duties, and A/C Premium SUVs for local and outstation duties. Bidders are required to have 2 years of past experience in similar services, and must submit documents such as Experience Criteria and Bidder Turnover certificates. No EMD or ePBG is required. The tender includes an Option Clause allowing the buyer to vary the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. The document also contains a ''Statement of Case'' which justifies the need for these Civil Hired Transport (CHT) services to support essential duties like conferences, administrative tasks, and conveyance of troops, thereby preserving the combat effectiveness of primary military vehicles. The service provider must comply with all applicable Indian laws, including labour laws.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer, the work will be deemed successfully completed when the service provider consistently provides the specified number and type of vehicles (Sedan and Premium SUV) in full compliance with all technical specifications (including vehicle model year, mileage, and AC/Non-AC requirements) throughout the entire contract period. Success is contingent on the timely availability of vehicles as per the demand for local and outstation duties at the specified location. Furthermore, the provider must adhere to all terms and conditions of the contract, the Service Level Agreement, and ensure full compliance with all mandated statutory and labour laws, such as The Minimum Wages Act, 1948, and The Payment of Wages Act, 1936.', 'The scope of work involves providing Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services to the 57 Mountain Artillery Brigade at Agartala Military Station. The service provider is required to supply vehicles for both local and outstation duties for a contract period of 9 months and 5 days. The primary purpose is the hiring of Civil Hired Transport (CHT) for various essential duties including conveyance of troops and officers, transport of essential goods, attending conferences and seminars, visits of senior officers, and providing administrative support. The work is divided into five categories: Sedan Local (120Kms x 12Hrs), Sedan Outstation (250Kms x 8Hrs), Premium SUV Local (80Kms x 10Hrs), Premium SUV Local (120Kms x 12Hrs), and Premium SUV Outstation (250Kms x 8Hrs). The provider must supply vehicles that meet the specified makes and models (e.g., Maruti Suzuki Dzire, Toyota Innova), are of the 2022-2025 model years, have run Upto 25,000 Kms, and are suitable for operation in Hilly and Plain areas. The services are to be delivered to the consignee located in TRIPURA WEST, with specified quantities for each vehicle category. The contractor must also adhere to all buyer-added terms, including an option clause for a 25% variation in contract quantity or duration.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6292140', '20-06-2025 14:00:00', '20-06-2025 14:30:00', '30 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'Nfr Construction', 'Genral Manager/construction/nfr', 'cs.rao17@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2500 km x 320 hours; Outstation', NULL, '1 Year', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '12,44,016', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '24,880', 'Yes', 5, 14, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the tender require an SUV vehicle type, with suggested models including Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra XUV 500, and Mahindra Scorpio. The usage variant is defined as 2500 km x 320 hours for outstation service. The vehicle model must be from the years 2025, 2024, or 2023, with total travel not exceeding 50,000 Kms. Further requirements specify a Non-A/C vehicle operating in Plains and using Diesel as its fuel type.', 'Rajiv Kumar', 'Guwahati', 'This bid document (GEM/2025/B/6292140) is for a tender by Nfr Construction, under the Ministry of Railways, for the provision of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services''. The specific requirement is for two SUV vehicles for outstation use, each contracted for a monthly package of 2500 km and 320 hours. The contract period is for one year, with an estimated value of INR 1,244,016. Bidders are required to submit an EMD of INR 24,880, and the successful bidder must provide an e-Performance Bank Guarantee of 5% for a duration of 14 months. The bid is a Two Packet Bid, and MSE/Startup exemptions for experience and turnover are applicable. The service is required for the Dy.CSTE/C/RE/GHY in Maligaon, Guwahati, Assam. Key pre-qualification criteria include the bidder having a fleet of at least 3 owned vehicles, 3 drivers on their payroll, and a business presence in Assam. The technical specifications mandate a Non-A/C, diesel SUV from the years 2023-2025 with less than 50,000 km travelled. Payment terms stipulate that the service provider must first pay salaries and statutory wages to their staff before claiming payment from the buyer.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon fulfillment of the following criteria: The successful bidder must submit the required Performance Security (ePBG) of 5% within 15 days of the contract award. At the time of vehicle deployment, the provider must submit a medical certificate from a Government/PSU hospital and a police verification for the deployed driver. On a continuous monthly basis, the provider must deliver the cab and taxi hiring service as per the specified package (2500 km & 320 hours) without fail. Crucially, before claiming monthly payment, the provider must submit documentary proof of having paid salaries as per minimum wages, along with EPF & ESI contributions, to their deployed staff. The contract is successfully executed through consistent adherence to these service delivery, documentation, and statutory compliance requirements for the entire one-year period.', 'The scope of work is to provide two SUV type vehicles on a monthly hiring basis for a contract duration of one year for the Office of Dy Chief Signal And Telecom Engineer Railway Electrification in Maligaon, Guwahati. The service entails each vehicle being available for a monthly usage of 2500 kilometers and 320 hours for outstation duties. The vehicles supplied must be from the model years 2023, 2024, or 2025, run on diesel, be Non-A/C, and have travelled less than 50,000 Kms. The service provider must have an operational office within the state of Assam. As part of the service, the provider is responsible for ensuring that each deployed driver has a valid medical certificate from a Government/PSU hospital and has undergone police verification, with these documents to be submitted at the time of deployment. The scope also includes the monthly submission of salary statements demonstrating compliance with minimum wages, EPF, and ESI for the drivers, which is a prerequisite for payment processing.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6292774', '09-06-2025 17:00:00', '09-06-2025 17:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Agriculture And Farmers Welfare', 'Department Of Agriculture Cooperation And Farmers Welfare', 'National Institute Of Agricultural Extension Management (manage)', 'Hyderabad', 'mvenugopal@manage.gov.in', 'Bus Hiring Service - Short Term - Local; 22-24, 25-27, 28-30, 34-36, 40-42, 49-52, 43-45, more than 52, 9-12, 13-15, 19-21; A.C. Deluxe (ACX); 50, 80, 100, 120, 150, Bus Hiring Service - Short Term - Local; 22-24, 25-27, 28-30, 34-36, 40-42, 49-52, 43-45, more than 52, 9-12, 13-15, 19-21; Deluxe (DLX); 50, 80, 100, 120, 150, Bus Hiring Service - Short Term - Outstation; 9-12, 13-15, 19-21, 22-24, 25-27, 28-30, 34-36, 40-42, 43-45, 49-52, more than 52; A.C. Deluxe (ACX); 200, 250, 300, Bus Hiring Service - Short Term - Outstation; 9-12, 13-15, 19-21, 22-24, 25-27, 28-30, 34-36, 40-42, 43-45, 49-52, more than 52; Deluxe (DLX); 200, 250, 300', NULL, '1 Year', '1,00,00,000', '5 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '38,32,200', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '1,15,000', 'Yes', 3, 14, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications detail four types of short-term bus hiring services: Local A.C. Deluxe (ACX), Local Deluxe (DLX), Outstation A.C. Deluxe (ACX), and Outstation Deluxe (DLX). For Local services, both ACX and DLX buses are required with seating capacities ranging from 9-12 up to more than 52 seats. The per day usage for local services is specified at 50, 80, 100, 120, or 150 KM(s) for 5, 8, 10, 12, or 16 hours. For Outstation services, both ACX and DLX buses are required with the same wide range of seating capacities. The per day usage for outstation services is set at 200, 250, or 300 KM(s) for 12, 14, or 16 hours. Across all categories, the required fuel type is Diesel, and the vehicle models must be from the years 2023, 2024, or 2025.', 'Pullabhotla Rama Murthy', 'Hyderabad', 'This bid document, GEM/2025/B/6292774, is for the procurement of various short-term Bus Hiring Services for the National Institute Of Agricultural Extension Management (MANAGE) in Hyderabad. The contract period is for one year. The services are categorized into Local and Outstation travel, with options for both A.C. Deluxe (ACX) and Deluxe (DLX) buses, accommodating various seating capacities. The bid requires bidders to have a minimum average annual turnover of 100 Lakhs for the last three years and 5 years of past experience in similar services, although exemptions are available for MSE and Startup entities. The estimated bid value is INR 3832200, with an EMD of 115000 and an ePBG requirement of 3.00% for 14 months. The document outlines specific buyer-added terms and conditions, including an option clause to vary the contract quantity by up to 25%, a requirement for the service provider to have a local office, and specific fleet ownership (30%) and manpower (40% on payroll) criteria. A detailed Service Level Agreement (SLA) is included, specifying penalties for service deficiencies such as delays, non-deployment of vehicles, breakdowns, and driver misbehavior, to ensure service quality and reliability.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed from the tender issuer''s perspective, the service provider must adhere to several key criteria. Primarily, the provider must consistently deliver quality services as per the defined Service Level Agreement (SLA), avoiding any penalties. This includes ensuring that the assigned bus and driver report to the designated location on time and as per the provided schedule. The vehicles deployed must be well-maintained, thoroughly cleaned, and have a sufficient tank of fuel. All buses must be equipped with an emergency medical kit, a fire extinguisher, and hold valid insurance and fitness certificates. In the event of a breakdown, a similar or higher class of bus must be provided as an alternate arrangement at the provider''s own cost. Drivers must possess valid commercial licenses and maintain polite and courteous behavior at all times. The service provider is also responsible for all statutory liabilities related to their employees, such as PF and ESI. Ultimately, successful completion is measured by the consistent, reliable, and safe provision of bus hiring services without any service failures or breaches of the contract terms.', 'The Scope of Service involves the hiring of buses as per the defined requirements of the buyer. The service is divided into basic packages: 
Local: This service covers one-side movement up to 50 kilometers from the reporting point. Duty hours and mileage calculation start and end at the reporting point, with no garage kilometers being applicable. 
Outstation: This service is for the movement of the buyer''s staff outside the city according to a provided schedule. No overtime is applicable, but a fixed per-night charge will be paid for night stays. The service is based on a minimum running kilometer per day, such as 200 Km(s), 250 Km(s), or 300 Km(s). 
Local*24X7: This is a 24x7 hiring service applicable for local travel only, with no overtime or night stay charges. 
Additionally, the scope includes providing buses with trained drivers who hold a valid commercial license. The service provider must ensure passenger safety during the performance of services and must have a mandatory, detailed contingency plan in place for any event of a mechanical breakdown for each bus and area of operation.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6292980', '20-06-2025 16:00:00', '20-06-2025 16:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Defence', 'Border Road Organisation', '***********', 'shankar.prasad3414@bro.gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - SUB SOIL INVESTIGATION', 'Empanelment of Consultants/Service Providers', '2 Month', '15,00,000', '1 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), OEM Authorization Certificate, OEM Annual Turnover *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '28,000', 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service are detailed under the ''Core'' section. The Description /Nomenclature of Service Proposed for procurement using custom bid functionality is ''SUB SOIL INVESTIGATION''. The service requires ''YES'' for Regulatory/ Statutory Compliance of Service and ''YES'' for Compliance of Service to SOW, STC, SLA etc. There are no specifications listed under the Addon(s) section.', '***********', 'East sikkim', 'This bid document, with Bid Number GEM/2025/Β/6292980, is for a ''Custom Bid for Services - SUB SOIL INVESTIGATION'' issued by the Border Road Organisation under the Ministry Of Defence. The contract period is for 2 months. Key dates include the Bid End Date on 20-06-2025 and Bid Opening Date on 20-06-2025, with a bid offer validity of 180 days. Bidders need a minimum average annual turnover of 15 Lakhs for the last 3 years and 1 year of past experience in similar services, with no exemptions for MSE or Startups in this regard. The bid is a Two Packet type, enabled for Reverse Auction with an H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination rule. An EMD of 28000 is required, payable to ''CDR 758 BRTF'' at SBI, GANGTOK. The service is to be delivered to a consignee in East Sikkim. The tender supports MII Compliance and MSE Purchase Preference. Buyer-added terms include an option clause allowing the buyer to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 50 percent, and clauses prohibiting assignment or sub-contracting without prior written consent from the buyer.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is deemed successfully completed upon the full and satisfactory execution of the SUB SOIL INVESTIGATION service in complete compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA). The completion is also subject to passing the inspection as per the ''SLBR52'' clause. All deliverables must be accepted by the specified consignee/reporting officer in East Sikkim within the 2-month contract period.', 'The scope of work involves conducting a ''SUB SOIL INVESTIGATION'' service for the Border Road Organisation. This is a single project-based or lumpsum-based service to be performed at a site located in East Sikkim. The contractor is responsible for executing the entire investigation as per the project requirements within the stipulated contract period of 2 months. The service must strictly adhere to all regulatory and statutory compliances, as well as the specifications detailed in the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA) of the tender.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6294667', '17-06-2025 17:00:00', '17-06-2025 17:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Coal', 'Coal India Limited', 'Coal India Limited', 'North Eastern Coalfields', 'pratanu.goswami@coalindia.in', 'Bus Hiring Service - Regular Basis - Local; 25-27, 28-30; 2400 Km*360 Hr , Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Km*360 Hr; Local', NULL, '3 Year', '17,00,000', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Request Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested i Doc 3 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC), *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experien Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibilit be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '7 Days', NULL, '55,43,60,994', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'AXIS BANK LTD', '69,300', NULL, 5, 38, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The tender includes technical specifications for two distinct vehicle hiring services. The first service is for a Bus Hiring on a regular basis for local use, with a seating capacity of 25-27 and 28-30 passengers. This is a Non-Deluxe (NDX) bus with a diesel engine and an Ex-Showroom model year. The usage variant is specified as 2400 Km and 360 Hr. There are no night or outstation charges associated with this service. The second service is for a Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring, specifically an SUV for local use. The acceptable car types include Hyundai Creta, Mahindra XUV300, and KIA Seltos. The usage variant is 2400 Km and 360 Hr on an Ex-showroom model. This vehicle is required to have Air Conditioning (A/C), operate in plains, run on diesel, and should have travelled up to 25,000 Kms.', 'Manash Pratim Dutta', 'Margherita', 'This bid document, issued by North Eastern Coalfields, a subsidiary of Coal India Limited under the Ministry of Coal, is for a two-packet bid for the hiring of two new vehicles for a contract period of three years. The services required are one 25-30 seater Non-Deluxe school bus with a driver and handyman, and one 5-seater SUV with a driver, both for school duty under NEC Margherita. The estimated bid value is INR 5,543,609.94 with an Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of INR 69,300. The bid end date is 17-06-2025. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 17 Lakhs over the last three years and past experience in similar services, although exemptions are available for startups. Bidders are required to submit several documents, including experience criteria, turnover certificates, PAN, and GST registration details, through the GeM portal. The contract includes an option clause for the buyer to increase or decrease the contract quantity by up to 25%. The service provider is responsible for the timely payment of salaries and wages to their staff. The document outlines detailed technical, commercial, and general terms, including requirements for vehicle maintenance, driver qualifications, breakdown procedures, statutory compliance, and penalties for non-performance. It also specifies that a formal agreement must be executed upon award, and performance security of 5% of the contract value is required.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer, the work will be considered successfully completed upon fulfillment of the following criteria: 1. Execution of a formal contract agreement on a non-judicial stamp paper within 30 days of the notification of award. 2. Successful deployment of the specified new vehicles (one school bus with driver/handyman and one SUV with driver) within 30 days of the Letter of Acceptance/Work Order. 3. Continuous, regular, and efficient service throughout the stipulated 3-year contract period to the complete satisfaction of the authorized department/staff. 4. Strict adherence to all technical terms, including proper maintenance of vehicles, ensuring all statutory documents (insurance, permits, fitness, PUC) are valid, maintaining logbooks, and providing a suitable replacement vehicle within 12 hours during breakdowns. 5. Full compliance with all statutory provisions, including the Motor Vehicle Act, labor laws, and payment of wages as per the Minimum Wages Act. 6. Successful completion of the 6-month Defect Liability Period after the contract, which includes rectifying any defects identified. 7. On completion of the entire work, the contractor must clear the site of all rubbish and debris and hand it over. 8. Submission of a ''no claim certificate'' to the Engineer-in-Charge to facilitate the processing of the final payment.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring of two new vehicles for North Eastern Coalfields (NEC) Margherita for a period of 3 years. The specific vehicles required are one 25-30 seater new school bus, which must be provided with a driver and a handyman, and one new 5-seater SUV provided with a driver. These vehicles are primarily for school duty, serving DPS Digboi and Carmel School Digboi, but can be engaged for any purpose or at any location as required by NEC. The service entails continuous operation for 12 hours daily, covering approximately 80 kms per day for 30 days a month, totaling around 2400 kms per month per vehicle. The contractor is responsible for providing new vehicles registered with the RTO of Assam and ensuring they are exclusively used for NEC duty. The scope includes bearing all costs related to fuel, lubricants, maintenance, repairs, and ensuring all vehicle documents (Registration, Comprehensive Insurance, Road Permit, Fitness Certificate, PUC) remain valid throughout the contract. The contractor must provide competent, skilled, and licensed drivers and a handyman, and is responsible for their salaries as per the Minimum Wage Act, which must be paid via bank transfer. A proper logbook must be maintained for each vehicle. In case of any breakdown, the contractor must provide a suitable substitute vehicle of equivalent capacity within 12 hours. The contractor must deploy the vehicles within 30 days of receiving the work order and must comply with all applicable statutory laws and regulations.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6295926', '10-06-2025 17:00:00', '10-06-2025 17:30:00', '180 Days', 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Revenue Department Uttar Pradesh', 'Board Of Revenue Government Of Uttar Pradesh', 'Collectorate Pilibhit', 'kalash.63208@gov.in', 'Hiring of Boats - Quick Response Vehicle (QRV) Boat; Less than 5 years; With Air-Conditioning; 20; 1000; Jet Drive / Jet Propulsion; Fibre-reinforced Plastic; Lifebuoys, 12 Volt Heavy Duty Battery, Rescue Life Jackets, Repair kit, Genset-2KW, First A..', NULL, '3 Months 12 Day', '3,00,000', '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),OEM Annual Turnover *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'Yes', '50% Lowest Priced Technically Qualified Bidders', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '10,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '10,000', NULL, 3, 6, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the hired boats are detailed under three categories: Core, Addon(s), and Additional Details. The core requirements specify the boat must be a Quick Response Vehicle (QRV) Boat, less than 5 years old, with an air-conditioned closed cabin. It needs a seating capacity of 20 and a carrying capacity for accessories of 1000 Kilos. The engine must be a Jet Drive / Jet Propulsion type, and the hull material should be Fibre-reinforced Plastic. The boat must be equipped with life-saving and fire-fighting accessories including Lifebuoys, a 12 Volt Heavy Duty Battery, Rescue Life Jackets, a Repair kit, a 2KW Genset, and a First Aid Box. The Service Provider is responsible for providing the fuel. The addon specifications confirm that Ration is required and Fuel Charges are included if the service provider supplies the fuel. Additional details specify the boat''s dimensions as Width 6.5 feet, Depth 2 feet 9 inch, and Length 22 fit. The draft is new, engine power is 14 HP, weight is 3 Quintal, and speed is 10 Km/h. The area of operation is unlimited, with delivery to the District, and an estimated daily travel distance of 10 Km.', 'Kailash Chandra Rathore', 'Pilibhit', 'This bid document, number GEM/2025/Β/6295926, is for the Hiring of Boats for the Revenue Department of Uttar Pradesh, specifically for the Collectorate Pilibhit. The tender is for 10 Quick Response Vehicle (QRV) Boats for a contract period of 3 months and 12 days, with an operational duration of 100 days. The bid end date is 10-06-2025, and the estimated bid value is INR 1,000,000, with a required EMD of INR 10,000 and an ePBG of 3% for 6 months. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 3 Lakhs over the last three years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. The boats must be less than 5 years old, air-conditioned, and come with a comprehensive set of accessories like life jackets, a repair kit, and a genset. The evaluation method is based on total value, and the bid is enabled for Reverse Auction (RA) among the top 50% of technically qualified bidders. The document also specifies that MSE and MII purchase preferences are applicable and outlines the conditions for the same. Buyer added terms include an option clause to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed from the tender issuer''s perspective, the selected service provider must fulfill the following criteria: The provider must supply 10 Quick Response Vehicle (QRV) Boats that strictly adhere to all technical specifications outlined in the tender, including being less than 5 years old, having air-conditioning, a seating capacity of 20, a 1000 kg carrying capacity, a Jet Drive engine, and a Fibre-reinforced Plastic hull. The boats must be delivered with all specified accessories (Lifebuoys, 12V Battery, Rescue Life Jackets, Repair kit, Genset-2KW, First Aid Box). The service must be rendered for the entire contract period of 3 months and 12 days, covering the specified 100 days of operation for the consignee at Collectorate Pilibhit. The provider is also responsible for supplying fuel and ration as required. Finally, the provider must comply with all terms and conditions of the contract, including the submission of the required Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) and adherence to all GeM and buyer-added clauses.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring and operation of 10 Quick Response Vehicle (QRV) Boats for the Collectorate Pilibhit. The service provider must supply boats that are less than 5 years old, equipped with air-conditioning, have a seating capacity for 20 people, and a carrying capacity of 1000 kg. The boats must have a Fibre-reinforced Plastic hull, be powered by a 14 HP Jet Drive/Jet Propulsion engine, and be capable of a speed of 10 Km/h. The provider is required to equip each boat with essential life-saving and operational accessories, including Lifebuoys, a 12 Volt Heavy Duty Battery, Rescue Life Jackets, a repair kit, a 2KW Genset, and a First Aid Box. The scope also includes the provision of fuel and ration by the service provider. The service is to be provided for a contract period of 3 Months and 12 Days, with a specific requirement of 100 operational days within this period. The place of delivery and operation is within the designated District.'),
(NULL, '10-06-2025 15:00:00', '10-06-2025 15:30:00', '180 Days', 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Basic Education Department Uttar Pradesh', NULL, 'Director Basic Education, Lucknow', 'bsa.bd-up@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 1500 km x 320 hours; Local', NULL, '10 Month', '1,00,00,000', '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', '50% Lowest Priced Technically Qualified Bidders', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '51,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Bank Of Baroda', '1,53,000', 'Yes', 3, 11, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require a SUV vehicle type, with Mahindra Bolero being one of the acceptable car options. The usage variant is specified as 1500 km x 320 hours for a Local type of service. The vehicle model must be from the year 2024, 2022, or 2023, and the total kilometers travelled should be up to 50,000 Kms. The vehicle must be equipped with A/C and will operate in the Plains area. The required fuel type is Diesel.', 'Virendra Kumar Singh', 'Badaun', 'This bid document, number GEM/2025/Β/6296089, is for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 1500 km x 320 hours; Local. The contract period is for 10 months. The tender is issued by the Director Basic Education, Lucknow, under the Basic Education Department of Uttar Pradesh. The bid end date is 10-06-2025 at 15:00:00, with the opening scheduled for 10-06-2025 at 15:30:00. The bid offer validity is 180 days. The estimated bid value is INR 5100000. Eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 100 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. Specifically, bidders must have completed either three similar services costing at least 40% of the estimated cost, two similar services costing at least 50%, or one similar service costing at least 80% of the estimated cost in the last three financial years plus the current year. Exemptions for MSE and Startup on experience and turnover are not applicable. Bidders must submit documents for Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, and a Certificate as requested in the ATC. The procurement will follow a Two Packet Bid system with a Reverse Auction (RA) enabled for the top 50% lowest priced technically qualified bidders. An EMD of INR 153000 is required, with Bank Of Baroda as the advisory bank. The successful bidder must furnish an ePBG of 3.00% of the contract value, valid for 11 months. The beneficiary for EMD and performance security is BSA BADAUN. The evaluation method will be total value wise. The buyer has included an OPTION CLAUSE, allowing for an increase or decrease in contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. The services are required for the consignee Virendra Kumar Singh at BSA OFFICE, CIVIL LINES, BADAUN, with a requirement of 17 vehicles for a duration of 10 months.', 'Successful completion of the contract will be determined by the fulfillment of the following conditions: The contractor must provide 17 SUV vehicles conforming to all technical specifications, including model year (2024, 2022, 2023), maximum kilometers travelled (Upto 50,000 Kms), A/C, and fuel type (Diesel), for the entire contract period of 10 months. The service must be delivered to the specified consignee (Virendra Kumar Singh, 243601, BSA OFFICE, CIVIL LINES, BADAUN). The contractor must adhere to the usage variant of 1500 km x 320 hours per month for each vehicle. The successful bidder is required to submit a performance security (ePBG) of 3.00% for a duration of 11 months. Full compliance with all applicable laws and acts, particularly Labour Laws such as The Minimum Wages Act, 1948, The Payment of Wages Act, 1936, and others as specified, is mandatory, and any non-compliance will be treated as a breach of contract. The contractor must also abide by the GeM General Terms and Conditions, the Service Level Agreement, and the Buyer Added Bid Specific Terms and Conditions, including the OPTION CLAUSE that allows the buyer to alter the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%.', 'The scope of work involves the provision of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services. The contractor is required to supply 17 vehicles of the SUV type, with Mahindra Bolero being an acceptable model. The vehicles must be of the model year 2024, 2022, or 2023, have travelled a maximum of 50,000 Kms, be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C), and run on Diesel. The service is classified as ''Local'' and will be provided in the ''Plains'' area of operation. The specified usage for each vehicle is 1500 km and 320 hours per month. The contract duration is 10 months. The services, including vehicles and drivers, must be provided to the consignee located at BSA OFFICE, CIVIL LINES, BADAUN. The contractor must ensure compliance with all applicable laws, including all Labour Laws as stipulated in the document. The scope is also subject to the OPTION CLAUSE, which allows the buyer to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25 percent.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6296948', '10-06-2025 19:00:00', '10-06-2025 19:30:00', '30 Days', 'Gujarat', 'Home Department Gujarat', 'Surendranagar District Police Office', 'Surendranagar', 'buyer1.sdpo.gj@gembuyer.in', 'Hiring of Safety Consultant', NULL, '2 Months 26 Day', '4,00,000', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '2,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.5, 3, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the Hiring of Safety Consultant detail the requirements for a standalone tunnel project. The consultant is required during the Development Stage and will be deployed Onsite. The project length is specified as 36 *12 FOOT and requires a manpower position of 200000. The key activities to be carried out by the consultant during the Development Phase, Construction Phase, and Operation and Maintenance Phase are all defined as ACCUPRESSURE TRACK.', 'Solanki Rajendrasinh Bhikhusinh', 'Surendranagar', 'This bid, with number GEM/2025/B/6296948, is for the ''Hiring of Safety Consultant'' by the Surendranagar District Police Office, Gujarat. The contract period is 2 months and 26 days, with an estimated bid value of INR 200,000. This is a two-packet bid requiring a minimum average annual turnover of 4 Lakhs and past experience, though exemptions are available for MSEs and Startups. A 0.50% e-Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) is required for 3 months. The bid includes provisions for MII Compliance and MSE Purchase Preference. The technical scope specifies an onsite consultant for a standalone tunnel project, responsible for ''ACCUPRESSURE TRACK'' activities during the development, construction, and operation phases. Important buyer-added terms include an option clause to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25% and a condition that the service provider must pay salaries to their staff before claiming reimbursement from the buyer, ensuring full compliance with all applicable labor laws.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be deemed successfully completed upon fulfillment of the following criteria: 1. The deployment of the Safety Consultant at the specified location for the entire contract duration of 2 months and 26 days. 2. Satisfactory completion of all activities as defined in the technical specifications, specifically the ''ACCUPRESSURE TRACK'' tasks across the development, construction, and operation phases. 3. Full compliance with all applicable labor laws for the deployed personnel, evidenced by the submission of statutory documents like PF, ESIC, and bank statements showing salary payments to staff. 4. Adherence to all buyer-added terms and conditions, general terms and conditions, and service level agreements stipulated in the bid document.', 'The scope of work involves providing the services of one (1) Safety Consultant for a total duration of 2 months and 26 days. The consultant must be deployed onsite at the consignee''s location, the Office of Superintendent of Police, Surendranagar. The work is for a standalone tunnel project with a specified length of 36 *12 FOOT. The consultant''s core responsibilities include carrying out ''ACCUPRESSURE TRACK'' activities during the Development Phase, Construction Phase, and Operation and Maintenance Phase of the project. A manpower position of 200000 is required for the role. The service provider is responsible for all aspects of the consultant''s employment, including the timely payment of salaries and wages and ensuring compliance with all statutory labor laws.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6298889', '13-06-2025 17:00:00', '13-06-2025 17:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Coal', 'Coal India Limited', 'South Eastern Coalfields Limited', 'Secl Bilaspur Chhattisgarh', 'chandeshwar.dayal@coalindia.in', 'Facility Management Services - LumpSum Based - Hiring 03 Nos of 10 KVA Silent Diesel Generator set or above rating for providing power backup to Boom Barrier and Weighbridges during the monsoon period at Jamuna Kotma Area SECL; Hiring 03 Nos of 10 KV..', NULL, '4 Month', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '12,06,689', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'State Bank of India', '15,100', NULL, 5, 12, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the Core facility management services require the Hiring of 03 Nos of 10 KVA Silent Diesel Generator set or above rating for providing power backup to Boom Barrier and Weighbridges during the monsoon period at Jamuna Kotma Area SECL. This description applies to the Type of Premises, the Type of services required, and the Service component. Regarding the Cost for Consumables/Materials, Consumables are to be provided by the service provider (inclusive in contract cost). Under Addon(s), the Input Tax Credit (ITC) details indicate 100% ITC on GST and NA for ITC on GST Cess.', 'Chandreshwar Dayal', 'Anupur', 'This is a GeM Bid (Bid Number: GEM/2025/B/6298889) issued by South Eastern Coalfields Limited (SECL), a subsidiary of Coal India Limited, under the Ministry of Coal. The work involves Facility Management Services on a LumpSum Basis for the hiring of 03 Nos of 10 KVA Silent Diesel Generator sets (or above rating) with 03 skilled manpower to provide power backup to Boom Barrier, Weighbridges, and IVTS server room at Area HQ (Jamuna Kotma Area) during the monsoon period. The contract period is 4 months (120 days). The estimated bid value is INR 12,06,689 with a Bid End Date of 13-06-2025 at 17:00:00. An Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of INR 15,100 and an ePBG of 5.00% are required. The DG sets must be deployed 24 hours a day. Diesel charges are payable based on consumption @3 ltrs./hr for 10 KVA DG set. A penalty of Rs. 1000.00 per day applies for non-deployment. The specific locations for installation are Amadand OCM, Govinda Siding, and I T server room Area HQ.', 'The work shall be considered successfully completed when the Contractor gives notice of completion of work, the Engineer-in-Charge or nominated officer inspects the work within 30 days and ascertains that no defects/deficiencies exist, and issues a Completion Certificate / Defect Liability Certificate indicating the date of completion. Additionally, on completion of the work, all rubbish, debris, brick bats etc. shall be removed by the contractor(s) at his/their own expense and the site cleaned and handed over to the company.', 'Name of Work- Deployment of 03 nos (10KVA DG set or above) with 03 nos skilled manpower on rental basis for providing power to weigh bridge/ boom barrier and IVTS server room Area HQ in case of power failure. DG sets should be deployed 24 hour for 120 days (04 months). Locations where Silent DG set will be installed on hiring basis are :- Amadand OCM, Govinda Siding and I T server room Area HQ. 1. Operation, operational maintenance and repair, shifting of DG set from one location to another as per requirement as and when required basis. Both DG sets shall be stationed near Boom Barrier or weighbridges and it should be available with diesel for immediate start when required. 2. Deployment of 03 nos. skilled manpower for operation/maintenance including of DG sets at Said location. Penalty: - In case of non-deployment of DG set at desired location, an amount of Rs. 1000.00 per day will be deducted as a penalty in addition to the proportion deduction in hiring charges for absenteeism. Note: - Diesel charges for DG set will be paid as per consumption/use of diesel @3 ltrs./hr for 10 KVA DG set.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6298912', '16-06-2025 09:00:00', '16-06-2025 09:30:00', '45 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Army', '***********', 'barkatia@nic.in', 'Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs, Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs', NULL, '9 Months 4 Day', '3,00,000', '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'Yes', '50% Lowest Priced Technically Qualified Bidders', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The tender requires two types of short-term cab and taxi hiring services. The first service is for four Sedan vehicles for local use with a package of 80Kms x 10Hrs. The acceptable car types are Maruti Suzuki Dzire, Hyundai Xcent, or Toyota Etios, from the model years 2020, 2021, 2022, or 2023, having travelled up to 25,000 Kms. These sedans must be Non-A/C and operate in Plains areas. The fuel type can be any, outstation night charges are applicable, and trips can be one-way. The second service is for one SUV vehicle, also for local use under an 80Kms x 10Hrs package. The required models are Mahindra Scorpio or Mahindra XUV 500 from the years 2020, 2021, 2022, or 2023, with mileage up to 25,000 Kms. This SUV must be A/C and operate in Hilly + Plain Areas. The fuel type can be any, outstation night charges are applicable, and trips are considered one-way.', '***********', 'Pithoragarh', 'This is a tender (Bid Number: GEM/2025/Β/6298912) issued by the Indian Army, Ministry of Defence, for the procurement of Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for both Sedan and SUV categories. The bid ends on 16-06-2025 at 09:00:00, with a contract period of 9 months and 4 days. The services are required in Pithoragarh, and bidders must have a geographic presence in Pithoragarh and Champawat. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 3 Lakhs for the last three years and 3 years of past experience. There is no exemption for MSEs or Startups on these criteria. The evaluation method will be total value wise, and a Reverse Auction will be conducted among the first 50% of lowest-priced technically qualified bidders. The tender specifies the need for 4 Sedans (Non-A/C) and 1 SUV (A/C) for a local usage package of 80Kms x 10Hrs. Additional qualifications include the bidder owning a fleet of at least 10 vehicles and having 5 drivers on payroll. The buyer has included an option clause to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. No EMD or ePBG is required for this bid. The bid mandates compliance with MII and gives preference to MSEs.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed, the service provider must provide the specified number of vehicles (4 Sedans and 1 SUV) for the required duration (10 days for Sedans, 2 days for SUVs within the contract period) at the designated location in Pithoragarh. The supplied vehicles must strictly adhere to all technical specifications, including vehicle type (Sedan/SUV), specific models (e.g., Maruti Dzire, Mahindra Scorpio), model year (2020-2023), mileage (Upto 25,000 Kms), and air conditioning requirements (Non-A/C for Sedan, A/C for SUV). The service must be consistently available as per the 80Kms x 10Hrs local usage package and operate within the specified areas (Plains for Sedans, Hilly + Plain for SUVs). The provider must ensure compliance with all contractual terms, including the buyer''s option clause and all applicable laws, particularly labor laws, throughout the contract period.', 'The scope of work involves providing Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for a contract period of 9 months and 4 days in Pithoragarh, Uttarakhand. The service is divided into two categories:
1. Sedan Vehicle Service: To provide 4 Sedan vehicles of models such as Maruti Suzuki Dzire, Hyundai Xcent, or Toyota Etios. The vehicles must be of the model year 2020, 2021, 2022, or 2023, be Non-A/C, and have travelled up to 25,000 Kms. The service is for local use under an 80Kms x 10Hrs package for a duration of 10 days within the contract period. The area of operation is Plains.
2. SUV Vehicle Service: To provide 1 SUV vehicle of models such as Mahindra Scorpio or Mahindra XUV 500. The vehicle must be of the model year 2020, 2021, 2022, or 2023, be A/C equipped, and have travelled up to 25,000 Kms. This service is also for local use under an 80Kms x 10Hrs package for a duration of 2 days within the contract period. The area of operation is Hilly + Plain Area.
For both services, outstation night charges are applicable, trips are considered one-way, and any fuel type is acceptable. The service provider is expected to have a fleet of 10 owned vehicles, 5 drivers on payroll, and a minimum of 3 years of experience with a business presence in Pithoragarh and Champawat. Any extra usage beyond the specified package will be charged as per RTO rates.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6299292', '16-06-2025 13:00:00', '16-06-2025 13:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Petroleum And Natural Gas', 'Bharat Petroleum Corporation Ltd', 'Bharat Petroleum Corporation Ltd', 'Aonla Depot', 'buycon449.bpcl.up@gembuyer.in', 'Hiring Of Agency For ISO Certification Service - ISO 9001 - Quality Management System (QMS), ISO 14001 - Environmental Management System (EMS), ISO 45001 - Occupational Health & Safety Management System (OHAS); Consulting, Initial Audit, Surveillance..', NULL, '3 Year', '3,00,000', '5 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC), OEM Authorization Certificate *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '3,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the hiring of an agency for ISO certification service require certification for ISO 9001 - Quality Management System (QMS), ISO 14001 - Environmental Management System (EMS), and ISO 45001 - Occupational Health & Safety Management System (OHAS). The required services include Consulting, Initial Audit, Surveillance Audit, and Re-certification Audit. The scope of work involves conducting workshops on ISO certification awareness for employees, providing guidance for documentation and implementation, training programs, framing relevant policies and objectives, and offering internal auditor training for Management Representatives. The agency must provide an ISO certification expert with knowledge expertise and a post-graduate degree in a relevant field, holding Lead Auditor and Lead Implementer certificates. The professional resources should have a total experience of 3 to 5 years. The service is to be deployed onsite, requires post-service support, and necessitates one consultant.', 'Naresh', 'Aonla', 'This bid, GEM/2025/B/6299292, is for the hiring of an agency for ISO Certification Services for Bharat Petroleum Corporation Ltd (BPCL) at their Aonla Depot. The scope includes certification for ISO 9001 (QMS), ISO 14001 (EMS), and ISO 45001 (OHAS), along with consulting, initial audits, and surveillance audits over a 3-year contract period. The estimated bid value is INR 300,000. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 3 Lakhs over the last three years and 5 years of past experience in similar services. The successful bidder will be responsible for conducting a gap analysis, internal auditor training, a two-stage certification audit, and two annual surveillance audits. Key deliverables include audit reports within 7 days of each audit and a valid NABCB accredited certificate for the Aonla Depot. The tender specifies a two-packet bid system with a total value-wise evaluation method. The contract includes special conditions such as the certifying agency must be NABCB accredited, have experience with Major Hazardous Industry (MHI), and adhere to strict timelines, with a penalty clause for delays. Payment will be made via NEFT within 15 days of successful completion of milestones and submission of invoices.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer, the work is considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of several key criteria. Primarily, the successful bidder must conduct all required audits, including gap analysis, internal auditor training, initial certification audit (Stage 1 and Stage 2), and subsequent annual surveillance audits. Following the audits, the agency must submit a detailed Audit Report within 7 working days of each audit''s completion. The ultimate success criterion is the issuance of a valid National Accreditation Board for Certification Bodies (NABCB) accredited certificate for AONLA DEPOT for ISO 9001:2015, ISO 11001:2015, and ISO 15001:2018 standards within 7 working days after the completion of the final audit. Successful completion also hinges on adhering to the specified timelines, such as completing the IMS Certification audit within 15 days and Internal Auditor''s training within 30 days from the issuance of the LOI/PO, and the submission of all required records and GST compliant invoices for payment processing.', 'The scope of work is for the Integrated Management System (IMS) Recertification at Aonla Depot. The work involves providing certification for ISO 9001:2015, ISO 11001:2015, and ISO 15001:2018 standards. The key activities include: 1. Conducting a Gap Analysis and Final Certification audit, which includes visits of auditors for the first stage audit and second stage audit, with lodging and boarding charges included. 2. Providing Internal Auditor''s training for Aonla Depot personnel, which can be conducted online. 3. Performing a Surveillance audit after one year and a second Surveillance audit after the second year. The detailed process includes conducting a GAP Audit of all ISO standards, arranging Internal Auditor Training Programme, conducting the first stage audit (document review) and second stage audit (Certification Audit, Technical Review), and suggesting corrective actions for any NCR''s or observations. The certification and surveillance audits must be carried out physically at the BPCL Aonla Depot, located at village Noopur, near Aonla Railway station, Uttar Pradesh, which handles receipt, storage, and distribution of petroleum products. The deliverables are an Audit Report to be submitted within 7 working days of each audit''s completion and the final Certificate to be issued within 7 working days of the final audit''s completion. The entire job must be completed within 15 days from the date of issuance of the PO/LOI for the initial certification.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6299545', '18-06-2025 11:00:00', '18-06-2025 11:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Coal', 'Coal India Limited', 'South Eastern Coalfields Limited', 'Secl Bilaspur Chhattisgarh', 'secldipka.soenm@coalindia.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Deployment on hiring basis of 06 nos mobile lighting tower with on-board silent DG set, mounted on Bolero Camper /Utility Van /suitable motor vehicle Chassis for providing mobile illumination facility at various places at Di..', 'Leasing Service of DG-Set; Operation and Maintenance Services of Power Generator(DG-Set)', '1 Year', '24,00,000', '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '7 Days', NULL, '77,56,347', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'State Bank of India', '97,000', 'Yes', 5, 15, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Applicable', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require the deployment of 06 mobile lighting towers on a hiring basis, each equipped with an on-board silent DG set and mounted on a suitable motor vehicle such as a Bolero Camper or Utility Van, to provide mobile illumination at the Dipka Expansion Project. The service must be fully compliant with all regulatory and statutory requirements, as well as the terms outlined in the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA). Broader technical standards for related activities mandate the adoption of the latest CPWD specifications for Civil and Electrical Engineering Works, and the Ministry of Surface Transport (MORTH) specifications for roads and bridges, all conforming to the adopted DSR/SOR of CIL/Subsidiary.', 'Pramod.C', 'Korba', 'This GeM (Government e-Marketplace) bid document, number GEM/2025/B/6299545, is issued by South Eastern Coalfields Limited (SECL) for a one-year contract for the deployment of six mobile lighting towers on a hiring basis at the Dipka Expansion Project. The estimated value of the contract is INR 7,756,347. The bid follows a Two Packet Bid system and requires bidders to have a minimum average annual turnover of 24 Lakhs over the last three years and at least three years of past experience in similar services. The scope of work involves providing six vehicle-mounted mobile lighting towers with on-board silent DG sets and operators for night-time illumination. The contract is governed by detailed General and Special Conditions of Contract, which cover aspects such as performance security (5% of contract value), payment terms, defect liability, safety codes, and an integrity pact. The document outlines all procedural, eligibility, technical, and commercial requirements for participation in the tender.', 'The work will be considered successfully completed after the contractor provides a formal notice of completion to the Engineer-in-Charge. An inspection will then be conducted within 30 days to verify that all work has been executed as per the contract and to identify any defects. Successful completion is contingent upon the rectification of any major defects to the satisfaction of the Engineer-in-Charge. A Defect Liability Certificate, or a Taking Over Certificate with a list of minor defects, will then be issued, marking the official date of completion. Additionally, the contractor must clear the work site of all debris, surplus materials, and temporary structures. The final acceptance requires the contractor to hand over all deliverables, including necessary documentation like as-built drawings, maintenance manuals, and statutory clearances, and to restore any affected auxiliary services. The contractor is also obligated to remedy any defects that appear within the six-month Defect Liability Period following completion.', 'The scope of work entails the deployment on a rental basis of 06 mobile lighting towers for a one-year period to provide illumination at various locations within the Dipka Expansion Project. Each unit must be mounted on a suitable vehicle (like a Bolero Camper/Utility Van) and equipped with a minimum 8-meter high, hydraulically operated, 360-degree rotatable telescopic mast. Each tower must have an on-board silent DG set with a minimum rating of 7.5 KVA, 230 Volt, single phase, and be fitted with at least 8 LED floodlights of 250 Watts each (or equivalent). The service includes operation, operational maintenance, repair, and shifting of the entire unit as and when required. The specified time of deployment is from 6 PM to 6 AM, with adjustments for seasonal variations from sunset to sunrise. The contractor is responsible for providing diesel for both the vehicle and the DG set. The vehicles provided must not be more than 2 years old, must be in good road-worthy condition with all statutory documents, and the deployed driver-cum-operator must be VTC trained with a valid driving license.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6300931', '16-06-2025 12:00:00', '16-06-2025 12:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'Eastern Railway', 'Eastern Railway Hq', 'dycmmg@er.railnet.gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2500 km x 720 hours; Local 24*7', NULL, '1 Year 3 Months 2 Day', NULL, '2 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '6,34,800', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', NULL, 'No', 5, 17, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require an SUV type vehicle for a monthly hiring service. The acceptable models include Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra XUV 500, Maruti Suzuki Vitara Brezza, Hyundai Creta, Renault Duster, Mahindra Scorpio, Mahindra Bolero, Mahindra Marazzo, KIA Carens, KIA Seltos, and Mahindra Bolero Neo. The usage variant is 2500 km x 720 hours for a Local 24*7 service. The vehicle must be a 2023, 2024, or 2025 model with travel under 25,000 Kms. A Non-A/C vehicle is required for operation in Plains, and it can use any fuel type. There are no add-ons specified.', 'Varun Kumar', 'Howrah', 'This bid, number GEM/2025/B/6300931, issued by the Eastern Railway Hq of the Ministry of Railways, is for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for one SUV. The contract period is 1 Year, 3 Months, and 2 Days, with a required past experience of 2 years in similar services. The estimated bid value is 634800, and it is a Single Packet Bid with a total value-wise evaluation method. No EMD is required, but an ePBG of 5.00% is mandated for a duration of 17 months. The service is required in West Bengal for the consignee Varun Kumar at the office of DY.CSTE/WORKS/ HOWRAH for a duration of 15 months. Key conditions include the provision of a vehicle with all necessary permits and licenses, a polite and uniformed driver, and adherence to a 24/7 service schedule including weekends and holidays. The contractor must have an office in the consignee''s state and is subject to penalties for service deficiencies as per the GeM contract. The buyer retains an option to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following criteria: 1. Consistent and uninterrupted provision of the specified SUV in a good, clean, and hygienic condition for the entire contract period. 2. The vehicle must possess and maintain all necessary legal documents, including fitness certificate, PUC, full comprehensive insurance, road permit, and commercial registration certificate at all times. 3. Adherence to the ''Round the Cloak Services'' requirement, ensuring the vehicle and driver are available 24/7, including Saturdays, Sundays, and holidays, as directed. 4. The contractor must provide a polite, courteous, alert driver in a white uniform who is equipped with a working mobile phone. 5. Immediate arrangement of a suitable substitute vehicle and driver in case of any unavailability, with prior information provided to the user. 6. Full compliance with all service-related instructions and statutory laws, including all applicable Labour Laws. 7. The service must be delivered without any deficiencies that would attract penalties under the GeM contract.', 'The scope of work involves providing one SUV type vehicle on a monthly hiring basis for ''Round the Cloak Services'' (24/7) for the official use of Dy.CSTE/WORKS/HWH/ER or other high officials of the Government of India. The service package includes a monthly usage of 2500 km and 720 hours. The vehicle must be a 2023-2025 model with mileage under 25,000 Kms. Acceptable models include Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra XUV 500, Hyundai Creta, among others. The vehicle must have all necessary permits, licenses, PUC, fitness certificate, and full comprehensive insurance. It should be kept clean and hygienic and display a red board stating ''On duty, Government of India''. The contractor must provide a polite, courteous, and alert driver wearing a white uniform and equipped with a working mobile phone. The driver is responsible for assisting with luggage and ensuring passenger safety. The service area covers the entire jurisdiction of Eastern Railway and beyond, with no extra payment for outstation travel. The service is required on all days, including Saturdays, Sundays, and holidays. The contractor must provide an immediate replacement vehicle if the regular one is unavailable and must visit the user for document verification within three days of the contract award.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6301148', '17-06-2025 18:00:00', '17-06-2025 18:30:00', '180 Days', 'Gujarat', 'Social Justice And Empowerment Department Gujarat', 'N/a', 'District Social Defence Office Bharuch', 'buycon72.sjedg.gj@gembuyer.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Hatchback; 2500 km x 320 hours; Outstation 24*7', NULL, '11 Months 5 Day', '6,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '3,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, 5, 14, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require a Hatchback vehicle for monthly cab and taxi hiring services. The acceptable car models include Maruti Suzuki Celerio, Maruti Suzuki Swift, Hyundai i10, Hyundai i20, Tata Tiago, Datsun Go, and Tata Bolt. The vehicle''s model year should be between 2020 and 2025, and it must have travelled up to 50,000 Kms. The service is for an ''Outstation 24*7'' usage variant, covering a package of 2500 km and 320 hours. The vehicle is required to be Non-A/C and can run on any fuel type. The area of operation includes both Hilly and Plain areas. There are no addons specified.', 'Christian Vivian', 'Bharuch', 'This is a bid (GEM/2025/B/6301148) issued by the District Social Defence Office Bharuch, under the Social Justice And Empowerment Department of Gujarat, for the procurement of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services''. The specific requirement is for a Hatchback vehicle for a usage package of 2500 km and 320 hours per month for Outstation 24*7 service. The contract period is 11 months and 5 days, with an estimated bid value of INR 300,000. Bidders must have a minimum average annual turnover of 6 Lakhs for the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services, although exemptions are available for MSE and Startup entities. A performance bank guarantee (ePBG) of 5.00% is required for a duration of 14 months. The bid is a Two Packet Bid, and evaluation will be on a total value wise basis. Additional qualifications require the bidder to have at least one owned vehicle, one driver on payroll, and a minimum of 3 years of experience in the related field. The service provider must also have an office in Gujarat, the state of the consignee. The service is required for the District Child Protection Society in Bharuch.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the successful completion of the work will be agreed upon based on the fulfillment of the following criteria: The service provider must consistently and uninterruptedly supply one specified Hatchback vehicle (from the approved list of models and year of manufacture) for the entire contract duration of 11 months and 5 days. The vehicle must be available for Outstation 24*7 duty and must meet the monthly usage requirements of 2500 km and 320 hours. The vehicle''s condition must adhere to the specified maximum of 50,000 Kms travelled at the start of the contract. The provider must ensure compliance with all contractual terms, including maintaining a service office in Gujarat and adhering to all applicable labor laws for their staff.', 'The scope of work is to provide one Hatchback vehicle on a monthly hiring basis for the District Child Protection Society in Bharuch, Gujarat. The service is required for a contract period of 11 months and 5 days. The vehicle must be one of the following models: Maruti Suzuki Celerio, Maruti Suzuki Swift, Hyundai i10, Hyundai i20, Tata Tiago, Datsun Go, or Tata Bolt, with a manufacturing year between 2020 and 2025. The vehicle must have travelled a maximum of 50,000 Kms and be non-air-conditioned. The service entails an ''Outstation 24*7'' availability with a monthly usage package of 2500 kilometers and 320 hours. The vehicle should be suitable for operation in both Hilly and Plain areas. The service provider is responsible for providing the vehicle and a driver on their payroll, and must maintain a service office within the state of Gujarat. The rate for any extra kilometers beyond the specified package will be as per the uploaded ATC.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6301157', '20-06-2025 14:00:00', '20-06-2025 14:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Power', 'Contracts And Materials', 'Damodar Valley Corporation', 'Damodar Valley Corporation', 'jayabrata.biswas@dvc.gov.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - Hiring of 12 nos of Petrol driven white coloured Maruti Suzuki Ciaz', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services', '6 Month', '16,85,722', '7 Years', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '7 Days', NULL, '56,19,072', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'PUNJAB NATIONAL BANK', '1,12,381', 'Yes', 3, 8, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require the hiring of 12 petrol-driven, white-coloured Maruti Suzuki Ciaz vehicles. The service must maintain regulatory and statutory compliance. Furthermore, it must be in full compliance with the Scope of Work (SOW), Special Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA) as outlined in the tender documents.', 'Gautam Kumar', 'Kolkata', 'This GeM bid (GEM/2025/B/6301157), issued by Damodar Valley Corporation, Ministry of Power, is for a custom service contract for the hiring of 12 petrol-driven, white-coloured Maruti Suzuki Ciaz vehicles on a monthly basis. The contract period is for 6 months with an estimated value of 56,190,72.00. The bid follows a two-packet system with a reverse auction, and requires an Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of 1,12,381 and a Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 3% for a duration of 8 months. The tender provides exemptions for Micro and Small Enterprises (MSEs) and Startups from the experience and turnover criteria, and also includes MSE purchase preference. The scope involves providing vehicles not older than five years with valid commercial registration for the use of Executive Directors at DVC, HQ, Kolkata. The contractor is responsible for all operational costs including fuel, maintenance, insurance, taxes, and driver salaries, while adhering to all statutory laws. Payment terms are based on the actual kilometers run, with a minimum guaranteed run of 12,000 km per vehicle over the six-month period. The tender outlines specific penalties for service deficiencies such as late or non-reporting of vehicles and lays down detailed qualifying requirements for bidders, including technical experience and financial turnover criteria.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer (DVC), the work will be deemed successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following criteria:
1. Consistent and timely deployment of the specified 12 Maruti Suzuki Ciaz vehicles, meeting all conditions regarding age, model, color, fuel type, and registration for the entire 6-month contract period.
2. Ensuring all vehicles are maintained in perfect running condition at all times, with immediate provision of a suitable substitute vehicle in case of any breakdown or withdrawal from service.
3. Full and continuous compliance with all statutory requirements, including the submission and renewal of valid documents like insurance, pollution certificates, fitness certificates, and road tax for all vehicles.
4. Meticulous maintenance and submission of daily LOG Books for each vehicle, accurately recording all journey details and duly certified by the availing DVC officials.
5. Adherence to all service level agreements, including the provision of well-trained, licensed, and properly dressed drivers who are paid minimum wages as per government regulations.
6. Successful completion of the contract period followed by a final reconciliation of all accounts, including adjustments for minimum guaranteed kilometers, penalties, and outstanding dues.
7. Issuance of a ''No Dues / No Objection Certificate'' by the Protocol & Liaison Officer, which confirms that the contractor has fulfilled all contractual obligations satisfactorily, thereby clearing the way for final payment.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring of 12 petrol-driven, white-coloured Maruti Suzuki Ciaz (Smart Sigma Hybrid) vehicles, or equivalent models with an engine capacity between 1462cc and 1600cc. These vehicles must have AC operation and valid commercial registration and should not be older than five years from the date of the NIT. The service is required for performing the duties of Executive Directors (EDs) at DVC, HQ, Kolkata, for a period of six (06) months or until a new contract is finalized.

The contractor''s responsibilities include:
1.  **Vehicle Provision:** Supplying 12 vehicles that are mechanically perfect and equipped with a spare wheel, a set of tools, and a First Aid Box.
2.  **Operational Hours:** The normal duty will be nine (09) hours per day. The vehicles are to be available on almost all working days, and may be required on Saturdays, Sundays, and holidays if necessary.
3.  **Guaranteed Run:** A minimum guaranteed run of 12,000 km is set for each vehicle for the entire six-month contract period.
4.  **Costs and Maintenance:** The contractor shall bear all expenses related to the vehicles, including fuel, lubricants, spares, maintenance, repairs, servicing, driver wages, insurance premiums, permits, and all applicable taxes and duties. However, Toll Tax and Parking Charges will be reimbursed at actuals upon submission of documentary evidence.
5.  **Driver Requirements:** Engaging well-trained drivers who possess a valid Public Service Driving License for commercial vehicles. Drivers must adhere to a neat and clean dress code featuring the DVC logo.
6.  **Compliance and Safety:** The contractor is responsible for the safe travel, punctuality, and comfort of the passengers. All statutory provisions applicable to providing commercial car hiring services must be complied with.
7.  **Documentation:** Maintaining a set of LOG Books for each vehicle to record details of every journey, which must be certified by the contractor and endorsed by the availing DVC officials. These logs must be deposited with DVC upon contract expiry.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6301186', '18-06-2025 10:00:00', '18-06-2025 10:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Coal', 'Coal India Limited', 'South Eastern Coalfields Limited', 'Secl Bilaspur Chhattisgarh', 'parul.agarwal@coalindia.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab and Taxi Hiring Service - Without Fuel - SUV; Mahindra Bolero /Bolero Neo/Thar Roxx or Equivalent; The age of vehicle shall not be not more than 2 years from the scheduled date of opening of Tender and shall be counted from the dat.. , Monthly Basis Cab and Taxi Hiring Service - Without Fuel - MUV; Mahindra Bolero camper or Equivalent; The age of vehicle shall not be not more than 2 years from the scheduled date of opening of Tender and shall be counted from the date of 1st registr..', NULL, '3 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC)', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '7 Days', NULL, '1,55,63,71,841', 'Item wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'State Bank of India', '1,97,00,02,49,20,03,48,500', NULL, 5, 39, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the Monthly Basis Cab and Taxi Hiring Service require vehicles across three schedules. For the SUV category (Schedules 1 and 3), the vehicle type is SUV, specified as Mahindra Bolero /Bolero Neo/Thar Roxx or Equivalent, with Air Conditioning (A/C). The engagement hours per day are 24. For the MUV category (Schedule 2), the vehicle type is MUV, specified as Mahindra Bolero camper or Equivalent, with Air Conditioning (A/C), and engagement hours per day are 12. Across all schedules, the Fuel type is Diesel, the Type of Terrain is Plain and Hilly, and a Driver is required. Fuel is to be provided by the Buyer via reimbursement to the Service Provider as per actual consumption. Regarding the Years of Vehicle Model, the age of the vehicle shall not be more than 2 years from the scheduled date of opening of Tender and shall be counted from the date of 1st registration of the vehicle. Vintage in KM is listed as As Per NIT.', 'Parul Kumar Agrawal', 'Baikunthpur', 'This GeM Bid Document (Bid Number: GEM/2025/B/6301186), issued by South Eastern Coalfields Limited (Ministry of Coal) for the SECL Bilaspur Chhattisgarh office, invites bids for Monthly Basis Cab and Taxi Hiring Services. The contract involves hiring 5 vehicles in total, split into three schedules: Schedule 1 requires 2 SUVs (24 hours/day), Schedule 2 requires 2 MUVs (12 hours/day), and Schedule 3 requires 1 SUV (24 hours/day), all with A/C and drivers, for a contract period of 3 years. The estimated bid value is INR 15,563,718.41. The bid end date is 18-06-2025. Bidders must provide an EMD (Schedule 1: INR 97000, Schedule 2: INR 49200, Schedule 3: INR 48500) and a 5% ePBG. Past experience in similar services is required, with no exemptions for MSEs or Startups regarding years of experience/turnover. The document outlines General Conditions of Contract, Service Level Agreements, and specific Additional Terms and Conditions including vehicle age limits (not more than 2 years), fuel reimbursement policies, and statutory compliance requirements.', 'The work is considered successfully completed when the contractor has provided the hiring services for the full contract period (3 years) as per the schedule, executed the work satisfactorily in every respect, rectified any defects/deficiencies detected within the defect liability period (if applicable), and obtained a Completion Certificate/Defect Liability Certificate from the Engineer-in-Charge. The final bill is settled, and the Security Deposit is refunded upon satisfactory performance and issuance of the No Defect Certificate/Completion Certificate.', 'The Scope of Work involves the Monthly Basis Cab and Taxi Hiring Service for South Eastern Coalfields Limited (SECL), specifically for the CISF of Baikunthpur Area, for a contract period of 3 years. The work consists of three slices: Slice 1 involves hiring 02 Nos LMV under SUV Category with AC (Mahindra Bolero /Bolero Neo/Thar Roxx or Equivalent) for 24 hours per day (03 Shifts), with an average running of 2500 km per month per vehicle. Slice 2 involves hiring 02 Nos Multi Utility Vehicle [MUV] Category with AC (Mahindra Bolero camper or Equivalent) for 12 hours per day (01 Shift), with an average running of 2500 km per month per vehicle. Slice 3 involves hiring 01 Nos LMV under SUV Category with AC (Mahindra Bolero /Bolero Neo/Thar Roxx or Equivalent) for 24 hours per day (03 Shifts), with an average running of 3000 km per month per vehicle. The contractor must provide vehicles not older than 2 years from the date of tender opening, inclusive of drivers, maintenance, repair, insurance, and taxes. Fuel costs are reimbursed based on actual consumption and specified fuel efficiency. The contractor is responsible for deploying skilled drivers, maintaining log books, ensuring statutory compliance (including minimum wages, bonus, PF, biometric attendance), and providing substitute vehicles in case of breakdown to ensure uninterrupted service.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6301653', '17-06-2025 19:00:00', '17-06-2025 19:30:00', '180 Days', 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Information And Public Relations Department Uttar Pradesh', 'N/a', 'Head Office', 'ashok.69547@gov.in', 'Hiring of Creative Agency - AS PER RFP; AS PER RFP; AS PER RFP; AS PER RFP; AS PER RFP; AS PER RFP; AS PER RFP; AS PER RFP', NULL, '1 Year', '4,00,00,000', '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '3 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '5,00,000', NULL, 5, 15, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'No', '09-06-2025 16:00:00', 'Lucknow', 'The technical specifications for the Hiring of a Creative Agency require that the Core, DAVP Vendors required, Type of Services, Print Ads, TV, Web, Radio, Outdoor, Other Creatives, and Language Versions all be ''AS PER RFP''. The specification for State is listed as ''NA''. In the additional details section, the ''Number of Pages (In case of other creatives)'', ''Specify language of master version'', and ''Please provide concept/theme/location or any other qualitative description of scope of services required for the deliverable selected'' are all specified as ''NA''.', 'Ashok Kumar Singh', 'Lucknow', 'This document is a Bid Document (GEM/2025/B/6301653) issued by the Information And Public Relations Department of Uttar Pradesh for the ''Hiring of Creative Agency''. The contract period is for 1 year with a Bid Offer Validity of 180 days. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 400 Lakhs for the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. The bid is a Two Packet type, and evaluation will be based on a total value wise evaluation. An EMD of 500,000 INR is required, along with an ePBG of 5.00% for 15 months. The bid specifies MII Compliance is required, but MSE Purchase Preference is not. The selection process follows a Quality and Cost-Based Selection (QCBS) method with 70% weightage given to the technical score and 30% to the financial score. Bidders must score a minimum of 70 out of 100 in the technical evaluation to be considered for financial bid opening. The technical evaluation covers criteria such as annual turnover, past projects, team structure, and a technical presentation. The scope of work involves providing comprehensive creative services, including conceptualizing, designing, and producing various media assets like print ads, videos, radio jingles, and digital content to publicize the schemes and initiatives of the Government of Uttar Pradesh. The contract includes a penalty clause for delays, with Liquidated Damages (LD) of 1% per week up to a maximum of 10% of the contract value. Payments will be made on a monthly basis based on satisfactory performance and work achievement, which will be verified by a DIPR committee.', 'The work is considered successfully completed based on the verification and validation of all work and reports submitted by the agency. This assessment is conducted by a designated DIPR Committee, chaired by the Director of Information. Successful completion is contingent upon the agency''s satisfactory performance and work achievement against the Scope of Work defined in the tender. Monthly payments are released only after this successful monthly assessment. The final mark of successful completion for the entire contract is signified by the return of the Performance Guarantee to the agency after the satisfactory completion of the job and after adjusting for any recoverable dues.', 'The scope of work for the Creative Agency involves conceptualizing, designing, and producing a wide range of artwork, creatives, and media assets for the Government of Uttar Pradesh. This includes content creation for various programs and projects in all media forms, such as television, radio, outdoor, print, and digital media. The agency must conduct research for creative inputs, design and create multi-media campaign dissemination strategies, and develop specific execution materials, with the ability to translate content into regional languages. The deliverables include media materials like jingles, cinema ads, short films, documentaries, and interactive shows; pre-press work for print materials like brochures, booklets, posters, and calendars; scripts for testimonials and ads; materials for online and mobile dissemination; and presentations and collaterals for conferences and exhibitions. The agency will also handle artwork for brand identity across websites, digital ads, and merchandise. The role extends to conducting photo/video shoots, translating creative assets from Hindi to English and other regional languages, and managing a list of indicative media assets such as 360 Print Ads, 156 Video Films, and 52 Radio Jingles annually. Furthermore, the agency is responsible for daily creative content generation, repackaging content into various formats like graphics and videos, conceptualizing innovative campaigns, storing all raw and processed content in a searchable DMS to be handed over to DIPR at the end of the contract, and providing support for hardware/software functioning. All intellectual property rights for the creations will vest with DIPR.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6302384', '17-06-2025 17:00:00', '17-06-2025 17:30:00', '30 Days', 'Ministry Of Steel', 'Mstc Limited', 'Mstc Limited', 'Mstc Limited', 'buycon33.mstc.lko@gembuyer.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Hatchback; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local', NULL, '2 Year', '4,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'In the event of any dispute or difference relating to the interpretation and application of the provisions of the contracts, such dispute or difference shall be refereed by either party for arbitration to a sole Arbitrator, to be appointed mutually by the parties to the contract. In case parties fail to reach a consensus in appointing the arbitrator, the same shall be appointed as per provisions of the Arbitration & Conciliation Act, 1996, as amended and rules framed there under. The language of the arbitration proceeding shall be English. The venue of the arbitration proceeding shall be at LUCKNOW. The award of the arbitration shall be binding on both the parties. The cost of arbitration including the fees of the Arbitrator, if any, shall be borne by both the parties equally. Each party shall be responsible for its own costs and professional fees, if any.', NULL, 'Indusind bank', '25,000', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, 'In the procurements of goods or works, which are covered by Para 1(b) above and which are divisible in nature, the ''Class-I Local Supplier'' shall get purchase preference over ''Class-Il Local Supplier'' as well as ''Non-Local Supplier, as per following procedure: Among all qualified bids, the lowest bid will be termed as L1. If L1 is ''Class-I Local Supplier, the contract for full quantity will be awarded to L1. If L1 bid is not a ''Class-I Local Supplier, 50% of the order quantity shall be awarded to L1. Thereafter, the lowest bidder among the ''Class-I Local Supplier will be invited to match the L1 price for the remaining 50% quantity subject to the Class-I Local Supplier''s quoted price falling within the margin of purchase preference, and contract for that quantity shall be awarded to such ''Class-I Local Supplier subject to matching the L1 price. In case such lowest eligible ''Class-I Local Supplier fails to match the L1 price or accepts less than the offered quantity, the next higher Class-l Local Supplier within the margin of purchase preference shall be invited to match the L1 price and so on and contract shall be awarded accordingly. In case some quantity is still left uncovered on Class-I Local Suppliers, then such balance quantity may also be ordered on the L1 bidder. In the procurements of goods or works, which are covered by para 1(b) above and which are not divisible in nature, and in procurement of services where the bid is evaluated on price alone, the ''Class-I Local Supplier'' shall get purchase preference over'' Class-II Local Supplier'' as well as ''Non-Local Supplier'', as per following procedure: Among all qualified bids, the lowest bid will be termed as L1. If L1 is ''Class-I Local Supplier, the contract will be awarded to L1. If L1 is not'' Class-I Local Supplier'', the lowest bidder among the ''Class-I Local Supplier'', will be invited to match the Ll price subject to Class-I Local Supplier''s quoted price falling within the margin of purchase preference, and the contract shall be awarded to such'' Class-I Local Supplier'' subject to matching the L1 price. In case such lowest eligible ''Class-I Local Supplier'' fails to match the L1 price, the ''Class-I Local Supplier'' with the next higher bid within the margin of purchase preference shall be invited to match the L1 price and so on and contract shall be awarded accordingly. In case none of the ''Class-I Local Supplier'' within the margin of purchase preference matches the L1 price, the contract may be awarded to the L1 bidder.', 'Yes', 'The participating MSEs in a tender, quoting price within the band of L1+15% are also be allowed to supply a portion of the requirement by bringing down their price to the L1 price arrived after tender evaluation. Such MSEs shall be ordered to supply up to 25% of the total tendered value. In case of more than one such eligible MSEs, the supply will be shared equally. In case tender item is non-splitable or non-dividable, MSTC reserves the rights, in appropriate cases, to award the contract in whole to MSE unit, who may otherwise qualify in the tender by fulfilling the prescribed eligibility requirement.', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require a Hatchback vehicle, with specific model options being Maruti Suzuki WagonR, Maruti Suzuki Swift, or Hyundai i20. The vehicle model year must be 2024 or 2025. The usage variant is for 2000 km and 320 hours on a monthly basis for local service. The vehicle must be air-conditioned, operate in plains, and use Diesel as fuel. It should have travelled up to 25,000 Kms. Additionally, outstation night charges are applicable for the service.', 'Abhishek Kumar Kanaujia', 'Lucknow', 'This GeM bid (GEM/2025/B/6302384) issued by Mstc Limited, under the Ministry of Steel, is for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for a Hatchback vehicle in Lucknow, Uttar Pradesh. The contract period is for 2 years. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with a total value wise evaluation method. Key requirements for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 4 Lakhs for the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. Exemptions for turnover and experience are available for MSE and Startup entities. The bid requires an EMD of 25,000. The service entails providing a Hatchback car for 2000 km and 320 hours per month. The vehicle must be a 2024 or 2025 model and be air-conditioned. The document includes detailed general terms and conditions outlining the scope of service, vehicle condition, driver conduct, payment terms, penalty clauses for non-compliance, and contract termination conditions. The service provider is responsible for all liabilities arising from accidents or driver negligence and must comply with all applicable labor laws, including paying salaries to staff before claiming payment from the buyer. The contract specifies penalties for issues like late reporting, non-reporting, and unclean vehicles. A security deposit of 5% of the contract value is required from the successful bidder.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the consistent and satisfactory fulfillment of all contractual obligations throughout the 2-year period. This includes providing the specified Hatchback vehicle (2024/2025 model) in excellent and clean condition, ensuring its timely availability as per the 2000 km/320 hours monthly requirement, and providing an immediate replacement in case of breakdown. Success is also contingent on the driver adhering strictly to the code of conduct, which includes being polite, wearing a uniform, following all traffic regulations, and maintaining confidentiality. Furthermore, the service provider must comply with all statutory and labor laws, submit accurate bills on time, and avoid penalties by adhering to all terms and conditions without fail, ultimately leading to the completion of the contract without termination for unsatisfactory service.', 'The scope of work involves providing one commercial Hatchback taxi service on a monthly basis for MSTC Limited''s office in Lucknow for a contract period of two years. The service package is for 2000 km and 320 hours per month. The vehicle must be a 2024 or 2025 model (e.g., Maruti Suzuki WagonR, Swift, Hyundai i20), diesel-fueled, air-conditioned, and maintained in excellent condition with clean upholstery and seat covers. The vehicle must be equipped with amenities such as mineral water, a first-aid box, a universal mobile charger, and display ''On Duty, Government of India'' plates. The vehicle will report to the residence of a designated employee and must be available round the clock, including for emergencies on short notice. The contractor is responsible for providing an immediate alternative vehicle in case of breakdown or driver absence. The driver must be uniformed, courteous, possess a valid commercial license, be familiar with Lucknow routes, and carry a mobile phone. The driver is expected to adhere to all traffic rules and maintain a duty slip for user verification. The scope covers both local travel (up to 50 km one-way) and outstation travel to nearby districts. While the company will reimburse toll tax upon submission of receipts, the service provider is responsible for road tax and all other operational costs.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6302573', '14-06-2025 14:00:00', '14-06-2025 14:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Power', 'Na', 'Ntpc Limited', 'Ussc Cpg2 Sipat', 'buyer68.nl.cg@gembuyer.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - HIRING OF 03 NOS SAFETY EXPERTS during overhauling for year 2025-2026', 'Operation and Maintenance Power House / Power Plant', '1 Month 1 Day', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '5,22,858', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, '''Class I local suppliers'' only are eligible to participate in this tender, as defined in the bidding documents/Public Procurement (Preference to Make in India), Order 2017 and its subsequent amendments/revisions issued by DPIIT. The bidders may apprise themselves of the relevant provisions of bidding documents in this regard before submission of their bids.', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service detail the hiring of 03 safety experts for an overhauling project for the year 2025-2026. It is mandatory for the service to have full regulatory and statutory compliance. Furthermore, the service must adhere to the requirements outlined in the Scope of Work (SOW), Special Terms and Conditions (STC), and the Service Level Agreement (SLA).', 'Hem Chandra Roy', 'Muzaffarpur', 'This tender, identified by Bid Number GEM/2025/B/6302573, is issued by Ntpc Limited, under the Ministry of Power, for a custom service contract. The service required is the ''HIRING OF 03 NOS SAFETY EXPERTS during overhauling for year 2025-2026'' at the Muzaffarpur Thermal Power Station in Kanti, Muzaffarpur. The contract has a duration of 30 days (1 Months and 1 Day) with a mobilization period of 7 days from the issuance of the Letter of Award (LOA). The bid is a Two Packet Bid with an estimated value of 522,858, and the evaluation method is total value wise. The bid end date is 14-06-2025 at 14:00:00, with a bid offer validity of 120 days. Key conditions include that EMD/Bid Security is not applicable, but MSE purchase preference is available. The scope involves deploying two qualified Safety Officers and one qualified Scaffolding Specialist to ensure all safety protocols are followed during the plant''s overhaul.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed, it must be fully executed as per the detailed Scope of Work. A final report must be submitted by the safety personnel before leaving the site. The ultimate success criterion is the formal certification of work completion by the Engineer-in-Charge (EIC), after which 100% payment will be processed.', 'The scope of work involves the deployment of three safety experts for a 30-day period during the overhauling at NTPC MTPS. This includes two Qualified Safety Officers and one Qualified Scaffolding Specialist. The Qualified Safety Officer must possess a degree in Mechanical/Electrical, a diploma in Industrial Safety, and a minimum of 5 years of experience in a power plant construction site. Their duties include monitoring all overhaul activities, ensuring proper work permits, conducting daily toolbox talks, checking PPE usage and T&P healthiness, overseeing lifting operations, ensuring electrical and fire safety, stopping any unsafe acts, attending daily review meetings, and submitting a final report. The Qualified Scaffolding Specialist requires a degree in Mechanical/Civil with 5 years of experience or a diploma with 10 years of experience, along with a certification from a reputed institute. Their responsibilities include pre-planning of scaffolds, overseeing erection and dismantling, daily inspections and tagging, providing on-the-job training, advising on safety issues, preparing SOPs, and ensuring compliance with all scaffolding and electrical safety norms. The vendor is responsible for all statutory compliances under labor laws, and a penalty of Rs 5000/day may be imposed for the non-availability of personnel at the site.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6303967', '20-06-2025 14:00:00', '20-06-2025 14:30:00', '60 Days', 'Ministry Of Road Transports And Highways', NULL, NULL, 'Regional Office Chennai', 'dev.indra@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium SUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Outstation 24*7', NULL, '1 Year', '3,00,000', '1 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, 3, 14, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require a Premium SUV for monthly cab and taxi hiring services. The specified car types include Toyota Fortuner, Ford Endeavour, and Toyota Innova Crysta. The service is based on a usage variant of 2000 km and 320 hours per month and is required for Outstation 24*7 service. The vehicle''s model year should be between 2021 and 2025, with total travel not exceeding 25,000 Kms. It must have Air Conditioning (A/C) and be suitable for operation in both Hilly and Plain Areas. Any fuel type is acceptable.', 'Perumal K', 'Chennai', 'This bid document, GEM/2025/B/6303967, is issued by the Ministry of Road Transports And Highways, Regional Office Chennai, for the procurement of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium SUV''. The service required is for one vehicle with a usage package of 2000 km x 320 hours for Outstation 24*7 duty. The contract period is for one year. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 3 Lakhs over the last three years and one year of past experience in similar services, with exemptions available for MSEs and Startups. The bid evaluation method is Total value wise evaluation under a Two Packet Bid system. An ePBG of 3.00% is required for a duration of 14 months. The bidder must be a registered taxi agency with GST and PAN, having an office in Chennai and the vehicle registered in Tamil Nadu. The document details specific requirements for the vehicle''s condition, maintenance, and insurance, as well as stringent criteria for the driver, including experience, conduct, and background. The service provider is obligated to comply with all applicable labor laws, including the Minimum Wages Act.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the consistent and uninterrupted fulfillment of all contractual obligations throughout the one-year period. This includes providing the specified Premium SUV model (2021-2025) in excellent, clean, and well-maintained condition for 2000 km and 320 hours of service per month, available 24*7 for both local and outstation trips. Success is contingent on supplying a qualified, professional driver who meets all specified criteria (valid license, minimum two years experience, good conduct, no criminal record) and ensuring a substitute vehicle and/or driver is provided immediately in case of any breakdown. The contractor must adhere strictly to all terms and conditions outlined in the bid document and its annexures, including comprehensive insurance coverage, compliance with all labor laws for the driver, and timely submission of monthly bills. Any failure to meet these terms and conditions may lead to the termination of the contract.', 'The scope of work involves providing one Premium SUV (such as Toyota Fortuner, Ford Endeavour, Toyota Innova Crysta) on a monthly hiring basis for a contract period of 12 months. The vehicle must be a model from 2021-2025, air-conditioned, registered in Tamil Nadu, and have comprehensive insurance. The service includes a usage limit of 2000 kilometers and 320 hours per month and must be available 24*7 for local and outstation trips, including weekends and holidays. The service provider is responsible for all maintenance, fuel, and upkeep of the vehicle, which must be kept clean with two sets of seat covers, towels, and napkins changed weekly. The provider must supply a qualified driver with a valid license, a minimum of two years of driving experience, who is well-behaved, has no criminal history, is equipped with a mobile phone, and is well-versed with the roads in Tamil Nadu. The service provider, a registered taxi agency with an office in Chennai, must ensure a substitute vehicle/driver is available in case of breakdown and is prohibited from sub-contracting the work. The provider must also ensure compliance with the Minimum Wages Act and other statutory laws for the driver.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6305343', '17-06-2025 17:00:00', '17-06-2025 17:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Defence', 'Dg Of Defence Estate', '***********', 'buycon2.mod.cn@gembuyer.in', 'Hiring of Third-Party Inspection Agency - Construction / Civil Engineering Works; To be entered by buyer as per domain; Government Test Agency', NULL, '2 Months 29 Day', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '09-06-2025 11:00:00', 'Chennai', 'The technical specifications for the hiring of a Third-Party Inspection Agency require the service to be in the domain of Construction / Civil Engineering Works. The material to be inspected will be entered by the buyer as per the domain. The service provider must be accredited as a Government Test Agency. The inspection is to take place at a Domestic location, specifically at the Seller''s Premises. The type of inspection required is a Design Review & Inspection, and the unit of inspection is Lumpsum. There are no add-on specifications mentioned in the core table.', '***********', 'Chennai', 'This is a bid for the ''Hiring of Third-Party Inspection Agency - Construction / Civil Engineering Works'' issued by the Dg Of Defence Estate, Ministry Of Defence, with Bid Number GEM/2025/B/6305343. The bid ends on 17-06-2025 at 17:00:00, with a contract period of 2 months and 29 days. The bid is a Two Packet type with Reverse Auction enabled (H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination). The total value of goods to be inspected is 365800 for the consignee in Chennai. The scope involves providing Structural Stability Certificates and structural drawings for three main locations: the Cantonment Board Office Main Building, the old Cantonment Board Marriage Hall at St. Thomas Mount, and the Decentralized Compost Yard in Nazarathpuram and Arumalaichavadi. Key activities include site inspections, conducting non-destructive tests (NDTs), preparing detailed reports on structural integrity, checking for water seepage and corrosion, and creating analysis models and new drawings for future expansion using software like STAAD PRO. The successful bidder must complete the work within 21 days from the work order issuance. The tender allows for MSE and Startup exemptions and includes an option clause for the buyer to vary the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. A pre-bid meeting is scheduled for 09-06-2025 in Chennai.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following criteria: 1. Submission of a comprehensive Structural Stability Certificate for the renovation of the Cantonment Board Office Main Building, which must be supported by a detailed site inspection report, solutions for renovation and water seepage, results from non-destructive tests (NDTs), and clear recommendations for repairs and maintenance. 2. Delivery of a Structural Stability Certificate with seal and signature for the old Cantonment Board Marriage Hall at St. Thomas Mount, accompanied by detailed reports verifying the building''s safety for future use and analyzing its current condition regarding cracks, seepage, and corrosion. 3. Provision of a Structural Stability Certificate along with new structural drawings for the ground, first, and second floors of the Cantonment Board Decentralized Compost Yard at specified locations. This must include a detailed site report, analysis of steel structures, a software-based model (STAAD PRO. V8) checking column and reinforcement details, and new drawings for future expansion. 4. Completion of all the specified tasks and delivery of all reports, certificates, and drawings for all mentioned sites within 21 days from the date of issuance of the work order.', 'The scope of work involves providing Structural Stability Certificates with structural drawings for multiple Cantonment Board properties. The work is divided into three main parts: 1. Structural Stability Certificate to renovate Cantonment Board Office Main Building: This includes a site inspection with a detailed report, providing a solution for renovation work on cracked locations in the brick wall, column, beam, and slab, identifying water seepage problems with solutions for future expansion, conducting non-destructive tests (NDTs) like the Ultrasonic Pulse Velocity (UPV) test on selected building components, and providing recommendations for repairs and maintenance to ensure the building''s stability. 2. Structural Stability Certificate for the old existing Cantonment Board Marriage Hall at St. Thomas Mount: This requires preparing a detailed report by visiting the site and analyzing cracked and non-cracked portions, water seepage, and reinforcement corrosion; preparing a report to verify if the building is safe for future use as a marriage hall; and providing a stability certificate with a seal and signature. 3. Structural Stability Certificate with Structural drawings for Ground, First and Second floor for Cantonment Board Decentralized Compost Yard in Nazarathpuram, St. Thomas Mount and Arumalaichavadi, C. Pallavaram: This includes preparing a detailed report from a site visit analyzing cracked and non-cracked portions; checking the steel truss, purlin, roof sheet, and connection details for future usage; creating a model and analysis using STAAD PRO. V8 to check column size and reinforcement details for floor extension; and preparing new structural drawings for future expansion including roof beam, roof slab, staircase, and an additional foundation column. These details are required for sites at both St. Thomas Mount and C.Pallavaram (Arumalaichavadi) Compost Yard for Pallavaram and Guindy Buildings. The entire work is to be completed within 21 days from the date of the work order issuance.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6305417', '17-06-2025 19:00:00', '17-06-2025 19:30:00', '45 Days', 'Ministry Of Finance', 'Department Of Revenue', 'Central Board Of Excise And Customs (cbec)', 'Bhopal', 'sram.ravi@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium Sedan; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local 24*7, Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium SUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local 24*7', NULL, '1 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', NULL, NULL, 5, 14, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '06-06-2025 11:00:00', 'Assistant Commissioner (Admin.), OFFICE OF THE COMMISSIONER (AUDIT) CENTRAL GST, CUSTOMS & CENTRAL EXCISE, CENTRAL GST BHAWAN, TIKRAPARA DHAMTARI ROAD, TIKRAPARA, RAIPUR (CHHATTISGARH) 492001, RAIPUR, CHHATTISGARH-492001, India Mobile No. - 7746050383', 'The tender requires two categories of vehicles on a monthly hiring basis for 24*7 local service with a usage variant of 2000 km x 320 hours. The first category is for a Premium Sedan, with acceptable models including Maruti Suzuki Ciaz, Honda City, or Hyundai Verna, which must run on Petrol. The second category is for a Premium SUV, with acceptable models such as Toyota Innova, Toyota Fortuner, or Toyota Innova Crysta, which can use any fuel type. For both categories, the vehicles must be of the model year 2023, 2024, or 2025, should have travelled up to 25,000 Kms, must be air-conditioned (A/C), and will operate in Plains areas.', 'Suresh Ram Ravi', 'Raipur', 'This bid (GEM/2025/B/6305417), issued by the Central Board Of Excise And Customs (cbec) in Bhopal, is for ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services'' for a one-year contract period. The requirement is for eight Premium Sedans (e.g., Maruti Suzuki Ciaz, Honda City) and one Premium SUV (e.g., Toyota Innova, Toyota Fortuner) to be provided to the Office of the Commissioner (Audit) Central GST in Raipur, Chhattisgarh. All vehicles must be from the model years 2023, 2024, or 2025, with a usage limit of 2000 km and 320 hours per month on a 24*7 local basis. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with an end date of 17-06-2025. No EMD is required, but a 5% ePerformance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) is mandatory for 14 months. The tender includes provisions for MSE Purchase Preference and MII compliance. Key buyer-added conditions stipulate that the bidder must be financially sound, have a service office in the consignee''s state, and provide proof of past project experience. The contract also contains an option clause allowing the buyer to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is considered successfully completed upon the consistent and uninterrupted provision of the specified number and type of vehicles (8 Premium Sedans and 1 Premium SUV) that strictly adhere to all technical specifications (including model year, A/C, and mileage) for the entire contract duration of 12 months. Success is further defined by the contractor''s full compliance with the service level agreement of 2000 km x 320 hours per month on a 24*7 local basis. The contractor must also adhere to all Buyer Added Bid Specific Terms and Conditions, such as maintaining a local office and not sub-contracting without prior consent. The ultimate measure of success is the due performance of all contractual obligations without any breach that would necessitate the invocation of the submitted Performance Security.', 'The scope of work is to provide ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services'' for a period of one year to the Office of the Commissioner (Audit) Central GST in Raipur, Chhattisgarh. The contractor is required to supply a total of nine vehicles as per the following specifications: 1. Premium Sedan (Quantity: 8): The vehicles must be one of the following models: Maruti Suzuki Ciaz, Honda City, or Hyundai Verna. They must be of the model year 2023, 2024, or 2025, with mileage up to 25,000 Kms, equipped with A/C, and must run on Petrol. Each vehicle is hired for a usage of 2000 km and 320 hours per month for local 24*7 service. 2. Premium SUV (Quantity: 1): The vehicle must be one of the following models: Toyota Innova, Toyota Fortuner, or Toyota Innova Crysta. It must be of the model year 2023, 2024, or 2025, with mileage up to 25,000 Kms, equipped with A/C, and can run on any fuel type. The vehicle is hired for a usage of 2000 km and 320 hours per month for local 24*7 service. General Obligations: The service provider must have an office located in the state of the consignee. The provider is directly responsible for the performance of the contract and is prohibited from assigning or sub-contracting the work without prior written consent from the buyer. The provider must also ensure compliance with all applicable labour laws.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6305513', '20-06-2025 14:00:00', '20-06-2025 14:30:00', '75 Days', 'Ministry Of Coal', 'Coal India Limited', 'Mahanadi Coalfields Limited', 'Mcl Sambalpur Odisha', 'jprakash@coalindia.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2842 Km x 682 hours; Outstation 24*7', NULL, '3 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '7 Days', NULL, '81,77,658', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'State Bank of India', '1,02,300', NULL, 5, 38, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require the hiring of an SUV type vehicle, with specific models suggested being Mahindra Scorpio, Mahindra Bolero, or Mahindra Bolero Neo. The service is for a usage variant of 2842 Km and 682 hours per month on an Outstation 24*7 basis. The vehicle model must be from the years 2022, 2023, 2024, or 2025 and should have travelled up to 1,00,000 Kms. The vehicle must be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C) and operate on Diesel fuel. The designated area of operation includes both Hilly and Plain areas.', 'Jagannath Satpathy', 'Talcher', 'This bid document, GEM/2025/B/6305513, issued by Mahanadi Coalfields Limited (MCL), Sambalpur Odisha, under the Ministry of Coal, is for the procurement of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services''. The specific requirement is for two SUV vehicles to operate 2842 km and 682 hours per month for outstation 24*7 duty. The contract period is for 3 years (36 months). The bid is a Two Packet Bid with an end date of 20-06-2025. The estimated bid value is Rs. 81,77,658, requiring an EMD of Rs. 102,300 and a Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 5% for a duration of 38 months. The evaluation method will be total value wise. The service is required for the General Manager''s office at Jagannath Area, Talcher. The document details specific terms, including an option clause for the buyer to alter the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. It outlines strict conditions for the service provider, such as the prohibition of sub-contracting without consent, the requirement for vehicles registered on or after September 4, 2022, and adherence to a minimum mileage of 11 km/litre. The contractor is responsible for all statutory compliances, vehicle maintenance, providing qualified drivers, and timely payment of wages and statutory dues to their staff. The document also includes detailed clauses on penalties for non-performance, termination of the contract, and price variation for labor and fuel costs. An Integrity Pact is a mandatory part of the agreement to ensure a fair and transparent process.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is considered successfully completed when the contractor has fulfilled all contractual obligations for the entire contract duration of three years without default. This includes the continuous and uninterrupted provision of two specified SUV vehicles in excellent working condition as per the technical specifications (AC fitted, clean, commercially registered, and registered on or after 04/09/2022). Success is contingent on the contractor ensuring complete statutory compliance for both vehicles and drivers at all times, including valid insurance, permits, fitness, and pollution certificates. The contractor must also ensure timely payment of salaries, wages, and statutory contributions like PF/CMPF to the deployed staff, submitting documentary proof monthly for bill processing. The daily maintenance of the vehicle movement register and its certification by the controlling officer is another key criterion. Overall, successful completion is defined by the satisfactory and seamless execution of the hiring service in adherence to all terms, conditions, and service levels stipulated in the bid document, leading to the natural conclusion of the contract term without invoking penalties for breach or termination.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring of two Bolero or equivalent AC-fitted SUV vehicles for use at Jagannath OCP, Jagannath Area. The service is required on a 24-hour non-shift duty basis, facilitated by two drivers per vehicle working in staggered shifts. The contract spans 1095 days (3 years), with a maximum monthly usage of 2842 km and 682 hours per vehicle. The vehicles provided must be of the model year 2022 or later (registered on or after 04/09/2022), operate on diesel, and maintain a minimum mileage of 11 km/litre. The contractor is fully responsible for all aspects of the service, including providing skilled, licensed, and well-behaved drivers in uniform. The contractor''s responsibilities also cover all operational and maintenance costs, such as fuel, regular servicing, repairs, and ensuring a standby vehicle of the same class is available during any breakdown. The scope includes ensuring all statutory requirements are met, such as commercial taxi registration, RC book, fitness certificate, pollution clearance, road tax, and comprehensive first-party insurance. The contractor must adhere to all labor laws, ensuring timely payment of wages and statutory dues (EPF/CMPF) to staff, and must use the Aadhaar Enabled Biometric Attendance System (AEBAS) and register on the Contract Labour Payment Management Portal (CLPMP) of Coal India Limited. The contractor must maintain a daily vehicle movement register for certification by the controlling officer.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6307917', '20-06-2025 10:00:00', '20-06-2025 10:30:00', '180 Days', 'Gujarat', 'Legal Department Gujarat', NULL, 'Chief Court Fees Office', 'buycon142.ldg.gj@gembuyer.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2500 km x 320 hours; Outstation 24*7', NULL, '9 Month', NULL, '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '18,81,810', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', NULL, NULL, 5, 11, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services require an SUV type vehicle. Acceptable models include Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra TUV300, or Mahindra Bolero, with a model year between 2022 and 2025. The vehicle must have travelled up to 1,00,000 Kms and must be equipped with Air Conditioning. The specified usage variant is 2500 km x 320 hours for an Outstation 24*7 type of service. The area of operation is Plains, and any fuel type is acceptable.', 'Vyas Chintankumar Rameshchandra', 'Ahmedabad', 'This Government e Marketplace (GeM) tender, with Bid Number GEM/2025/B/6307917 dated 05-06-2025, is issued by the Chief Court Fees Office, Legal Department, Gujarat. It seeks ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services'' for a contract period of 9 months. The requirement is for five SUV vehicles, each allocated for 2500 km and 320 hours per month on an Outstation 24*7 basis. The estimated bid value is 1,881,810. The process involves a Two Packet Bid with a Reverse Auction (H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination). Bidders must possess 3 years of past experience, with no exemptions for MSEs or Startups on this specific criterion, although MSE purchase preference is applicable. A 5% e-Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) for 11 months is required, while an Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) is not. The five vehicles are to be deployed to consignee offices in Ahmedabad, Mehsana, Nadiad, Bhavnagar, and Vadodara.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following conditions: 1. Continuous and satisfactory provision of five SUV vehicles that meet all technical specifications (Vehicle Type, Model Year, Km Travelled, A/C) for the entire contract period of 9 months. 2. Adherence to the monthly usage limits of 2500 km and 320 hours for each of the five vehicles. 3. Ensuring 24*7 availability for outstation services at the five specified consignee locations. 4. Complete compliance with all terms and conditions of the bid, the Service Level Agreement, and all applicable labor laws such as The Minimum Wages Act, 1948, The Payment of Gratuity Act, 1972, etc.', 'The scope of work entails providing ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services'' for a contract period of 9 months. The service provider must supply a total of five SUV vehicles. The specified models are Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra TUV300, or Mahindra Bolero. Each vehicle must be a model from 2022 to 2025, have travelled a maximum of 1,00,000 Kms, and be equipped with functional Air Conditioning. The service is designated as ''Outstation 24*7'', with each vehicle''s monthly usage capped at 2500 km and 320 hours. One vehicle must be deployed to each of the five consignee locations: Office of the Inspecting Officer (Court-Fees) in Ahmedabad, Mehsana, Nadiad, Bhavnagar, and Vadodara. The provider is also responsible for ensuring full compliance with all applicable labor laws and the terms mentioned in the contract. The contract is subject to an option clause that allows the buyer to increase or decrease the quantity or duration by up to 25%.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6308145', '19-06-2025 14:00:00', '19-06-2025 14:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Coal', 'Coal India Limited', 'Mahanadi Coalfields Limited', 'Mcl Sambalpur Odisha', 'saptdeeproshni.minz@coalindia.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 3000 km per month and 24 hrs per day; Outstation 24*7', NULL, '3 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '75,23,969', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'State Bank of India', '94,100', 'Yes', 5, 38, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Purchase preference to Micro and Small Enterprises (MSEs): Purchase preference will be given to MSEs as defined in Public Procurement Policy for Micro and Small Enterprises (MSEs) Order, 2012 dated 23.03.2012 issued by Ministry of Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises and its subsequent Orders/Notifications issued by concerned Ministry. If the bidder wants to avail the Purchase preference, the bidder must be the manufacturer of the offered product in case of bid for supply of goods. Traders are excluded from the purview of Public Procurement Policy for Micro and Small Enterprises. In respect of bid for Services, the bidder must be the Service provider of the offered Service. Relevant documentary evidence in this regard shall be uploaded along with the bid in respect of the offered product or service. If L-1 is not an MSE and MSE Seller (s) has/have quoted price within L-1+ 15% of margin of purchase preference /price band defined in relevant policy, such Seller shall be given opportunity to match L-1 price and contract will be awarded', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the required service detail the need for an SUV-type vehicle. Acceptable models include the Mahindra TUV300, Mahindra Scorpio, Mahindra Bolero, or Mahindra Bolero Neo. The vehicle model should be from the years 2022, 2023, 2024, or 2025 (Ex Showroom Model) and must have travelled up to 75,000 Kms. The service required is for an outstation 24*7 basis with a usage variant of 3000 km per month and 24 hours per day. The vehicle must be equipped with air conditioning (A/C), operate on diesel fuel, and will be used in plain areas.', 'Pramod Swarnkar', 'Belpahar', 'This tender, with Bid Number GEM/2025/B/6308145 dated 04-06-2025, is issued by Mahanadi Coalfields Limited, Sambalpur Odisha, for the hiring of two SUV cabs on a monthly basis. The service is for the Safety Department and Excavation Department, ILBL OCP, Lakhanpur Area. The contract period is 3 years. The scope entails providing two AC SUV vehicles (Bolero or equivalent) with a 6+1 seating capacity, operating 24 hours a day with a maximum run of 3000 km per month. The estimated bid value is 75,23,969, with an EMD of 94,100 and a 5% ePBG required for 38 months. The bid is a Two Packet type with a 120-day offer validity. Key requirements for the vehicles include a registration date on or after 03/09/22 and a minimum mileage of 11 km/litre. The successful bidder must submit a Performance Security within 15 days of the contract award. The tender document includes detailed terms regarding driver conduct, vehicle maintenance, statutory compliance, payment of salaries to staff, and penalties for non-performance. A Price Variation Clause for both labour and fuel (petrol/diesel) is applicable. Given the tender value exceeds 50 lakhs, an Integrity Pact is also a part of the contract.', 'The successful completion of the work is contingent upon the contractor''s adherence to several key criteria from the tender issuer''s perspective. The primary requirement is the uninterrupted provision of two specified AC SUV vehicles on a 24-hour basis for the entire 3-year contract period, fulfilling a maximum run of 3000 km per month. Success is measured by the consistent deployment of qualified, licensed, and well-behaved drivers to ensure round-the-clock service. The vehicles must be perpetually maintained in excellent, clean, and safe running condition, with all statutory documents such as commercial registration, fitness certificates, comprehensive insurance, and pollution control certificates being current and valid. In the event of a breakdown, the contractor must promptly provide a suitable standby vehicle. Furthermore, the contractor must fully comply with all applicable labor laws for deployed staff, maintain a daily vehicle movement register for certification by the controlling officer, and submit all required documentation for bill processing. The work is deemed successfully completed only when these services are rendered consistently and satisfactorily throughout the contract''s duration without any default.', 'The Scope of Work involves the hiring of two air-conditioned (AC) covered jeeps, such as a Bolero or an equivalent SUV model, each with a seating capacity of 6+1. The service is to be provided to the Safety Department and Excavation Department at ILBL OCP, Lakhanpur Area, MCL. This service is required on a 24-hour duty basis for a contract period of three years (1095 days), with a maximum usage of 3000 kilometers per month for each vehicle. The contractor must deploy two qualified and licensed drivers per vehicle to ensure continuous 24-hour availability through a staggered rest schedule. The contractor''s responsibilities include all operational aspects such as providing fuel (diesel), regular maintenance, and repairs to keep the vehicles in excellent and safe running condition at all times. The contractor must ensure that all vehicles possess valid statutory documents, including commercial registration, fitness certificate, comprehensive insurance, pollution certificate, and road tax clearance. In the event of a breakdown, a standby vehicle of the same class must be provided immediately. The contractor is also required to maintain a daily vehicle movement logbook for certification by the designated controlling officer.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6308216', '19-06-2025 14:00:00', '19-06-2025 14:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Labour And Employment', NULL, 'Employees State Insurance Corporation (esic)', 'Esicmh Baddi', 'vikas.verma1@esic.nic.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; 1500 KM x 240 hours; Outstation', NULL, '2 Year', '9,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '8,88,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '9,000', 'Yes', 3, 26, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the tender require a Sedan type vehicle for monthly cab and taxi hiring services. The specified car options include Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, Hyundai Xcent, and Toyota Etios. The usage variant is 1500 KM x 240 hours per month for outstation service. The vehicle model must be from the years 2022, 2023, 2024, or 2025, and it should have travelled up to 50,000 Kms. The vehicle must have Air Conditioning (A/C) and will operate in both Hilly and Plain Areas. Any fuel type is acceptable.', 'Vikas Verma', 'Baddi', 'This bid document, number GEM/2025/B/6308216 dated 04-06-2025, is for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for the Employees State Insurance Corporation (esic), specifically for the Esicmh Baddi office. The service required is for one Sedan category vehicle for a contract period of 2 years, with a monthly usage of 1500 KM and 240 hours for outstation duties. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with an estimated value of 888,000. Key dates include a bid end date of 19-06-2025 at 14:00:00 and an opening date of 19-06-2025 at 14:30:00, with an offer validity of 180 days. Bidders must have a minimum average annual turnover of 9 Lakhs for the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. Exemptions for turnover and experience are available for MSEs and Startups. The tender requires an EMD of 9000 and an ePBG of 3.00% for a duration of 26 months. The beneficiary for the service is the Medical Superintendent, ESIC Model Hospital, Baddi, Himachal Pradesh. The document outlines additional qualifications such as the bidder having a registered office in Distt. Solan of H.P &/or Panchkula, Chandigarh & Mohali, and specific rates for extra kilometers and overtime hours. It also includes a checklist of required documents such as technical bid forms, undertakings, EMD proof, PAN, GST, vehicle RC, proof of ownership, and a declaration of not being blacklisted.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the successful completion of the work is contingent upon the service provider consistently delivering the taxi hiring service in strict accordance with the contract''s terms and conditions for the entire 2-year duration. This includes providing the specified Sedan vehicle, meeting the model year and mileage criteria, ensuring its availability for 240 hours and 1500 km per month, and maintaining all necessary documentation like commercial registration, insurance, and pollution certificates. A crucial success criterion is the service provider''s compliance with payment obligations, specifically paying salaries and statutory wages (PF, ESIC) to their deployed staff on time before claiming payment from the buyer. Adherence to all labor laws and the terms specified in the Buyer Added Bid Specific Terms and Conditions, such as the option clause and financial standing requirements, will also be critical indicators of successful contract completion. The submission and maintenance of the 3% Performance Security (ePBG) for 26 months serves as a financial guarantee for performance, and the fulfillment of the contract without invoking this security would signify success.', 'The scope of work involves providing one Sedan type commercial vehicle on a monthly hiring basis for a contract period of two years (24 months) for the ESIC Model Hospital in Baddi, Himachal Pradesh. The service provider is required to supply a vehicle from the approved list (Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, Hyundai Xcent, Toyota Etios) of model year 2022, 2023, 2024, or 2025, with total mileage not exceeding 50,000 Kms. The service package includes 1500 kilometers and 240 hours of usage per month for outstation duty in Hilly and Plain areas. The vehicle must be equipped with a functional air conditioner. The scope also includes providing one driver on the service provider''s payroll. Any travel exceeding 4500 kms per quarter will be charged as per the rate fixed by the state government for commercial vehicles. Any extra duty hours will be compensated at Rs. 100 per hour, with a daily cap of Rs. 400. The service provider must ensure the vehicle has valid commercial registration, insurance, and pollution certificates at all times during the contract period and must comply with all applicable labor laws.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6308525', '14-06-2025 14:00:00', '14-06-2025 14:30:00', '30 Days', 'Punjab', 'Civil Aviation Department, Punjab', 'N/a', 'Room No 13 14 15 Bays 17 Building Sec 17 Chd', 'puran.chand617@punjab.gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local 24*7', NULL, '5 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Not Applied', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require a Sedan vehicle type, with the acceptable car models being Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, or Hyundai Xcent. The specified usage variant is 2000 km x 320 hours for a Local 24*7 service. The vehicle provided must be from the model year 2022 or 2021 and should have travelled upto 25,000 Kms. A mandatory requirement is the presence of Air Conditioning (A/C). The area of operation is designated as Plains, and the vehicle can be of any fuel type. There are no addon specifications listed.', 'Puran Chand', 'Chandigarh u.t', 'This GeM bid, number GEM/2025/B/6308525 dated 04-06-2025, is for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for a Sedan vehicle. The contract is issued by the Civil Aviation Department, Punjab, for a duration of 5 years. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with a total value wise evaluation method, closing on 14-06-2025 at 14:00:00. The service requires one vehicle for 2000 km and 320 hours per month on a local 24*7 basis. Key conditions include no exemptions for MSE or Startups, no EMD or ePBG requirement, and MII compliance is mandatory. The consignee is Puran Chand in Chandigarh. The buyer has included an option clause to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. Bidders must comply with all applicable Labour Laws.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be deemed successfully completed upon the consistent fulfillment of the following conditions for the entire 5-year contract period: The service provider must supply one Sedan vehicle that strictly adheres to all technical specifications, including the model year (2022, 2021), make (Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, Hyundai Xcent), initial mileage (Upto 25,000 Kms), and having a functional A/C. The service must be provided reliably on a Local 24*7 basis, fulfilling the monthly usage requirement of 2000 km and 320 hours. Continuous and complete adherence to the GeM General Terms and Conditions, the Service Level Agreement, and all applicable labour laws (such as The Minimum Wages Act, 1948, The Payment of Wages Act, 1936, etc.) is mandatory.', 'The scope of work entails providing one Sedan vehicle under the ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services'' category for the Civil Aviation Department, Punjab, for a total contract period of 5 years (60 months). The service must be available on a ''Local 24*7'' basis to meet a monthly usage of ''2000 km x 320 hours''. The area of operation is specified as ''Plains''. The vehicle provided must be a Sedan from the model year ''2022'' or ''2021'', with acceptable models being ''Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, Hyundai Xcent''. At the start of the service, the vehicle must have a total mileage of ''Upto 25,000 Kms''. The vehicle must be equipped with functional air conditioning (A/C) and can operate on any fuel type. The service is required for the consignee Puran Chand at ROOM NO 13,14,15 17 BAYS BUILDING SECTOR-17 CHANDIGARH U.T 160017. The service provider is also mandated to ensure full compliance with all applicable labour laws throughout the contract duration.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6309026', '17-06-2025 10:00:00', '17-06-2025 10:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'South East Central Railway', 'Hq New General Manager Secr', 'buyer19.mr.cg@gembuyer.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local', NULL, '2 Year', '15', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '12,78,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '25,560', NULL, 5, 26, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the tender require a Premium SUV for hire. The acceptable car types include Toyota Innova and Tata Harrier. The vehicle is intended for a usage variant of 2000 km and 320 hours per month for local service. The required year of the vehicle model must be 2023, 2024, or 2025, with a total travelled distance of up to 25,000 Kms. The vehicle must be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C) and will operate in plains areas. The specified fuel type for the vehicle is Petrol.', 'Roshan Pancham Gajbhiye', 'Nagpur', 'This bid, number GEM/2025/B/6309026, is for the monthly hiring of a Premium SUV cab and taxi service for the South East Central Railway, under the Ministry of Railways. The contract period is for 2 years, with an estimated bid value of 1,278,000. The service required is for one vehicle to cover 2000 km and 320 hours per month for a consignee in Nagpur, Maharashtra. Key dates include the bid end date on 17-06-2025 and the bid opening on the same day, with a bid offer validity of 90 days. Bidders are required to have past experience in similar services. Financial eligibility criteria include an aggregate turnover of at least 1.5 times the bid value over the last three financial years and liquidity of 5% of the estimated bid value. The vehicle provided must be a 2023-2025 model, not more than 2 years old, commercially registered, and meet all statutory requirements including insurance and pollution standards. The contract includes an option clause for the buyer to increase or decrease the quantity or duration by up to 25%. A performance security of 5% of the contract value is required. The evaluation method will be on a total value wise basis.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the consistent and satisfactory fulfillment of all contractual obligations by the service provider. This includes: providing a vehicle that strictly adheres to all technical specifications (Premium SUV, model year 2023-2025, good condition, A/C, commercial permit); ensuring the vehicle''s uninterrupted availability 24 hours a day, including holidays, for the specified monthly usage of 2000 km and 320 hours; maintaining a daily log book for accurate usage tracking; ensuring the driver is professional, well-dressed, equipped with a mobile phone, and possesses all valid licenses; complying with all statutory and safety norms, including vehicle fitness, insurance, pollution standards, and equipping the vehicle with a medical kit and fire extinguisher; and submitting accurate invoices as per the contract''s payment terms. The contract''s successful performance may also be demonstrated by the mutual agreement to extend the service duration for up to 6 months beyond the initial period.', 'The scope of work involves providing one Premium SUV for cab and taxi hiring services on a monthly basis for a contract period of 24 months. The service is for the Office of CWM MIB Workshop, Nagpur. The vehicle must be a 2023, 2024, or 2025 model, such as a Toyota Innova, Tata Harrier, Hyundai Alcazar, or Tata Safari or equivalent, and should not be more than 2 years old. It must be a petrol vehicle with working air conditioning, in a neat, clean, and good fettle condition. The vehicle must have a commercial transport permit for Maharashtra, valid fitness certificate, insurance, and pollution compliance certificate, and meet at least BS-6 emission standards. The service package is for 2000 km and 320 hours per month. The vehicle must be available 24 hours a day, on all days including holidays, for local and outstation travel as required. The service provider must supply a well-dressed driver with a valid driving license and a mobile phone. A log book for daily entry of kilometers utilized must be maintained by the contractor. The provider is also responsible for ensuring the vehicle is equipped with an emergency medical kit and fire extinguisher and maintains a minimum fuel level to avoid service interruptions. All costs related to fuel, maintenance, driver''s salary, and statutory compliance are within the contractor''s scope.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6312611', '20-06-2025 13:00:00', '20-06-2025 13:30:00', '90 Days', 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Woman Welfare Department Uttar Pradesh', 'Directorate Of Bal Vikas & Pushtahar', 'Lucknow', 'con1.icds.agra@gembuyer.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local', NULL, '9 Month', '27,00,000', '3 Year', 'No', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'Yes', '50% Lowest Priced Technically Qualified Bidders', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '54,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'Yes (Mediation clause document) as per DOE OM No.F.1/2/2024-PPD dated 03.06.2024 mediation clause should not be routinely included in contracts and pre-litigation mediation can be taken up without any such clause also', 'State Bank of India', '1,62,000', 'Yes', 3, 10, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications outline the requirements for a Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Service. The service requires SUV type vehicles with acceptable models being Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra Scorpio, Mahindra Bolero, or Mahindra Bolero Neo. The vehicle model year must be 2021, and the total kilometers travelled should be up to 50,000 Kms. The usage variant is specified as 2000 km and 320 hours on a local service basis. The vehicle must be equipped with air conditioning (A/C), operate in plains, and can use any type of fuel.', 'Ajeet Kumar Gautam', 'Agra', 'This bid, number GEM/2025/B/6312611 dated 05-06-2025, is for the procurement of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local'' for the Directorate Of Bal Vikas & Pushtahar, under the Woman Welfare Department of Uttar Pradesh. The contract period is for 9 months. The bid follows a Two Packet Bid system with a Reverse Auction for the 50% lowest priced technically qualified bidders. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 27 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services, with exemptions available for startups. The estimated bid value is 54,00,000, requiring an EMD of 1,62,000 and an ePBG of 3.00% for 10 months. The beneficiary is the District Programme Officer in Agra, requiring 16 vehicles. Specific buyer conditions include the service provider having an office in the consignee''s state and owning at least 20% of the required vehicle fleet. The bid submission deadline is 20-06-2025 at 13:00:00.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of all contractual obligations by the selected bidder for the entire 9-month duration. This includes: the continuous provision of 16 SUV vehicles that meet all specified technical criteria (2021 model, under 50,000 kms, A/C enabled, and specified car types); adherence to the monthly usage limit of 2000 km and 320 hours per vehicle; ensuring service availability at all specified locations within Agra; and compliance with all buyer-added terms and conditions, such as maintaining a local office and owning 20% of the vehicle fleet.', 'The scope of work involves providing Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for a duration of 9 months. The provider must supply a total of 16 SUV-type vehicles. The vehicles must be of the 2021 model year, have travelled a maximum of 50,000 kms, be air-conditioned, and can be any of the following models: Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra Scorpio, Mahindra Bolero, or Mahindra Bolero Neo. The service is classified as ''Local'' and will operate in ''Plains''. The service entails a usage of 2000 km and 320 hours per vehicle per month. The service must be delivered to multiple locations, including AGRA CITY, BICHPURI, KIRAWALI, FATEHPUR SIKRI, BARAULI AHIR, SHAMSHABAD, PINAHAT, FATEHABAD, JAITPURKALA, BAH, ETMADPUR, KHANDAULI, SAIYAN, AKOLA, KHERAGAR, and JAGNER in AGRA. The Service Provider is required to have an office located in the state of the consignee (Uttar Pradesh), must own a minimum of 20% of the bid quantity of vehicles, and must provide a dedicated/toll-free telephone number for service support.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6312707', '19-06-2025 15:00:00', '19-06-2025 15:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Power', NULL, NULL, 'Bureau Of Energy Efficiency', 'avadhm.pandey@beeindia.gov.in', 'Hiring of Consultant for Energy Efficiency Services - Consulting Firm; East and North East Zone for Appointment of PMA for providing professional or expert manpower at SDAs for the implementation and enforcement of the activities undertaken by SDAs..', NULL, '3 Year', '10,00,00,000', '7 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC),OEM Authorization Certificate,OEM Annual Turnover,Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '9,00,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Bank Of Baroda', '10,00,000', 'Yes', 3, 48, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '12-06-2025 15:00:00', 'https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_MzY2ZWQ1OGQtMTc5Yy00NGVjLWIyMGEtNTgxMTRjNWYxYzNh@thread.v2/0?context={"Tid":"79304f37-e0bb-4919-ac85-bff78fa2faff","Oid":"832477bf-dd6c-48be-a87b-b8ae7aa5e163"}', 'The technical specifications for the ''Hiring Of Consultant For Energy Efficiency Services'' mandate that the service provider must be a ''Consulting Firm''. The scope of work, defined under the ''Consulting Category'', is for the ''East and North East Zone for Appointment of PMA for providing professional or expert manpower at SDAs for the implementation and enforcement of the activities undertaken by SDAs under Perform Achieve & Trade (PAT) Scheme''. The specific ''Qualification of the Consultant'', ''Total Experience of the Consultant'', and ''Certification of Consultant'' are to be as per the Request for Proposal (RfP) document. The ''Deployment of Consultant'' must be ''Onsite''. There are no addon specifications listed.', 'Anil Kumar Rai', 'New Delhi', 'This tender (GEM/2025/B/6312707) is for the ''Hiring of Consultant for Energy Efficiency Services'' issued by the Bureau of Energy Efficiency (BEE), Ministry of Power. The objective is to appoint a Project Management Agency (PMA) to provide professional and expert manpower to State Designated Agencies (SDAs) in the East and North-East Zone for the implementation and enforcement of the Perform Achieve & Trade (PAT) Scheme. The contract period is 3 years. The evaluation of bids will be done using a Two Packet Bid system based on the Least Cost Method (LCS), with a minimum of 70 technical marks required to qualify. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 1000 Lakhs for the last 3 years and 7 years of past experience in similar services. The scope involves deploying a team of 20 experts (including Accredited Energy Auditors, Energy Managers, Project Associates, Legal, and Finance Experts) across 7 states. The PMA will be responsible for providing comprehensive technical assistance, supporting PAT rule enforcement, conducting data analysis, building stakeholder capacity, and assisting with legal and financial aspects of the scheme. Payment to the selected agency will be made on a quarterly basis, equivalent to 25% of the annual contract value.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be deemed successfully completed based on the fulfillment of several key performance indicators. The core criterion is the agency''s ability to complete at least 80% of the tasks outlined in the mutually approved Quarterly Action Plan for each quarter. Success is also measured by the timely submission of comprehensive monthly and quarterly activity reports in the prescribed format to both the State Designated Agencies (SDAs) and the Bureau of Energy Efficiency (BEE). The agency must ensure the proper punctuality and performance of its deputed manpower. The satisfactory completion and acceptance of all deliverables, as detailed in the scope of work, are mandatory for payment. Consistent failure to meet these criteria, particularly the 80% task completion threshold, will be considered unsatisfactory performance, leading to financial penalties and potential termination of the contract.', 'The scope of work is to appoint a Project Management Agency (PMA) to provide technical assistance and full-time professional/expert manpower to State Designated Agencies (SDAs) in the East & North-East Zone for the effective implementation and enforcement of the Perform Achieve & Trade (PAT) Scheme. The PMA is required to depute a total of 20 full-time experts, including Accredited Energy Auditors (AEA), Energy Auditors/Managers (EA/EM), Project Associates (PA), Legal Experts (LE), and Finance Experts (FE), across the states of Chhattisgarh, Odisha, West Bengal, Assam, Bihar, Meghalaya, and Tripura. The detailed activities include: 1. PAT Scheme Implementation and Enforcement: Identify and suggest new energy-intensive sectors for inclusion, support BEE/SDA in communicating PAT notifications, conduct inspections for non-compliance, coordinate with SERC for adjudication processes, and assist in the Check Verification (CV) of Designated Consumers (DCs). 2. Planning, Coordination, and Reporting: Prepare action plans for DC visits, coordinate with state industrial departments to identify prospective DCs, review and analyze reports submitted by DCs (Forms-A, B, C, D, MEA, M&V), and prepare dashboards on state-level energy consumption. 3. Capacity Building: Organize and support capacity-building programs for DCs, MSMEs, and other stakeholders on topics such as energy efficiency technologies, normalization, and M&V protocols. 4. Documentation and Technical Assistance: Compile case study reports, maintain a database of notifications and DC information, prepare correspondence letters, and provide technical assistance for the analysis of data submitted by DCs for normalization calculations. 5. Legal and Financial Support: Provide support to SDAs in legal compliance related to RTI queries or litigation, educate stakeholders on PAT rules, explore opportunities for EE Financing, prepare reports on EE financing in MSME sectors, and support the organization of Investment Bazar/workshops.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6314324', '17-06-2025 18:00:00', '17-06-2025 18:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Information And Broadcasting', 'Ministry Of Information And Broadcasting', 'Prasar Bharati Broadcasting Corporation Of India', 'Doordarshan Kendra Shimla', 'ddoddkshimla@prasarbharati.gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local 24*7, Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local 24*7', NULL, '1 Year', '25,00,000', '2 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'State Bank of India', '75,000', 'Yes', 3, 14, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The tender requires hiring services for two categories of vehicles: SUV and Sedan. For the SUV category, the vehicle type must be an SUV, with acceptable models including Mahindra XUV 500, Renault Duster, Mahindra Scorpio, Mahindra Marazzo, and Mahindra Xylo. The usage variant is 2000 km x 320 hours for Local 24*7 service. The required vehicle model year is 2023, with travel up to 50,000 Kms. It should be a Non-A/C, Diesel vehicle for operation in Hilly Areas, and outstation night charges are applicable. For the Sedan category, two separate requirements are listed with identical specifications. The vehicle type is Sedan, with acceptable models such as Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, Hyundai Xcent, Tata Zest, Toyota Etios, Hyundai Aura, and Maruti Suzuki Tour S. The usage variant, service type, model year, and travelled kilometers are the same as the SUV (2000 km x 320 hours, Local 24*7, 2023 model, Upto 50,000 Kms). The Sedans must also be Non-A/C for operation in Hilly Areas, but the specified fuel type is Petrol. Outstation night charges are applicable for the Sedans as well.', 'Baljeet Singh, Virender Singh, Nitesh', 'Shimla', 'This GeM bid (GEM/2025/B/6314324), dated 05-06-2025, is for the procurement of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services'' by Doordarshan Kendra Shimla, under the Ministry of Information and Broadcasting. The contract period is for one year. The tender requires two types of vehicles: one SUV and a total of three Sedans, both for a usage of 2000 km x 320 hours on a local 24*7 basis. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with a validity of 90 days. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 25 Lakhs over the last three years and two years of similar service experience, although exemptions are available for MSEs and Startups. Financial requirements include an EMD of 75,000 and an ePBG of 3.00% for 14 months. Additional qualifications for bidders include owning a fleet of at least 8 vehicles, having 5 drivers on payroll, and maintaining a geographic presence in Himachal Pradesh. The consignees are located in Shimla. Key buyer-added conditions include an option clause to modify the contract quantity by up to 25%, a requirement for the service provider to have a local office in the consignee''s state, and a payment clause mandating the provider to pay staff salaries before claiming reimbursement from the buyer.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be deemed successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following criteria:
1. The service provider must supply the specified number and type of vehicles (one SUV and three Sedans) that strictly adhere to all technical specifications, including model year (2023), fuel type, Non-A/C requirement, and condition (Upto 50,000 Kms travelled).
2. The vehicles must be consistently available for the stipulated duration (2000 km and 320 hours per month) on a 24*7 basis for the entire one-year contract period.
3. The service provider must maintain a service office within the state of the consignee (Himachal Pradesh) as required for service and support.
4. Strict adherence to the payment terms, which requires the service provider to pay salaries and wages to its staff first and then submit all statutory documents (PF, ESIC) and bank statements as proof to the buyer for reimbursement.
5. Full compliance with all applicable Labour Laws, including The Minimum Wages Act, 1948, The Payment of Wages Act, 1936, etc., must be ensured throughout the contract period.
6. The provider must ensure seamless service delivery for the designated consignees and accommodate additional requirements such as the estimated number of outstation nights per month for each vehicle.', 'The scope of work involves providing Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for a contract period of one year to Doordarshan Kendra, Shimla. The service provider is required to supply a total of four vehicles operating in Hilly Areas within Himachal Pradesh. Vehicle requirements are as follows: 1. One (1) SUV: The vehicle must be a 2023 Diesel model with mileage up to 50,000 Kms, provided on a Non-A/C basis. It is required for 2000 km and 320 hours of Local 24*7 service per month. Acceptable models include Mahindra XUV 500, Renault Duster, Mahindra Scorpio, Mahindra Marazzo, and Mahindra Xylo. An estimated 5 outstation nights per month are required for this vehicle. 2. Three (3) Sedans: The vehicles must be 2023 Petrol models with mileage up to 50,000 Kms, provided on a Non-A/C basis. Each is required for 2000 km and 320 hours of Local 24*7 service per month. Acceptable models include Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, Hyundai Xcent, Tata Zest, Toyota Etios, Hyundai Aura, and Maruti Suzuki Tour S. An estimated 4 outstation nights per month are required for each Sedan. Service Provider Obligations: - The provider must maintain an office in Himachal Pradesh for service and support. - The provider must pay salaries and wages to its deployed staff and furnish proof of payment (including statutory contributions like PF, ESIC) before claiming payment from the buyer. - The provider must comply with all applicable Labour Laws.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6315136', '20-06-2025 11:00:00', '20-06-2025 11:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Steel', 'Rashtriya Ispat Nigam Limited', 'Rashtriya Ispat Nigam Limited', 'Visakhapatnam Steel Plant', 'dvravikumar@vizagsteel.com', 'Hiring of Third-Party Inspection Agency - Minerals, Ores, Coal & Coke, Non-metallic Mineral Products, LIMESTONE; LIMESTONE as per Bid Document; NABL accredited', NULL, '3 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', NULL, 'No', 3, 42, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the hiring of a third-party inspection agency require expertise in the domain of Minerals, Ores, Coal & Coke, Non-metallic Mineral Products, and specifically LIMESTONE. The material to be inspected is LIMESTONE, as detailed in the bid document. The service provider must be NABL accredited. The inspection location is domestic, with the inspection site being either Visakhapatnam Port (VPT) and/or Adani Gangavaram Port (AGPL). The inspection type involves Joint Sampling and analysis as per the bid document, and the unit of inspection is on a per-vessel basis.', 'Amitava Haldar', 'Visakhapatnam', 'This tender (GEM/2025/B/6315136), issued by Rashtriya Ispat Nigam Limited (RINL), Visakhapatnam Steel Plant, is for the appointment of a Public Analyst for a three-year contract. The scope involves providing third-party inspection services, specifically joint sampling and analysis, for up to 56,00,000 Metric Tons of Low Silica (SMS Grade) Limestone imported through Visakhapatnam Port (VPT) and/or Adani Gangavaram Port (AGPL). The bid is a two-packet type with a contract period of 3 years and an offer validity of 90 days. Bidders must meet pre-qualification criteria, including experience with similar jobs valuing at least Rs. 1.40 lakh in each of the last 3 years, a turnover of at least Rs. 2.80 lakh in any one of the last 3 years, and NABL accreditation. The successful bidder is required to submit a performance security deposit (ePBG) of 3% of the contract value for a duration of 42 months. The work involves collecting samples as per Indian Standards, preparing a four-part composite sample for each vessel, and conducting various tests including screen analysis, chemical analysis, and index tests (Tumbler, Shatter, Decrepitation). Timely submission of analysis certificates and reports is a critical requirement. The tender specifies that MII and MSE purchase preferences are applicable and a Reverse Auction will be conducted among technically qualified bidders.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of several key conditions. Primarily, success is contingent on satisfactory performance as certified by the Raw Materials department of RINL for each assignment. This includes the strict adherence to reporting timelines: the 2nd part of the composite sample must be delivered to HOD (QA & TD), VSP, within 7 days of vessel discharge completion. The certificate of sampling and analysis, covering all required parameters, must be prepared in six sets and submitted within 15 days of the vessel''s discharge completion. Additionally, moisture content reports must be submitted within 3 to 4 days of sample collection. Failure to meet these deadlines for submitting certificates or samples will result in non-payment for the respective parameters for that vessel. Consistent satisfactory performance in line with all contract conditions is essential, as failure to do so may lead to contract termination.', 'The scope of work involves the appointment of a Public Analyst for Joint Sampling and Analysis of Low Silica (SMS Grade) Limestone imported through Visakhapatnam Port (VPT) and/or Adani Gangavaram Port (AGPL). The analyst will work alongside the seller''s appointed analyst, following Indian Standards IS: 2109-1982 and IS 1760. Key activities include: 1) Collection of samples during cargo unloading at the wharfs, with or without an Auto Sampler facility. 2) Daily collection of samples for moisture analysis of limestone transferred from the port to the steel plant via conveyor or rakes. 3) Preparation of one composite sample (minimum 200 Kgs each) per vessel, divided into four parts: an ''Umpire Sample'' to be retained, a sample for RINL''s HOD (QA & TD) to be delivered within 7 days, a sample for the seller''s representative, and a sample for analysis by the Public Analyst. 4) The analysis of the fourth sample must cover chemical composition (CaO, MgO, SiO2, Al2O3, Fe2O3, P, S), total moisture, screen analysis for various sizes ((+)85mm, (+)80-85mm, 40-80mm, (-)15mm), and index tests including Tumbler Index (IS 6495), Shatter Index (IS 9963), and Decrepitation Index (IS 10345). 5) Submission of the certificate of sampling and analysis in six sets within 15 days of vessel discharge completion, and submission of moisture reports within 3-4 days of sample collection. Scanned copies of reports must also be emailed to designated RINL and port officials.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6315993', '20-06-2025 10:00:00', '20-06-2025 10:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Petroleum And Natural Gas', 'Brahmaputra Cracker And Polymer Limited', 'Brahmaputra Cracker And Polymer Limited', 'Lepetkata', 'buycon4.bcplbga.as@gembuyer.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - HIRING OF SERVICE FOR SMALL PICK-UP TRUCK MINIMUM 01 MT FOR 02 YEARS (ON-CALL BASIS) AT GDU-DULIAJAN ON LIMITED TENDER BASIS', 'Bus Hiring Service - Short Term', '2 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'Yes', 'Certificate (Requested in ATC),Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '3 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require the HIRING OF SERVICE FOR SMALL PICK-UP TRUCK MINIMUM 01 MT FOR 02 YEARS (ON-CALL BASIS) AT GDU-DULIAJAN ON LIMITED TENDER BASIS. The service must have Regulatory/ Statutory Compliance and also be in Compliance of Service to SOW, STC, SLA etc. There are no Addon(s) specified.', 'Pankaj Das', 'Duliajan', 'This GeM bid document (GEM/2025/B/6315993), dated 06-06-2025, is for a Custom Bid for Services issued by Brahmaputra Cracker And Polymer Limited. The tender is for the "HIRING OF SERVICE FOR SMALL PICK-UP TRUCK MINIMUM 01 MT FOR 02 YEARS (ON-CALL BASIS) AT GDU-DULIAJAN ON LIMITED TENDER BASIS". The contract period is for 2 years, and the bid is a Two Packet Bid type with an end date of 20-06-2025. The evaluation method is Total value wise evaluation. Startups are given an exemption for turnover, but there is no exemption for MSEs regarding years of experience and turnover. However, MSE Purchase Preference is applicable. No EMD or ePBG is required for this tender. The scope involves an Annual Rate Contract (ARC) for shifting materials/spares between GDU Duliajan and BCPL Lepetkata Plant, with the contractor providing the truck (min 1T capacity), driver, helper, and fuel for an estimated 96 trips. Bidders are required to quote a total rate inclusive of GST.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is considered successfully completed upon the satisfactory execution of the 2-year Annual Rate Contract (ARC). This entails the contractor consistently making a small pick-up truck of minimum 01 MT capacity available on an on-call basis for the entire contract period. Success is defined by the timely and efficient completion of all requested trips for shifting materials/spares between GDU Duliajan and BCPL Lepetkata Plant. The service provided must include the vehicle, accessories, driver, helper, and fuel as per the scope. Continuous adherence to all regulatory/statutory requirements, the Scope of Work (SOW), Standard Terms and Conditions (STC), Service Level Agreement (SLA), and all applicable labor laws throughout the contract term is mandatory for the work to be deemed successfully completed.', 'The scope of work is for an Annual Rate Contract (ARC) for the hiring of a service for a small pick-up truck with a minimum capacity of 01 MT. The service is required for a period of 02 years on an on-call basis at GDU-Duliajan. The primary task is the shifting of materials and spares from GDU Duliajan, BCPL unit to BCPL Lepetkata Plant, or vice-versa. The scope for the contractor includes providing the small pick-up truck along with all necessary accessories, a driver, a helper, and fuel.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6319151', '20-06-2025 14:00:00', '20-06-2025 14:30:00', '30 Days', 'Ministry Of Finance', 'Department Of Revenue', 'Central Board Of Direct Taxes (cbdt)', 'Cit Appeals Hisar', 'buycon1802.cbdtc.hr@gembuyer.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Outstation 24*7', NULL, '9 Month', '3,00,000', '2 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '4,71,600', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the required service detail the hiring of an SUV type vehicle. The acceptable car models include Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra XUV 500, and KIA Carens. The usage variant is specified as 2000 km x 320 hours per month for Outstation 24*7 service. The vehicle''s model year should be between 2020 and 2024, and it should have travelled up to 50,000 Kms. The vehicle must be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C) and will operate in Plains areas. Any fuel type is acceptable. No specific add-ons are required.', 'Ram Kumar', 'Hisar', 'This GeM bid (GEM/2025/B/6319151), issued by Cit Appeals Hisar under the Ministry of Finance, is for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services. The service requires one SUV for a contract period of 9 months, with a usage of 2000 km and 320 hours per month on an outstation 24*7 basis. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with an estimated value of 471,600. Key bidder qualifications include a minimum average annual turnover of 3 Lakhs for the last 3 years and 2 years of past experience in similar services, although exemptions are available for MSEs and Startups. The contract requires the vehicle to be a 2020-2025 model, well-maintained, and insured, with a maximum permissible monthly hiring charge of Rs. 50,000/- + GST. The successful bidder must deposit a security/EMD of Rs. 30,000/- and enter into a formal contract. The terms and conditions detail requirements for driver conduct, vehicle maintenance, timely submission of bills with trip sheets, and strict compliance with all applicable labor laws. The evaluation method is total value wise, and the contract includes an option clause allowing the buyer to vary the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed, the service provider must consistently provide one SUV that meets all specified technical requirements (model year 2020-2025, well-maintained, insured, etc.) and is available 24x7 for the entire 9-month contract period. The provider must ensure the vehicle and the deployed driver adhere to all terms, including maintaining professional conduct, possessing valid documentation, and complying with all Motor Vehicle and Labor laws. Success is contingent upon the punctual and uninterrupted availability of the service, with immediate vehicle replacement (within one hour) during breakdowns. Furthermore, the provider must submit accurate monthly bills with duly countersigned trip sheets by the 5th of the succeeding month. The contract is deemed successful if these services are rendered without any instances of non-compliance, misbehavior, or service irregularities that would lead to penalties or termination of the contract as stipulated in the agreement.', 'The scope of work involves providing one SUV type vehicle (such as Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra XUV 500, KIA Carens) on a monthly hiring basis for a period of 9 months. The vehicle is required for a usage limit of 2000 km and 320 hours per month and must be available for service 24x7, including holidays, for both local and outstation duties, which may include travel to locations like Ludhiana, Chandigarh, and Delhi. The vehicle provided must be a model from 2020 to 2025, preferably the latest model, with mileage up to 50,000 kms. It must be in perfect mechanical condition, comprehensively insured, have all necessary permits, and be equipped with A/C and safety airbags. The interior and exterior of the vehicle must be well-maintained and cleaned daily. The service provider must also supply a dedicated, experienced (over 3 years), and well-behaved driver with a valid license and mobile phone. The driver must wear a decent uniform and have knowledge of local routes as well as Hindi and English. The scope includes all operational costs such as fuel, maintenance, repairs, insurance, permits, driver''s salary and allowances, and toll charges within the fixed monthly rate. The provider is also responsible for maintaining a daily logbook for mileage and time, submitting monthly bills with trip sheets for payment, and ensuring full compliance with all statutory labor laws for the deployed personnel.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6319440', '17-06-2025 19:00:00', '17-06-2025 19:30:00', '180 Days', 'Ministry Of Civil Aviation', 'Airports Authority Of India (aai)', 'Airports Authority Of India ,rhq Nr - Rangpuri', 'Aai Rhq Nr', 'buycon198.aairnr.up@gembuyer.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2500 km x 320 hours; Local 24*7', NULL, '2 Year', '6,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '18,16,536', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'State Bank of India', '36,331', NULL, 5, 27, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the required service detail a Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Service. The core requirement is for an SUV vehicle type, with suggested models being Mahindra TUV300, Mahindra Scorpio, or Mahindra Bolero. The usage variant is specified as 2500 km x 320 hours for Local 24*7 service. The vehicle model should be from the years 2023, 2024, or 2025 and must have travelled up to 50,000 Kms. The vehicle must be equipped with A/C, operate in Plains, and use Diesel fuel. There are no add-on specifications mentioned.', 'Hidaytullah', 'Farrukhabad', 'This GeM bid document (GEM/2025/B/6319440, dated 06-06-2025) issued by the Airports Authority of India (AAI), Ministry of Civil Aviation, is for the procurement of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2500 km x 320 hours; Local 24*7''. The specific work is for the ''Hiring of 01 No. AC Mahindra Bolero or equivalent or Higher Segment Vehicle with Commercial Registration for Office use of AAI ACS, Farrukhabad''. The contract period is for 2 years, with a potential extension of 12 months based on satisfactory performance. The estimated bid value is INR 18,16,536, with a required EMD of INR 36,331 and a Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 5.00% for 27 months. Key bidder eligibility criteria include a minimum average annual turnover of 6 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. The bid is a two-packet system, and bidders must comply with all terms, including statutory obligations like EPF, ESI, and the Minimum Wages Act. The contract details comprehensive obligations for the service provider regarding vehicle maintenance, driver conduct, logbook management, and adherence to all applicable laws, with specified penalties for non-compliance. The paying authority is the Officer In-Charge, AAI, ACS Farrukhabad.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer (AAI), the work will be considered successfully completed upon the contractor''s consistent and satisfactory performance throughout the contract period. This includes providing the specified vehicle (AC Mahindra Bolero or equivalent) for the stipulated 2500 KM & 320 Hours per month, without any defaults or lapses. The vehicle must be maintained in perfect working condition, adhering to the age (not older than April-2023) and mileage (under 50,000 km) criteria. The driver provided must be uniformed, licensed, well-behaved, and punctual at all times. Crucially, the contractor must demonstrate full and timely compliance with all statutory and labor laws, including the payment of minimum wages, EPF, and ESI, and provide documentary proof with monthly bills. Accurate and tamper-proof maintenance of logbooks for verification is mandatory. The successful completion of the contract, leading to the release of the security deposit, is contingent upon the fulfillment of all these terms and conditions without incurring penalties and resolving any dues.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring of one (01) AC Mahindra Bolero or an equivalent or higher segment 7-seater vehicle with a driver for office use at AAI ACS, Farrukhabad. The service is required on a regular basis, covering all days from Monday to Sunday, for a monthly usage of 2500 KM and 320 Hours. The contract period is for two years, extendable by another 12 months upon satisfactory performance. The vehicle provided must not be older than April 2023, must have run less than 50,000 km, and must be commercially registered with all valid documents such as RC, insurance, PUC, and permits. The contractor is responsible for all operational costs including fuel, lubricants, repairs, maintenance, driver wages, road taxes, insurance, and permits. The contractor must ensure compliance with all applicable labor laws, including the Minimum Wages Act, EPF, and ESI Acts. The driver must be qualified, licensed, experienced, uniformed, well-behaved, and equipped with a mobile phone for coordination. The contractor is also responsible for maintaining proper logbooks for the vehicle''s usage for verification and billing purposes.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6319716', '17-06-2025 18:00:00', '17-06-2025 18:30:00', '60 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'Eastern Railway', 'Malda Division', 'chandrapatel.2008@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 1500 km x 720 hours; Outstation 24*7', NULL, '3 Years 1 Day', '6,00,000', NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Bidder Turnover, Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '13,17,11,976', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '26,400', NULL, 5, 42, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require a SUV type vehicle, with options including Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra TUV300, or Mahindra Scorpio. The vehicle should be a recent model from the years 2025, 2024, or 2023 and must have travelled Upto 50,000 Kms. The required usage variant is 1500 km x 720 hours for an Outstation 24*7 type of service. The vehicle must be Non-A/C and capable of operating in both Hilly + Plain Area. Any fuel type is acceptable. No specific add-ons are mentioned.', 'Chandra Kumar Patel', 'Malda', 'This is a tender (Bid Number: GEM/2025/B/6319716) issued by the Malda Division of Eastern Railway, Ministry of Railways, for the hiring of a non-AC SUV cab on a monthly basis. The contract period is for 3 years and 1 day. The service required is for one SUV (such as a Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra TUV300, or Mahindra Scorpio) to be available 24x7 for outstation duty, covering 1500 km and 720 hours per month. The estimated bid value is 1317119.76 INR, with an Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of 26400 INR and an e-Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 5% required for 42 months. The minimum average annual turnover for bidders is 6 Lakhs, though exemptions are available for MSEs and Startups. Key requirements for the vehicle include being a 2023 model or newer, in excellent working condition, commercially registered, and possessing a taxi permit valid for West Bengal, Jharkhand, and Bihar. The contractor is responsible for all associated costs, including fuel, maintenance, driver''s salary, insurance, taxes, and tolls. The tender includes an option clause allowing the buyer to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. The contract is governed by GeM''s General Terms and Conditions and includes specific buyer-added terms regarding vehicle condition, driver conduct, and penalties for service failures.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be deemed successfully completed upon the consistent fulfillment of the following criteria throughout the contract period: The contractor must provide one specified non-AC SUV (2023 model or newer) in good, defect-free, and proper working condition at all times. The vehicle and a skilled, uniformed driver must be available 24x7 for official use and must report to the Sr. DEE/G/MLDT or his representative as required. The contractor must ensure the vehicle is always adequately fueled and maintained, providing a suitable standby vehicle during maintenance and a replacement within one hour during breakdowns. The service must be provided continuously without interruption, even during bandhs or natural calamities. The contractor must adhere to all legal and statutory requirements, including the Contract Labour Act 1970, minimum wage laws, and payment of all taxes and tolls. The contractor must fully indemnify the Railway Administration against all claims arising from accidents, damages, or breaches of contract terms. The satisfactory performance of all these obligations, as judged solely by the railway administration, constitutes the successful completion of the work.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring of one Non-AC SUV road vehicle (such as a TUV-300, Scorpio, Ertiga, or similar) complete with a driver and fuel for the official use of the Electrical General Department of Malda Division, Eastern Railway. The service is required for a duration of 3 years (36 months) on a 24x7 basis. The contract covers a running distance of 1500 km and 720 hours per month, with running charges calculated for an average of 50 km per day. The vehicle must be supplied at any location within the division as required across the states of West Bengal, Jharkhand, and Bihar. The hiring charge is all-inclusive, covering vehicle maintenance, repairs, license fees, permits, insurance, registration, all taxes (including toll taxes), fuel, lubricants, other consumables, and the wages for two drivers. The vehicle must be a 2023 model or newer, commercially registered, and maintained in excellent condition. The contractor is also responsible for providing a skilled driver with a valid license, ensuring the vehicle is available at all times, providing a standby vehicle during maintenance, and replacing the vehicle within one hour in case of en-route breakdown.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6320024', '17-06-2025 21:00:00', '17-06-2025 21:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Finance', 'Department Of Revenue', 'Central Board Of Excise And Customs (cbec)', 'Jaipur Zone', 'aocex-sik-rj@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local 24*7', NULL, '1 Year', '5,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), OEM Authorization Certificate, OEM Annual Turnover, Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, 3, 15, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require a Sedan type vehicle for monthly cab and taxi hiring services. The acceptable car models include Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, Hyundai Xcent, and Toyota Etios. The vehicle will be used for a usage variant of 2000 km and 320 hours per month on a Local 24*7 basis. The required model year for the vehicle is 2023, 2024, or 2025, and it should have travelled up to 50,000 Kms. The vehicle must be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C) and will operate in the Plains area. Any fuel type is acceptable.', 'Rajesh Yadav', 'Sikar', 'This bid document, GEM/2025/B/6320024, issued by the Jaipur Zone of the Central Board of Excise And Customs (cbec), invites tenders for the hiring of one Sedan cab on a monthly basis for a contract period of one year. The service required is for 2000 km and 320 hours per month on a 24*7 local basis. Key dates include the bid end date on 17-06-2025, with a bid offer validity of 90 days. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 5 Lakhs over the last three years and 3 years of past experience in similar services, although exemptions are available for MSEs and Startups. The evaluation will be based on a total value wise method within a two-packet bid system. The successful bidder will be required to furnish an ePBG of 3.00% for a duration of 15 months. The consignee is the Assistant Commissioner, CGST DIVISION-SIKAR. The tender includes several buyer-added terms and conditions, such as an option clause to vary the contract quantity by up to 25%, a requirement for the bidder to be financially sound, and the service provider to have an office in the consignee''s state. The detailed terms specify that the vehicle must not be more than 3 years old, should be registered as a taxi, run on petrol or diesel only, and be provided with a licensed, experienced, and well-behaved driver. The contract specifies a performance security of 3% of the total contract value to be submitted upon award.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be deemed successfully completed upon the fulfillment of several key conditions. Firstly, the successful bidder must furnish a Performance Security equivalent to 3% of the total contract value to ensure due performance throughout the contract period. The contractor must consistently provide a vehicle that meets all specifications, including being less than three years old, in excellent condition, with all necessary permits, and registered for commercial taxi purposes. The service must be reliable, with the vehicle and driver available as required, including on holidays and weekends, and a replacement vehicle must be provided promptly in case of any breakdown. The driver must be professional, licensed, experienced, and well-behaved. Critically, the service provider must maintain an accurate logbook for all journeys, have it certified by the designated officer, and submit it with monthly bills for payment. Full compliance with all applicable laws, including GST and labor laws, and indemnifying the department against any liabilities arising from accidents or negligence are also essential for the successful completion of the contract.', 'The scope of work involves providing one small-size Sedan vehicle, such as a Dzire, Xcent, Amaze, or an equivalent model, in white color, for hire on a monthly basis for the Central Goods & Service Tax Division, Sikar. The contract is for a period of one year. The vehicle is to be used for a maximum of 2000 kms per month for official duties, operating approximately 25-26 days a month. The general service hours are from 9:00 AM to 9:00 PM, but the vehicle must be available on any day required, including Saturdays, Sundays, and holidays. The vehicle provided must not be more than three years old, must be in very good condition with a clean interior, and registered as a TAXI/Transport vehicle. It should have all valid documents including registration, comprehensive insurance, and pollution certificates, and must run only on petrol or diesel. The service provider must also supply a qualified and experienced driver with a valid commercial license who is well-behaved, familiar with local routes, and has a mobile phone for constant contact. The driver is expected to wear a uniform and maintain a logbook for all trips, which must be signed by the officer using the vehicle. The billing will be on a monthly basis, supported by the duty slips and the logbook. In case of a vehicle breakdown, the provider must arrange for a suitable replacement immediately at their own cost.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6321294', '17-06-2025 21:00:00', '17-06-2025 21:30:00', '80 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Defence Production', 'Bharat Earth Movers Limited (beml)', '***********', 'buyer197.bemlb.ka@gembuyer.in', 'Custom Bid for Services - TOTAL CHARGES INCLUDING GST FOR HIRING OF 15T MOBILE CRANE FOR 18 JOBS', 'Support Services', '2 Months 2 Day', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '3,18,600', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications outline the requirements for a custom bid service, specifically for ''TOTAL CHARGES INCLUDING GST FOR HIRING OF 15T MOBILE CRANE FOR 18 JOBS''. The service provider must ensure full compliance with all regulatory and statutory obligations. Additionally, the service must strictly adhere to the defined Scope of Work (SOW), Special Terms and Conditions (STC), and the Service Level Agreement (SLA).', '***********', 'Kolar', 'This bid document, with Bid Number GEM/2025/B/6321294, is for a ''Custom Bid for Services - TOTAL CHARGES INCLUDING GST FOR HIRING OF 15T MOBILE CRANE FOR 18 JOBS'', issued by Bharat Earth Movers Limited (beml) under the Ministry of Defence. The bid has an end date of 17-06-2025 and a bid offer validity of 80 days. The contract period is specified as 2 months and 2 days, although the scope of work mentions a period of one year. The estimated bid value is 318600, and the evaluation will be based on the total value. The bid is a Two Packet Bid type with no EMD or ePBG required. The service involves hiring a 15T mobile crane with an operator for 18 jobs, where one job equals one day of up to 8 hours of operation. The consignee is located in Kolar. The bid indicates compliance with MII and MSE purchase preference policies. Key conditions include an option clause allowing the buyer to vary the contract quantity or duration by up to 50%. The successful bidder must comply with all applicable labor laws. Payment terms are 60 days credit (45 days for MSME).', 'The work will be considered successfully completed upon fulfilling the following criteria from the tender issuer''s perspective:
1. Successful completion of the work is subject to certification by the Maintenance department.
2. Strict compliance with the entire Scope of Work (SOW), Special Terms and Conditions (STC), and Service Level Agreement (SLA).
3. Ensuring no damage is caused to either machines or company property during the removal and shifting operations.
4. The mobile crane and all lifting tackles must possess a valid Fitness Certificate as per the Factories Act, certified by an authorized agency, throughout the contract period.
5. The firm must obtain and maintain a valid Safety Permit to carry out all works inside the factory premises.', 'The scope of work is for the hiring of a 15T Mobile Crane for removing condemned machines, Sub-Assemblies, and Heavy Structures from Production shops for a period of one year. The firm is required to deploy the 15T mobile crane along with an operator to shift Heavy Structures from the shops to various locations as per the instructions of the In-charge maintenance, on a need basis, with a prior intimation of 01 day. The operator must inspect the site and provide instructions for site clearance before commencing the work. The firm must provide all necessary lifting tackles, such as chains with hook blocks/ropes, for handling the tasks. Utmost care must be taken during the removal of condemned machines and shifting to the salvage yard to ensure no damage is caused to any machine or company property. The Mobile Crane Operator must be covered under ESI/Medical Coverage, and the firm must obtain a Safety Permit for working inside the factory. Both the Mobile Crane and its lifting tackles must have a valid Fitness Certificate as per the Factories Act, certified by an Authorized Agency. One ''JOB'' is defined as one day of a maximum of 8 hours of operation.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6323708', '19-06-2025 14:00:00', '19-06-2025 14:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'Diesel Loco Modernisation Works', 'Diesel Loco Modernisation Works, Patiala', 'dycmm4dmw@dmw.railnet.gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2500 km x 320 hours; Outstation 24*7', NULL, '2 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '24,480', 'Yes', 5, 30, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the required service detail the hiring of an SUV type vehicle. Acceptable car models include Mahindra XUV 500, Mahindra Scorpio, or KIA Carens. The usage variant is specified as 2500 km x 320 hours for an Outstation 24*7 type of service. The vehicle model must be from the year 2024 or 2025 and should not be older than March 2024, with total kilometers travelled being up to 25,000 Kms. The vehicle must have air conditioning (A/C), operate in the Plains area, and use Petrol as its fuel type.', 'Reena Garg', 'Patiala', 'This is a bid invitation, number GEM/2025/B/6323708, issued by Diesel Loco Modernisation Works, Patiala, under the Ministry of Railways for the hiring of a Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Service. The service requires an SUV for a usage of 2500 km x 320 hours per month with 24*7 outstation availability. The bid end date is 19-06-2025 at 14:00:00, with a bid offer validity of 120 days. The contract period is for 2 years. The bid is a single packet type with a total value wise evaluation method. An EMD amount of 24480 is required, and an ePBG of 5.00% is mandated for a duration of 30 months. MSE and Startup exemptions for experience and turnover are not provided. The required vehicle must be a 2024 or 2025 model, not older than March 2024, from specified makes like Mahindra XUV 500, Mahindra Scorpio, or KIA Carens. One vehicle is required for the consignee Reena Garg at DMW, Hospital, Patiala for a duration of 24 months. The bid includes an option clause for the buyer to increase or decrease the quantity or duration by up to 25%. Bidders must not be under liquidation or bankrupt and must provide a dedicated toll-free number for service support.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following criteria: The contractor must provide one SUV that strictly adheres to all specified technical specifications, including the model (Mahindra XUV 500, Mahindra Scorpio, or KIA Carens), model year (not older than March 2024), fuel type (Petrol), and condition (A/C enabled, travelled up to 25,000 Kms). The vehicle must be made available for the entire contract period of 2 years (24 months) and consistently meet the monthly usage requirement of 2500 km and 320 hours with 24*7 outstation availability. The contractor must comply with all buyer-added terms and conditions, including the submission of all required certificates and documents as per the ATC and SLA. The service must be delivered without interruption to the specified consignee, and the provider must maintain a dedicated support line throughout the contract duration. Adherence to all applicable labour laws is also a mandatory condition for successful contract completion.', 'The scope of work involves providing one SUV vehicle on a monthly hiring basis for a contract period of 2 years (24 months). The service is for the Diesel Loco Modernisation Works, Patiala, with the vehicle assigned to the consignee Reena Garg at DMW, Hospital, Patiala. The required service is for ''Outstation 24*7'' usage, covering 2500 kilometers and 320 hours per month. The vehicle must be an SUV, with acceptable models being Mahindra XUV 500, Mahindra Scorpio, or KIA Carens. A critical requirement is that the vehicle''s model year must be from 2024 or 2025, and it should not be older than March 2024. The vehicle must be readily available at the time of contract award, have an odometer reading of up to 25,000 Kms, be air-conditioned, and operate on Petrol fuel in the Plains area. The service provider is also required to mention the specific Make/Brand and year of the vehicle in their offer, submit all necessary certificates and documents as per the tender''s ATC, SLA, and Terms & Conditions, and provide a dedicated/toll-free telephone number for service support.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6324079', '19-06-2025 14:00:00', '19-06-2025 14:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Finance', 'Department Of Revenue', 'Central Board Of Direct Taxes (cbdt)', 'Principal Commissioner Of Income Tax Tirupati', 'buycon779.cbdtc.ap@gembuyer.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local 24*7', NULL, '9 Month', '5,00,000', '3 Year', 'No', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), OEM Authorization Certificate, OEM Annual Turnover *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '3,60,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the required service mandate a Sedan vehicle type, with acceptable models being Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, or Hyundai Xcent. The usage variant is specified as 2000 km x 320 hours per month. The service required is Local 24*7. The vehicle model must be from the year 2023, 2024, or 2025, and should have travelled upto 50,000 Kms. An Air Conditioning (A/C) facility is a mandatory requirement. The area of operation is Plains, and the vehicle can use any fuel type.', 'Pynam Ravindra Kumar', 'Tirupati', 'This bid document, number GEM/2025/B/6324079, issued by the Principal Commissioner Of Income Tax Tirupati under the Ministry of Finance, is for the procurement of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local 24*7''. The contract period is for 9 months with an estimated bid value of 360000. The bid end date is 19-06-2025. This is a Two Packet Bid, and the evaluation will be on a total value wise basis. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 5 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. While startups are exempt from turnover and experience criteria, MSEs are not. Bidders are required to submit documents such as Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, OEM Authorization Certificate, and OEM Annual Turnover. The service requires one Sedan vehicle for a duration of 9 months, to be provided to the consignee Pynam Ravindra Kumar in Tirupati. The buyer has included an option clause allowing for a 25 percent increase or decrease in contract quantity or duration.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the consistent and uninterrupted provision of one Sedan cab service for the entire contract duration of 9 months, strictly adhering to all specified technical specifications. This includes providing a vehicle of the model year 2023, 2024, or 2025, with functional A/C, that meets the monthly usage requirements of 2000 km and 320 hours. Success is also contingent on the service provider''s full compliance with all terms and conditions outlined in the bid document, the Buyer Added Bid Specific Terms and Conditions, and the Service Level Agreement, ensuring the service is available 24*7 locally at the specified location in Tirupati without any defaults or breaches of contract.', 'The scope of work involves providing one Sedan type vehicle on a monthly hiring basis for the Principal Commissioner Of Income Tax, Tirupati. The service is required for a contract period of 9 months. The vehicle must be one of the specified models such as Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, or Hyundai Xcent, and must be of the model year 2023, 2024, or 2025 with total running upto 50,000 Kms. The vehicle must be equipped with a functional air conditioner (A/C). The service entails providing the vehicle for a monthly usage of up to 2000 kilometers and 320 hours, operating locally in the plains region on a 24*7 basis. The service is to be provided to the consignee, Pynam Ravindra Kumar, at the Aayakar Bhavan (Income Tax Office), K T Road, Tirupati - 517501.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6324132', '19-06-2025 14:00:00', '19-06-2025 14:30:00', '30 Days', 'Ministry Of Finance', 'Department Of Expenditure', 'Controller General Of Accounts (cga)', 'Public Financial Management System', 'suman.17@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local', NULL, '1 Year', '6,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'State Bank of India', '13,680', 'Yes', 5, 12, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require a Sedan vehicle of the 2024 model year with mileage up to 75,000 Kms. Acceptable car types include Maruti Suzuki Dzire, Hyundai Xcent, Ford Aspire, Volkswagen Ameo, Toyota Etios, and Maruti Suzuki Tour S. The usage variant is defined as 2000 km x 320 hours for local service. The vehicle must be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C) and can be of any fuel type, operating in the Plains area.', 'SUMAN', 'Panchkula', 'The bid document (GEM/2025/B/6324132), dated 09-06-2025, is for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for one Sedan vehicle. The contract period is one year, with a monthly usage of 2000 km and 320 hours for local service. The bid is issued by the Public Financial Management System, under the Ministry of Finance, and closes on 19-06-2025. Key requirements for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 6 Lakhs for the last three years and 3 years of past experience in similar services, with exemptions available for MSEs and Startups. The bid is a two-packet type with a total value-wise evaluation method. It requires an EMD of 13680 and an ePBG of 5% for a duration of 12 months. The buyer has included an option clause to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. The scope of work specifies qualitative requirements for both the driver (e.g., 2-3 years of experience, commercial license) and the vehicle (e.g., neat & clean, well-maintained). All service providers must ensure compliance with applicable labour laws.', 'The work will be considered successfully completed upon the consistent and satisfactory provision of the specified cab hiring service for the entire contract period of one year. This entails providing one Sedan vehicle that adheres to all technical specifications (2024 model, A/C, neat and clean condition, etc.) and a driver who meets all qualitative requirements (2-3 years experience, commercial license, physically fit, etc.). The provider must meet the monthly usage of 2000 km and 320 hours and operate as per the defined work schedule of 10 hours per day, 6 days a week. Successful completion is contingent on full compliance with all terms and conditions stipulated in the bid document, the Service Level Agreement, and all applicable laws and regulations.', 'The scope of work is for the outsourcing of one operational vehicle for the PFMS State Directorate in Panchkula, Haryana, on a monthly basis for a one-year contract. The service involves providing a Sedan cab for local use, with a monthly cap of 2000 km and 320 hours. The vehicle must be a 2024 model, with mileage up to 75,000 Kms, equipped with A/C, and maintained in a neat, clean, and tidy condition at all times. The driver provided must have a minimum of 2-3 years of experience, preferably be between 18-45 years of age, be proficient in Hindi, physically fit, and hold a commercial driving license. The required working hours are 10 hours per day for 6 days a week, up to a maximum of 30 days in a month. The scope also includes performing any other duties assigned by the department.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6325110', '20-06-2025 14:00:00', '20-06-2025 14:30:00', '100 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'South Eastern Railway', 'South Eastern Railway', 'jayanta.m3112@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - MUV; 2000 km x 320 hours for FOR THE USE OF AMM COACHING SRC OFFICE AT SANTRAGACHI S E RAILWAY; Outstation 24*7', NULL, '2 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '21,360', 'Yes', 5, 26, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the required service detail a Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Service. The Vehicle Type must be an MUV, with acceptable models including Tata Xenon Yodha, Mahindra Bolero Maxitruck, Ashok Leyland Dost, and Tata Xenon XT. The Usage Variant is specified as 2000 km x 320 hours for FOR THE USE OF AMM COACHING SRC OFFICE AT SANTRAGACHI S E RAILWAY. The Type of Service required is Outstation 24*7. The vehicle''s model year should be 2024, 2025, or 2023, and it should have travelled Upto 50,000 Kms. The vehicle must be Non-A/C and operate on Diesel fuel. The designated Area of Operation is Plains.', 'Ashis Kumar Ghosh', 'Santragachi', 'This bid, GEM/2025/B/6325110, issued by the Ministry of Railways, South Eastern Railway, is for the procurement of a Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Service. The service is required for the AMM COACHING SRC OFFICE AT SANTRAGACHI S E RAILWAY for a contract period of 2 years. The scope involves one MUV type vehicle for 2000 km and 320 hours per month on a 24*7 outstation basis. The bid offer is valid for 100 days from the end date of 20-06-2025. The required EMD is 21360, and a Performance Bank Guarantee of 5.00% is required for 26 months. Bidders must have a geographic presence in West Bengal and are required to submit documents for Experience Criteria and Bidder Turnover. The contract includes an option clause allowing the buyer to increase or decrease the quantity or duration by up to 25%. Key conditions state the vehicle must be commercially registered, not more than two years old, available 24/7 at short notice, and capable of operating on difficult railway terrains. The successful bidder must submit all vehicle documents and a Performance Security. The contract may be extended by up to 6 months based on satisfactory performance.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the successful completion of the work is contingent upon the contractor''s adherence to several key criteria throughout the 24-month contract period. Firstly, the contractor must consistently provide one specified MUV, which is commercially registered, not more than two years old, and maintained in good condition. Secondly, the service must be available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, with the vehicle being provided promptly even at short notice for exigencies as required by the Railway. Thirdly, the contractor must ensure the vehicle and driver can operate effectively on railway sites, including difficult and non-motorable terrains. Adherence to the monthly usage limits of 2000 km and 320 hours is mandatory. Finally, successful completion is marked by the fulfillment of all contractual obligations without penalty, including the timely submission of all required documents and the Performance Security, leading to the eventual release of the security deposit after the contract term concludes.', 'The scope of work involves the supply of one MUV type, non-A/C, diesel-powered four-wheeler road vehicle on a monthly hiring basis for a duration of 24 months. The service is for the use of the AMM COACHING SRC OFFICE AT SANTRAGACHI S E RAILWAY. Acceptable vehicle models include Tata Xenon Yodha (Double Cabin), Mahindra Bolero Maxitruck (Double Cabin), Ashok Leyland Dost (Double Cabin), and Tata Xenon XT (Double Cabin). The provided vehicle must not be more than two years old from its first purchase date, must be in good condition, and must be commercially registered. The service entails a usage of approximately 2000 KM and 320 hours per month and must be available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, even at short notice. The vehicle is required to run on railway sites, including difficult terrain and non-motorable roads, for purposes such as relief in exigencies like breakdowns, accidents, derailments, and for the inspection of higher officials. The vehicle will remain in the custody of the contractor''s driver at all times, and the Railway will not be liable for any loss or damage to the vehicle or provide any accommodation or allowance for the driver.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6325706', '17-06-2025 19:00:00', '17-06-2025 19:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Water Resources River Development And Ganga Rejuvenation', 'National Projects Construction Corporation Limited', 'National Projects Construction Corporation Limited', 'Npcc Ltd.', 'sriman.204385@npcc.gov.in', 'Hiring of Consultants - Milestone/Deliverable Based - Engineering Consultancy Services Including TPQA for Construction of State-of-the-Art Integrated Farmers Training Centre at Kausalyaganga Fish Farm Odisha; Engineering Design, Project Management, E..', NULL, '1 Year', NULL, '7 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '3 Days', NULL, '11,85,788', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'ICICI', '23,720', NULL, 5, 12, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for this consultancy service fall under the core category of Engineering Consultancy Services Including TPQA for the Construction of a State-of-the-Art Integrated Farmers Training Centre at Kausalyaganga Fish Farm, Odisha. The required consultant''s profile includes expertise in Engineering Design, Project Management, and Engineering Consultancy Services. A Proof of Concept (POC) is not definitively required, indicated by ''Yes, No''. The deployment of consultants and resources can be Offsite, Onsite, or Hybrid, as specified in the scope of work. There are no addon specifications mentioned in the table.', 'Sriman Kumar Pattnaik', 'Bhubaneswar', 'This is a tender (Bid Number: GEM/2025/B/6325706, e-NIT No.: NPCC/SEZ/AC/OPDC/KG/TC/602) issued by National Projects Construction Corporation Limited (NPCC) on behalf of the Director of Fisheries, Odisha, for the ''Hiring of Consultants for Engineering Consultancy Services Including TPQA for Construction of State-of-the-Art Integrated Farmers Training Centre at Kausalyaganga Fish Farm Odisha''. The project is located in Puri, Odisha, with an estimated cost of ₹1185.78 Lakh and a consultancy work value of ₹11,85,788.00. The contract period is 1 year, with a required past experience of 7 years in similar services. Key dates include the bid end time on 17-06-2025 at 19:00:00 and bid opening at 19:30:00 on the same day, with a bid validity of 120 days. The selection process is a Two Packet Bid based on Quality & Cost Based Selection (QCBS) with a 70:30 weightage for technical and financial scores, respectively, and a minimum qualifying technical score of 60. An Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of ₹23,720 is required, and a Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) of 5.00% is mandated for a duration of 12 months.', 'The successful completion of the tender is contingent upon several key criteria from the issuer''s perspective. The consultant must adhere strictly to the time schedule for all deliverables, as any slippage will lead to penalties. Success is defined by the timely preparation and submission of all required drawings (including detailed, GFC, and structural drawings), which must be vetted by a designated institution like IIT/NIT. The consultant must provide comprehensive TPQA reports during the project''s execution at 30%, 60%, and 90% physical completion stages. A critical success factor is the final acceptance of the project by the owner/client, the Director of Fisheries, Odisha, which includes the verification of as-built drawings. Furthermore, the work is considered successfully completed only after the consultant provides all necessary support during the 12-month Defects Liability Period (DLP), obtaining the final completion certificate from all concerned authorities, and ensuring all deliverables as per Annexure ''B'' are submitted and approved.', 'The Scope of Work for the consultant is comprehensive, covering the entire project lifecycle from conception to post-completion. It includes preparing detailed architectural, GFC, and structural drawings using software like STAAD-PRO; creating a detailed layout of the scheme; and providing a detailed report on geo-technical findings. The consultant is responsible for all design details and calculations (structural, electrical, mechanical) and must get them certified and proof-checked by NPCC or other designated agencies like IITs/NITs. A key responsibility is developing and implementing a quality assurance scheme, including submitting quality control test reports and vetting the construction agency''s running bills. The work also involves preparing ''good for construction'' drawings, conducting regular site visits to resolve issues, and obtaining all necessary approvals from local and statutory bodies (e.g., Pollution Control Board). The consultant must also design the project following Green Building Norms, prepare tender documents for equipment procurement, and submit completion reports, O&M manuals, and as-built drawings. The scope extends to the 12-month Defects Liability Period, during which the consultant must provide drawings and details for any required rectification.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6326088', '16-06-2025 10:00:00', '16-06-2025 10:30:00', '60 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Army', '***********', 'bala.610666-cgo@gov.in', 'Hiring of Custom House Agent - Lumpsum Based - Export; PREPARATION OF ARCHITECTURAL AND STRUCTURAL DRAWINGS INCLUDING STRUCTURAL DESIGN, PREPARATION OF DETAILED ESTIMATE & YARD STICK; PREPARATION OF ARCHITECTURAL AND STRUCTURAL DRAWINGS INCLUDING STR..', NULL, '2 Months 2 Day', '50,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'H1-Highest Priced Bid Elimination', 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '15,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'GE Tirunelveli', '30,000', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications outline a service for an Export type shipment with an Inland port for clearance. The service inclusions, nature of cargo, type of commodity, and the value of the consignment during the contract duration are all defined as the PREPARATION OF ARCHITECTURAL AND STRUCTURAL DRAWINGS INCLUDING STRUCTURAL DESIGN, PREPARATION OF DETAILED ESTIMATE & YARD STICK. The cargo is specified to be Non-Dangerous.', '***********', 'Tirunelveli', 'This is a tender (Bid Number: GEM/2025/B/6326088) issued by the Indian Army, Ministry of Defence, for the ''PREPARATION OF ARCHITECTURAL AND STRUCTURAL DRAWINGS INCLUDING STRUCTURAL DESIGN, PREPARATION OF DETAILED ESTIMATE & YARD STICK : PROVISION OF CIVIL WORKS FOR ASR & MSSR RADARS AT INS PARUNDU, RAMNAD''. The contract period is 2 months and 2 days, with an estimated bid value of 1,500,000 INR (15 Lakhs). The bid is a Two Packet Bid with a total value wise evaluation method. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 50 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services, though exemptions are available for MSE and Startup entities. The work, with a completion period of 60 days, involves providing consultancy for civil works including the construction of an antenna tower, radar equipment complex, DG sheds, and other associated structures. The successful consultant must be enlisted with MES in specified categories and provide comprehensive architectural and structural design services, including drawings vetted by IIT, detailed estimates, and continuous technical support through the construction phase.', 'The work will be considered successfully completed upon fulfillment of several criteria from the tender issuer''s perspective. The consultant must prepare and submit complete conceptual plans and architectural drawings, which must be approved by the User and the Director (Arch) of HQ, CE Navy, Visakhapatnam & CWE Navy Chennai. Subsequently, the consultant must provide structural analysis and design drawings for all buildings, which must be accompanied by a Design Basis Report and a vetting certificate from an IIT/IISc, confirming compliance with all standards for safety, soundness, and economy; these also require approval from the Director (Designs), HQ, CE Navy, Visakhapatnam. A detailed estimate and yardstick must be prepared based on these approved drawings. Finally, the consultant is required to provide continuous technical support as needed until the successful completion of the work, including throughout the construction phase.', 'The scope of work is for the ''PREPARATION OF ARCHITECTURAL AND STRUCTURAL DRAWINGS INCLUDING STRUCTURAL DESIGN, PREPARATION OF DETAILED ESTIMATE & YARD STICK : PROVISION OF CIVIL WORKS FOR ASR & MSSR RADARS AT INS PARUNDU, RAMNAD''. This includes the design and drawings for the following civil works: 1. A 24-meter high RCC Antenna Tower with a staircase, lift for heavy equipment (up to 1000 Kg), and other fittings. 2. A G+2 Radar Equipment Room Complex of size 12.90 x 12.90 mtr with washrooms and a staircase. 3. Two DG Sheds of sizes 6.00x5.00 mtr and 6.00x8.00 mtr. 4. A parking shed of size 9.00x7.00 mtr. 5. A concrete platform for a transformer. The services required to facilitate this work include: a. Architecture Services: Preparation of complete conceptual plans, architectural drawings (elevations, sections), site plans, 3D views (interior & exterior), and 3 different walk-through models. b. Structural Services: Structural design and drawing for all buildings, supported by relevant design data (STAAD File), and proof checking & vetting from IIT. c. Detailed Estimate: Preparation of a Detailed Estimate & Yardstick as per SSR 2020 and market rate analysis based on the approved drawings. All work is to be carried out using BIM-based software with final submissions in DWG/CAD and PDF formats.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6326748', '20-06-2025 10:00:00', '20-06-2025 10:30:00', '90 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'Central Railway', 'Central Railway Stores Deptt', 'dycmmetl@cr.railnet.gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 1500 km x 320 hours; Local', NULL, '2 Year', NULL, '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '12,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', NULL, 'Yes', 5, 30, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the required service detail the hiring of an SUV type vehicle. The acceptable car models include Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra XUV 500, Maruti Suzuki Vitara Brezza, Maruti Suzuki XL6, Hyundai Creta, Renault Duster, Mahindra XUV300, and Mahindra Scorpio. The vehicle will be used for local service with a usage variant of 1500 km x 320 hours per month. The required vehicle model year is 2024 or 2025, with total travel up to 25,000 Kms. The service requires a Non-A/C vehicle to operate in plains, and it can run on any fuel type.', 'Umang Gopal Dubey', 'Mumbai', 'This bid document, number GEM/2025/B/6326748 dated 10-06-2025, is for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services by the Central Railway Stores Deptt, Ministry Of Railways. The contract period is for 2 years, requiring a single SUV for local use up to 1500 km and 320 hours per month. The estimated bid value is 1,200,000, and the contract requires a 5% ePBG for a duration of 30 months. Bidders must have 3 years of past experience in similar services, and only contractors located in Maharashtra state are eligible to quote. The scope of work is divided into two parts: the deployment and operation of the vehicle (including fuel, maintenance, and all necessary permits) and the deployment of a driver (whose salary and compliance with labour laws are the contractor''s responsibility). The driver''s salary is fixed as per a specified structure. Successful completion of the contract is contingent upon receiving a certificate from the user department confirming satisfactory service and no pending dues, which is necessary for the refund of the performance guarantee.', 'The successful completion of the tender is determined by the fulfillment of the contract for its entire duration. Upon completion, the contractor must obtain a certificate from the user department which validates that the service was rendered successfully and that there are no pending dues whatsoever against the contractor. The refund of the Performance Guarantee is subject to the submission and acceptance of this certificate.', 'The scope of work involves providing monthly cab hiring services and is structured in two main parts: a) Deployment and operations of the vehicle, and b) Deployment of the driver. For vehicle operations, the contractor must provide one SUV compliant with the specified technical requirements, inclusive of fuel, on a monthly basis. The contractor is responsible for all maintenance, repairs, washing, and cleaning, which must be carried out in off-duty hours. Furthermore, the contractor must ensure the vehicle has all necessary and valid permits and clearances, including fitness certificate, PUC, full comprehensive insurance, road permit, and registration certificate. For the driver''s deployment, the contractor must provide one driver per vehicle who possesses a valid driving license and has had their criminal antecedents verified by the Police Authority. The driver must be approved by the user officer, and the contractor must provide them with proper uniform, badges, and photo identity cards. The contractor is solely responsible for paying the driver''s salary according to the specified structure and ensuring full compliance with all applicable Labour Laws, including PF, ESI, and Minimum Wages Act. Invoicing must be done monthly in two parts, corresponding to vehicle charges and driver emoluments, with documentary proof of salary payment required for bill processing.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6327217', '20-06-2025 12:00:00', '20-06-2025 12:30:00', '180 Days', 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Basic Education Department Uttar Pradesh', NULL, 'Director Basic Education, Lucknow', 'bsa.mo-up@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 1500 km x 320 hours; Local 24*7', NULL, '9 Month', '8,00,000', '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '27,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Bank Of Baroda', '27,000', NULL, 2.5, 9, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require the provision of an SUV type vehicle, specifically mentioning Mahindra Bolero as an option. The usage variant is defined as 1500 km x 320 hours on a monthly basis. The service is required locally on a 24*7 basis. The vehicle model should be from the year 2022, with total travel not exceeding 1,00,000 Kms. The vehicle must be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C), operate in Plains areas, and run on Diesel fuel. There are no add-on specifications mentioned.', 'Vimlesh Kumar', 'Moradabad', 'This bid document, number GEM/2025/B/6327217 dated 10-06-2025, is for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for the Basic Education Department of Uttar Pradesh. The service required is for an SUV type vehicle for a usage of 1500 km and 320 hours per month on a local 24*7 basis, with a contract period of 9 months. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with an estimated value of 27,000,000 and requires an EMD of 27,000 and an ePBG of 2.50% for 9 months. The beneficiary for the service is the BSA OFFICE in Moradabad, requiring a total of 10 vehicles. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 8 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. There are no exemptions for MSE or Startups for experience and turnover. The bid specifies detailed past performance criteria and requires additional qualifications regarding the fleet of owned vehicles, drivers on payroll, and experience with government agencies. The evaluation method is on a total value wise basis. The bid includes an option clause allowing the buyer to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the consistent and uninterrupted provision of 10 SUV vehicles for the entire 9-month contract period, strictly adhering to all specified technical specifications. This includes ensuring each vehicle meets the 2022 model year, is diesel-fueled, has A/C, has travelled under 1,00,000 kms, and is available for the stipulated 1500 km and 320 hours monthly usage on a Local 24*7 basis. Success also hinges on the contractor''s full compliance with all terms and conditions laid out in the bid document, the Buyer Added Bid Specific Terms and Conditions, and the Service Level Agreement. Final success is marked by the completion of the contract term without any breach, confirmed through satisfactory service delivery and adherence to all contractual obligations.', 'The scope of work involves providing Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for a duration of 9 months. The service provider is required to supply a total of 10 vehicles to the consignee located at BSA OFFICE, COURT ROAD MORADABAD. The vehicles must be of the SUV type (e.g., Mahindra Bolero), manufactured in the year 2022, and run on Diesel fuel. Each vehicle should be equipped with Air Conditioning and have a total mileage of up to 1,00,000 Kms. The required service entails a usage limit of 1500 kilometers and 320 hours per vehicle per month, provided on a ''Local 24*7'' basis within the ''Plains'' area of operation. The scope also mandates that the service provider must own the fleet of vehicles, have drivers on their payroll, and possess relevant experience, including providing vehicles to government agencies. The provider must also quote rates for extra kilometer and extra hour usage beyond the specified package.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6327237', '20-06-2025 14:00:00', '20-06-2025 14:30:00', '30 Days', 'Gujarat', 'Agriculture And Co-operation Department Gujarat', 'Directorate Of Agriculture', 'Joint Director Of Agriculture Extension', 'buycon31.da.gj@gembuyer.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2500 km x 320 hours; Local', NULL, '11 Months 5 Day', '15,00,000', '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), OEM Authorization Certificate, OEM Annual Turnover, Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '4,70,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Service require an SUV vehicle, with Maruti Suzuki Ertiga listed as a preferred option. The vehicle model must be from the year 2020. The service is for local use, with a specified usage variant of 2500 km and 320 hours. The vehicle should have travelled a maximum of 50,000 Kms. The service requires a Non-A/C vehicle operating in the Plains area. Any fuel type is acceptable. There are no add-ons specified.', 'Arpit Dedaniya', 'Chhotaudepur', 'This GeM bid document (GEM/2025/B/6327237), dated 10-06-2025, is for the procurement of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2500 km x 320 hours; Local'' for the Joint Director Of Agriculture Extension, Directorate Of Agriculture, under the Agriculture And Co-operation Department of Gujarat. The contract period is for 11 months and 5 days. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with an estimated value of 470,000. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 15 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. Exemptions for MSE and Startups are not applicable. The service requires one SUV vehicle for the office in Chhotaudepur, Gujarat, with Arpit Dedaniya as the consignee and reporting officer. The evaluation method is total value-wise. The bid includes an option clause allowing the buyer to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. The tender is governed by the GeM General Terms and Conditions and the associated Service Level Agreement.', 'The bid document does not explicitly list a section for ''Success Criteria'' for the completion of the work. However, from a tender issuer''s perspective, the work would be deemed successfully completed upon the consistent and satisfactory provision of the hired cab service for the entire contract duration of 11 months and 5 days. This includes: providing one SUV vehicle that meets all the specified technical requirements (2020 model, Non-A/C, local use, etc.), ensuring the vehicle is available for the stipulated 2500 km and 320 hours per month, providing a qualified driver, and adhering to all terms laid out in the GeM General Terms and Conditions and the Service Level Agreement for this service.', 'The scope of work involves providing one SUV type vehicle (e.g., Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, 2020 model or newer) on a monthly hire basis for a contract period of 11 months and 5 days. The service is required for the Office of the Deputy Director of Agriculture Extension in Chhotaudepur. The vehicle package is for local travel within the Plains area of operation, with a monthly usage limit of 2500 kilometers and 320 hours. The provided vehicle must be Non-Air Conditioned and can utilize any fuel type. The service provider is responsible for supplying the vehicle along with a driver who must be on the provider''s payroll. The provider must also own a fleet of vehicles. The work is subject to an OPTION CLAUSE, which allows the buyer to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6327360', '17-06-2025 12:00:00', '17-06-2025 12:30:00', '100 Days', 'Ministry Of Fisheries Animal Husbandry Dairying', 'Department Of Fisheries', 'Fishery Survey Of India', 'Cochin Base Of Fishery Survey Of India', 'sajina.pm@fsi.gov.in', 'Hiring of Boats - Tugboat; Less than 10 years; Without Air-Conditioning; 4-6 Persons; 100; Inboard; Steel; Fire Extinguisher, Lifebuoys; Service Provider', NULL, '1 Month 19 Day', NULL, '1 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '50,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require the hiring of a Tugboat that is less than 10 years old and constructed with a Steel hull. The boat must have an Inboard engine type, a seating capacity for 4-6 persons, and a carrying capacity for accessories of 100 Kilos. It is specified to be without air-conditioning. For safety, the boat must be equipped with Life Saving Accessories and Fire Fighting Accessories, specifically a Fire Extinguisher and Lifebuoys. The Service Provider is responsible for providing the fuel. Under Addon(s), it is specified that Ration is not required (NA) and there will be no separate Fuel Charges if the Service Provider is providing fuel (NA).', 'Sajina P M', 'Cochin', 'This Government e-Marketplace (GeM) bid (Number: GEM/2025/B/6327360), issued by the Cochin Base of Fishery Survey of India, is for the hiring of two Tugboats for a contract period of 1 month and 19 days. The estimated bid value is 50,000. The primary scope of work involves towing the non-propelled fishing trawler ''Matsya Varshini'' from the Cochin Shipyard ISRF dock yard to the Fishery Survey of India''s Marine Engineering Division jetty in Cochin, and also assisting in its final positioning. The bid is set to end and open on 17-06-2025, with a bid offer validity of 100 days. Bidders are required to have at least one year of past experience in similar services, although exemptions are available for MSEs and Startups. The evaluation method is total value wise, and no EMD or ePBG is required. Payment terms are set to within 30 days after the successful completion of the work. The tender also includes standard clauses such as an option for the buyer to vary the contract quantity by up to 25% and mandates compliance with all applicable labour laws.', 'The work will be considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following criteria: The vessel ''Matsya Varshini'' must be safely towed from its present location at the Cochin Shipyard ISRF dock yard and delivered to the FSI-MED Slipway Jetty in Cochin 16. Furthermore, the service provider must successfully assist in the positioning of the vessel at the destination jetty to the satisfaction of the tender issuing authority.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring of two Tugboats for the specific purpose of towing the fishing trawler ''Matsya Varshini'', which is without propulsion. The operation requires moving the vessel from its current location at Cochin Shipyard Ltd, ISRF yard Cochin, to its destination at the FSI-MED Slipway Jetty, Cochin 16. In addition to towing, the scope includes assisting in the positioning of the ''Matsya Varshini'' at the destination jetty. The vessel to be towed is a Trawler-cum-Purse-seiner with an overall length of 36.5 meters and a GRT of 268.8. The service provider is responsible for providing the tugboats, which must meet the tender''s technical specifications, along with the necessary crew and fuel for the operation. The required number of operational days during the contract is 2.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6327796', '20-06-2025 14:00:00', '20-06-2025 14:30:00', '180 Days', 'Gujarat', 'Agriculture And Co-operation Department Gujarat', 'Directorate Of Horticulture', 'Krishi Bhavan Gandhinagar', 'buycon5.dh.gj@gembuyer.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Outstation 24*7', NULL, '11 Month', '3,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', 'This bid has been created/published with floor price(minimum value) selected by the Buyer. Service Providers are advised to quote above the minimum floor value.', NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the required service, Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2000 Km X 320 Hours; Outstation 24*7, are as follows. The core requirements include the provision of an SUV type vehicle, with specific options being Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Maruti Suzuki XL6, or Mahindra Bolero. The usage variant is defined as 2000 km x 320 hours per month for Outstation 24*7 service. The vehicle''s model year must be from 2021 to 2025, and it should have travelled upto 50,000 Kms. The air conditioning requirement is specified as Non-A/C. The vehicle must be operable in both Hilly and Plain areas and can use any fuel type. There are no add-ons specified.', 'Chavada Mehul Dharamsibhai', 'Morbi', 'This is a bid invitation (Bid Number: GEM/2025/B/6327796, Dated: 10-06-2025) issued by the Directorate Of Horticulture, Krishi Bhavan Gandhinagar, under the Agriculture And Co-operation Department of Gujarat. The tender is for the procurement of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Outstation 24*7'' for a contract period of 11 months. The bid submission ends on 20-06-2025 at 14:00:00, with the opening scheduled for 14:30:00 on the same day. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 3 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services, although exemptions are available for MSE and Startup entities. The evaluation will be based on the total value. The service requires one SUV vehicle (Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Maruti Suzuki XL6, or Mahindra Bolero) of model year 2021 or newer, to be provided for 11 months to the Office of Deputy Director of Horticulture in Morbi, Gujarat. The contract allows the buyer an option to increase or decrease the quantity or duration by up to 25%. Bidders must provide several documents, including vehicle insurance, driver''s license, RC book, and driver''s identification, and must have a service office in the state of the consignee.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following criteria throughout the 11-month contract period: 1. Continuous provision of one SUV vehicle that meets all specified technical requirements (Vehicle Type: SUV - Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, XL6, or Bolero; Model Year: 2021 or newer; Km Travelled: Upto 50,000 Kms; Non-A/C). 2. Adherence to the monthly usage limits of 2000 km and 320 hours for Outstation 24*7 service within the specified Hilly and Plain operational areas. 3. Timely and uninterrupted service delivery to the specified consignee address in Morbi. 4. Maintenance of all required documentation in a valid and current state, including vehicle insurance, RC book, and driver''s license, adhar, and pan card. 5. Compliance with all buyer-added terms and conditions, including the Integrity Pact and providing a dedicated support number and escalation matrix. 6. Full compliance with all applicable labor laws and GeM General Terms and Conditions for the entire duration of the contract.', 'The scope of work involves providing one vehicle on a monthly basis for Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for the Office of Deputy Director of Horticulture in Morbi, Gujarat, for a contract period of 11 months. The specific requirements are as follows:

1.  **Vehicle Provision:** The contractor must provide one SUV vehicle. The acceptable models are Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Maruti Suzuki XL6, or Mahindra Bolero. The vehicle''s model year must be 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024, or 2025, with total mileage not exceeding 50,000 Kms. The vehicle should be Non-A/C and can be of any fuel type.

2.  **Service Usage & Availability:** The service entails a usage of 2000 kilometers and 320 hours per month. It must be available for Outstation duties on a 24*7 basis and should be capable of operating in both Hilly and Plain areas.

3.  **Location:** The service is to be provided to the Consignee, Chavada Mehul Dharamsibhai, at the Office of Deputy Director of Horticulture, Block No. 227, 2nd Floor, Taluka Seva Sadan, Lalbaug, Morbi, 363641.

4.  **Documentation:** The contractor is required to submit and maintain valid copies of the vehicle''s insurance, RC book, driver''s license, driver''s Adhar card and PAN card, GST details, and a full photograph of the vehicle to show its condition.

5.  **Service Support:** The service provider must have an office located in the state of the Consignee (Gujarat) and provide a dedicated/toll-free telephone number and an escalation matrix for service support.

6.  **Compliance:** The contractor must comply with all Buyer Added Bid Specific Terms and Conditions, including undertakings on financial standing, and adhere to the Integrity Pact and all applicable labor laws.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6327866', '20-06-2025 13:00:00', '20-06-2025 13:30:00', '45 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Defence', 'Dg Of Defence Estate', '***********', 'imran.khan-dgde@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; 1500 km x 260 hours; Local 24*7', NULL, '1 Year', '10,00,000', '1 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 1 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 2 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 3 (Requested in ATC), Additional Doc 4 (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require a Sedan vehicle, specifically a Maruti Suzuki Dzire, for a monthly hiring service. The usage variant is 1500 km and 260 hours on a Local 24*7 basis. The vehicle model must not be older than 02 years and should have travelled a maximum of 50,000 Kms. It is required to have Air Conditioning (A/C) and must be a Petrol fuel type vehicle. The area of operation is specified as Hilly + Plain Area. There are no addon specifications listed.', '***********', 'Jabalpur', 'This bid document (GEM/2025/B/6327866), issued by the Dg Of Defence Estate under the Ministry Of Defence, is for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services. The service requires one Sedan vehicle for a contract period of 1 year in Jabalpur. The specified usage is 1500 km and 260 hours per month on a 24*7 local basis. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with a validity of 45 days, ending on 20-06-2025. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 10 Lakhs for the last 3 years and 1 year of past experience in similar services, with no exemptions for MSEs or Startups. The technical requirements mandate a petrol-based Sedan, not older than 2 years, with A/C, and having run up to 50,000 kms. The rate for extra usage is fixed at Rs. 12.50 per kilometer. The contract includes an option clause allowing the buyer to vary the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. No EMD or ePBG is required for this tender.', 'The work will be considered successfully completed upon the consistent and uninterrupted provision of one Sedan vehicle as per all the technical specifications for the entire contract duration of 12 months. This includes ensuring the vehicle is available 24*7, meets the monthly usage package of 1500 km and 260 hours, is not older than 02 years, is equipped with A/C, and operates effectively in the specified Jabalpur area (Hilly + Plain). Successful completion is also contingent on the contractor''s full compliance with all bid terms, buyer-added conditions, the Service Level Agreement, and all applicable statutory laws, particularly Labour Laws. Performance will be monitored and certified by the Consignee/Reporting Officer in Jabalpur.', 'The scope of work entails providing one Sedan vehicle (specified as a Maruti Suzuki Dzire) on a monthly hiring basis for a total contract period of 12 months. The service is required for the consignee located in JABALPUR. The vehicle must be available for service on a Local 24*7 basis. The monthly hiring package covers a usage of 1500 km and 260 hours. Any travel exceeding the monthly kilometer limit will be compensated at a rate of Rs. 12.50 per kilometer. The vehicle provided must be a Petrol model, not more than 02 years old, with an odometer reading of up to 50,000 Kms at the time of deployment. The vehicle must be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C) and must be suitable for operation in both Hilly and Plain terrains.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6327998', '20-06-2025 13:00:00', '20-06-2025 13:30:00', '60 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'Eastern Railway', 'Eastern Railway Hq', 'rishi.banerjee1977@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Outstation', NULL, '1 Year', NULL, '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '4,92,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the service require an SUV vehicle type, with options including Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Hyundai Creta, or Mahindra Scorpio. The usage variant is specified as 2000 km x 320 hours for outstation service. The vehicle model must be from the year 2024 or 2025 and should have travelled up to 25,000 Kms. The vehicle is required to be Non-A/C and will operate in Plains. Any fuel type is acceptable. There are no add-on specifications mentioned.', 'Kashi Rajkumar', 'Kolkata', 'This is a bid document (GEM/2025/B/6327998) issued by the Eastern Railway Hq, Ministry of Railways, for the procurement of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Outstation''. The contract period is for 1 year, with a bid offer validity of 60 days from the bid end date of 20-06-2025. The estimated bid value is 492,000, and the evaluation will be done on a total value basis. Bidders are required to have 3 years of past experience in similar services, and both MSE and Startup exemptions for experience and turnover are not permitted. Key additional qualifications include having a fleet of owned vehicles, drivers on payroll, and having provided 100% of demanded vehicles in a single contract to a government agency in the past three years. The service is required in West Bengal for one vehicle for a duration of 12 months. The buyer has included several specific conditions, such as an option clause to vary the contract quantity by up to 25%, a requirement for the service provider to own 30% of the bid quantity of vehicles, and the necessity of having a local office. The vehicle will be used for Night Inspection and Emergency duty, must have all necessary permits, and be maintained in a clean and hygienic condition with a polite and uniformed driver.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the consistent and uninterrupted provision of the specified SUV cab service for the entire contract duration, adhering to all terms and conditions. This includes ensuring the vehicle is always in good working condition with all necessary permits, licenses, and insurance. The vehicle and driver must be available as required, particularly for Night Inspection and Emergency duties. The driver must comply with the specified code of conduct, including being polite, courteous, alert, and wearing a white uniform. The contractor must maintain the vehicle in a clean and hygienic state and provide immediate suitable replacements in case of any breakdown or driver unavailability. Successful completion also hinges on the contractor''s compliance with all statutory requirements like timely payment of wages to staff and providing all required documents for verification within 3 days of the contract award. The ultimate success criterion is the smooth delivery of the service without any deficiencies that would attract penalties or lead to contract termination.', 'The scope of work involves providing one SUV vehicle (Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Hyundai Creta, or Mahindra Scorpio of model year 2024/2025) on a monthly basis for a contract period of 12 months. The service entails a usage of 2000 km and 320 hours per month for outstation travel, operating primarily within the jurisdiction of Eastern Railway and beyond as required. The vehicle is to be used for Night Inspection and Emergency duty for Operating Officers of PCOM/ER, Government of India. The service provider must ensure the vehicle has all necessary documents, including fitness certificate, PUC, full comprehensive insurance, and road permits. The vehicle must be kept clean and hygienic, and a red board with ''On duty, Government of India'' must be displayed. The provider must supply a polite, courteous, and alert driver with a white uniform and a working mobile phone. The service provider is responsible for arranging a suitable replacement vehicle and driver immediately in case of any service interruption. The scope also includes having a service office in West Bengal, providing a dedicated toll-free number for support, and submitting an escalation matrix.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6328214', '20-06-2025 14:00:00', '20-06-2025 14:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Railways', 'Indian Railways', 'Diesel Loco Modernisation Works', 'Diesel Loco Modernisation Works, Patiala', 'dycmm4dmw@dmw.railnet.gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2500 km x 320 hours; Outstation 24*7', NULL, '2 Year', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', '25,770', NULL, 5, 30, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require a SUV type vehicle, with specific options being Mahindra XUV 500, Mahindra Scorpio, or KIA Carens. The usage variant is defined as 2500 km x 320 hours per month. The service type is for Outstation 24*7. The vehicle model should be from the year 2024 or 2025 and should not be older than May 2024. The vehicle must have travelled upto 25,000 Kms. An Air Conditioning (A/C) facility is required, and the area of operation will be Plains. The specified fuel type for the vehicle is Petrol.', 'Vaishnav Mishra', 'Patiala', 'This Government e-Marketplace (GeM) bid document, number GEM/2025/B/6328214 dated 10-06-2025, is for the procurement of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2500 km x 320 hours; Outstation 24*7''. The tender is issued by the Diesel Loco Modernisation Works, Patiala, under the Ministry of Railways. The contract period is for 2 years. The bid end date is 20-06-2025, with an offer validity of 120 days. The procurement requires an EMD amount of 25770 and an ePBG of 5.00% for a duration of 30 months. The evaluation method is total value wise. The service requires one SUV vehicle for a duration of 24 months for the consignee Vaishnav Mishra at PCMM office DMW. Specific buyer-added conditions include an option clause allowing a 25% increase or decrease in contract quantity or duration, a requirement for bidders to be financially sound, and for the vehicle model to be from 2024 or 2025. Purchase preference for MSEs and MII compliance are applicable, but exemptions for experience and turnover for MSEs and Startups are not provided.', 'The bid document does not explicitly list the key performance indicators or success criteria for the final acceptance of the work. It states that bidders must submit documents and adhere to the clauses as per the attached ATC (Additional Terms and Conditions), SLA (Service Level Agreement), and Terms & Conditions. From the perspective of the tender issuer, the success of the contract would be the consistent and uninterrupted provision of the specified SUV vehicle, meeting all technical requirements (such as model year 2024/2025, 2500 km/320 hours monthly usage, A/C, etc.) for the entire 24-month contract period, in compliance with the agreed-upon SLA and terms.', 'The scope of work involves providing one SUV vehicle for ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services'' for a contract period of two years. The service is required for the PCMM office DMW in Patiala. The vehicle must be a SUV, specifically a Mahindra XUV 500, Mahindra Scorpio, or KIA Carens, with a model year of 2024 or 2025 and should not be older than May 2024. The vehicle should have run for a maximum of 25,000 Kms and must be equipped with A/C. The scope includes a monthly usage of 2500 km and 320 hours for Outstation 24*7 service within plain areas. The vehicle''s fuel type must be Petrol. Additionally, the service provider is required to have a dedicated toll-free telephone number for service support.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6330636', '20-06-2025 10:00:00', '20-06-2025 10:30:00', '45 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Army', '***********', 'sumitjena.222a@gov.in', 'Hiring of Air Conditioners and Desert Coolers - Monthly Based - Air Conditioner; Split Air Conditioner', NULL, '1 Month', NULL, NULL, 'Yes Complete', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '12,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', '16-06-2025 09:00:00', 'LEKABALI', 'The technical specifications are for the hiring of an Air Conditioner. The required equipment is a Split Air Conditioner with a capacity of 1.5 Ton, intended for cooling purposes. The age of the equipment must be between 2 to 3 years. There is no requirement for a remote control, transformer, installation, stand, or manpower. The district and zipcode are specified as NA.', '***********', 'Dhemaji', 'This bid document, with Bid Number GEM/2025/B/6330636 dated 10-06-2025, is issued by the Indian Army, under the Department of Military Affairs, Ministry of Defence. The tender is for the ''Hiring of Air Conditioners and Desert Coolers - Monthly Based - Air Conditioner; Split Air Conditioner'' for a contract period of 1 month. The bid end date is 20-06-2025 at 10:00:00, with a bid offer validity of 45 days. The estimated bid value is 12000 and the evaluation method is total value wise. It is a Two Packet Bid with no provision for RA, EMD, or ePBG. Bid splitting is not applied. The bid supports MII Compliance and MSE Purchase Preference, with exemptions from experience and turnover criteria for MSEs. A pre-bid meeting is scheduled for 16-06-2025 at 556 ASC BN, LEKABALI. The buyer has included an option clause to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25 percent. A key condition is that the service provider must have an office in the state of the consignee, which is located in Dhemaji, and must submit documentary evidence for the same.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed, the service provider must provide one unit of a Split Air Conditioner meeting all the specified technical criteria (1.5 Ton, cooling function, 2-3 years old) to the consignee in Dhemaji for the entire contract period of 1 month. The provider must also prove they have an office in the state of the consignee, as this is a mandatory requirement under the ''Service & Support'' clause. Furthermore, successful completion is contingent upon the provider''s adherence to all applicable laws, including labour laws such as The Minimum Wages Act, 1948, and The Payment of Wages Act, 1936, as any non-compliance will be treated as a breach of contract.', 'The scope of work involves the hiring of one Split Air Conditioner on a monthly basis. The specific equipment required is a 1.5 Ton Split Air Conditioner that provides cooling functionality. The supplied unit must be between 2 to 3 years old. The service is required for a contract period of one month for a consignee located in Dhemaji. The scope does not include the provision of a remote control, transformer, installation services, a stand, or any manpower. The service provider must maintain an office in the state of the consignee to ensure service and support, and must be prepared for a potential increase or decrease in contract quantity or duration by up to 25% as per the option clause.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6333911', '18-06-2025 09:00:00', '18-06-2025 09:30:00', '60 Days', 'Ministry Of Finance', 'Department Of Revenue', 'Central Board Of Excise And Customs (cbec)', 'Customs Commissionerate Ludhiana', 'renus.g059401@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local 24*7', NULL, '1 Year', '10,00,000', '2 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '5,80,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require an SUV vehicle, with suggested options being Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra Scorpio, or Mahindra Bolero. The usage variant is specified as 2000 km x 320 hours for Local 24*7 service. The vehicle model must be from the year 2025, 2024, or 2023, with total travel up to 25,000 Kms. The vehicle must be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C), operate in Plains, and use Petrol as fuel.', 'Renu Sharma', 'Sahnewal', 'The bid, GEM/2025/B/6333911, issued by the Customs Commissionerate Ludhiana, is for the monthly hiring of one SUV Cab & Taxi Service for a contract period of one year. The service entails a usage of 2000 km and 320 hours per month on a local 24*7 basis. The estimated bid value is 580,000. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 10 Lakhs for the last 3 years and 2 years of past experience in similar services. Key technical requirements for the vehicle include it being an SUV model from 2023-2025 (e.g., Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra Scorpio, Mahindra Bolero), petrol-fueled, with A/C, and having run up to 25,000 Kms. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with no EMD or ePBG requirement. Additional conditions stipulate that the vehicle must be owned by the bidder, not sublet, and used exclusively by the department. The service provider must ensure the vehicle is roadworthy, provide a dedicated driver, maintain a log book, and bear all liabilities related to challans, accidents, or driver''s wages. The contract can be terminated for poor service. The need for this tender arises from the impending expiration of existing vehicle hire contracts on 24.06.2025 and 05.07.2025.', 'The work will be deemed successfully completed when the service provider consistently meets the following criteria: 1. The provision of the specified SUV vehicle in accordance with all technical specifications (model, year, condition) for the entire contract duration. 2. Ensuring the vehicle and a dedicated driver are available 24*7 to fulfill the monthly requirement of 2000 km and 320 hours without interruption. 3. Maintaining the vehicle in a roadworthy condition at all times and ensuring its exclusive use for the department. 4. Immediate provision of a replacement vehicle and/or driver in case of any breakdown or non-availability. 5. Accurate maintenance of a daily log book for time and mileage. 6. Strict compliance with all contractual terms, including instructions given by the department and all applicable labor laws for the driver. 7. Avoidance of any instance of unsatisfactory performance, which could lead to contract termination.', 'The scope of work is to provide one SUV type vehicle on a monthly hiring basis for the Customs Commissionerate Ludhiana. The service is required for a duration of 12 months. The vehicle must be available for Local 24*7 service, covering a monthly package of 2000 km and 320 hours. The vehicle provided must be a petrol-fueled SUV (e.g., Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra Scorpio, Mahindra Bolero) of model year 2023, 2024, or 2025 with functional air conditioning. The vehicle must be owned by the bidder, and subletting is not permitted. It should be exclusively used by the department. A dedicated driver must be provided, and the contractor is solely responsible for their wages, benefits, and compliance with labor laws. The contractor shall also be liable for all fines, challans, damages, and accidents related to the vehicle or driver. A log book for daily reporting, relieving time, and meter readings must be maintained. In the event of a vehicle breakdown or driver unavailability, a suitable replacement must be provided immediately. The vehicle''s condition and original documents will be physically inspected before the contract is awarded. Online billing will be done as per the GeM Portal.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6335491', '19-06-2025 14:00:00', '19-06-2025 14:30:00', '120 Days', 'Ministry Of Petroleum And Natural Gas', 'Bharat Petroleum Corporation Ltd', 'Bharat Petroleum Corporation Ltd', 'Pipeline Projects Mumbai', 'prajapatidevang@bharatpetroleum.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium SUV; 3500 Km x 364 hours; Outstation 24*7', 'Providing Vehicle Hire services on Monthly/ weekly / per day call basis OR Providing Passenger vehicles/Multiutility Vehicles on hire basis/ Commercial Vehicles on hire basis OR Providing Transportation services including car/jeep/bus services with any Central / State Govt Organization / PSU / Public Listed Company during last Three (3) years from original bid due date.', '5 Month', '8,00,000', '3 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria,Bidder Turnover,Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, 'No', 'No', 'ICICI', NULL, 'Yes', 5, '14 Months', 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require a Premium SUV for monthly cab and taxi hiring services. The specified options for the type of car include Toyota Fortuner, Tata Harrier, and Toyota Innova Crysta. The vehicle''s usage variant is defined as 3500 Km x 364 hours for outstation 24*7 service. The vehicle model must be from after December 2024 and should have travelled up to 25,000 Kms. It must be equipped with A/C, operate in plains, and run on diesel fuel. Additionally, outstation night charges are applicable for the service.', 'Bhagwan Sukri, Prajapati Devang', 'Bina, Rajkot', 'This bid document, GEM/2025/B/6335491, issued by Bharat Petroleum Corporation Ltd (BPCL) for the Ministry of Petroleum and Natural Gas, is for the hiring of Premium SUV cab and taxi services on a monthly basis for a contract period of 5 months. The service requirement is for 3500 km and 364 hours, including 24*7 outstation duties. Key bid dates are an end time of 19-06-2025 at 14:00:00 and an opening time of 19-06-2025 at 14:30:00, with a bid offer validity of 120 days. The tender follows a two-packet bid system with total value-wise evaluation. Financial requirements for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 8 Lakhs over the last 3 years and at least 3 years of past experience in similar services. There is no exemption for MSEs or Startups for experience and turnover criteria. A performance security deposit (ePBG) of 5.00% is required for 14 months, with ICICI as the advisory bank. The tender is for the hiring of vehicles for the VBPL (Vadinar Bina Pipeline) Pipeline Projects. The scope involves providing different types of SUVs, such as Toyota Innova Crysta and Mahindra Scorpio N, with first registration on or after December 1, 2024, to be deployed at various locations including Rajkot, Thamna, and Ujjain. The contract includes specific terms regarding vehicle maintenance, driver qualifications, trip sheet management, statutory compliance, and penalties for non-fulfillment of conditions.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work is considered successfully completed upon fulfillment of the following criteria: The contractor must provide the specified vehicles, which are commercially registered, in good and well-maintained condition, at the required time and place without delays. The vehicles must be equipped as per the contract, and the drivers must be skilled, licensed, medically fit, police-verified, and adhere to all safety and professional conduct standards. Daily trip sheets must be accurately maintained, signed by the user, and submitted for verification to facilitate billing. The contractor must bear all operational costs, including fuel, maintenance, insurance, and statutory taxes, and comply with all applicable laws such as the Motor Vehicle Act, Minimum Wages Act, and PF Act. The contractor must also guarantee the work for a 12-month defect liability period post-completion, rectifying any issues at their own cost. Successful completion is formally acknowledged by the issuance of a Completion Certificate by the Engineer-in-Charge after verifying that all contractual obligations have been met, all temporary works have been removed, and the site is cleaned.', 'The scope of work involves providing monthly cab and taxi hiring services for Bharat Petroleum Corporation Limited''s (BPCL) Vadinar-Bina Pipeline Project for a period of 5 months. The contractor is required to supply commercially registered, air-conditioned, close-body Premium and standard SUVs that are in good condition, with first registration on or after December 1, 2024. The services are required for project activities across Gujarat and Madhya Pradesh, including locations like Rajkot, Thamana (Anand), and Ujjain. The vehicles will operate 12 hours a day (typically 8 AM to 8 PM), all days of the week, for a minimum running of 3500 Kms per month. The quoted rates must be inclusive of all running costs such as fuel, oil, lubricants, repairs, maintenance, driver''s salary as per Minimum Wages, taxes, insurance, and other statutory requirements. The scope also includes providing packaged drinking water for passengers. The contractor is responsible for all toll and parking charges, which will be reimbursed based on actuals via the FASTAG system. Skilled, uniformed, and licensed drivers with police verification must be provided. These drivers must be equipped with a mobile phone with location services and adhere to all safety regulations. The contractor is required to maintain daily trip sheets for each vehicle, which will form the basis for monthly billing.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6339901', '18-06-2025 11:00:00', '18-06-2025 11:30:00', '30 Days', 'Ministry Of Commerce And Industry', 'Department Of Commerce', 'Directorate General Of Foreign Trade (dgft)', 'Ra Kochi', 'leena.nelson@nic.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium Sedan; 2500 km x 320 hours; Outstation 24*7', NULL, '1 Year', '5,00,000', '1 Year', 'No', 'No', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications outline the requirement for a Premium Sedan for outstation 24*7 service, with a usage variant of 2500 km x 320 hours. The vehicle must be a 2025 model that has travelled up to 25,000 Kms. The acceptable car types are Maruti Suzuki Ciaz, Honda City, Hyundai Verna, and Volkswagen Vento. The vehicle is required to have air conditioning (A/C) and must be a petrol model suitable for operation in both Hilly and Plain areas. No specific add-ons are mentioned.', 'Aneesh T S', 'Kochi', 'This tender, with Bid Number GEM/2025/B/6339901, is floated by the Directorate General Of Foreign Trade (dgft), Ra Kochi, under the Ministry of Commerce and Industry for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services. The service required is for one Premium Sedan with a usage package of 2500 km and 320 hours per month, including 24*7 outstation capability, for a contract period of 1 year. The bid is a Two Packet Bid with a total value-wise evaluation method. Bidders must have a minimum average annual turnover of 5 Lakhs for the last 3 years and at least 1 year of past experience in similar services. No exemptions for turnover or experience are granted to MSEs or Startups. The service provider must have a presence across Kerala, have at least one owned vehicle, and one driver on payroll. The consignee is the O/o Joint Director General of Foreign Trade in Kochi, requiring the service for 12 months. The buyer has included an option clause to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be considered successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following conditions for the entire 1-year contract period: 1. Consistent and uninterrupted provision of one Premium Sedan meeting all technical specifications, including the model year (2025), make (Maruti Suzuki Ciaz, Honda City, Hyundai Verna, or Volkswagen Vento), and condition (Upto 25,000 Kms travelled, A/C functional). 2. Adherence to the monthly usage package of 2500 km and 320 hours for Outstation 24*7 service. 3. The vehicle and driver must be available 24x7 at the disposal of the office and stationed at the office premises unless on official duty. 4. Full compliance with all financial terms, including the agreed-upon rates for extra usage and the understanding that no separate overtime, night, or outstation charges will be paid. 5. Strict adherence to all buyer-added bid specific terms and conditions, general terms and conditions, and the Service Level Agreement for the entire duration of the contract.', 'The scope of work is to provide one Premium Sedan on a monthly hiring basis for a contract duration of one year (12 months) to the Directorate General Of Foreign Trade (dgft) in Kochi. The service entails a monthly package of 2500 km and 320 hours for 24*7 outstation service. The vehicle provided must be a 2025 petrol model with a maximum travel of 25,000 Kms, with acceptable models being Maruti Suzuki Ciaz, Honda City, Hyundai Verna, or Volkswagen Vento. The vehicle must have air conditioning and be suitable for operation in Hilly and Plain areas. The provider must ensure a driver and the vehicle are available 24x7 at the office''s disposal. The vehicle is to be stationed at the office 24x7 unless out for an official purpose. The bidder must quote an all-inclusive price as no additional payments will be made for overtime, night duties, or outstation charges. The buyer has an OPTION CLAUSE to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25 percent.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6340078', '18-06-2025 11:00:00', '18-06-2025 11:30:00', '30 Days', 'Ministry Of Finance', 'Department Of Revenue', 'Central Board Of Direct Taxes (cbdt)', 'Cit Audit Hyderabad', 'buyer533.cbdtc.ts@gembuyer.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local 24*7', NULL, '1 Year', '10,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes Complete', 'Yes Complete', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC) *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, NULL, 'Total value wise evaluation', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications require a Premium SUV for service. The acceptable car types include Toyota Innova, Toyota Fortuner, and Toyota Innova Crysta. The vehicle model must be from the year 2021 and should have travelled up to 25,000 Kms. The service required is on a Local 24*7 basis with a usage variant of 2000 km x 320 hours. The vehicle must be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C) and is intended for operation in Plains. Any fuel type is acceptable. There are no add-on specifications listed.', 'Anjala Sahu', 'Hyderabad', 'This is a bid invitation (GEM/2025/B/6340078, dated 13-06-2025) issued by Cit Audit Hyderabad, under the Ministry of Finance, for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services. The specific requirement is for one SUV for a contract period of one year, with a usage of 2000 km and 320 hours per month on a local 24*7 basis. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 10 Lakhs over the last three years and 3 years of past experience in similar services, although exemptions are available for MSEs and Startups. The bid process is a Two Packet Bid system with evaluation based on the total value. No Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) or e-Performance Bank Guarantee (ePBG) is required. The tender includes a buyer-added option clause allowing for a 25% increase or decrease in contract quantity or duration. The consignee is Anjala Sahu in Hyderabad for a duration of 12 months. Bidders must adhere to all applicable labour laws, and the contract is governed by GeM''s General Terms and Conditions.', 'For the work to be considered successfully completed, the contractor must consistently provide a Premium SUV of the specified make/model (or an upgraded version) which is clean, odourless, and well-maintained with all specified amenities. The vehicle must be operated by an experienced, competent, and well-behaved driver with police verification and knowledge of the local area. The contractor is responsible for ensuring the vehicle is always ready for duty with sufficient fuel and has comprehensive insurance. A critical success factor is the ability to provide an immediate replacement vehicle in case of any breakdown. Furthermore, successful completion is contingent on the contractor''s adherence to all statutory and operational responsibilities, including timely payment of salaries and wages to their staff as per labor laws, and submitting proof of such compliance to the buyer before claiming payments. The vehicle must be used exclusively for the Income Tax Department''s work, and any violation of the agreed-upon clauses would be considered a failure to meet the contract terms, leading to potential termination.', 'The bidder is responsible for providing the specific Make/Model of the vehicle as required by the O/o Pr. CIT(Audit), Hyderabad, with upgraded versions being acceptable at the same rates. The vehicle must be properly cleaned, odourless, with neat seat covers, white curtains, white towels, napkins, and a perfume bottle. It must be manned by an experienced and competent driver who meets RTO requirements, has a working mobile phone, and complies with labor laws. The contractor shall ensure the vehicle''s fuel tank is sufficiently filled for daily duty. The driver must be well-behaved, follow all instructions, and refrain from smoking or carrying inflammable substances; the contractor must withdraw any unsuitable personnel. In case of vehicle defects or breakdowns, a replacement vehicle of similar specification must be urgently arranged. The contractor bears full responsibility for all operational costs, including fuel, oil, lubricants, repairs, maintenance, taxes, and RTO formalities, which must be included in the quoted rates. The vehicle must have comprehensive insurance coverage, including personal accident cover for the driver. The driver must have knowledge of the local language and area, and must have undergone police verification. The hired vehicle is to be used exclusively for the Income Tax Department, and violation of any clause may result in the immediate revocation of the contract.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6341007', '20-06-2025 13:00:00', '20-06-2025 13:30:00', '30 Days', 'Ministry Of Finance', 'Department Of Revenue', 'Central Board Of Excise And Customs (cbec)', 'Customs Commissionerate', 'kakivk.g219101@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - SUV; 2000 km x 320 hours; Outstation', NULL, '1 Year', NULL, '2 Year', 'Yes | Partial | Experience - 1 year (s)', 'Yes | Complete', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, Certificate (Requested in ATC), OEM Authorization Certificate, OEM Annual Turnover *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Two Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '6,28,800', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services require an SUV vehicle. The acceptable models are Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra XUV 500, and Maruti Suzuki XL6. The service is for outstation use with a usage variant of 2000 km x 320 hours. The vehicle model must be from the year 2024 or 2023 and should have travelled upto 50,000 Kms. The vehicle must be equipped with Air Conditioning (A/C) and will be operated in Hilly Areas. Any fuel type is acceptable for the vehicle.', 'Kaki Vijaya Kumar', 'Tirupati', 'This GeM bid document (GEM/2025/B/6341007), dated 13-06-2025, is for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services by the Customs Commissionerate, under the Ministry of Finance. The requirement is for one SUV for outstation duty in Andhra Pradesh, with a monthly package of 2000 km and 320 hours, for a contract period of one year. The estimated bid value is 628,800. It is a Two Packet Bid with a total value wise evaluation method. Bidders are required to have 2 years of past experience in similar services, although exemptions are provided for MSEs (1 year experience required) and DPIIT registered Startups (complete exemption). Key documents required from the seller include Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover, and OEM Authorization Certificate. No EMD or ePBG is required for this tender. The bid supports MII Compliance and MSE Purchase Preference. The consignee is the Assistant Commissioner of Customs in Tirupati. A buyer-added option clause permits a variation of up to 25% in contract quantity or duration.', 'For the tender work to be considered successfully completed, the service provider must consistently provide one SUV vehicle that strictly adheres to all specified technical specifications (including vehicle model, year, km travelled, and A/C requirement) for the entire contract duration of 12 months. The vehicle must be available for the stipulated monthly usage of 2000 km and 320 hours for outstation service. Successful completion is contingent upon the satisfactory performance of the service as determined by the designated Consignee/Reporting Officer. Furthermore, the provider must ensure full compliance with all terms and conditions outlined in the bid document, the GeM General Terms and Conditions, the Service Level Agreement, and all applicable laws.', 'The scope of work is to provide one SUV for Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for a contract period of one year. The service entails a monthly usage package of 2000 km and 320 hours for outstation duties, operating within Hilly Areas in the state of Andhra Pradesh. The vehicle provided must be an SUV from the year 2024 or 2023, with a total travel history of up to 50,000 Kms, and must be equipped with Air Conditioning. Acceptable models specified are Maruti Suzuki Ertiga, Mahindra XUV 500, and Maruti Suzuki XL6. The service is to be rendered to the Assistant Commissioner of Customs in Tirupati. The scope is subject to a buyer-added option clause that allows for an increase or decrease of up to 25 percent in the contract quantity or duration. The provider must specify rates for extra usage per kilometer and per hour beyond the chosen package.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6341691', '18-06-2025 11:00:00', '18-06-2025 11:30:00', '30 Days', 'Ministry Of Finance', 'Department Of Revenue', 'Central Board Of Excise And Customs (cbec)', 'Gst Commissionerate Bengaluru East Karnataka Zone', 'blreast.admin@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local', NULL, '1 Year', '40,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes Complete', 'Yes Complete', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '66,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'State Bank of India', NULL, NULL, 3, 15, 'Bid splitting not applied.', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the tender require the hiring of Sedan type vehicles for local service. The required usage variant is 2000 km x 320 hours per month. The vehicle models must be from the year 2024 or 2025 and should have travelled up to 25,000 Kms. A list of acceptable car models includes Honda Amaze, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, Hyundai Xcent, Tata Tigor, Ford Aspire, Volkswagen Ameo, Tata Zest, Nissan Sunny, Toyota Etios, Hyundai Aura, and Maruti Suzuki Tour S. The vehicles are required to be Non-A/C, operate in the Plains, and run on Petrol. The Addon(s) section has no specifications.', 'S Gururaja', 'Bengaluru', 'The bid, with number GEM/2025/B/6341691, is for the procurement of ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local''. The contract period is for 1 year with a bid offer validity of 30 days from the bid end date of 18-06-2025. The buyer is the Gst Commissionerate Bengaluru East Karnataka Zone, under the Ministry of Finance. The estimated bid value is 6,600,000. Bidders are required to have a minimum average annual turnover of 40 Lakhs over the last 3 years and 3 years of past experience in similar services. Exemptions for turnover and experience are available for MSEs and Startups. The tender requires the provision of 11 vehicles. Additional qualifications include the service provider having a fleet of at least 4 owned vehicles, 4 drivers on payroll, and a registered office in Bangalore. The service provider must also have experience providing 11 vehicles in a single contract to a government agency. A performance security (ePBG) of 3.00% is required for a duration of 15 months. The evaluation method will be on a total value wise basis. Buyer-specific terms include the service provider owning at least 30% of the bid quantity of vehicles and having at least 40% of the required manpower on their payroll.', 'From the tender issuer''s perspective, the work will be deemed successfully completed upon the fulfillment of the following criteria throughout the contract period: The service provider must consistently supply 11 Sedan vehicles that meet all technical specifications, including model year (2024, 2025), usage limits (2000 km x 320 hours monthly), and condition (Upto 25,000 Kms travelled), for the entire 12-month contract duration. The provider must maintain an office in the state of the consignee. The provider must ensure that at least 40% of the required manpower is on their payroll and that they own at least 30% of the vehicle fleet. Continuous and uninterrupted service must be provided as per the agreement. Adherence to all buyer-added terms and conditions, including the option clause and compliance with applicable labor laws, is mandatory for the contract to be considered successfully executed.', 'The scope of work involves providing ''Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local'' for the GST Commissionerate, Bengaluru East Karnataka Zone. The service provider is required to supply a total of 11 Sedan type vehicles for a contract period of 1 year. The vehicles must be of the model year 2024 or 2025, Non-A/C, run on petrol, and have travelled a maximum of 25,000 Kms. The service is for local use within the Plains area of operation. The provider must own a minimum of 30% of the vehicle fleet (at least 4 vehicles) and have a minimum of 4 drivers on their payroll. The service provider must also have an operational office located in the state of the consignee (Karnataka). The service will be delivered to the OFFICE OF THE PRINCIPAL COMMISSIONER OF CENTRAL TAX, GST COMMISSIONERATE, BENGALURU EAST TTMC/BMTC, OLD AIRPORT ROAD DOMLUR, BENGALURU-560071. The buyer reserves the right to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%.'),
('GEM_2025_B_6341767', '18-06-2025 11:00:00', '18-06-2025 11:30:00', '30 Days', 'Ministry Of Finance', 'Department Of Revenue', 'Central Board Of Excise And Customs (cbec)', 'Gst Commissionerate Bengaluru East Karnataka Zone', 'blreast.admin@gov.in', 'Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Premium Sedan; 2000 km x 320 hours; Local', NULL, '1 Year', '20,00,000', '3 Year', 'Yes Complete', 'Yes Complete', 'Experience Criteria, Bidder Turnover *In case any bidder is seeking exemption from Experience / Turnover Criteria, the supporting documents to prove his eligibility for exemption must be uploaded for evaluation by the buyer', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Single Packet Bid', '2 Days', NULL, '6,00,000', 'Total value wise evaluation', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 3, 15, 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 'The technical specifications for the tender require a Premium Sedan vehicle for local service. The specified usage variant is 2000 km x 320 hours. The vehicle model must be from the year 2024 or 2025 and should have travelled upto 25,000 Kms. Acceptable car types include Maruti Suzuki Ciaz, Honda City, Hyundai Verna, Volkswagen Vento, Toyota Corolla, and Skoda Rapid. The vehicle must be Non-A/C, operate in the Plains, and use Petrol as its fuel type.', 'S Gururaja', 'Bengaluru', 'This bid document (GEM/2025/B/6341767) dated 13-06-2025 is for the procurement of Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for a Premium Sedan for the Gst Commissionerate Bengaluru East Karnataka Zone, under the Ministry of Finance. The contract period is for one year with an estimated bid value of 600,000. Key eligibility criteria for bidders include a minimum average annual turnover of 20 Lakhs over the last three years and 3 years of past experience in similar services, with exemptions available for MSEs and Startups. The tender requires one vehicle to be provided for 12 months. The service provider''s registered office must be in Bangalore, and they must have at least one driver on their payroll and own at least one vehicle. The evaluation method is total value wise. A performance security (ePBG) of 3.00% is required for a duration of 15 months. The bid includes an option clause allowing the buyer to increase or decrease the contract quantity or duration by up to 25%. Bidders are required to comply with MII and MSE purchase preference policies and all applicable labor laws.', 'From the perspective of the tender issuer, the work will be considered successfully completed when the selected service provider delivers one Premium Sedan cab service consistently for the entire contract duration of 12 months, strictly adhering to all specified technical specifications. This includes providing a 2024 or 2025 model vehicle with the specified features, meeting the monthly usage requirement of 2000 km and 320 hours. Success is also contingent on the provider maintaining an office in the consignee''s state, ensuring the driver is on their payroll, owning the vehicle, and complying with all buyer-added terms, GeM General Terms and Conditions, and all applicable Labour Laws for the duration of the contract.', 'The scope of work is to provide one Premium Sedan for Monthly Basis Cab & Taxi Hiring Services to the OFFICE OF THE PRINCIPAL COMMISSIONER OF CENTRAL TAX, GST COMMISSIONERATE, BENGALURU EAST. The service is required for a duration of 12 months. The service provider must supply a local, non-air-conditioned, petrol-fueled vehicle of model year 2024 or 2025, with mileage up to 25,000 Kms. Acceptable models include Maruti Suzuki Ciaz, Honda City, Hyundai Verna, Volkswagen Vento, Toyota Corolla, or Skoda Rapid. The scope includes a monthly usage of 2000 kilometers and 320 hours. The service provider is required to own the vehicle, have the driver on their payroll, and maintain an office in the state of the consignee. The service will operate in the Plains area.'),
(NULL, '16-06-2025 16:00:00', '13-06-2025 15:00:00', '30 days', 'Department Of Space', 'Department Of Space', 'Indian Space Research Organization', 'Satish Dhawan Space Centre Shar', NULL, 'Custom Bid for Services - CAMC OF NETWORK ELEMENTS SERVERS ETC', NULL, '2 Year', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This document is a Reverse Auction (RA) notice, RA Number GEM/2025/R/499715, issued by Satish Dhawan Space Centre Shar of the Indian Space Research Organization, Department of Space. The RA is for a "Custom Bid for Services - CAMC OF NETWORK ELEMENTS SERVERS ETC" with a contract period of 2 years. The RA is scheduled to start on 13-06-2025 at 15:00:00 and end on 16-06-2025 at 16:00:00. The process includes an auto-extension feature where if an offer is submitted in the last 15 minutes, the end time is extended by another 15 minutes. The notice provides exemptions for Micro or Small Enterprises (MSE) and Startups from the "Bidder Turnover" and "Experience Criteria", provided they meet the quality and technical specifications. Supporting documents for exemption must be uploaded. Participation in the RA is considered consent for a 30-day extension of offer validity. The document explicitly states that for technical specifications, terms & conditions, and other details, bidders must refer to the Bid document GEM/2025/B/6016585. The bid is governed by General Terms and Conditions, and a Service Level Agreement will be applicable. It also mentions compliance with GeM GTC clause 26 regarding restrictions on procurement from bidders of countries sharing a land border with India.', 'The successful completion of the contract will be determined by the fulfillment of several conditions. The vendor must provide the Comprehensive Annual Maintenance Contract (CAMC) for Network Elements and Servers for the entire contract period of 2 years. A key condition for success is meeting the quality and technical specifications as detailed in the referenced Bid document GEM/2025/B/6016585. Performance will be governed by the Service Level Agreement which will be applicable for each service provided. The engagement is also subject to the General Terms and Conditions of the GeM Marketplace. Compliance with GeM GTC clause 26 regarding bidders from countries sharing a land border with India is mandatory, and any false declaration will lead to immediate termination of the contract.', 'The scope of work is to provide services for the "CAMC OF NETWORK ELEMENTS SERVERS ETC". This involves a Comprehensive Annual Maintenance Contract for network elements and servers. The duration of this service contract is for a period of 2 Year. The detailed technical specifications, terms, and conditions defining the full scope are contained within the separate Bid document GEM/2025/B/6016585, which bidders are instructed to refer to for complete details.'),
(NULL, '18-06-2025 09:00:00', NULL, '30 Days', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Air Force', '***********', NULL, 'Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs', NULL, '1 Year', '20,00,000', NULL, 'No', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This document is a Reverse Auction (RA) notice, RA Number: GEM/2025/R/500936 dated 16-06-2025, issued by the Indian Air Force under the Department Of Military Affairs, Ministry Of Defence. The tender is for the procurement of "Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs" for a contract period of one year. The RA is scheduled to start on 17-06-2025 at 09:00:00 and end on 18-06-2025 at 09:00:00. An auto-extension feature is active, where if a seller submits an offer in the last 15 minutes, the end time will be extended by 15 minutes. Bidders are required to have a Minimum Average Annual Turnover of 20 Lakh for the last 3 years. MSEs are not exempted from the Years of Experience and Turnover criteria, but Startups are exempted from both, provided they meet quality and technical specifications. Participation in the RA implies consent to an extension of offer validity by 30 days. For detailed technical specifications, terms & conditions, bidders must refer to the Bid document GEM/2025/B/6208411. The procurement is governed by the General Terms and Conditions (GTC) of GeM, and a Service Level Agreement will be applicable. Bidders from countries sharing a land border with India must be registered with the Competent Authority to be eligible, and any false declaration regarding this will lead to contract termination and legal action.', 'Successful completion of the contract will be determined by the fulfillment of the following conditions: The provision of "Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs" in strict accordance with the quality and technical specifications outlined in the referenced Bid document GEM/2025/B/6208411. Adherence to the applicable Service Level Agreement for each service provided in the Marketplace. Full compliance with the General Terms and Conditions of the GeM portal, including Clause 26 regarding restrictions on procurement from bidders of a country sharing a land border with India. Maintaining compliance throughout the contract period of one year is mandatory, as non-compliance can be a ground for immediate termination of the contract.', 'The scope of work involves providing Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services for a contract period of one year. The specific service requirement is for a Sedan type vehicle for Local use, under the package of 80 Kms x 10 Hrs. The detailed technical specifications, terms, and conditions governing the service are contained in the referenced Bid document GEM/2025/B/6208411. The service delivery will be governed by an applicable Service Level Agreement as provided in the Marketplace.'),
(NULL, '18-06-2025 09:00:00', NULL, '30 days by the date of RA initiation', 'Ministry Of Defence', 'Department Of Military Affairs', 'Indian Air Force', '***********', NULL, 'Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs', NULL, '8 Months 20 Day', NULL, NULL, 'No', 'No', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, 'RA', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'In terms of GeM GTC clause 26 regarding Restrictions on procurement from a bidder of a country which shares a land border with India, any bidder from a country which shares a land border with India will be eligible to bid in this tender only if the bidder is registered with the Competent Authority. While participating in bid, Bidder has to undertake compliance of this and any false declaration and non-compliance of this would be a ground for immediate termination of the contract and further legal action in accordance with the laws.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This document is a Reverse Auction (RA) notification, RA Number GEM/2025/R/500947 dated 16-06-2025, issued by the Indian Air Force, Department Of Military Affairs, Ministry Of Defence. The RA is for the procurement of "Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs". The RA is scheduled to start on 17-06-2025 at 09:00:00 and end on 18-06-2025 at 09:00:00. The contract period is specified as 8 Months 20 Day. There are no exemptions for MSE or Startups regarding years of experience and turnover. An auto-extension feature is in place, where if any seller submits an offer in the last 15 minutes, the RA end time will be extended by another 15 minutes, with no limit on such extensions. Participation in the RA implies the bidder''s consent for a 30-day extension of their offer validity from the date of RA initiation. The document states that a Service Level Agreement will be applicable for the service. It also highlights compliance with GeM GTC clause 26, which restricts procurement from bidders of a country sharing a land border with India unless they are registered with the Competent Authority. Bidders must undertake this compliance, and any false declaration will lead to immediate contract termination and further legal action. For detailed technical specifications, terms & conditions, and other details, bidders are instructed to refer to the Bid document GEM/2025/B/6239604.', 'Successful completion and acceptance of the work are contingent upon the vendor fulfilling several conditions. The primary condition is the provision of "Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs" for the entire contract period of 8 Months 20 Day. All services must strictly adhere to the applicable Service Level Agreement as provided in the Marketplace. The vendor must also comply with the General Terms and Conditions governing the bid. A critical compliance requirement is adherence to GeM GTC clause 26 regarding restrictions on procurement from a bidder of a country which shares a land border with India; the bidder must be registered with the Competent Authority. A false declaration or non-compliance with this clause will be a ground for immediate termination of the contract, indicating failure. Final acceptance is subject to meeting all terms and conditions specified in the referenced Bid document GEM/2025/B/6239604.', 'The scope of work involves the provision of "Short Term Cab & Taxi Hiring Services - Sedan; Local; 80Kms x 10Hrs" for the Indian Air Force. The service is to be provided for a contract period of 8 Months 20 Day. The selected vendor''s responsibilities include supplying Sedan type cabs for local travel on a hiring basis, with a defined package of 80 Kilometers and 10 Hours. The service delivery must be in accordance with the applicable Service Level Agreement for each service as provided in the Marketplace and must also be governed by the General Terms and Conditions of the bid. A key obligation for the bidder is to undertake compliance with GeM GTC clause 26, which pertains to restrictions on procurement from bidders of countries sharing a land border with India. The vendor must ensure they are registered with the Competent Authority if applicable, as any false declaration or non-compliance will result in contract termination. All technical specifications, detailed terms, and other conditions are outlined in the referenced Bid document GEM/2025/B/6239604.'),
